    const ABOUT_COPY = String.raw`Five Days, Two AI Coding Agents and a Slightly Unnecessary Number of Supernovas

Back in the late 1980s, like thousands of other impressionable young computer owners, I became completely addicted to a game called Elite.

I first encountered it at the house of my best mate, Ronnie Barker—not, regrettably, the famous comedian, although the name did lend the whole arrangement a certain sitcom quality.

It was Ronnie's BBC Micro, which meant that he was naturally the commander-in-chief and I only occasionally got a turn at the controls. Most of the time, I served as navigator, trading adviser, back-seat pilot and unsolicited expert on how he should have handled the docking approach he had just completely ruined.

We staged several heroic all-night sessions, sustained by vast platefuls of ham-and-salad sandwiches made with Mighty White bread, several litres of Cherry Coke and some distinctly amateur experimentation with smoking.

The soundtrack was provided by two cassettes that seemed to play in an endless loop: Dire Straits' Love Over Gold, released in September 1982, and Genesis's Invisible Touch, released in June 1986.

Between them, they became the unofficial soundtrack to interstellar trading, piracy and repeated failure to dock properly. For hours, Mark Knopfler and Phil Collins took turns accompanying us around the galaxy while the cassette deck quietly prepared to play the whole lot again.

It was probably not a lifestyle recommended by doctors, parents, musicians or computer manufacturers, but at the time it felt like ideal preparation for a career in interstellar commerce.

For hours, we flew, traded, fought pirates and attempted to dock without converting the ship into an expensive cloud of wireframe debris. By morning, the room would be full of smoke, sandwich crumbs, cassette hiss and the glow of the television, while Ronnie and I remained completely convinced that travelling to another procedurally generated star system was far more important than sleep.

A couple of years after the BBC Master was released in 1986, my parents bought me one of my own.

At last, I no longer had to wait patiently for Ronnie to surrender the controls. I could now lose entire nights, crash into space stations and make catastrophic trading decisions in the comfort of my own home.

Ronnie had a colour monitor.

I got a green monochrome one.

At the time, this felt slightly less glamorous, but I suspect it left a permanent mark on me, because the HUD in Ultra Elite is green. I did not consciously set out to recreate my old monitor, but apparently some design decisions spend forty years quietly waiting for another opportunity.

An Entire Universe in Almost No Memory

Elite was created by Ian Bell and David Braben and originally published by Acornsoft for the BBC Micro in 1984.

It was written largely in 6502 assembly language and was an astonishing feat of software engineering. The BBC Micro had just 32KB of RAM—a quantity of memory that modern software can now consume while deciding whether a button should have rounded corners.

Despite those constraints, Elite gave us fast wireframe 3D graphics, hidden-line removal, spaceships, space stations, trading, combat, docking, pirates, police, fuel scoops and the ever-present possibility of being murdered while carrying seven tonnes of luxury goods.

It also contained eight procedurally generated galaxies, each with 256 star systems.

Every system had its own name, economy, government, population, species and gloriously strange description. Because the generation was deterministic, everyone who played experienced the same universe. Lave was always Lave. Diso was always Diso. And somewhere out there was always a planet best known for its inhabitants' exciting new cuisine or their inexplicably passionate hatred of something very specific.

It was extraordinarily clever.

More than forty years later, I am still slightly baffled by what Bell and Braben managed to achieve with such limited memory and processing power. The entire game occupied less data than a fairly modest modern email attachment, yet somehow managed to make the BBC Micro feel as though it contained a complete universe.

The series eventually evolved through several sequels and, much later, into Elite Dangerous: an enormous online space-trading and combat simulator with multiplayer, planetary exploration, billions of star systems and more controls than the average commercial airliner.

But I have always retained enormous affection for the original.

For me, Elite was an introduction to what computer games could really be.

It was not merely a collection of blocks falling down a screen or a little man jumping between platforms. It felt like an actual universe—one that existed whether I was playing it or not.

Watford Electronics and the World's Least Efficient Commute

A few years later, at the age of sixteen, Ronnie and I ended up with Saturday jobs at Watford Electronics—one of the best-known suppliers of BBC Micro hardware, upgrades and peripherals.

Getting there required a degree of commitment entirely out of proportion to the salary. We cycled roughly fifteen miles from Barnet to Watford, worked all day for the princely sum of £1.15 an hour, and then cycled fifteen miles home again.

Not that much of the money ever made it home with us.

Most weeks, we spent our wages in the shop before leaving the building, buying computer parts, upgrades and assorted electronic treasures. Watford Electronics had effectively invented a closed-loop payroll system in which the money briefly appeared on our payslips before returning immediately to the till.

Unfortunately, they were not always the most inspiring employers.

On one memorable occasion, a customer came in with a faulty computer. I managed to work out what was wrong and fix it for them, which I rather naively assumed was exactly the sort of thing a computer shop might consider useful.

Instead, I got told off.

Apparently, diagnosing and repairing a customer's computer showed altogether too much initiative for a sixteen-year-old Saturday employee. I had crossed some invisible boundary between "cheap shop assistant" and "person who was actually helping."

So the employment package consisted of £1.15 an hour, a thirty-mile bicycle commute, the opportunity to hand most of our wages straight back to our employer, and occasional disciplinary action for being competent.

Naturally, at the time, we still thought it was brilliant.

Having spent our childhoods staying up all night playing with BBC computers, Ronnie and I had somehow found jobs surrounded by the machines, upgrades and electronic components we obsessed over.

It was less a carefully planned career path than a failure to escape orbit.

[ Many Years Later (in a french accent) ]

Enter the Machines

With the AI coding tools now at our disposal, I recently decided to conduct a small experiment.

I gave myself a few constraints.

I would create my own tribute to the original Elite: a browser-based space-trading and combat game inspired by the look, feel and systems of the 1984 original.

It would run in a web browser.

It would be contained in a single HTML file.

And I would not personally write a single line of code.

Five days later—having consumed virtually all my available credits, tokens and possibly several acres of data-centre cooling water—I had produced a surprisingly faithful recreation using Anthropic's Claude Code and OpenAI Codex.

Saying that it took five days is, however, slightly misleading.

The basic wireframe game was working after roughly two days.

The remaining three days were spent adding things that the project absolutely did not need.

This process is sometimes known as "scope creep."

In my case, it was less of a creep and more of a full-scale military invasion.

Just One More Small Feature

I began with a simple wireframe homage to Elite.

Then I thought the ships might look better with proper surfaces.

So I added surfaces.

The surfaces looked a little plain, so I added textures.

The textures looked rather flat, so I added directional lighting, reflections and glow effects.

The engines still appeared slightly lifeless, so I added animated exhausts, ion trails and luminous engine flares.

Then the launch sequence seemed a bit abrupt, so I added a cinematic launch sequence.

Naturally, once I had a launch sequence, I needed a docking sequence.

And once I had docking and launch sequences, it seemed ridiculous not to build the interiors of the station hangars.

These became the game's loading and docked environments, complete with animated machinery, service vehicles, landing pads, atmospheric lighting and various pieces of equipment whose exact purpose remains a mystery even to me.

I added animated cockpit displays, targeting systems, pilot radio chatter and a more sophisticated rendering engine.

I added genuine 3D laser calculations, docking-computer guidance, collision detection, engine trails, weapon glows and cut-scene animations.

At some point, I apparently forgot that I was making a tribute to a wireframe game from 1984.

A Glorious Geek-Fest of Elite

To make the underlying universe reasonably faithful, I turned to Mark Moxon's extraordinary Elite on the 6502 website.

The site is a glorious geek-fest of all things Elite: original source code, detailed annotations, technical explanations, comparisons between different versions, deep dives into the game's inner workings and enough historical and programming detail to make an entire weekend disappear without warning.

You can begin by reading about procedural galaxy generation and, several hours later, find yourself studying hidden-line removal, ship-drawing routines, flight mechanics and the ingenious tricks used to squeeze an entire universe into a few tens of kilobytes.

It is less a website and more an archaeological excavation conducted by someone who found a 6502 processor instead of a Roman villa.

For this project, it proved invaluable.

Mark's research helped me understand and reconstruct the original procedural galaxy-generation system, so the familiar systems, economies, populations, governments and descriptions closely match those of the classic game.

The site also documents the ship blueprints and rendering data in a form considerably more approachable than the raw assembly language.

I used that information to rebuild the original vessels from their vertices and edges, creating an object library that remains recognisably faithful to the original designs.

Except that my versions now have surfaces.

And materials.

And lights.

And windows.

And rather more dramatic engines.

Procedurally Generated Scope Creep

Then I made the mistake of thinking about planets.

Obviously, an industrial planet could not look the same as an agricultural planet.

Industrial worlds needed to appear darker, more urbanised and polluted. Agricultural and low-population worlds needed to look greener and bluer. Some required deserts, ice caps or cloud systems. Others needed rings or dusty, toxic atmospheres.

These details are generated from the properties and descriptions of each system, so the appearance of a planet reflects the information behind it rather than being selected entirely at random.

And if I was going to have different planets, I would clearly need different types and colours of stars.

Once the stars had different colours, their light obviously needed to be reflected in the windows and hulls of every nearby ship.

Anything less would have been completely unacceptable.

The background stars also looked slightly too peaceful, so I added the occasional supernova.

Again, essential.

One Webpage, No Sensible Limits

The resulting game, now called Ultra Elite, is entirely open source and still publishes, rather improbably, as a single webpage: one generated HTML file containing its JavaScript, rendering code, game logic, ship data, procedural-generation system, audio, animations and all the other machinery required to make it work.

The development source has since been split into normal local JavaScript, CSS and template files, because even nostalgia has limits. The release build is still a single HTML file, now around 800KB and roughly 18,000 generated lines—which is either impressively compact or evidence that I have completely lost control of the project.

Despite all the textures, lighting, reflections, engine glows, atmospheric planets, supernovas and cinematic sequences, Ultra Elite still includes an old-school mode.

Switch it on and the fancy bits disappear. The ships return to wireframe, the visual effects are stripped back and the game once again looks much closer to the original BBC Micro version.

No textured hulls.

No glowing engines.

No dramatic atmospheric lighting.

Just crisp wireframes, black space, a green HUD and the persistent possibility of dying because you still cannot dock properly.

It felt important to preserve that mode. The modern effects are fun, but the stark wireframe look is what made the original Elite so distinctive—and, even after all these years, it still has a charm and atmosphere entirely of its own.

Nothing has been copied and pasted from the original game's source code.

It is a new implementation, built from scratch, but informed by research into how the original systems, ships and procedural universe worked.

What I have created is not intended to replace or compete with Elite.

It is a tribute to it: a celebration of the ideas, ingenuity and extraordinary technical skill behind the original.

It is also an experiment in what one person can now create with modern AI coding tools, even when that person repeatedly responds to a nearly finished project by saying:

"That looks good—but wouldn't it be better if the station had a fully modelled hangar?"

It is not quite finished.

There are still bugs to eliminate, systems to balance and features that could be improved.

There are also, almost certainly, several more entirely unnecessary visual effects waiting to be added.

But it is already playable, surprisingly satisfying and, considering that the public release still runs from one generated HTML file, I think it looks rather good.

I have also tested it extremely thoroughly.

By which I mean I have spent several hours flying around, trading, shooting things and repeatedly crashing into space stations while calling it software development.

I even pulled a full all-nighter while building it, which felt oddly appropriate.

In some respects, very little has changed since Ronnie's house.

The Mighty White ham-and-salad sandwiches have gone. Cherry Coke has been replaced by Coke Zero and industrial quantities of coffee.

I am, regrettably, still smoking—although I really must give some serious thought to stopping.

The technology has changed beyond recognition, but the basic ingredients remain remarkably familiar: too much caffeine, not enough sleep and a complete inability to leave Elite alone.

More than forty years later, I am still staying up all night because of the same game.

Project Links

Source code and change history: https://github.com/dansto1974/UltraElite`;
    const SAVE_KEY = "ultraEliteSave";
    const SAVE_FORMAT = "ultra-elite-commander";
    const SAVE_FILE_MAGIC = "UEC2";
    const SAVE_FILE_SECRET = "ultra-elite-save-file-v2";
    const SAVE_FIELDS = ["commander", "galaxy", "current", "target", "credits", "fuel", "kills", "legal", "playerShip", "cargoCap", "missiles", "graphicsMode", "fxLevel", "marketStock"];

    function bytesToBase64(bytes) {
      let bin = "";
      const chunk = 0x8000;
      for (let i = 0; i < bytes.length; i += chunk) {
        bin += String.fromCharCode(...bytes.subarray(i, i + chunk));
      }
      return btoa(bin);
    }

    function base64ToBytes(text) {
      const bin = atob(text);
      const bytes = new Uint8Array(bin.length);
      for (let i = 0; i < bin.length; i++) bytes[i] = bin.charCodeAt(i);
      return bytes;
    }

    function textToBytes(text) {
      return new TextEncoder().encode(String(text));
    }

    function bytesToText(bytes) {
      return new TextDecoder().decode(bytes);
    }

    function xorSaveBytes(bytes, nonce) {
      const rand = mulberry(hash32(`${SAVE_FILE_SECRET}:${nonce}`));
      const out = new Uint8Array(bytes.length);
      for (let i = 0; i < bytes.length; i++) out[i] = bytes[i] ^ Math.floor(rand() * 256);
      return out;
    }

    function saveChecksum(nonce, payload) {
      return (hash32(`${SAVE_FILE_SECRET}:${nonce}:${payload}`) >>> 0).toString(36);
    }

    function encodeCommanderSaveFile(data) {
      const payload = JSON.stringify(data);
      const nonce = `${Date.now().toString(36)}${Math.floor(Math.random() * 0xFFFFFF).toString(36)}`;
      const encrypted = xorSaveBytes(textToBytes(payload), nonce);
      const envelope = {
        magic: SAVE_FILE_MAGIC,
        version: 2,
        nonce,
        checksum: saveChecksum(nonce, payload),
        data: bytesToBase64(encrypted)
      };
      return `${SAVE_FILE_MAGIC}.${bytesToBase64(textToBytes(JSON.stringify(envelope)))}`;
    }

    function decodeCommanderSaveFile(text) {
      const raw = String(text || "").trim();
      if (!raw.startsWith(`${SAVE_FILE_MAGIC}.`)) return JSON.parse(raw);
      const envelope = JSON.parse(bytesToText(base64ToBytes(raw.slice(SAVE_FILE_MAGIC.length + 1))));
      if (!envelope || envelope.magic !== SAVE_FILE_MAGIC || !envelope.nonce || !envelope.data) {
        throw new Error("Invalid commander file envelope");
      }
      const payload = bytesToText(xorSaveBytes(base64ToBytes(envelope.data), envelope.nonce));
      if (envelope.checksum !== saveChecksum(envelope.nonce, payload)) {
        throw new Error("Commander file checksum mismatch");
      }
      return JSON.parse(payload);
    }

    function commanderSaveData() {
      return {
        format: SAVE_FORMAT,
        galaxySeedVersion: 2,
        commander: game.commander, galaxy: game.galaxy, current: game.current, target: game.target,
        credits: game.credits, fuel: game.fuel, kills: game.kills, legal: game.legal, playerShip: playerShipModel(), cargoCap: game.cargoCap,
        cargo: game.cargo, equipment: game.equipment, missiles: game.missiles, graphicsMode: game.graphicsMode, fxLevel: game.fxLevel,
        marketStock: game.marketStock || {}
      };
    }

    function canSaveCommander() {
      return !!game.docked && !game.transition && !game.jumpCountdown && !game.playerDestroyed;
    }

    function applyCommanderSave(data) {
      if (!data || typeof data !== "object") throw new Error("Invalid commander file");
      if (data.format && data.format !== SAVE_FORMAT) throw new Error("Unknown commander file format");
      if (!data.galaxySeedVersion && data.galaxy === 0 && data.current === 0 && data.target === 1) {
        data.current = LAVE_INDEX;
        data.target = DISO_INDEX;
      }
      for (const key of SAVE_FIELDS) {
        if (key in data) game[key] = data[key];
      }
      game.commander = normalizeCommanderName(game.commander);
      game.galaxy = clamp(Math.trunc(Number(game.galaxy) || 0), 0, galaxies.length - 1);
      const maxSystem = galaxies[game.galaxy].length - 1;
      game.current = clamp(Math.trunc(Number(game.current) || LAVE_INDEX), 0, maxSystem);
      game.target = clamp(Math.trunc(Number(game.target) || DISO_INDEX), 0, maxSystem);
      game.cargo = { ...Object.fromEntries(GOODS.map((g) => [g[0], 0])), ...(data.cargo || {}) };
      game.marketStock = data.marketStock && typeof data.marketStock === "object" ? data.marketStock : {};
      game.equipment = { ...Object.fromEntries(Object.keys(game.equipment).map((k) => [k, false])), ...(data.equipment || {}) };
      normalizeLaserFit();
      applyPlayerShipStats();
      game.fxLevel = game.fxLevel === "classic" ? "classic" : "ultra";
      game.graphicsMode = game.fxLevel === "classic" ? "wire" : "solid";
      game.docked = true;
      setViewMode("fwd");
      game.dockedAt = null;
      restoreShipSystems();
      game.speed = 0;
      game.rollRate = game.pitchRate = game.yawRate = 0;
      game.transition = null;
      game.dockScene = null;
      game.jumpCountdown = null;
      game.playerDestroyed = false;
      game.autoDock = false;
      game.witchspace = false;
      shipDiagramState.model = playerShipModel();
    }

    function saveGame() {
      if (!canSaveCommander()) {
        setMessage("Save unavailable in flight. Dock first.", true);
        return false;
      }
      localStorage.setItem(SAVE_KEY, JSON.stringify(commanderSaveData()));
      setMessage("Commander saved to browser storage.", true);
      return true;
    }

    function browserSaveExists() {
      try {
        return !!localStorage.getItem(SAVE_KEY);
      } catch {
        return false;
      }
    }

    function loadBrowserSave(silent = false) {
      let raw = null;
      try {
        raw = localStorage.getItem(SAVE_KEY);
      } catch {
        if (!silent) setMessage("Browser save storage unavailable.");
        return false;
      }
      if (!raw) {
        if (!silent) setMessage("No saved commander found.");
        return false;
      }
      try {
        applyCommanderSave(JSON.parse(raw));
        if (!silent) setMessage("Commander loaded.", true);
        renderPanel();
        return true;
      } catch {
        if (!silent) setMessage("Commander file corrupted.");
        return false;
      }
    }

    function loadGame() {
      loadBrowserSave(false);
    }

    function deleteBrowserSave() {
      try {
        localStorage.removeItem(SAVE_KEY);
        setMessage("Browser save deleted.", true);
      } catch {
        setMessage("Browser save storage unavailable.");
      }
      renderPanel();
    }

    function saveFilename() {
      const name = String(game.commander || "commander").trim().toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z0-9]+/g, "-").replace(/^-|-$/g, "") || "commander";
      return `ultra-elite-${name}.uelite`;
    }

    function downloadCommanderFile() {
      if (!canSaveCommander()) {
        setMessage("Commander export unavailable in flight. Dock first.", true);
        return;
      }
      downloadText(saveFilename(), encodeCommanderSaveFile(commanderSaveData()));
      setMessage("Commander file downloaded.", true);
    }

    function uploadCommanderFile(file) {
      if (!file) return;
      const reader = new FileReader();
      reader.onload = () => {
        try {
          const data = decodeCommanderSaveFile(reader.result || "");
          applyCommanderSave(data);
          localStorage.setItem(SAVE_KEY, JSON.stringify(commanderSaveData()));
          setMessage(`Commander loaded from ${file.name}.`, true);
          renderPanel();
        } catch {
          setMessage("Commander file corrupted.");
        }
      };
      reader.onerror = () => setMessage("Could not read commander file.");
      reader.readAsText(file);
    }

    function renderGameFrame() {
      updateReadouts();
      drawSpace();
      drawScanner();
      drawForeAftRadar();
    }

    function update(dt) {
      const simStart = performance.now();
      game.world = null;
      buildWorldSnapshot();
      timeSimPhase("jump", () => updateJumpCountdown(dt));
      if (game.transition) {
        const tr = game.transition;
        const step = Math.min(dt, 1 / 30);
        if (!tr.waitingForRestart) tr.t += step;
        if (tr.kind === "death") updateDeathTransitionEvents(tr, step);
        if ((tr.kind === "hyperspace" || tr.kind === "galactic") && ultraFxEnabled()) {
          const jp = clamp(tr.t / tr.dur, 0, 1);
          const bigJump = tr.kind === "galactic";
          if (tr.fromQ && tr.trajectoryQ && !tr._arrived) {
            const solveEnd = (tr.departureEnd ?? (bigJump ? .22 : .26)) * .62;
            const solve = easeInOut(clamp(jp / Math.max(.05, solveEnd), 0, 1));
            game.camera.q = quatSlerp(tr.fromQ, tr.trajectoryQ, solve);
          }
          if (!tr._jumpAccelShake && jp >= .05) {
            tr._jumpAccelShake = true;
            game.screenShake = Math.max(game.screenShake || 0, bigJump ? 2.1 : 1.55);
          }
          if (!tr._jumpDecelShake && jp >= .74) {
            tr._jumpDecelShake = true;
            game.screenShake = Math.max(game.screenShake || 0, bigJump ? 2.7 : 2.05);
          }
          if (tr.onArrive && !tr._arrived && jp >= (tr.arrivalAt ?? .74)) {
            tr._arrived = true;
            tr.onArrive();
            game.camera.q = arrivalStationFacingQuat(game.camera);
            tr.arrivalQ = ensureCameraQuat(game.camera);
          }
        }
        if (tr.kind === "launch") {
          const p = clamp(tr.t / tr.dur, 0, 1);
          if (tr.fromPos && tr.toPos) {
            game.camera.pos = vec(
              lerp(tr.fromPos.x, tr.toPos.x, p),
              lerp(tr.fromPos.y, tr.toPos.y, p),
              lerp(tr.fromPos.z, tr.toPos.z, p)
            );
          } else {
            game.camera.pos.z = lerp(tr.fromZ, tr.toZ, p);
          }
          game.speed = lerp(tr.fromSpeed, tr.toSpeed, p);
        }
        if (tr.kind === "launchHangar") {
          if (!tr._servos && tr.t >= 1.15) {
            tr._servos = true;
            eliteAudio.play("hangarServo");
          }
          if (!tr._engines && tr.t >= 2) {
            tr._engines = true;
            eliteAudio.play("launchSpool");
          }
          if (!tr._clamps && tr.t >= 3.32) {
            tr._clamps = true;
            eliteAudio.play("clampRelease");
          }
          if (!tr._lift && tr.t >= 3.4) {
            tr._lift = true;
            game.screenShake = Math.max(game.screenShake || 0, .55);
          }
          if (!tr._exitPunch && tr.t >= 4.85) {
            tr._exitPunch = true;
            eliteAudio.play("blastOff");
            game.screenShake = Math.max(game.screenShake || 0, .75);
          }
        }
        if (tr.kind === "dockHangar" && !tr._servos && tr.t >= 5.85) {
          tr._servos = true;
          eliteAudio.play("hangarServo");
        }
        if (tr.kind === "dockHangar" && !tr._landed && tr.t >= 7.15) {
          tr._landed = true;
          game.screenShake = Math.max(game.screenShake || 0, 1.35);
          eliteAudio.play("clampEngage");
        }
        if (tr.kind === "dockHangar" && !tr._serviceComms && tr.t >= 7.65) {
          tr._serviceComms = true;
          const scene = tr.scene || game.dockScene || {};
          const stationName = scene.stationName || game.dockedAt || `${currentSystem().name} STATION`;
          commsMessage(`${stationName.toUpperCase()} CONTROL`, stationControllerLine("dockComplete"), "station");
          if (scene.hullRepaired) commsMessage(`${stationName.toUpperCase()} SERVICE`, scene.repairLine || "Hull repair complete.", "station");
          if (scene) scene._sequenceServiceComms = true;
        }
        if (tr.kind === "death" && tr.t >= tr.dur) {
          tr.t = tr.dur;
          tr.waitingForRestart = true;
          game.screenShake = 0;
        } else if (tr.t >= tr.dur) {
          game.transition = null;
          tr.onComplete();
        }
      } else if (!game.docked) {
        timeSimPhase("control", () => {
          if (!game.jumpCountdown?.trajectoryControl) updatePlayerControls(dt);
        });
        timeSimPhase("comms", () => {
          game.commsClock -= dt;
          if (game.commsClock <= 0) {
            game.commsClock = 16 + Math.random() * 26;
            const talkers = worldSnapshot().ships.filter((s) => s.role && s.role !== "pod");
            const station = dockableTarget();
            if (station && (Math.random() < .32 || !talkers.length)) {
              commsMessage(`${station.name.toUpperCase()} CONTROL`, stationChatterLine(), "station");
            } else if (talkers.length) {
              const t = pick(talkers);
              hail(t, ambientChatterLine(t));
            }
          }
        });
        timeSimPhase("traffic", () => updateStationTraffic(dt));
        timeSimPhase("player", () => {
          const playerSpeedBefore = game.speed;
          if (keys.has("Equal") || keys.has("NumpadAdd")) game.speed += dt * 120;
          if (keys.has("Minus") || keys.has("NumpadSubtract")) game.speed -= dt * 120;
          game.speed = clamp(game.speed, 0, game.maxSpeed);
          const playerShipForBoost = playerWorldShip(game.camera, { engineBoost: game.playerEngineBoost || 0 });
          registerShipAcceleration(playerShipForBoost, game.speed - playerSpeedBefore, dt);
          game.playerEngineBoost = playerShipForBoost.engineBoost || 0;
          if (keys.has("Space")) fireLaser();

          if (game.autoDock) updateAutoDock(dt);
          const fwd = forwardVector(game.camera);
          game.camera.pos = add(game.camera.pos, scale(fwd, game.speed * dt));
          tryManualDockingCapture();
          updatePlayerEngineTrails(dt);
          for (const star of game.stars) {
            const rel = cameraTransform(star, game.camera);
            if (rel.z < -1200 || rel.z > 3000 || Math.abs(rel.x) > 2600 || Math.abs(rel.y) > 1500) {
              // Recycle relative to where the camera is actually facing (camera-local +Z),
              // not a fixed world-space +Z offset - otherwise turning away from the initial
              // orientation places new stars outside the view frustum and the field thins
              // out over time instead of replenishing ahead of the ship.
              const p = cameraLocalToWorld(game.camera, vec((Math.random() - .5) * 3200, (Math.random() - .5) * 1800, 2400 + Math.random() * 1400));
              star.x = p.x;
              star.y = p.y;
              star.z = p.z;
            }
          }
        });
        timeSimPhase("objects", () => {
          for (const o of game.objects) {
            if (o.type === "station") updateStation(o, dt);
            else if (o.type === "ship") {
              if (o.aiMode === "stationLaunch" || o.aiMode === "stationDock") updateStationTrafficShip(o, dt);
              else { updateShipAI(o, dt); clampOutsideStation(o); }
              updateEngineTrails(o, dt);
            }
            else if (o.type === "planet" || o.type === "sun") o.rot = (o.rot || 0) + dt * (o.rotSpeed || .06);
            else if (o.type === "missile") updateMissile(o, dt);
            else if (o.type === "asteroid" || o.type === "boulder" || o.type === "splinter" || o.type === "hermit") {
              o.rot = (o.rot || 0) + dt * (o.tumbleRot || .3);
              o.pitch = (o.pitch || 0) + dt * (o.tumblePitch || .2);
              if (o.vel) o.pos = add(o.pos, scale(o.vel, dt));
            }
            else if (o.vel) o.pos = add(o.pos, scale(o.vel, dt));
            if ((o.type === "canister" || o.type === "plate") && game.equipment.fuelScoop && len(sub(o.pos, game.camera.pos)) < 38) scoopCargo(o);
            if (!o._remove) handlePlayerCollision(o);
            if (!o._remove) handlePlayerLargeCollision(o);
            if (!o._remove) updateSolarFuelScoop(o, dt);
          }
        });
        timeSimPhase("collide", () => resolveObjectCollisions());
        timeSimPhase("spawn", () => {
          let liveShipCount = 0;
          let liveRockCount = 0;
          game.objects = game.objects.filter((o) => {
            if (o._remove) return false;
            const d = len(sub(o.pos, game.camera.pos));
            const keep = shouldKeepShip(o, d);
            if (keep) {
              if (o.type === "ship") liveShipCount++;
              else if (o.type === "asteroid" || o.type === "boulder") liveRockCount++;
            }
            return keep;
          });
          game.world = null;
          buildWorldSnapshot();
          if (game.targetObject && !isWorldObjectLive(game.targetObject)) game.targetObject = nearestTarget(false);
          spawnAmbientEncounter(dt, liveShipCount);
          if (Math.random() < dt * .012 && liveRockCount < 4) {
            spawnAsteroid(Math.random, game.camera.pos);
            game.world = null;
            buildWorldSnapshot();
          }
        });
        timeSimPhase("systems", () => {
          updateCabinTemperature(dt);
          rechargeShipSystems(dt);
          game.laserHeat = clamp(game.laserHeat - dt * 18, 0, 100);
          game.legal = Math.max(0, game.legal - dt * 0.025);
        });
      }
      else {
        game.rollRate = game.pitchRate = game.yawRate = 0;
        if (game.controlHold) {
          for (const hold of Object.values(game.controlHold)) {
            hold.dir = 0;
            hold.time = 0;
          }
        }
      }
      timeSimPhase("effects", () => {
        game.explosions = game.explosions.filter((e) => (e.t += dt) < e.dur);
        trimParticleStore(game.explosions, 28);
        game.smokePuffs = game.smokePuffs.filter((p) => (p.t += dt) < p.dur);
        if (DEV_DISABLE_ENGINE_EFFECTS) game.smokePuffs = game.smokePuffs.filter((p) => p.kind !== "enginePlasma");
        trimParticleStore(game.smokePuffs, 300);
        game.screenShake = Math.max(0, (game.screenShake || 0) - dt * 7.5);
        if (DEV_DISABLE_LASER_EFFECTS) {
          game.playerShot = null;
          game.enemyShots.length = 0;
        } else {
          game.enemyShots = game.enemyShots.filter((s) => (s.t += dt) < s.dur);
        }
        if (game.messageTimer > 0) game.messageTimer -= dt;
        if (game.panelOpen && (game.panel === "ship" || game.panel === "library")) {
          const diagram = byId("shipDiagram");
          if (diagram) drawShipDiagram(diagram, dt);
        }
      });
      timeSimPhase("audio", () => eliteAudio.update(dt));
      recordSimPhase("sim", performance.now() - simStart);
      timeSimPhase("render", () => renderGameFrame());
    }

    function dockingComputerAvoidance() {
      let avoid = vec();
      let nearest = Infinity;
      const avoidTypes = new Set(["ship", "asteroid", "boulder", "splinter", "canister", "plate", "missile"]);
      for (const o of game.objects) {
        if (!o || o._remove || !avoidTypes.has(o.type)) continue;
        const away = sub(game.camera.pos, o.pos);
        const d = len(away);
        if (d <= .001) continue;
        const radius = (o.r || (MODELS[o.model] ? modelBoundingRadius(MODELS[o.model]) : 20) || 20) + 155;
        const range = Math.max(360, radius * 4.2);
        if (d > range) continue;
        const pressure = clamp((range - d) / range, 0, 1);
        const closing = dot(bodyVelocity(o), norm(away));
        const closingBoost = closing > 12 ? clamp(closing / 120, 0, .65) : 0;
        avoid = add(avoid, scale(norm(away), pressure * pressure * (1 + closingBoost)));
        nearest = Math.min(nearest, d - radius);
      }
      return { dir: len(avoid) > .001 ? norm(avoid) : null, nearest };
    }

    function updateAutoDock(dt) {
      const st = dockableTarget();
      if (!st) {
        game.autoDock = false;
        setMessage("Docking computer lost station lock.");
        return;
      }
      if (st.type !== "station") {
        const state = typeof game.autoDock === "object" ? game.autoDock : (game.autoDock = { stage: "final" });
        const to = sub(st.pos, game.camera.pos);
        const d = len(to);
        const avoidance = dockingComputerAvoidance();
        const desiredDir = avoidance.dir ? norm(add(norm(to), scale(avoidance.dir, .42))) : norm(to);
        const avoidSlow = avoidance.nearest < 130 ? .55 : avoidance.nearest < 230 ? .76 : 1;
        game.camera.q = quatSlerp(ensureCameraQuat(game.camera), quatLookRotation(desiredDir), dt * 1.8);
        game.speed = lerp(game.speed, (d > 260 ? 90 : 24) * avoidSlow, dt * 1.3);
        state.hud = { stage: "final", range: d, slotRange: d, lateral: 0, alignment: 1, avoidance: Number.isFinite(avoidance.nearest) ? avoidance.nearest : null };
        if (d < 165) dock(true);
        return;
      }

      const state = typeof game.autoDock === "object" ? game.autoDock : (game.autoDock = { stage: "marshal" });
      const slot = stationAutoDockFrame(st);
      const inward = scale(slot.outward, -1);
      const right = slot.right || norm(cross(slot.up, slot.outward));
      if (!state.laneRight || !state.laneUp) {
        state.laneRight = { ...right };
        state.laneUp = { ...slot.up };
      }
      const laneRight = norm(state.laneRight);
      const laneUp = norm(state.laneUp);
      const frontness = dot(sub(game.camera.pos, slot.center), slot.outward);
      const marshal = add(slot.center, add(scale(slot.outward, 1380), add(scale(laneRight, 520), scale(laneUp, 210))));
      const goSide = state.goSide || (state.goSide = Math.random() < .5 ? -1 : 1);
      const goAround = add(slot.center, add(scale(slot.outward, 1720), add(scale(laneRight, goSide * 760), scale(laneUp, 320))));
      const approach = add(slot.center, scale(slot.outward, 760));
      const final = add(slot.center, scale(slot.outward, 118));
      const finalAim = add(slot.center, scale(inward, 150));
      const relToAxis = sub(game.camera.pos, slot.center);
      const lateral = len(sub(relToAxis, scale(slot.outward, dot(relToAxis, slot.outward))));
      const stageTarget = state.stage === "marshal"
        ? (frontness < 420 ? marshal : approach)
        : state.stage === "goAround"
          ? goAround
          : state.stage === "approach"
          ? approach
          : state.stage === "align"
            ? final
            : slot.center;
      const toTarget = sub(stageTarget, game.camera.pos);
      const d = len(toTarget);
      const slotDist = len(sub(game.camera.pos, slot.center));
      const avoidance = dockingComputerAvoidance();
      const trafficClose = Number.isFinite(avoidance.nearest) && avoidance.nearest < (state.stage === "final" ? 34 : 72);
      const forward = forwardVector(game.camera);
      const alignment = dot(forward, inward);

      if (state.stage === "marshal" && (frontness > 720 || (d < 300 && frontness > 360))) state.stage = "approach";
      if (state.stage === "approach" && frontness < 840 && lateral < 360) state.stage = "align";
      if (state.stage === "align" && frontness < 240 && lateral < 190 && alignment > .82) state.stage = "final";

      const offTrajectory = state.stage !== "marshal" && state.stage !== "goAround" && state.stage !== "final" && (
        (state.stage === "approach" && (lateral > 820 || frontness < -220)) ||
        (state.stage === "align" && (lateral > 560 || frontness < -240 || (trafficClose && lateral > 170)))
      );
      state.offTrackTime = offTrajectory ? (state.offTrackTime || 0) + dt : Math.max(0, (state.offTrackTime || 0) - dt * 1.8);
      if (state.stage !== "goAround" && state.offTrackTime > 1.65) {
        state.stage = "goAround";
        state.offTrackTime = 0;
        state.goAroundCount = (state.goAroundCount || 0) + 1;
        state.goSide *= -1;
        state.announced = "";
        commsMessage("TRAFFIC CONTROL", "Approach unstable. Go around and re-enter the lane.", "station");
      }
      if (state.stage === "goAround" && d < 190 && frontness > 980) {
        state.stage = "marshal";
        state.offTrackTime = 0;
        state.announced = "";
      }
      const freshStage = state.stage !== state.announced;
      if (freshStage) {
        state.announced = state.stage;
        const line = state.stage === "marshal"
          ? "Docking computer: acquiring front approach lane."
          : state.stage === "goAround"
            ? "Docking computer: go-around. Reacquiring approach."
          : state.stage === "approach"
            ? "Docking computer: lining up with station slot."
            : state.stage === "align"
              ? "Docking computer: matching slot rotation."
              : "Docking computer: final approach.";
        setMessage(line, true);
      }

      const desiredDir = state.stage === "final"
        ? norm(add(scale(inward, 1.7), scale(norm(sub(finalAim, game.camera.pos)), 2.6)))
        : state.stage === "align"
          ? norm(add(scale(inward, 2.4), scale(norm(sub(final, game.camera.pos)), 1.8)))
          : norm(toTarget);
      const avoidWeight = state.stage === "final"
        ? (trafficClose ? .24 : .08)
        : state.stage === "align" ? .44 : state.stage === "goAround" ? .72 : .66;
      const steeredDir = avoidance.dir ? norm(add(desiredDir, scale(avoidance.dir, avoidWeight))) : desiredDir;
      const desiredQ = quatLookRotation(steeredDir, slot.up);
      const turnRate = state.stage === "final" ? 5.6 : state.stage === "align" ? 3.35 : state.stage === "goAround" ? 2.45 : 2.05;
      game.camera.q = quatSlerp(ensureCameraQuat(game.camera), desiredQ, 1 - Math.exp(-turnRate * dt));
      game.rollRate = 0;
      game.pitchRate = 0;
      game.yawRate = 0;

      if (state.stage !== "marshal" && state.stage !== "goAround" && frontness > -150 && frontness < 980 && lateral > .1) {
        const axisPoint = add(slot.center, scale(slot.outward, frontness));
        const lateralVec = sub(game.camera.pos, axisPoint);
        const correctionRate = state.stage === "final" ? 2.9 : state.stage === "align" ? 1.65 : .8;
        game.camera.pos = sub(game.camera.pos, scale(lateralVec, clamp(correctionRate * dt, 0, .16)));
      }

      const targetSpeed = state.stage === "marshal" ? (d > 500 ? 118 : 72)
        : state.stage === "goAround" ? (d > 520 ? 108 : 76)
          : state.stage === "approach" ? (d > 260 ? 70 : 42)
          : state.stage === "align" ? 24
            : 19;
      const headingAlign = clamp(dot(forwardVector(game.camera), steeredDir), 0, 1);
      const steeringSpeedMul = lerp(.38, 1, headingAlign * headingAlign);
      const avoidSlow = avoidance.nearest < 115 ? .42 : avoidance.nearest < 240 ? .66 : avoidance.nearest < 380 ? .84 : 1;
      game.speed = lerp(game.speed, targetSpeed * avoidSlow * steeringSpeedMul, dt * (state.stage === "final" ? 1.8 : 1.25));

      state.hud = {
        stage: state.stage,
        range: d,
        slotRange: slotDist,
        lateral,
        alignment: clamp(alignment, 0, 1),
        avoidance: Number.isFinite(avoidance.nearest) ? avoidance.nearest : null
      };
      if (state.stage === "final" && slotDist < 82 && lateral < 105 && alignment > .88) dock(true);
    }

    function controlHoldTime(axis, input, dt) {
      if (!game.controlHold) game.controlHold = {};
      const hold = game.controlHold[axis] || (game.controlHold[axis] = { dir: 0, time: 0 });
      if (!input) {
        hold.dir = 0;
        hold.time = 0;
      } else if (hold.dir !== input) {
        hold.dir = input;
        hold.time = dt;
      } else {
        hold.time += dt;
      }
      return hold.time;
    }

    function controlRamp(holdTime, initial = .24, rampSeconds = .48) {
      const t = clamp(holdTime / rampSeconds, 0, 1);
      const eased = t * t * (3 - 2 * t);
      return lerp(initial, 1, eased);
    }

    function updateAxisRate(rate, input, dt, accel, maxRate, damping = .055, ramp = 1) {
      if (input) rate += input * accel * ramp * dt;
      else rate *= Math.pow(damping, dt);
      return clamp(rate, -maxRate, maxRate);
    }

    function updatePlayerControls(dt) {
      const rollInput = (keys.has("KeyA") ? 1 : 0) - (keys.has("KeyD") ? 1 : 0);
      const pitchInput = (keys.has("KeyW") ? 1 : 0) - (keys.has("KeyS") ? 1 : 0);
      const yawInput = ((keys.has("KeyE") || keys.has("Period")) ? 1 : 0) - ((keys.has("KeyQ") || keys.has("Comma")) ? 1 : 0);
      const rollRamp = controlRamp(controlHoldTime("roll", rollInput, dt), .38, .36);
      const pitchRamp = controlRamp(controlHoldTime("pitch", pitchInput, dt), .28, .42);
      const yawRamp = controlRamp(controlHoldTime("yaw", yawInput, dt), .28, .42);
      game.rollRate = updateAxisRate(game.rollRate || 0, rollInput, dt, 5.6, 2.05, .055, rollRamp);
      game.pitchRate = updateAxisRate(game.pitchRate || 0, pitchInput, dt, 4.05, 1.42, .055, pitchRamp);
      game.yawRate = updateAxisRate(game.yawRate || 0, yawInput, dt, 3.75, 1.24, .055, yawRamp);
      if (Math.abs(game.rollRate) > .001) rotateCameraLocal(game.camera, vec(0, 0, 1), game.rollRate * dt);
      if (Math.abs(game.pitchRate) > .001) rotateCameraLocal(game.camera, vec(1, 0, 0), game.pitchRate * dt);
      if (Math.abs(game.yawRate) > .001) rotateCameraLocal(game.camera, vec(0, 1, 0), game.yawRate * dt);
    }

    function lerpAngle(a, b, t) {
      const d = Math.atan2(Math.sin(b - a), Math.cos(b - a));
      return a + d * clamp(t, 0, 1);
    }

    function updateStation(o, dt) {
      o.rot = (o.rot || 0) + dt * (o.rotSpeed || .34);
      if (!o.basePos) o.basePos = { ...o.pos };
      o.pos = { ...o.basePos };
    }

    function shipForward(o) {
      return norm(rotateShipPoint(vec(0, 0, 1), o.rot || 0, o.pitch || 0, o.roll || 0));
    }

    function shipForwardWorld(o) {
      return o?.quat ? norm(quatRotate(o.quat, vec(0, 0, 1))) : shipForward(o);
    }

    function shipRight(o) {
      return norm(rotateShipPoint(vec(1, 0, 0), o.rot || 0, o.pitch || 0, 0));
    }

    function yawPitchForDirection(dir) {
      return {
        yaw: Math.atan2(-dir.x, Math.hypot(dir.y, dir.z)),
        pitch: Math.atan2(-dir.y, dir.z)
      };
    }

    function setNoseDirection(o, dir, roll = o.roll || 0) {
      if (len(dir) < .001) return;
      const { yaw, pitch } = yawPitchForDirection(norm(dir));
      o.rot = yaw;
      o.pitch = pitch;
      o.roll = roll;
    }

    function steerVelocity(o, desired, dt, accel = 95, maxSpeed = 120) {
      // Elite's ships are nose-led: tactics set pitch/roll/acceleration, and the ship
      // moves along its current nose vector. The previous browser model changed velocity
      // directly and then rotated the mesh to follow it, which made ships slide around
      // like drones. Keep the desired-vector callers, but convert that into turn inputs
      // and scalar speed here.
      const desiredLen = len(desired);
      const speedBefore = o.speed ?? len(o.vel || vec());
      if (o.speed === undefined) {
        const initialSpeed = len(o.vel || vec());
        o.speed = clamp(initialSpeed || maxSpeed * .38, maxSpeed * .18, maxSpeed);
        if (initialSpeed > 1) orientShipToVelocity(o, 1);
      }
      const currentForward = shipForward(o);
      const dir = desiredLen > 1 ? scale(desired, 1 / desiredLen) : currentForward;
      const beforeTurnAlignment = dot(currentForward, dir);
      const { yaw, pitch } = yawPitchForDirection(dir);
      const speedRatio = clamp(o.speed / Math.max(1, maxSpeed), 0, 1);
      const turnRate = lerp(2.35, 1.05, speedRatio);
      o.rot = lerpAngle(o.rot || 0, yaw, dt * turnRate);
      o.pitch = lerpAngle(o.pitch || 0, pitch, dt * turnRate * .82);

      const sideError = dot(shipRight(o), dir);
      const bankTarget = clamp(-sideError * .58, -.62, .62);
      o.roll = lerpAngle(o.roll || 0, bankTarget, dt * 2.8);

      const alignment = dot(shipForward(o), dir);
      const targetSpeed = maxSpeed * (alignment > .78 ? 1 : alignment > .32 ? .76 : .42);
      const speedStep = accel * (targetSpeed > o.speed ? .72 : 1.15) * dt;
      if (Math.abs(targetSpeed - o.speed) <= speedStep) o.speed = targetSpeed;
      else o.speed += Math.sign(targetSpeed - o.speed) * speedStep;
      if (beforeTurnAlignment < -.35) o.speed = Math.max(o.speed - accel * .22 * dt, maxSpeed * .22);
      o.speed = clamp(o.speed, maxSpeed * .16, maxSpeed);
      registerShipAcceleration(o, o.speed - speedBefore, dt);
      o.vel = scale(shipForward(o), o.speed);
      o.pos = add(o.pos, scale(o.vel, dt));
    }

    function orientShipToVelocity(o, dt) {
      const v = o.vel || vec();
      if (len(v) < .01) return;
      // rotatePoint applies yaw (around Y) then pitch (around X) to the model's local
      // +Z nose vector, giving forward' = (-sin(yaw), -cos(yaw)*sin(pitch), cos(yaw)*cos(pitch)).
      // Solving that for forward' == normalize(v) gives these two formulas — grouping
      // vx with hypot(vy,vz) for yaw and using plain vz (not hypot(vx,vz)) for pitch.
      // A first attempt at this (atan2(-v.x,-v.z) / atan2(-v.y,hypot(v.x,v.z))) matched
      // normalize(v) for the X- and Z-aligned test vectors but silently flipped the
      // nose for general 3D velocity — always verify Euler-angle fixes against a vector
      // with all three components nonzero, axis-aligned cases can pass by coincidence.
      const yaw = Math.atan2(-v.x, Math.hypot(v.y, v.z));
      const pitch = Math.atan2(-v.y, v.z);
      o.rot = lerpAngle(o.rot || 0, yaw, dt * 3.4);
      o.pitch = lerpAngle(o.pitch || 0, pitch, dt * 3.1);
      o.roll = lerpAngle(o.roll || 0, clamp(-v.x / 90, -0.65, 0.65), dt * 2.2);
    }

    // Hostiles no longer only ever fight the player: pirates/aliens sometimes pick a
    // nearby trader as prey instead, and police prefer to hunt down a nearby pirate.
    // o.target is either null (meaning the player) or a live reference to another ship.
    function pickPreyFor(o) {
      let best = null, bestD = Infinity;
      for (const x of worldSnapshot().ships) {
        if (x.type !== "ship" || x === o || x.hostile || x.aiMode === "flee") continue;
        const d = len(sub(x.pos, o.pos));
        if (d < 1400 && d < bestD) { best = x; bestD = d; }
      }
      return best;
    }

    function pickHostileFor(o) {
      let best = null, bestD = Infinity;
      for (const x of worldSnapshot().ships) {
        if (x.type !== "ship" || x === o || !x.hostile || x.role === "police") continue;
        const d = len(sub(x.pos, o.pos));
        if (d < 1800 && d < bestD) { best = x; bestD = d; }
      }
      return best;
    }

    function assignHostileTarget(o) {
      if (o.role === "police") {
        o.target = pickHostileFor(o);
        return;
      }
      if (!o.thargoid && Math.random() < .55) {
        const prey = pickPreyFor(o);
        o.target = prey;
        if (prey) prey.huntedBy = o;
      } else {
        o.target = null;
      }
      if (isAlienShip(o) && Math.random() < .45) hail(o, hostileThreatLine(o));
    }

    function hostileTargetPos(o) {
      return o.target ? o.target.pos : game.camera.pos;
    }

    function enemyLaserVisual(attacker) {
      const spec = npcLaserSpec(attacker);
      let palette = { color: "#ff9b45", core: "#fff0c8" };
      if (attacker.thargoid || isAlienShip(attacker)) palette = { color: "#74ffba", core: "#e7fff2" };
      else if (attacker.role === "police") palette = { color: "#42dfff", core: "#effcff" };
      else if (attacker.role === "pirate") palette = { color: "#ff4b35", core: "#ffe2b8" };
      if (spec.power >= 6 && !isAlienShip(attacker)) palette = attacker.role === "pirate"
        ? { color: "#ff7955", core: "#fff4d4" }
        : { color: "#8fe8ff", core: "#ffffff" };
      return {
        ...palette,
        width: spec.width,
        glow: spec.glow,
        forks: spec.forks,
        jitter: 54 + spec.power * 12 + (attacker.role === "pirate" ? 18 : 0),
        dur: spec.dur,
        soundClass: spec.soundClass,
        laserPower: spec.power
      };
    }

    function pushEnemyLaserShot(attacker, targetPos = null, targetRadius = 0, options = {}) {
      const visual = enemyLaserVisual(attacker);
      if (DEV_DISABLE_LASER_EFFECTS) return visual;
      const side = shipRight(attacker);
      const hardpoint = (attacker.r || 50) * .18 * (Math.random() < .5 ? -1 : 1);
      const nose = Math.max(24, (attacker.r || 50) * .42);
      const from = add(attacker.pos, add(scale(shipForward(attacker), nose), scale(side, hardpoint)));
      const miss = targetPos
        ? add(
          scale(shipRight(attacker), (Math.random() - .5) * Math.max(10, targetRadius * .18)),
          scale(vec(0, 1, 0), (Math.random() - .5) * Math.max(6, targetRadius * .12))
        )
        : null;
      const canopyHit = targetPos ? null : {
        x: (Math.random() - .5) * .86,
        y: (Math.random() - .5) * .6
      };
      const sparkCount = targetPos ? 5 + Math.floor(Math.random() * 5) : 8 + Math.floor(Math.random() * 6);
      const sparks = Array.from({ length: sparkCount }, () => {
        const a = Math.random() * TAU;
        return {
        x: Math.cos(a),
        y: Math.sin(a),
        len: (targetPos ? 9 : 18) + Math.random() * (targetPos ? 34 : 58),
        drift: (targetPos ? 6 : 10) + Math.random() * (targetPos ? 26 : 46),
        life: .75 + Math.random() * (targetPos ? .45 : .7),
        size: 1.1 + Math.random() * (targetPos ? 2.1 : 2.8),
        warm: Math.random()
        };
      });
      const worldImpact = !!targetPos && options.impact !== false;
      game.enemyShots.push({
        from,
        to: targetPos ? add(targetPos, miss) : null,
        t: 0,
        dur: targetPos ? visual.dur + (worldImpact ? .18 : 0) : visual.dur + .24,
        beamDur: visual.dur,
        missile: false,
        color: visual.color,
        core: visual.core,
        width: visual.width,
        glow: visual.glow,
        forks: visual.forks,
        screenAim: canopyHit,
        screenOffset: targetPos ? null : { x: 0, y: 0 },
        sparks,
        flare: !targetPos || worldImpact
      });
      return visual;
    }

    function launchThargon(mothership) {
      const stats = shipStats("thargon");
      const forward = shipForward(mothership);
      const side = shipRight(mothership);
      const up = norm(cross(side, forward));
      const offset = add(scale(forward, Math.max(58, (mothership.r || 90) * .55)), add(scale(side, (Math.random() - .5) * 90), scale(up, (Math.random() - .5) * 55)));
      const thargon = {
        type: "ship",
        model: "thargon",
        name: "THARGON",
        pos: add(mothership.pos, offset),
        vel: add(scale(forward, 95), scale(side, (Math.random() - .5) * 35)),
        rot: mothership.rot || 0,
        pitch: mothership.pitch || 0,
        roll: Math.random() * TAU,
        r: stats.r,
        color: shipColor("thargon"),
        hp: stats.hp,
        maxHp: stats.hp,
        hostile: true,
        role: "alien",
        thargon: true,
        aiMode: "attack",
        target: null,
        bounty: 50,
        attackClock: .45 + Math.random() * .75,
        wobble: Math.random() * TAU,
        npcMissiles: 0,
        decalSeed: hash32(`${mothership.decalSeed || 1}:thargon:${Math.floor(Math.random() * 99999)}`)
      };
      setNoseDirection(thargon, sub(game.camera.pos, thargon.pos), thargon.roll);
      game.objects.push(thargon);
      eliteAudio.play("missile");
      setMessage("THARGOID launches Thargon drone!", true);
      if (Math.random() < .65) hail(mothership, hostileThreatLine(mothership));
    }

    function fireAtShip(attacker, target) {
      if (stationBlocksLaser(attacker.pos, target.pos)) return;
      const profile = npcCombatProfile(attacker);
      const visual = pushEnemyLaserShot(attacker, target.pos, target.r || 50);
      const dmg = profile.damage;
      if (!DEV_DISABLE_LASER_EFFECTS) eliteAudio.playAt("enemyLaser", attacker.pos, { range: Math.max(1800, profile.range + 420), laserClass: visual?.soundClass });
      target.hp -= dmg;
      if (!DEV_DISABLE_LASER_EFFECTS) eliteAudio.playAt("hit", target.pos, { range: 1400, gain: .5 });
      addImpactShake(.14, target.pos, 850);
      if (!DEV_DISABLE_LASER_EFFECTS) spawnSmokePuffs(target.pos, clamp((target.r || 50) / 80, .45, 1.7), 2);
      if (target.hp <= 0) destroyObject(target, false);
      else {
        maybeHailMercy(target, attacker.name, .9);
        setMessage(`${attacker.name} attacks ${target.name}.`);
      }
    }

    function fireAtPlayer(o) {
      if (!o._hailed && Math.random() < .5) {
        o._hailed = true;
        hail(o, hostileThreatLine(o));
      }
      const profile = npcCombatProfile(o);
      const thargon = o.thargoid && (o.npcMissiles || 0) > 0 && Math.random() < profile.thargonChance;
      if (thargon) {
        o.npcMissiles--;
        launchThargon(o);
        return;
      }
      const missile = (o.npcMissiles || 0) > 0 && !o.thargoid && Math.random() < .3;
      if (missile) {
        o.npcMissiles--;
        if (game.equipment.ecm && Math.random() < .75) {
          eliteAudio.play("ecm");
          setMessage(`${o.name} missile jammed by ECM.`, true);
          flash();
          return;
        }
        spawnMissile({ pos: add(o.pos, scale(shipForward(o), Math.max(28, o.r * .35))), target: null, source: o, hostile: true });
        eliteAudio.play("missile");
        setMessage(`${o.name} launches a missile!`, true);
        return;
      }
      const externalTarget = game.viewMode === "ext" && !game.docked;
      const playerRadius = Math.max(42, modelBoundingRadius(MODELS[playerShipModel()]) || 72);
      if (stationBlocksLaser(o.pos, game.camera.pos, o)) return;
      const energyBefore = game.energy;
      const visual = externalTarget ? pushEnemyLaserShot(o, { ...game.camera.pos }, playerRadius, { impact: true }) : pushEnemyLaserShot(o);
      if (!DEV_DISABLE_LASER_EFFECTS) eliteAudio.playAt("enemyLaser", o.pos, { range: Math.max(1800, profile.range + 420), laserClass: visual?.soundClass });
      const arc = damagePlayer(profile.damage, o.name, { sourcePos: o.pos });
      if (!DEV_DISABLE_LASER_EFFECTS) eliteAudio.playAt("hit", o.pos, { range: 1700, gain: .65 });
      addImpactShake(o.thargoid ? 1.3 : .85);
      if (!DEV_DISABLE_LASER_EFFECTS && externalTarget && game.energy < energyBefore) {
        const towardAttacker = norm(sub(o.pos, game.camera.pos));
        const hitPos = add(game.camera.pos, scale(towardAttacker, playerRadius * .38));
        spawnSmokePuffs(hitPos, .7, 3);
      }
      setMessage(`${o.name} ${arc === "aft" ? "aft" : "fore"} laser strike.`);
    }

    // A hard override on top of whatever a ship's aiMode steering wants: other terms
    // (fleeing the player, dogfighting a target, even the cruise/orbit standoff logic
    // itself under some geometries) can still add up to point a ship at the station, so
    // this pushes back the moment any ship gets within its hull + a margin, regardless
    // of mode. Zero outside that zone, so it's a no-op for the vast majority of frames.
    function stationAvoidance(pos, shipR) {
      const station = primaryStation();
      if (!station) return vec();
      const toShip = sub(pos, station.pos);
      const dist = len(toShip);
      const safeDist = stationClearanceRadius() + shipR + 340;
      if (dist >= safeDist) return vec();
      const away = dist > 1 ? scale(toShip, 1 / dist) : vec(0, 1, 0);
      return scale(away, (safeDist - dist) * 3);
    }

    // stationAvoidance steers a ship away from the station, but turn-rate/momentum limits
    // mean a fast ship already aimed at the station when it enters the safe zone can't
    // always turn away before its next few frames of forward motion would carry it inside
    // the hull. This is the hard guarantee: after movement, snap the position back out to
    // the hull + margin if it ended up closer, so no ship ever visually renders inside the
    // station regardless of how its steering got there.
    function clampOutsideStation(o) {
      const station = primaryStation();
      if (!station) return;
      const toShip = sub(o.pos, station.pos);
      const dist = len(toShip);
      const minDist = stationClearanceRadius() + (o.r || 60);
      if (dist >= minDist) return;
      const away = dist > 1 ? scale(toShip, 1 / dist) : vec(0, 1, 0);
      o.pos = add(station.pos, scale(away, minDist));
    }

    function updateStationTraffic(dt) {
      const station = primaryStation();
      if (!station || len(sub(station.pos, game.camera.pos)) > 5200) return;
      game.trafficClock -= dt;
      if (game.trafficClock > 0) return;
      game.trafficClock = 8 + Math.random() * 15;
      const activeTraffic = worldSnapshot().ships.filter((o) => o.aiMode === "stationLaunch" || o.aiMode === "stationDock").length;
      if (activeTraffic >= 2) return;
      const kind = Math.random() < .54 ? "launch" : "dock";
      spawnStationTraffic(kind, Math.random);
    }

    function stationLaunchLaneBlocker(o, center, outward, right, up) {
      const candidates = [
        { pos: game.camera.pos, r: playerCollisionRadius(), name: game.commander },
        ...worldSnapshot().ships.filter((x) => x !== o && !x._remove)
      ];
      let best = null;
      for (const x of candidates) {
        const rel = sub(x.pos, o.pos);
        const ahead = dot(rel, outward);
        if (ahead < 40 || ahead > 980) continue;
        const lane = sub(rel, scale(outward, ahead));
        const lateral = len(lane);
        const limit = (o.r || 55) + (x.r || 55) + 150;
        if (lateral > limit) continue;
        const score = ahead + lateral * 2.2;
        if (!best || score < best.score) best = { obj: x, ahead, lateral, lane, score };
      }
      if (!best) return null;
      const sideSign = dot(best.lane, right) >= 0 ? -1 : 1;
      const upSign = dot(best.lane, up) >= 0 ? -1 : 1;
      return norm(add(scale(outward, 1.6), add(scale(right, sideSign * 1.25), scale(up, upSign * .55))));
    }

    function updateStationTrafficShip(o, dt) {
      const station = o.trafficStation && isWorldObjectLive(o.trafficStation)
        ? o.trafficStation
        : primaryStation();
      if (!station) {
        o.aiMode = "cruise";
        return;
      }
      o.trafficAge = (o.trafficAge || 0) + dt;
      const { center, outward, right, up } = stationSlotAxes(station);
      const offset = o.trafficSlotOffset || vec();
      const speedMul = shipStats(o.model).speed || 1;
      if (o.aiMode === "stationLaunch") {
        const target = add(center, add(offset, scale(outward, 1800)));
        const panicDir = stationLaunchLaneBlocker(o, center, outward, right, up);
        if (panicDir) {
          o.engineBoost = Math.max(o.engineBoost || 0, 1.2);
          if (!o._launchPanicAt || performance.now() - o._launchPanicAt > 1400) {
            o._launchPanicAt = performance.now();
            shipHail(o, "flee", "Traffic lane blocked! Breaking hard!", .75, 5500);
          }
          steerVelocity(o, scale(panicDir, 960), dt, 175, 168 * speedMul);
        } else {
          steerVelocity(o, sub(target, o.pos), dt, 70, 96 * speedMul);
        }
        if (dot(sub(o.pos, center), outward) > 1500 || o.trafficAge > 16) {
          o.aiMode = "cruise";
          o.trafficStation = null;
          o.orbitCenter = add(station.pos, scale(outward, stationClearanceRadius() + 980));
          o.orbitRadius = 720 + Math.random() * 760;
          o.orbitAngle = Math.random() * TAU;
          o.orbitSpeed = (Math.random() > .5 ? 1 : -1) * (.16 + Math.random() * .22);
        }
        return;
      }

      const toShip = sub(o.pos, center);
      const along = dot(toShip, outward);
      const lateral = sub(toShip, scale(outward, along));
      const gateOffset = scale(offset, clamp(along / 1200, 0, 1));
      const target = add(center, add(gateOffset, scale(outward, -80)));
      steerVelocity(o, sub(target, o.pos), dt, 78, 90 * speedMul);
      if ((along < -35 && len(lateral) < 120) || o.trafficAge > 18) {
        o._remove = true;
          if (o === game.targetObject) game.targetObject = primaryStation();
      }
    }

    function updateShipAI(o, dt) {
      const avoidStation = stationAvoidance(o.pos, o.r || 60);
      if (o.hostile && objectIntervalDue(o, "_senseClock", dt, .18, .16)) {
        const stale = o.target && (o.target.hp <= 0 || !isWorldObjectLive(o.target) || len(sub(o.target.pos, o.pos)) > 2200);
        if (o.target === undefined || stale) assignHostileTarget(o);
      }
      const targetPos = o.hostile ? hostileTargetPos(o) : game.camera.pos;
      const d = len(sub(targetPos, o.pos));

      if (o.hostile && o.role !== "police" && !o.thargoid && o.maxHp && o.hp < o.maxHp * .32 && o.aiMode !== "flee" && !o._fleeCommitted) {
        o._fleeCommitted = true;
        o.aiMode = "flee";
        o.fleeFrom = { ...targetPos };
        setMessage(`${o.name} breaks off and flees.`);
        shipHail(o, "flee", fleeLine(o), .6, 12000);
      }

      if (o.aiMode === "flee") {
        const from = o.fleeFrom || game.camera.pos;
        const away = norm(sub(o.pos, from));
        const jink = vec(Math.sin(performance.now() / 650 + (o.wobble || 0)) * 90, Math.cos(performance.now() / 800 + (o.wobble || 0)) * 60, 0);
        const speedMul = shipStats(o.model).speed || 1;
        steerVelocity(o, add(add(scale(away, 300), jink), avoidStation), dt, 135, 150 * speedMul);
        if (len(sub(o.pos, from)) > 7200 && o !== game.targetObject) o.aiMode = "cruise";
        return;
      }

      if (o.hostile) {
        const profile = npcCombatProfile(o);
        // Distance-banded tactics, echoing the source's tactics routine ("ships that are
        // too close turn away" / appropriately-ranged aggressive ships close in): without
        // this, ships always steered toward a point near the player's nose regardless of
        // range, so they flew straight through the player on a collision course instead of
        // dogfighting — and sat at point-blank range where the laser hit-test excludes them.
        // targetPos is either the player or another ship (see assignHostileTarget) — pirates
        // and aliens don't only ever fight the player now.
        const away = norm(sub(o.pos, targetPos));
        const lateral = norm(cross(away, vec(0, 1, 0)));
        const orbitDir = len(lateral) > .01 ? lateral : vec(1, 0, 0);
        const jink = Math.sin(performance.now() / 900 + (o.wobble || 0));
        let desired;
        if (d < 260) {
          desired = add(scale(away, 260), scale(orbitDir, 120 * jink));
        } else if (d < 900) {
          // orbitSign is fixed per ship so the orbit always circles the same way; jink
          // only breathes the radius in and out. Previously jink (peak +-130) directly
          // scaled orbitDir with no fixed sign, which is *larger* than the 30-unit inward
          // pull, so the ship's entire tangential heading flipped every time the sine
          // term crossed zero (~every 2.8s) instead of circling smoothly one direction —
          // exactly the "flips and only moves a little before flipping again" symptom.
          if (o.orbitSign === undefined) o.orbitSign = Math.random() > .5 ? 1 : -1;
          desired = add(add(scale(scale(away, -1), 30), scale(orbitDir, 140 * o.orbitSign)), scale(away, 40 * jink));
        } else if (o.target) {
          desired = sub(targetPos, o.pos);
        } else {
          const lead = add(game.camera.pos, scale(forwardVector(game.camera), Math.max(80, game.speed * .8)));
          desired = sub(lead, o.pos);
        }
        const speedMul = shipStats(o.model).speed || 1;
        steerVelocity(o, add(desired, avoidStation), dt, profile.accel, profile.maxSpeed * speedMul);
        o.attackClock -= dt;
        if (o.attackClock <= 0 && d > profile.minRange && d < profile.range) {
          o.attackClock = profile.cooldownMin + Math.random() * profile.cooldownJitter;
          if (isAlienShip(o) && Math.random() < .42) hail(o, hostileThreatLine(o));
          if (o.target) fireAtShip(o, o.target);
          else fireAtPlayer(o);
        }
      } else if (o.huntedBy && isWorldObjectLive(o.huntedBy) && o.huntedBy.target === o) {
        o.aiMode = "flee";
        o.fleeFrom = { ...o.huntedBy.pos };
        setMessage(`${o.name} is under attack and flees.`);
        shipHail(o, "flee", fleeLine(o), .6, 12000);
      } else if (d < 460 && Math.random() < dt * .5) {
        o.aiMode = "flee";
        o.fleeFrom = { ...game.camera.pos };
        setMessage(`${o.name} panics and flees.`);
        shipHail(o, "flee", fleeLine(o), .6, 12000);
      } else if (o.aiMode === "formation") {
        o.orbitAngle += (o.orbitSpeed || .18) * dt;
        const speedMul = shipStats(o.model).speed || 1;
        const center = o.orbitCenter || cameraLocalToWorld(game.camera, vec(0, 0, 900));
        const target = add(center, vec(
          Math.cos(o.orbitAngle) * (o.orbitRadius || 300),
          Math.sin(o.orbitAngle * .9) * ((o.orbitRadius || 300) * .42) + (o.formationY || 0) * .2,
          Math.sin(o.orbitAngle) * (o.orbitRadius || 300) * .45 + ((o.formationZ || 900) - 900) * .25
        ));
        steerVelocity(o, add(sub(target, o.pos), avoidStation), dt, 110, 115 * speedMul);
      } else if (o.aiMode === "orbit") {
        o.orbitAngle += (o.orbitSpeed || .18) * dt;
        const speedMul = shipStats(o.model).speed || 1;
        const center = o.orbitCenter || vec();
        const target = add(center, vec(
          Math.cos(o.orbitAngle) * (o.orbitRadius || 360),
          Math.sin(o.orbitAngle * 1.3 + (o.wobble || 0)) * 90,
          Math.sin(o.orbitAngle) * (o.orbitRadius || 360) * .7
        ));
        steerVelocity(o, add(sub(target, o.pos), avoidStation), dt, 85, 95 * speedMul);
      } else {
        const speedMul = shipStats(o.model).speed || 1;
        const station = primaryStation();
        const center = station ? station.pos : vec();
        // Cruising ships used to steer straight at the station's exact position with only
        // a small +-160/220 wobble, which lands well inside its real ~226-247 unit hull, so
        // they flew straight through it. Loiter around a slowly-drifting point on a safe
        // standoff ring clear of the hull instead.
        const standoff = stationClearanceRadius() + 1050;
        const loiterAngle = performance.now() / 5000 + (o.wobble || 0);
        const loiterPoint = add(center, vec(
          Math.cos(loiterAngle) * standoff,
          Math.sin(loiterAngle * .7) * standoff * .24,
          Math.sin(loiterAngle) * standoff
        ));
        const away = d < 360 ? scale(norm(sub(o.pos, game.camera.pos)), 360 - d) : vec();
        const cruise = add(add(sub(loiterPoint, o.pos), away), avoidStation);
        steerVelocity(o, cruise, dt, 55, 82 * speedMul);
      }
    }

    function project(p, w, h) {
      if (!finiteVec3(p) || p.z <= 8) return null;
      const f = Math.min(w, h) * .82;
      if (!Number.isFinite(f) || f <= 0) return null;
      return { x: w / 2 + (p.x / p.z) * f, y: h / 2 - (p.y / p.z) * f, s: f / p.z };
    }

    const RENDER_NEAR_PLANE = 8.05;

    function clipCamPolygonNear(verts, near = RENDER_NEAR_PLANE) {
      if (!verts.length) return [];
      const out = [];
      for (let i = 0; i < verts.length; i++) {
        const a = verts[i];
        const b = verts[(i + 1) % verts.length];
        const aIn = a.z > near;
        const bIn = b.z > near;
        if (aIn && bIn) {
          out.push(b);
        } else if (aIn && !bIn) {
          const t = (near - a.z) / (b.z - a.z || 1);
          out.push(vec(lerp(a.x, b.x, t), lerp(a.y, b.y, t), near));
        } else if (!aIn && bIn) {
          const t = (near - a.z) / (b.z - a.z || 1);
          out.push(vec(lerp(a.x, b.x, t), lerp(a.y, b.y, t), near));
          out.push(b);
        }
      }
      return out;
    }

    function hexToRgb(hex) {
      const clean = String(hex || "#e9f2e4").replace("#", "");
      const n = parseInt(clean.length === 3 ? clean.replace(/(.)/g, "$1$1") : clean, 16);
      return { r: (n >> 16) & 255, g: (n >> 8) & 255, b: n & 255 };
    }

    function rgbToHex(r, g, b) {
      const toHex = (v) => clamp(Math.round(v), 0, 255).toString(16).padStart(2, "0");
      return `#${toHex(r)}${toHex(g)}${toHex(b)}`;
    }

    function distantModelColor(o) {
      const base = hexToRgb(o?.color || shipColor(o?.model, o?.police));
      const anchor = o?.type === "missile" ? { r: 68, g: 22, b: 18 }
        : ALIEN_MODELS.includes(o?.model) ? { r: 36, g: 28, b: 48 }
        : o?.police ? { r: 26, g: 42, b: 48 }
        : { r: 34, g: 38, b: 36 };
      const tint = o?.police || ALIEN_MODELS.includes(o?.model) || o?.type === "missile" ? .36 : .24;
      return rgbToHex(
        anchor.r * (1 - tint) + base.r * tint,
        anchor.g * (1 - tint) + base.g * tint,
        anchor.b * (1 - tint) + base.b * tint
      );
    }

    function shadedColor(hex, shade, alpha = 1) {
      const c = hexToRgb(hex);
      const floor = 10;
      return `rgba(${Math.round(c.r * shade + floor)}, ${Math.round(c.g * shade + floor)}, ${Math.round(c.b * shade + floor)}, ${alpha})`;
    }

    function faceNormal(a, b, c) {
      const u = sub(b, a);
      const v = sub(c, a);
      return norm(vec(
        u.y * v.z - u.z * v.y,
        u.z * v.x - u.x * v.z,
        u.x * v.y - u.y * v.x
      ));
    }

    function starLightDirection(center) {
      const sun = primarySun();
      if (!sun) return norm(vec(-.45, .6, -1));
      const sunCam = cameraTransform(sun.pos, game.camera);
      return norm(sub(sunCam, center));
    }

    // Shared by collectSolidFaces (drawable polygon fills, indexed over the compact
    // model.faces list) and collectWireFaceVisibility (a visible/hidden flag per raw
    // normal index, including entries with no built face) — both need "is this face
    // pointing at the camera", just keyed by different arrays, so only this inner test
    // is factored out rather than the two loops themselves.
    // Trusts each face's winding order: buildBlueprint winds faces to their outward
    // normals, so the winding IS the orientation. Re-deriving
    // "outward" by flipping away from the object centroid (the old behaviour) breaks flat
    // double-sided appendages (Cougar wings, missile fins, the alloy plate) whose plane
    // passes through the centroid — both sides of the sheet got flipped the same way, so
    // culling/lighting couldn't tell top from bottom.
    function faceFacing(verts) {
      const n = faceNormal(verts[0], verts[1], verts[2]);
      const center = scale(verts.reduce((sum, p) => add(sum, p), vec()), 1 / verts.length);
      return { n, center, facing: -dot(n, norm(center)) };
    }

    // One engine for both graphics modes: wireframe is these same face polygons with a
    // flat black fill (occluding whatever is behind, exactly like a solid fill would)
    // instead of the lit/textured one, so "wire", "solid" and "both" (lit fill + edges
    // on top) all share one fill path instead of wireframe keeping a separate bespoke
    // black-occluder pass.
    function collectSolidFaces(model, camVerts, points, baseColor, alpha = 1, flat = false, decal = null, options = {}) {
      if (!model.faces) return [];
      const faces = [];
      model.faces.forEach((face, faceIndex) => {
        const normalIndex = model.faceNormalIndices ? model.faceNormalIndices[faceIndex] : faceIndex;
        const wireMaskFace = !model.wireMaskFaces || !!model.wireMaskFaces[faceIndex];
        if (options.wireMask && !wireMaskFace) return;
        if (options.wireSheetFill && wireMaskFace) return;
        let projected = face.map((i) => points[i]);
        let verts = face.map((i) => camVerts[i]);
        let clipped = false;
        if (projected.some((p) => !p)) {
          if (!options.project) return;
          verts = clipCamPolygonNear(verts);
          if (verts.length < 3) return;
          projected = verts.map((p) => options.project(p));
          if (projected.some((p) => !p)) return;
          clipped = true;
        }
        const avgZ = verts.reduce((sum, p) => sum + p.z, 0) / verts.length;
        const { n, center, facing: cameraFacing } = faceFacing(verts);
        if (cameraFacing <= -0.015) return;
        if (flat) {
          faces.push({ kind: "poly", projected, camVerts: verts, avgZ, fillStyle: "#000", faceIndex, normalIndex });
          return;
        }
        const facing = clamp(cameraFacing, 0, 1);
        // Strongly sun-driven so every object has a distinct dark side: a low ambient
        // floor plus a wide Lambert term, and only a whisper of camera-facing fill so
        // the shadow terminator isn't washed out on faces pointing at the viewer.
        const lit = clamp(.12 + Math.max(0, dot(n, starLightDirection(center))) * .82 + facing * .05, .1, .95);
        const grain = Math.abs(Math.sin(center.x * .037 + center.y * .071 + center.z * .043 + face.length * 1.7));
        faces.push({
          kind: "poly",
          projected,
          camVerts: verts,
          project: options.project || null,
          uv: !clipped && model.faceUV && model.faceUV[faceIndex],
          decalUV: !clipped && model.decalUV && model.decalUV[faceIndex],
          imageProjection: !clipped && model.imageProjectionUV && model.imageProjectionUV[faceIndex],
          faceIndex,
          normalIndex,
          avgZ,
          fillStyle: shadedColor(baseColor, lit * (.92 + grain * .12), alpha),
          metal: options.textures !== false,
          metalAlpha: clamp((.34 + facing * .34) * (options.metalAlphaMul ?? 1), .18, .78),
          texture: clipped ? null : options.texture || null,
          imageDecals: clipped ? null : options.imageDecals || null,
          decal: clipped ? null : decal
        });
      });
      return faces;
    }

    function collectWireFaceVisibility(model, camVerts) {
      if (!model.normals || !model.faceByNormalIndex) return null;
      const objectCenter = scale(camVerts.reduce((sum, p) => add(sum, p), vec()), 1 / camVerts.length);
      return model.normals.map((normal, faceIndex) => {
        const face = model.faceByNormalIndex[faceIndex];
        if (face && face.length >= 3) {
          return faceFacing(face.map((i) => camVerts[i])).facing > -0.015;
        }
        const n = norm(vec(normal[0], normal[1], normal[2]));
        return -dot(n, norm(objectCenter)) > -0.015;
      });
    }

    function wireEdgeVisible(model, edgeIndex, faceVisible, camVerts = null, edgeCullNormalsCam = null, points = null) {
      const edgeNormal = edgeCullNormalsCam && edgeCullNormalsCam[edgeIndex];
      if (edgeNormal) return true;
      if (!faceVisible || !model.edgeFaces) return true;
      const faces = model.edgeFaces[edgeIndex];
      if (!faces) return true;
      // [-1,-1] marks a silhouette-edge decoration (e.g. Krait's wingtip antennae) that no
      // face can occlude, so it draws regardless of face visibility.
      if (faces[0] < 0) return true;
      return !!faceVisible[faces[0]] || !!faceVisible[faces[1]];
    }

    function collectSolidDetails(model, o, camVerts, points, w, h, scaleFactor = 1, camera = game.camera, options = {}) {
      const mode = options.mode || "solid";
      const wireDetails = mode === "wire";
      if ((wireDetails && options.wireDetails !== true) || !model.details) return [];
      const roll = o.roll ?? (o.rot || 0) * .7;
      const orient = (v) => o.quat ? quatRotate(o.quat, v) : rotateShipPoint(v, o.rot || 0, o.pitch || 0, roll);
      const details = [];
      for (const detail of model.details) {
        if (options.enginesOnly && detail.type !== "engine") continue;
        const isLineDetail = detail.type === "line" || detail.type === "polyline";
        const markedProtrudingEdge = isLineDetail && detail.indices?.length === 2
          ? model.wireCullEdgeKeys?.has(detail.indices[0] < detail.indices[1] ? `${detail.indices[0]},${detail.indices[1]}` : `${detail.indices[1]},${detail.indices[0]}`)
          : false;
        if (options.protrudingEdgesOnly && !markedProtrudingEdge) continue;
        if (options.skipProtrudingEdges && markedProtrudingEdge) continue;
        if (detail.type === "beacon") {
          if (wireDetails) continue;
          const source = Number.isInteger(detail.index)
            ? model.verts[detail.index]
            : Array.isArray(detail.indices) && detail.indices.length
              ? model.verts[detail.indices[0]]
              : Array.isArray(detail.point)
                ? detail.point
                : null;
          if (!source) continue;
          const camPoint = add(worldDirToCam(orient(vec(source[0] * scaleFactor, source[1] * scaleFactor, source[2] * scaleFactor)), camera), o.cam || vec());
          const projected = o.project ? o.project(camPoint) : project(camPoint, w, h);
          if (!projected) continue;
          details.push({
            kind: "beacon",
            projected: [projected],
            avgZ: camPoint.z,
            color: detail.color || "#ffb642",
            seed: hash32(`${o.name || o.model || "model"}:${detail.index ?? 0}:beacon`)
          });
          continue;
        }
        const normal = detail.normal
          ? worldDirToCam(norm(orient(vec(detail.normal[0], detail.normal[1], detail.normal[2]))), camera)
          : null;
        const vertsOnSurface = detail.indices
          ? detail.indices.map((i) => camVerts[i])
          : detail.points.map(([x, y, z]) => add(worldDirToCam(orient(vec(x * scaleFactor, y * scaleFactor, z * scaleFactor)), camera), o.cam || vec()));
        if (vertsOnSurface.length < (isLineDetail ? 2 : 3)) continue;
        const surfaceCenter = scale(vertsOnSurface.reduce((sum, p) => add(sum, p), vec()), 1 / vertsOnSurface.length);
        const cullEpsilon = detail.cullEpsilon ?? (wireDetails ? .015 : -.08);
        if (normal && detail.cull !== false && -dot(normal, norm(surfaceCenter)) <= cullEpsilon) continue;
        const lift = normal ? (detail.lift ?? (detail.type === "engine" ? 5 : 3)) * scaleFactor : 0;
        const verts = normal && lift
          ? vertsOnSurface.map((p) => add(p, scale(normal, lift)))
          : vertsOnSurface;
        const projected = verts.map((p) => o.project ? o.project(p) : project(p, w, h));
        if (projected.some((p) => !p) || verts.length < (isLineDetail ? 2 : 3)) continue;
        if (isLineDetail) {
          if (wireDetails && markedProtrudingEdge) continue;
          details.push({
            kind: "line",
            projected,
            avgZ: verts.reduce((sum, p) => sum + p.z, 0) / verts.length,
            strokeStyle: wireDetails ? (options.wireColor || "#e9f2e4") : (detail.color || "#eef7ed"),
            lineWidth: detail.width || 1.2
          });
          continue;
        }
        const engineVisual = detail.type === "engine"
          ? engineDetailVisual(o.engineGlow ?? 1, detail.stroke || "#ffffff")
          : null;
        const wireColor = options.wireColor || "#e9f2e4";
        details.push({
          kind: "poly",
          projected,
          avgZ: verts.reduce((sum, p) => sum + p.z, 0) / verts.length,
          fillStyle: wireDetails ? "#000" : (detail.type === "engine" ? engineVisual.fill : (detail.color || "#101915")),
          strokeStyle: wireDetails ? (detail.stroke || wireColor) : (detail.type === "engine" ? engineVisual.stroke : detail.stroke || null),
          lineWidth: detail.width || 1.2,
          fillInset: wireDetails ? (options.wireFillInset ?? 1.1) : 0,
          glow: !wireDetails && detail.type === "engine",
          glowAlpha: wireDetails ? 0 : (engineVisual?.glowAlpha ?? 1),
          glass: !wireDetails && detail.type === "window"
        });
      }
      return details;
    }

    function collectProtrudingModelEdges(model, camVerts, points, strokeStyle = "#e9f2e4", lineWidth = 1.2) {
      if (!model.edges) return [];
      const items = [];
      for (let edgeIndex = 0; edgeIndex < model.edges.length; edgeIndex++) {
        const marked = !!model.edgeCullNormals?.[edgeIndex] || model.edgeFaces?.[edgeIndex]?.[0] < 0;
        if (!marked) continue;
        const [a, b] = model.edges[edgeIndex];
        const pa = points[a], pb = points[b];
        if (!pa || !pb) continue;
        const va = camVerts[a], vb = camVerts[b];
        items.push({
          kind: "line",
          projected: [pa, pb],
          avgZ: (va.z + vb.z) / 2,
          strokeStyle,
          lineWidth
        });
      }
      return items;
    }

    function polygonBounds(points) {
      return points.reduce((b, p) => ({
        minX: Math.min(b.minX, p.x),
        maxX: Math.max(b.maxX, p.x),
        minY: Math.min(b.minY, p.y),
        maxY: Math.max(b.maxY, p.y)
      }), { minX: Infinity, maxX: -Infinity, minY: Infinity, maxY: -Infinity });
    }

    function pointInPolygon(x, y, points) {
      let inside = false;
      for (let i = 0, j = points.length - 1; i < points.length; j = i++) {
        const a = points[i], b = points[j];
        const crosses = (a.y > y) !== (b.y > y);
        if (crosses && x < (b.x - a.x) * (y - a.y) / ((b.y - a.y) || 1e-6) + a.x) inside = !inside;
      }
      return inside;
    }

    function insetProjectedPolygon(points, amount) {
      if (!points?.length) return [];
      const center = points.reduce((sum, p) => ({ x: sum.x + p.x, y: sum.y + p.y }), { x: 0, y: 0 });
      center.x /= points.length;
      center.y /= points.length;
      return points.map((p) => {
        const dx = center.x - p.x;
        const dy = center.y - p.y;
        const d = Math.hypot(dx, dy);
        const t = d > 0 ? Math.min(amount / d, .42) : 0;
        return { x: p.x + dx * t, y: p.y + dy * t };
      });
    }

    function itemScreenCenter(item) {
      return item.projected.reduce((sum, p) => ({ x: sum.x + p.x, y: sum.y + p.y }), { x: 0, y: 0 });
    }

    function itemOccludedByCloserPolys(item, occluders) {
      if (!item?.projected?.length || !occluders?.length) return false;
      const center = itemScreenCenter(item);
      center.x /= item.projected.length;
      center.y /= item.projected.length;
      for (const blocker of occluders) {
        if (!blocker.projected?.length || blocker.avgZ >= item.avgZ - .35) continue;
        if (pointInPolygon(center.x, center.y, blocker.projected)) return true;
        const samples = [center, ...item.projected];
        let hits = 0;
        for (const sample of samples) {
          if (pointInPolygon(sample.x, sample.y, blocker.projected)) hits++;
        }
        if (hits >= Math.max(1, Math.ceil(samples.length * .34))) return true;
      }
      return false;
    }

    function projectedHull(points) {
      const pts = points
        .filter(Boolean)
        .map((p) => ({ x: p.x, y: p.y }))
        .sort((a, b) => a.x - b.x || a.y - b.y);
      if (pts.length <= 3) return pts;
      const half = [];
      const pushHullPoint = (p) => {
        while (half.length >= 2) {
          const a = half[half.length - 2], b = half[half.length - 1];
          if ((b.x - a.x) * (p.y - a.y) - (b.y - a.y) * (p.x - a.x) > 0) break;
          half.pop();
        }
        half.push(p);
      };
      for (const p of pts) pushHullPoint(p);
      const lower = half.slice();
      half.length = 0;
      for (let i = pts.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) pushHullPoint(pts[i]);
      return lower.concat(half.slice(1, -1));
    }

    function distanceToSegment(px, py, a, b) {
      const vx = b.x - a.x, vy = b.y - a.y;
      const wx = px - a.x, wy = py - a.y;
      const len2 = vx * vx + vy * vy || 1;
      const t = clamp((wx * vx + wy * vy) / len2, 0, 1);
      const dx = px - (a.x + vx * t), dy = py - (a.y + vy * t);
      return Math.hypot(dx, dy);
    }

    function laserFootprintHit(o, rel, w, h) {
      const model = MODELS[o.model || "cobra"];
      if (!model?.verts?.length) return null;
      const cx = w / 2, cy = h / 2;
      const rect = space.getBoundingClientRect();
      const dpr = rect.width ? w / rect.width : 1;
      const edgeTolerance = clamp(5.5 * dpr, 4, 13);
      const roll = o.roll ?? (o.rot || 0) * .7;
      const orient = (v) => o.quat ? quatRotate(o.quat, v) : rotateShipPoint(v, o.rot || 0, o.pitch || 0, roll);
      const mesh = modelMeshForRender(model, game.camera, w, h, {
        centerCam: rel,
        orient,
        project: (p) => project(p, w, h)
      });
      const { camVerts, points } = mesh;
      const faceItems = collectSolidFaces(model, camVerts, points, "#000", 1, true, null, { project: (p) => project(p, w, h) });
      let nearestEdge = Infinity;
      for (const item of faceItems) {
        const bounds = polygonBounds(item.projected);
        if (cx >= bounds.minX - edgeTolerance && cx <= bounds.maxX + edgeTolerance && cy >= bounds.minY - edgeTolerance && cy <= bounds.maxY + edgeTolerance) {
          if (pointInPolygon(cx, cy, item.projected)) return { depth: item.avgZ, screenDist: 0 };
          for (let i = 0; i < item.projected.length; i++) {
            const d = distanceToSegment(cx, cy, item.projected[i], item.projected[(i + 1) % item.projected.length]);
            nearestEdge = Math.min(nearestEdge, d);
          }
        }
      }

      const hull = projectedHull(points);
      if (hull.length >= 3) {
        const bounds = polygonBounds(hull);
        if (cx >= bounds.minX - edgeTolerance && cx <= bounds.maxX + edgeTolerance && cy >= bounds.minY - edgeTolerance && cy <= bounds.maxY + edgeTolerance) {
          if (pointInPolygon(cx, cy, hull)) return { depth: rel.z, screenDist: 0 };
          for (let i = 0; i < hull.length; i++) {
            const d = distanceToSegment(cx, cy, hull[i], hull[(i + 1) % hull.length]);
            nearestEdge = Math.min(nearestEdge, d);
          }
        }
      }

      if (points.some(Boolean)) {
        const projectedRadius = Math.max(edgeTolerance, (modelBoundingRadius(model) / Math.max(1, rel.z)) * Math.min(w, h) * .82);
        const center = project(rel, w, h);
        const dist = center ? Math.hypot(center.x - cx, center.y - cy) : Infinity;
        if (dist <= projectedRadius * .42 + edgeTolerance) return { depth: rel.z, screenDist: dist };
      }

      if (nearestEdge <= edgeTolerance) return { depth: rel.z, screenDist: nearestEdge };
      return null;
    }

    function shouldKeepShip(o, distance) {
      if (o.type !== "ship") return true;
      if (o === game.targetObject || o.target === game.targetObject) return true;
      if (distance < 9000 && (o.hostile || o.aiMode === "flee" || o.target)) return true;
      const rel = cameraTransform(o.pos, game.camera);
      if (rel.z > -300 && rel.z < 16000) {
        const projected = project(rel, space.width, space.height);
        if (projected && projected.x > -160 && projected.x < space.width + 160 && projected.y > -160 && projected.y < space.height + 160) return true;
      }
      return distance < 16000;
    }

    let hullTextureCanvas = null;
    const ROCK_MODEL_NAMES = new Set(["asteroid", "boulder", "splinter", "hermit"]);

    function isRockModelName(modelName) {
      return ROCK_MODEL_NAMES.has(modelName);
    }

    function isRockEntity(o) {
      return !!o && (isRockModelName(o.model) || ROCK_MODEL_NAMES.has(o.type));
    }

    function buildHullTexture() {
      const size = 400;
      const c = document.createElement("canvas");
      c.width = size;
      c.height = size;
      const tc = c.getContext("2d");
      const rng = mulberry(hash32("hull-metal-texture"));

      const base = tc.createLinearGradient(0, 0, size, size);
      base.addColorStop(0, "#dfe6df");
      base.addColorStop(.5, "#aab4ac");
      base.addColorStop(1, "#c7cfc8");
      tc.fillStyle = base;
      tc.fillRect(0, 0, size, size);

      tc.globalAlpha = .7;
      for (let i = 0; i < 320; i++) {
        const y = rng() * size;
        const x = rng() * size;
        const streak = 40 + rng() * 160;
        const shade = 110 + Math.floor(rng() * 100);
        tc.strokeStyle = `rgba(${shade},${shade + 4},${shade},${.25 + rng() * .45})`;
        tc.lineWidth = .8 + rng() * 1.6;
        tc.beginPath();
        tc.moveTo(x, y);
        tc.lineTo(x + streak, y + (rng() - .5) * 6);
        tc.stroke();
      }

      tc.globalAlpha = .9;
      for (let i = 0; i < 1100; i++) {
        const x = rng() * size, y = rng() * size;
        const shade = rng() > .5 ? 15 + rng() * 35 : 220 + rng() * 35;
        tc.fillStyle = `rgba(${shade},${shade},${shade},${.15 + rng() * .3})`;
        const s = rng() > .7 ? 2 : 1;
        tc.fillRect(x, y, s, s);
      }

      tc.globalAlpha = 1;
      tc.strokeStyle = "rgba(30,40,32,.42)";
      tc.lineWidth = 1.6;
      const panels = 5;
      for (let i = 1; i < panels; i++) {
        const p = (size / panels) * i;
        tc.beginPath(); tc.moveTo(p, 0); tc.lineTo(p, size); tc.stroke();
        tc.beginPath(); tc.moveTo(0, p); tc.lineTo(size, p); tc.stroke();
      }

      const sheen = tc.createLinearGradient(0, 0, size, size * .6);
      sheen.addColorStop(0, "rgba(255,255,255,.22)");
      sheen.addColorStop(.35, "rgba(255,255,255,0)");
      sheen.addColorStop(.7, "rgba(255,255,255,0)");
      sheen.addColorStop(1, "rgba(255,255,255,.12)");
      tc.fillStyle = sheen;
      tc.fillRect(0, 0, size, size);

      return c;
    }

    function getHullTexture() {
      if (!hullTextureCanvas) hullTextureCanvas = buildHullTexture();
      return hullTextureCanvas;
    }

    const rockTextureCache = new Map();

    function buildRockTexture(seed = 1) {
      const size = 360;
      const c = document.createElement("canvas");
      c.width = size;
      c.height = size;
      const tc = c.getContext("2d");
      const rng = mulberry(hash32(`rock-texture:${seed}`));

      const base = tc.createLinearGradient(0, 0, size, size);
      base.addColorStop(0, "#b9aa91");
      base.addColorStop(.45, "#807868");
      base.addColorStop(1, "#c2b398");
      tc.fillStyle = base;
      tc.fillRect(0, 0, size, size);

      for (let i = 0; i < 1800; i++) {
        const x = rng() * size, y = rng() * size;
        const shade = rng() < .5 ? 40 + rng() * 65 : 175 + rng() * 55;
        tc.fillStyle = `rgba(${shade},${shade * .96},${shade * .82},${.08 + rng() * .18})`;
        const s = rng() > .85 ? 2 : 1;
        tc.fillRect(x, y, s, s);
      }

      for (let i = 0; i < 34; i++) {
        const x = rng() * size, y = rng() * size;
        const r = 7 + rng() * 34;
        const g = tc.createRadialGradient(x, y, 0, x, y, r);
        g.addColorStop(0, `rgba(40,34,28,${.12 + rng() * .18})`);
        g.addColorStop(.55, `rgba(65,55,45,${.05 + rng() * .11})`);
        g.addColorStop(1, "rgba(0,0,0,0)");
        tc.fillStyle = g;
        tc.beginPath();
        tc.ellipse(x, y, r * (1.1 + rng() * .8), r * (.45 + rng() * .55), rng() * TAU, 0, TAU);
        tc.fill();
      }

      tc.lineCap = "round";
      for (let i = 0; i < 44; i++) {
        let x = rng() * size, y = rng() * size;
        const steps = 3 + Math.floor(rng() * 5);
        tc.strokeStyle = `rgba(34,29,24,${.16 + rng() * .22})`;
        tc.lineWidth = .7 + rng() * 1.8;
        tc.beginPath();
        tc.moveTo(x, y);
        for (let s = 0; s < steps; s++) {
          x += (rng() - .5) * 58;
          y += (rng() - .5) * 58;
          tc.lineTo(x, y);
        }
        tc.stroke();
      }

      const dust = tc.createLinearGradient(0, 0, size, size * .8);
      dust.addColorStop(0, "rgba(255,245,210,.12)");
      dust.addColorStop(.55, "rgba(255,245,210,0)");
      dust.addColorStop(1, "rgba(40,32,24,.16)");
      tc.fillStyle = dust;
      tc.fillRect(0, 0, size, size);
      return c;
    }

    function getRockTexture(seed = 1) {
      const key = hash32(`rock:${seed}`);
      let canvas = rockTextureCache.get(key);
      if (!canvas) {
        canvas = buildRockTexture(key);
        rockTextureCache.set(key, canvas);
        if (rockTextureCache.size > 24) rockTextureCache.delete(rockTextureCache.keys().next().value);
      }
      return canvas;
    }

    const stationTextureCache = new Map();

    function buildStationTexture(style = stationStyleForSystem(currentSystem())) {
      const size = 420;
      const c = document.createElement("canvas");
      c.width = size;
      c.height = size;
      const tc = c.getContext("2d");
      const rng = mulberry(style.seed || 1);
      const wealth = style.wealth ?? .5;
      const grime = style.grime ?? .4;
      const shine = style.shine ?? .5;

      const base = tc.createLinearGradient(0, 0, size, size);
      base.addColorStop(0, wealth > .72 ? "#f7fbf2" : wealth < .32 ? "#8f8372" : "#d6ddd2");
      base.addColorStop(.52, wealth > .72 ? "#bbc8bd" : wealth < .32 ? "#6d6257" : "#aab5aa");
      base.addColorStop(1, wealth > .72 ? "#e2ece4" : wealth < .32 ? "#9d866f" : "#c5cec4");
      tc.fillStyle = base;
      tc.fillRect(0, 0, size, size);

      // Smaller station-scale paneling than ships: lots of fine hull plates sell size.
      const panels = wealth > .72 ? 18 : wealth < .32 ? 13 : 16;
      tc.strokeStyle = wealth > .72 ? "rgba(245,255,248,.32)" : "rgba(20,25,20,.36)";
      tc.lineWidth = 1;
      for (let i = 1; i < panels; i++) {
        const p = i * size / panels;
        tc.beginPath(); tc.moveTo(p, 0); tc.lineTo(p + (rng() - .5) * 2, size); tc.stroke();
        tc.beginPath(); tc.moveTo(0, p); tc.lineTo(size, p + (rng() - .5) * 2); tc.stroke();
      }

      const pipeRuns = 16 + Math.floor((1 - wealth) * 10);
      for (let i = 0; i < pipeRuns; i++) {
        const horizontal = rng() > .5;
        const pos = rng() * size;
        const start = rng() * size * .18;
        const end = size - rng() * size * .18;
        const wobble = (rng() - .5) * 5;
        const pipeW = .9 + rng() * (wealth > .72 ? 1.4 : 2.4);
        tc.strokeStyle = wealth > .72 ? "rgba(210,230,220,.5)" : "rgba(50,45,38,.58)";
        tc.lineWidth = pipeW + 2.2;
        tc.lineCap = "round";
        tc.beginPath();
        if (horizontal) {
          tc.moveTo(start, pos);
          tc.lineTo((start + end) * .5, pos + wobble);
          tc.lineTo(end, pos + wobble * .4);
        } else {
          tc.moveTo(pos, start);
          tc.lineTo(pos + wobble, (start + end) * .5);
          tc.lineTo(pos + wobble * .4, end);
        }
        tc.stroke();
        tc.strokeStyle = wealth > .72 ? "rgba(245,255,250,.62)" : "rgba(145,122,92,.5)";
        tc.lineWidth = pipeW;
        tc.stroke();
      }

      const greebles = 70 + Math.floor((1 - wealth) * 55);
      for (let i = 0; i < greebles; i++) {
        const x = rng() * size, y = rng() * size;
        const w = 4 + rng() * 18;
        const h = 3 + rng() * 14;
        const raised = rng() > .42;
        tc.fillStyle = raised
          ? (wealth > .72 ? "rgba(230,242,232,.44)" : "rgba(54,50,43,.48)")
          : "rgba(5,8,6,.34)";
        tc.fillRect(x, y, w, h);
        tc.strokeStyle = wealth > .72 ? "rgba(255,255,255,.28)" : "rgba(20,16,12,.38)";
        tc.lineWidth = .8;
        tc.strokeRect(x + .5, y + .5, w, h);
        if (rng() < .38) {
          tc.fillStyle = wealth > .72 ? "rgba(90,255,230,.28)" : "rgba(255,150,52,.22)";
          tc.fillRect(x + w * .2, y + h * .25, Math.max(1, w * .2), Math.max(1, h * .45));
        }
      }

      const vents = 34 + Math.floor(grime * 26);
      tc.strokeStyle = wealth > .72 ? "rgba(75,95,85,.45)" : "rgba(18,15,12,.58)";
      for (let i = 0; i < vents; i++) {
        const x = rng() * size, y = rng() * size;
        const slats = 3 + Math.floor(rng() * 5);
        const w = 10 + rng() * 22;
        tc.lineWidth = .8 + rng() * .7;
        for (let s = 0; s < slats; s++) {
          tc.beginPath();
          tc.moveTo(x, y + s * 3);
          tc.lineTo(x + w, y + s * 3 + (rng() - .5) * 1.2);
          tc.stroke();
        }
      }

      tc.globalAlpha = .65;
      for (let i = 0; i < 900; i++) {
        const x = rng() * size, y = rng() * size;
        const streak = 6 + rng() * (wealth > .72 ? 34 : 70);
        const shade = wealth > .72 ? 180 + rng() * 60 : 70 + rng() * 90;
        tc.strokeStyle = `rgba(${shade},${shade + (wealth > .72 ? 8 : 2)},${shade},${.08 + rng() * .24})`;
        tc.lineWidth = .5 + rng() * 1.2;
        tc.beginPath();
        tc.moveTo(x, y);
        tc.lineTo(x + streak, y + (rng() - .5) * 3);
        tc.stroke();
      }

      if (grime > .18) {
        for (let i = 0; i < 80 + grime * 120; i++) {
          const x = rng() * size, y = rng() * size, r = 5 + rng() * (12 + grime * 34);
          const rust = rng() < grime * .72;
          const g = tc.createRadialGradient(x, y, 0, x, y, r);
          g.addColorStop(0, rust ? `rgba(118,58,24,${.18 + grime * .32})` : `rgba(8,10,8,${.14 + grime * .22})`);
          g.addColorStop(.55, rust ? `rgba(90,45,20,${.08 + grime * .18})` : `rgba(12,14,12,${.08 + grime * .16})`);
          g.addColorStop(1, "rgba(0,0,0,0)");
          tc.fillStyle = g;
          tc.beginPath();
          tc.ellipse(x, y, r * (1 + rng()), r * (.45 + rng() * .7), rng() * TAU, 0, TAU);
          tc.fill();
        }
      }

      if (shine > .45) {
        const sheen = tc.createLinearGradient(0, 0, size, size * .7);
        sheen.addColorStop(0, `rgba(255,255,255,${.12 + shine * .22})`);
        sheen.addColorStop(.35, "rgba(255,255,255,0)");
        sheen.addColorStop(.75, "rgba(255,255,255,0)");
        sheen.addColorStop(1, `rgba(210,255,245,${.06 + shine * .12})`);
        tc.fillStyle = sheen;
        tc.fillRect(0, 0, size, size);
      }

      tc.globalAlpha = 1;
      return c;
    }

    function getStationTexture(style) {
      const key = `${style?.seed || 0}:${Math.round((style?.wealth ?? .5) * 100)}`;
      let canvas = stationTextureCache.get(key);
      if (!canvas) {
        canvas = buildStationTexture(style);
        stationTextureCache.set(key, canvas);
        if (stationTextureCache.size > 16) stationTextureCache.delete(stationTextureCache.keys().next().value);
      }
      return canvas;
    }

    // --- Procedural hull decals ------------------------------------------------------
    // Decals use whole-hull object-space UVs, so stripes continue across adjacent faces
    // instead of resetting per panel. The seed is system/model/role based, giving local
    // traffic a recognisable livery whenever the commander returns to a system.
    const decalCache = new Map();

    const DECAL_STYLES = {
      police:  { tint: [42, 168, 255], accent: [230, 250, 255], alpha: .6 },
      pirate:  { tint: [18, 16, 15],   accent: [135, 18, 12],   alpha: .7 },
      hauler:  { tint: [20, 18, 12],   accent: [230, 182, 28],  alpha: .78 },
      trader:  { tint: [54, 62, 50],   accent: [212, 175, 55],  alpha: .58 },
      private: { tint: [46, 52, 60],   accent: [145, 160, 150], alpha: .54 },
      alien:   { tint: [92, 38, 128],  accent: [190, 90, 255],  alpha: .58 }
    };

    function rgba(rgb, alpha) {
      return `rgba(${rgb[0]},${rgb[1]},${rgb[2]},${alpha})`;
    }

    function drawAngledStripe(targetCtx, x, width, color, alpha, angle = -.62) {
      const size = DECAL_TEXTURE_SIZE;
      const slope = Math.tan(angle);
      targetCtx.strokeStyle = rgba(color, alpha);
      targetCtx.lineWidth = width;
      targetCtx.lineCap = "butt";
      targetCtx.beginPath();
      targetCtx.moveTo(x - size * .45, -30);
      targetCtx.lineTo(x + size * .45 + slope * size, size + 30);
      targetCtx.stroke();
    }

    function drawPirateSigil(targetCtx, rng, style, tightness) {
      const size = DECAL_TEXTURE_SIZE;
      const cx = size * (.32 + rng() * .36);
      const cy = size * (.28 + rng() * .42);
      const radius = (38 + rng() * 32) / tightness;
      targetCtx.save();
      targetCtx.translate(cx, cy);
      targetCtx.rotate((rng() - .5) * .9);
      targetCtx.lineCap = "round";
      targetCtx.lineJoin = "round";
      const kind = Math.floor(rng() * 4);
      const dark = rgba(style.tint, .86);
      const mark = rgba(style.accent, .74);
      const pale = "rgba(235,235,220,.78)";
      if (kind === 0) {
        // Skull + crossed bones, stylised enough to survive projection onto low-poly hulls.
        targetCtx.strokeStyle = dark;
        targetCtx.lineWidth = Math.max(3, radius * .13);
        for (const a of [-.58, .58]) {
          targetCtx.save();
          targetCtx.rotate(a);
          targetCtx.beginPath();
          targetCtx.moveTo(-radius * .8, radius * .52);
          targetCtx.lineTo(radius * .8, -radius * .52);
          targetCtx.stroke();
          for (const x of [-radius * .82, radius * .82]) {
            targetCtx.beginPath();
            targetCtx.arc(x, x < 0 ? radius * .54 : -radius * .54, radius * .12, 0, TAU);
            targetCtx.stroke();
          }
          targetCtx.restore();
        }
        targetCtx.fillStyle = pale;
        targetCtx.beginPath();
        targetCtx.ellipse(0, -radius * .12, radius * .52, radius * .58, 0, 0, TAU);
        targetCtx.fill();
        targetCtx.fillRect(-radius * .32, radius * .18, radius * .64, radius * .34);
        targetCtx.fillStyle = "rgba(10,8,8,.84)";
        for (const x of [-radius * .2, radius * .2]) {
          targetCtx.beginPath();
          targetCtx.arc(x, -radius * .12, radius * .12, 0, TAU);
          targetCtx.fill();
        }
        targetCtx.fillRect(-radius * .22, radius * .32, radius * .1, radius * .16);
        targetCtx.fillRect(-radius * .05, radius * .32, radius * .1, radius * .16);
        targetCtx.fillRect(radius * .12, radius * .32, radius * .1, radius * .16);
      } else if (kind === 1) {
        // Crossed blades.
        targetCtx.strokeStyle = dark;
        targetCtx.lineWidth = Math.max(3, radius * .12);
        for (const a of [-.55, .55]) {
          targetCtx.save();
          targetCtx.rotate(a);
          targetCtx.beginPath();
          targetCtx.moveTo(0, radius * .76);
          targetCtx.lineTo(0, -radius * .66);
          targetCtx.stroke();
          targetCtx.fillStyle = mark;
          targetCtx.beginPath();
          targetCtx.moveTo(0, -radius);
          targetCtx.lineTo(radius * .18, -radius * .58);
          targetCtx.lineTo(0, -radius * .72);
          targetCtx.lineTo(-radius * .18, -radius * .58);
          targetCtx.closePath();
          targetCtx.fill();
          targetCtx.fillRect(-radius * .32, radius * .42, radius * .64, radius * .12);
          targetCtx.restore();
        }
      } else if (kind === 2) {
        // Jagged warning mask.
        targetCtx.fillStyle = mark;
        targetCtx.beginPath();
        for (let i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
          const a = -Math.PI / 2 + i / 8 * TAU;
          const r = i % 2 ? radius * .46 : radius;
          targetCtx.lineTo(Math.cos(a) * r, Math.sin(a) * r);
        }
        targetCtx.closePath();
        targetCtx.fill();
        targetCtx.strokeStyle = dark;
        targetCtx.lineWidth = Math.max(3, radius * .1);
        targetCtx.stroke();
        targetCtx.fillStyle = "rgba(8,6,6,.8)";
        targetCtx.beginPath();
        targetCtx.moveTo(-radius * .42, -radius * .1);
        targetCtx.lineTo(-radius * .08, radius * .08);
        targetCtx.lineTo(-radius * .48, radius * .18);
        targetCtx.closePath();
        targetCtx.fill();
        targetCtx.beginPath();
        targetCtx.moveTo(radius * .42, -radius * .1);
        targetCtx.lineTo(radius * .08, radius * .08);
        targetCtx.lineTo(radius * .48, radius * .18);
        targetCtx.closePath();
        targetCtx.fill();
      } else {
        // Claw/sabre tally.
        targetCtx.strokeStyle = mark;
        targetCtx.lineWidth = Math.max(4, radius * .15);
        for (let i = -1; i <= 1; i++) {
          targetCtx.beginPath();
          targetCtx.moveTo(-radius * .55 + i * radius * .33, radius * .8);
          targetCtx.quadraticCurveTo(-radius * .1 + i * radius * .18, 0, radius * .34 + i * radius * .18, -radius * .86);
          targetCtx.stroke();
        }
      }
      targetCtx.restore();
    }

    function drawHaulerLogo(targetCtx, rng, style, x, y, radius, mirrored = false) {
      targetCtx.save();
      targetCtx.translate(x, y);
      if (mirrored) targetCtx.scale(-1, 1);
      targetCtx.rotate((rng() - .5) * .12);
      targetCtx.fillStyle = rgba(style.accent, .72);
      targetCtx.beginPath();
      const sides = 6 + Math.floor(rng() * 3);
      for (let i = 0; i < sides; i++) {
        const a = -Math.PI / 2 + i / sides * TAU;
        const r = radius * (i % 2 ? .72 : 1);
        targetCtx.lineTo(Math.cos(a) * r, Math.sin(a) * r);
      }
      targetCtx.closePath();
      targetCtx.fill();
      targetCtx.strokeStyle = rgba(style.tint, .62);
      targetCtx.lineWidth = Math.max(3, radius * .12);
      targetCtx.stroke();
      targetCtx.strokeStyle = "rgba(255,255,255,.55)";
      targetCtx.lineWidth = Math.max(2, radius * .07);
      targetCtx.beginPath();
      targetCtx.moveTo(-radius * .62, 0);
      targetCtx.lineTo(radius * .62, 0);
      targetCtx.moveTo(0, -radius * .62);
      targetCtx.lineTo(0, radius * .62);
      targetCtx.stroke();
      targetCtx.restore();
    }

    function drawHaulerLivery(targetCtx, rng, style, tightness, sys) {
      const size = DECAL_TEXTURE_SIZE;
      const panelAlpha = .34 + (1 - sys.economy / 7) * .16;
      const primary = [28 + rng() * 28, 64 + rng() * 40, 76 + rng() * 34].map(Math.round);
      targetCtx.fillStyle = rgba(primary, panelAlpha);
      targetCtx.fillRect(0, size * .18, size, size * .14);
      targetCtx.fillRect(0, size * .68, size, size * .14);
      targetCtx.fillStyle = rgba(style.accent, .64);
      targetCtx.fillRect(0, size * .47, size, Math.max(14, 24 / tightness));
      targetCtx.fillStyle = rgba(style.tint, .42);
      const stripeW = Math.max(10, 18 / tightness);
      targetCtx.fillRect(size * .18, 0, stripeW, size);
      targetCtx.fillRect(size * (1 - .18) - stripeW, 0, stripeW, size);
      targetCtx.strokeStyle = "rgba(255,255,255,.45)";
      targetCtx.lineWidth = Math.max(2, 3 / tightness);
      for (const y of [size * .18, size * .32, size * .47, size * .53, size * .68, size * .82]) {
        targetCtx.beginPath();
        targetCtx.moveTo(0, y);
        targetCtx.lineTo(size, y);
        targetCtx.stroke();
      }
      const logoR = Math.max(22, 40 / Math.sqrt(tightness));
      drawHaulerLogo(targetCtx, rng, style, size * .29, size * .5, logoR, false);
      drawHaulerLogo(targetCtx, rng, style, size * .71, size * .5, logoR, true);
      // Registration-style cargo ticks, mirrored to read as deliberate branding.
      const ticks = Math.round(5 + tightness * 2);
      targetCtx.fillStyle = "rgba(20,20,16,.38)";
      for (let i = 0; i < ticks; i++) {
        const y = size * (.22 + i * .56 / Math.max(1, ticks - 1));
        targetCtx.fillRect(size * .04, y, size * .09, Math.max(4, 7 / tightness));
        targetCtx.fillRect(size * .87, y, size * .09, Math.max(4, 7 / tightness));
      }
      // A little freight safety striping, kept to the edges so it reads commercial, not camo.
      const hazardGap = Math.max(24, 42 / tightness);
      for (let i = -2; i < 6; i++) {
        drawAngledStripe(targetCtx, i * hazardGap, hazardGap * .22, style.accent, .42, -.78);
        drawAngledStripe(targetCtx, size - i * hazardGap, hazardGap * .22, style.accent, .32, -.78);
      }
    }

    function drawCamoPatch(targetCtx, rng, cx, cy, radius, color, alpha, stretch = 1.55, angle = 0) {
      const points = 9 + Math.floor(rng() * 5);
      targetCtx.save();
      targetCtx.translate(cx, cy);
      targetCtx.rotate(angle);
      targetCtx.scale(stretch, 1);
      targetCtx.fillStyle = rgba(color, alpha);
      targetCtx.beginPath();
      for (let i = 0; i < points; i++) {
        const a = i / points * TAU;
        const r = radius * (.62 + rng() * .55);
        const x = Math.cos(a) * r;
        const y = Math.sin(a) * r;
        if (i === 0) targetCtx.moveTo(x, y);
        else targetCtx.lineTo(x, y);
      }
      targetCtx.closePath();
      targetCtx.fill();
      targetCtx.restore();
    }

    function drawCamoField(targetCtx, rng, style, tightness, density, angle, accentChance = .22) {
      const size = DECAL_TEXTURE_SIZE;
      const count = Math.round(density * (1 + tightness * .35));
      const baseRadius = size / (5.2 + tightness * 1.7);
      for (let i = 0; i < count; i++) {
        const color = rng() < accentChance ? style.accent : style.tint;
        const alpha = style.alpha * (.62 + rng() * .38);
        const radius = baseRadius * (.65 + rng() * 1.05);
        const cx = rng() * size;
        const cy = rng() * size;
        drawCamoPatch(targetCtx, rng, cx, cy, radius, color, alpha, 1.25 + rng() * 1.4, angle + (rng() - .5) * .75);
        if (cx < radius * 1.6) drawCamoPatch(targetCtx, rng, cx + size, cy, radius, color, alpha, 1.25 + rng() * 1.4, angle);
        if (cx > size - radius * 1.6) drawCamoPatch(targetCtx, rng, cx - size, cy, radius, color, alpha, 1.25 + rng() * 1.4, angle);
      }
    }

    function buildDecalTexture(seed, role, sys, band, modelName) {
      const size = DECAL_TEXTURE_SIZE;
      const c = document.createElement("canvas");
      c.width = c.height = size;
      const tc = c.getContext("2d");
      const rng = mulberry(hash32(`decal:${seed}:${role}:${band}:${sys.name}:${modelName || ""}`));
      const style = DECAL_STYLES[role] || DECAL_STYLES.private;
      const wealth = 1 - sys.economy / 7;   // 1 = Rich Industrial, 0 = Poor Agricultural
      const order = sys.government / 7;     // 1 = Corporate State, 0 = Anarchy
      const model = MODELS[modelName];
      const sizeFactor = model ? clamp(modelOverallSize(model) / 145, .65, 4.2) : 1;
      const tightness = Math.sqrt(sizeFactor);
      // White = untouched hull under the multiply blend.
      tc.fillStyle = "#fff";
      tc.fillRect(0, 0, size, size);

      if (role === "hauler") {
        drawHaulerLivery(tc, rng, style, tightness, sys);
      } else if (role === "pirate") {
        drawCamoField(tc, rng, style, tightness, 9 + (1 - order) * 4, -.82, .34);
        const marks = Math.round(4 + tightness * 4 + (1 - order) * 2);
        const gap = size / marks;
        for (let i = -2; i < marks + 3; i++) {
          const angry = rng() > .72;
          drawAngledStripe(tc, i * gap + (rng() - .5) * gap, gap * (.34 + rng() * .35), angry ? style.accent : style.tint, angry ? .58 : style.alpha * .85, rng() > .5 ? -.92 : .82);
        }
        const sigils = Math.max(2, Math.round(1 + tightness * 1.4));
        for (let i = 0; i < sigils; i++) drawPirateSigil(tc, rng, style, tightness);
      } else if (role === "police") {
        const bands = Math.round(3 + tightness * 3);
        const gap = size / bands;
        for (let i = -1; i < bands + 2; i++) {
          drawAngledStripe(tc, i * gap + rng() * 8, gap * .38, style.tint, style.alpha, -.12);
        }
        tc.fillStyle = rgba(style.accent, .55);
        tc.fillRect(0, size * .47, size, Math.max(8, 18 / tightness));
      } else if (role === "alien") {
        const veins = Math.round(8 + tightness * 6);
        tc.strokeStyle = rgba(style.tint, style.alpha);
        tc.lineCap = "round";
        for (let i = 0; i < veins; i++) {
          tc.lineWidth = 4 + rng() * 12 / tightness;
          tc.beginPath();
          const y = rng() * size;
          tc.moveTo(-20, y);
          for (let s = 0; s < 6; s++) tc.lineTo((s + 1) * size / 6, y + Math.sin(s * 1.7 + rng() * 2) * 30);
          tc.stroke();
        }
      } else {
        drawCamoField(tc, rng, style, tightness, 7 + (1 - wealth) * 4, -.48, wealth > .68 ? .28 : .16);
        const stripes = Math.round((2 + (1 - wealth) * 2.2) * tightness);
        const gap = size / Math.max(1, stripes);
        for (let i = -1; i < stripes + 2; i++) {
          drawAngledStripe(tc, i * gap + (rng() - .5) * gap * (1 - order), gap * (.22 + rng() * .18), style.tint, style.alpha * .42, -.45);
        }
        if (wealth > .68) {
          drawAngledStripe(tc, size * (.25 + rng() * .5), Math.max(4, 8 / tightness), style.accent, .58, -.08);
        }
      }

      // Battle damage: soft scorch blotches, heavier per band.
      const scorches = band === 0 ? 0 : band === 1 ? 5 : 13;
      for (let i = 0; i < scorches; i++) {
        const sx = rng() * size, sy = rng() * size, sr = 14 + rng() * (band === 2 ? 46 : 26);
        const gGrad = tc.createRadialGradient(sx, sy, 0, sx, sy, sr);
        gGrad.addColorStop(0, `rgba(12,10,8,${.55 + rng() * .3})`);
        gGrad.addColorStop(.6, "rgba(20,16,12,.3)");
        gGrad.addColorStop(1, "rgba(20,16,12,0)");
        tc.fillStyle = gGrad;
        tc.beginPath();
        tc.arc(sx, sy, sr, 0, TAU);
        tc.fill();
      }
      return c;
    }

    function getShipDecal(o) {
      if (game.fxLevel === "classic" || o.type !== "ship") return null;
      if (HACK_PROJECT_X_SKIN_ALL_SHIPS || TEST_BITMAP_SKINS_ALL_MESHES) return null;
      const sys = currentSystem();
      const metaRole = modelGameMeta(o.model).decalRole;
      if (metaRole === "none") return null;
      const role = metaRole || (o.police ? "police"
        : ALIEN_MODELS.includes(o.model) ? "alien"
        : o.role === "pirate" ? "pirate"
        : (o.role === "trader" && HAULER_MODELS.includes(o.model)) ? "hauler"
        : (o.role || "private"));
      const dmg = o.maxHp ? clamp(1 - (o.hp ?? o.maxHp) / o.maxHp, 0, 1) : 0;
      const band = dmg > .55 ? 2 : dmg > .25 ? 1 : 0;
      const seed = o.decalSeed ?? hash32(`${game.galaxy}:${sys.index}:${o.model}:${role}`);
      const key = `${seed}:${role}:${band}:${sys.name}:${o.model}`;
      let canvas = decalCache.get(key);
      if (!canvas) {
        canvas = buildDecalTexture(seed, role, sys, band, o.model);
        decalCache.set(key, canvas);
        if (decalCache.size > 64) decalCache.delete(decalCache.keys().next().value);
      }
      return canvas;
    }

    function previewDecalRole(modelName) {
      if (POLICE_MODELS.includes(modelName)) return "police";
      if (ALIEN_MODELS.includes(modelName)) return "alien";
      if (HAULER_MODELS.includes(modelName)) return "hauler";
      if (PIRATE_MODELS.includes(modelName) && !TRADER_MODELS.includes(modelName)) return "pirate";
      return "trader";
    }

    function getPreviewShipDecal(modelName) {
      if (!SHIP_MODEL_LIST.includes(modelName)) return null;
      return getShipDecal({
        type: "ship",
        model: modelName,
        role: previewDecalRole(modelName),
        decalSeed: hash32(`preview:${game.galaxy}:${game.current}:${modelName}`)
      });
    }

    const imageDecalCache = new Map();
    const projectedImageDecalSourceCache = new Map();

    function getProjectedImageDecalSource(key, dataUrl) {
      if (!dataUrl) return null;
      let entry = projectedImageDecalSourceCache.get(key);
      if (!entry) {
        const img = new Image();
        img.decoding = "async";
        img.src = dataUrl;
        entry = { img };
        projectedImageDecalSourceCache.set(key, entry);
        if (projectedImageDecalSourceCache.size > 160) projectedImageDecalSourceCache.delete(projectedImageDecalSourceCache.keys().next().value);
      }
      return entry.img.complete && entry.img.naturalWidth ? entry.img : null;
    }

    function bitmapSkinRole(o) {
      const modelName = o?.model || "";
      if (o?.type === "station" || o?.type === "hermit" || modelName === "coriolis" || modelName === "dodoStation") return "station";
      if (isRockEntity(o)) return modelName === "hermit" || o?.type === "hermit" ? "hermit" : "rock";
      if (o?.type === "cargo" || o?.type === "canister" || modelName === "cargo") return "cargo";
      if (o?.type === "missile" || modelName === "missile") return "missile";
      if (modelGameMeta(modelName).hiddenUntilDiscovered) return "project";
      if (o?.police || POLICE_MODELS.includes(modelName)) return "police";
      if (ALIEN_MODELS.includes(modelName)) return "alien";
      if (o?.role === "pirate" || (PIRATE_MODELS.includes(modelName) && !TRADER_MODELS.includes(modelName))) return "pirate";
      if ((o?.role === "trader" && HAULER_MODELS.includes(modelName)) || HAULER_MODELS.includes(modelName)) return "hauler";
      return "trader";
    }

    function mixRgb(a, b, t) {
      return {
        r: a.r * (1 - t) + b.r * t,
        g: a.g * (1 - t) + b.g * t,
        b: a.b * (1 - t) + b.b * t
      };
    }

    function rgbCss(c, alpha = 1) {
      return `rgba(${Math.round(c.r)},${Math.round(c.g)},${Math.round(c.b)},${alpha})`;
    }

    function roleBitmapPalette(o) {
      const modelName = o?.model || "";
      const role = bitmapSkinRole(o);
      const base = modelBaseColor(modelName) || (
        role === "station" ? "#72796f"
          : role === "rock" || role === "hermit" ? "#8e856e"
          : role === "cargo" ? "#b58b35"
          : role === "missile" ? "#8f2a20"
          : shipColor(modelName, role === "police")
      );
      const baseRgb = hexToRgb(base);
      const table = {
        project: { tint: "#ffd45f", accent: "#ff2d86", dark: "#16120d", line: "#f7e8ad" },
        police: { tint: "#1e6088", accent: "#5edfff", dark: "#07111a", line: "#dff8ff" },
        alien: { tint: "#6d35a8", accent: "#49ff91", dark: "#100819", line: "#d8b2ff" },
        pirate: { tint: "#45262a", accent: "#ff4a34", dark: "#090807", line: "#b8a098" },
        hauler: { tint: "#9d7a2d", accent: "#ffe250", dark: "#1a1710", line: "#f8d875" },
        station: { tint: "#5f665f", accent: "#ffba3c", dark: "#111513", line: "#aeb8aa" },
        hermit: { tint: "#806f56", accent: "#ffba3c", dark: "#16120d", line: "#c8b285" },
        rock: { tint: "#887b62", accent: "#c5b28a", dark: "#171411", line: "#b7aa90" },
        cargo: { tint: "#b3842e", accent: "#ffe650", dark: "#15120a", line: "#ffeaa6" },
        missile: { tint: "#84221b", accent: "#ff553e", dark: "#120606", line: "#ffc8ba" },
        trader: { tint: "#55635b", accent: "#8fd8a3", dark: "#101512", line: "#c5dfc8" }
      }[role] || {};
      const tint = hexToRgb(table.tint || base);
      return {
        role,
        base: mixRgb(baseRgb, tint, .46),
        light: mixRgb(baseRgb, { r: 255, g: 255, b: 255 }, .34),
        dark: mixRgb(baseRgb, hexToRgb(table.dark || "#101010"), .68),
        accent: hexToRgb(table.accent || "#8fd8a3"),
        line: hexToRgb(table.line || "#dbe5d8")
      };
    }

    function drawBitmapSkinChevron(tc, size, rng, palette, y, mirrored = false) {
      const stripe = size * (.035 + rng() * .018);
      const count = 9;
      tc.save();
      tc.translate(size / 2, y);
      if (mirrored) tc.scale(1, -1);
      tc.rotate((rng() - .5) * .16);
      for (let i = -count; i <= count; i++) {
        tc.fillStyle = i % 2 === 0 ? rgbCss(palette.accent, .78) : rgbCss(palette.dark, .92);
        tc.fillRect(i * stripe * 1.9, -stripe * 1.6, stripe, stripe * 5.2);
      }
      tc.restore();
    }

    function drawBitmapSkinPanels(tc, size, rng, palette, role, side) {
      tc.strokeStyle = rgbCss(palette.line, role === "rock" ? .18 : .25);
      tc.lineWidth = size * .0045;
      for (let i = 0; i < 18; i++) {
        const x = rng() * size;
        const y = rng() * size;
        const w = size * (.08 + rng() * .28);
        const h = size * (.035 + rng() * .16);
        tc.beginPath();
        tc.moveTo(x, y + h * .18);
        tc.lineTo(x + w * .18, y);
        tc.lineTo(x + w, y);
        tc.lineTo(x + w, y + h * .82);
        tc.lineTo(x + w * .82, y + h);
        tc.lineTo(x, y + h);
        tc.closePath();
        tc.stroke();
      }
      tc.globalAlpha = .42;
      tc.strokeStyle = rgbCss(palette.dark, .7);
      tc.lineWidth = size * .0025;
      for (let i = 0; i < 60; i++) {
        const x = rng() * size;
        const y = rng() * size;
        const len = size * (.03 + rng() * .2);
        tc.beginPath();
        tc.moveTo(x, y);
        tc.lineTo(x + len * (.3 + rng()), y + len * (rng() - .5) * .32);
        tc.stroke();
      }
      tc.globalAlpha = 1;
      if (role === "station" || role === "hermit") {
        tc.strokeStyle = rgbCss(palette.line, .14);
        tc.lineWidth = size * .006;
        const gap = size / 9;
        for (let i = -1; i <= 10; i++) {
          tc.beginPath();
          tc.moveTo(i * gap, 0);
          tc.lineTo(i * gap + size * .38, size);
          tc.stroke();
        }
      }
      if (role === "rock") {
        for (let i = 0; i < 48; i++) {
          const r = size * (.006 + rng() * .026);
          const x = rng() * size;
          const y = rng() * size;
          const grad = tc.createRadialGradient(x - r * .35, y - r * .35, 0, x, y, r * 1.9);
          grad.addColorStop(0, "rgba(255,255,255,.12)");
          grad.addColorStop(.5, rgbCss(palette.dark, .24));
          grad.addColorStop(1, "rgba(0,0,0,0)");
          tc.fillStyle = grad;
          tc.beginPath();
          tc.arc(x, y, r * 2, 0, TAU);
          tc.fill();
        }
      }
      if (role === "alien") {
        tc.strokeStyle = rgbCss(palette.accent, .28);
        tc.lineWidth = size * .006;
        for (let i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
          const y = size * (.15 + i * .1 + (rng() - .5) * .04);
          tc.beginPath();
          tc.moveTo(0, y);
          for (let x = 0; x <= size; x += size / 6) tc.quadraticCurveTo(x + size * .05, y + Math.sin(i + x * .02) * size * .08, x + size / 6, y);
          tc.stroke();
        }
      }
      if (role === "project") {
        const grad = tc.createLinearGradient(0, side === "top" ? size : 0, size, side === "top" ? 0 : size);
        grad.addColorStop(0, "rgba(255,255,255,.52)");
        grad.addColorStop(.22, "rgba(255,255,255,.08)");
        grad.addColorStop(.52, "rgba(255,45,134,.42)");
        grad.addColorStop(1, "rgba(255,255,255,.0)");
        tc.fillStyle = grad;
        tc.beginPath();
        tc.moveTo(size * .08, 0);
        tc.lineTo(size * .32, 0);
        tc.lineTo(size * .72, size);
        tc.lineTo(size * .46, size);
        tc.closePath();
        tc.fill();
      }
    }

    function buildBitmapSkinTexture(o, side) {
      const size = DECAL_TEXTURE_SIZE;
      const c = document.createElement("canvas");
      c.width = c.height = size;
      const tc = c.getContext("2d");
      const modelName = o?.model || o?.type || "mesh";
      const role = bitmapSkinRole(o);
      const palette = roleBitmapPalette(o);
      const rng = mulberry(hash32(`bitmap-skin:${modelName}:${role}:${side}:${o?.police ? 1 : 0}`));
      const baseGrad = tc.createLinearGradient(0, 0, size, size);
      baseGrad.addColorStop(0, rgbCss(palette.light, .95));
      baseGrad.addColorStop(.45, rgbCss(palette.base, .92));
      baseGrad.addColorStop(1, rgbCss(palette.dark, .94));
      tc.fillStyle = baseGrad;
      tc.fillRect(0, 0, size, size);

      const vignette = tc.createRadialGradient(size * .44, size * .38, 0, size * .5, size * .5, size * .72);
      vignette.addColorStop(0, "rgba(255,255,255,.08)");
      vignette.addColorStop(.62, "rgba(0,0,0,0)");
      vignette.addColorStop(1, "rgba(0,0,0,.34)");
      tc.fillStyle = vignette;
      tc.fillRect(0, 0, size, size);

      drawBitmapSkinPanels(tc, size, rng, palette, role, side);

      if (role === "hauler" || role === "station" || role === "cargo") {
        drawBitmapSkinChevron(tc, size, rng, palette, size * .18, false);
        drawBitmapSkinChevron(tc, size, rng, palette, size * .82, true);
      } else if (role === "pirate") {
        tc.save();
        tc.translate(size / 2, size * (side === "top" ? .38 : .62));
        tc.rotate((rng() - .5) * .3);
        tc.strokeStyle = rgbCss(palette.accent, .78);
        tc.lineWidth = size * .03;
        tc.beginPath();
        tc.moveTo(-size * .16, -size * .1);
        tc.lineTo(size * .16, size * .1);
        tc.moveTo(size * .16, -size * .1);
        tc.lineTo(-size * .16, size * .1);
        tc.stroke();
        tc.restore();
      } else if (role === "police") {
        tc.fillStyle = rgbCss(palette.accent, .36);
        for (let i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
          const y = size * (.28 + i * .14);
          tc.beginPath();
          tc.moveTo(size * .18, y);
          tc.lineTo(size * .5, y + size * .07);
          tc.lineTo(size * .82, y);
          tc.lineTo(size * .74, y + size * .05);
          tc.lineTo(size * .5, y + size * .1);
          tc.lineTo(size * .26, y + size * .05);
          tc.closePath();
          tc.fill();
        }
      } else if (role === "trader") {
        tc.strokeStyle = rgbCss(palette.accent, .35);
        tc.lineWidth = size * .02;
        tc.beginPath();
        tc.moveTo(size * .12, size * .78);
        tc.lineTo(size * .88, size * .22);
        tc.stroke();
      }

      tc.fillStyle = rgbCss(palette.line, role === "rock" ? .16 : .6);
      tc.font = `bold ${Math.round(size * .042)}px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
      tc.textAlign = "center";
      tc.textBaseline = "middle";
      const label = role === "rock" ? "" : modelDisplayName(modelName).replace(/[^A-Z0-9 ]/g, "").slice(0, 13);
      if (label) {
        tc.save();
        tc.translate(size / 2, side === "top" ? size * .55 : size * .46);
        tc.rotate(side === "top" ? Math.PI / 2 : -Math.PI / 2);
        tc.fillText(label, 0, 0);
        tc.restore();
      }
      return c;
    }

    function getGeneratedBitmapSkin(modelName, side, key) {
      const entry = globalThis.ULTRA_ELITE_BITMAP_SKINS?.[modelName]?.[side];
      const url = typeof entry === "string" ? entry : entry?.src;
      return url ? getProjectedImageDecalSource(`${key}:${side}:generated`, url) : null;
    }

    function generatedBitmapSkinMirrorX(modelName, side) {
      const entry = globalThis.ULTRA_ELITE_BITMAP_SKINS?.[modelName]?.[side];
      return !!(entry && typeof entry === "object" && entry.mirrorX);
    }

    function buildProjectedImageDecalTexture(modelName, side) {
      const size = DECAL_TEXTURE_SIZE;
      const c = document.createElement("canvas");
      c.width = c.height = size;
      const tc = c.getContext("2d");
      tc.clearRect(0, 0, size, size);
      tc.save();
      tc.globalCompositeOperation = "source-over";
      const rng = mulberry(hash32(`image-decal-test:${modelName}:${side}`));
      const baseAlpha = side === "top" ? .82 : .56;
      tc.translate(size / 2, size / 2);
      if (side === "bottom") tc.scale(1, -1);
      tc.rotate((rng() - .5) * .08);
      tc.fillStyle = `rgba(5,14,20,${baseAlpha})`;
      tc.beginPath();
      tc.moveTo(-size * .36, -size * .18);
      tc.lineTo(size * .34, -size * .08);
      tc.lineTo(size * .2, size * .16);
      tc.lineTo(-size * .42, size * .09);
      tc.closePath();
      tc.fill();
      tc.strokeStyle = `rgba(255,236,138,${side === "top" ? .74 : .42})`;
      tc.lineWidth = size * .018;
      tc.lineJoin = "round";
      tc.stroke();
      tc.strokeStyle = "rgba(255,255,255,.62)";
      tc.lineWidth = size * .008;
      for (let i = -2; i <= 2; i++) {
        const y = i * size * .055;
        tc.beginPath();
        tc.moveTo(-size * .26, y - size * .07);
        tc.lineTo(size * .19, y - size * .01);
        tc.stroke();
      }
      tc.fillStyle = "rgba(255,236,138,.78)";
      tc.font = `${Math.round(size * .056)}px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
      tc.textAlign = "center";
      tc.textBaseline = "middle";
      tc.fillText(side === "top" ? "PROJECT X" : "PX-04", 0, size * .245);
      tc.restore();
      return c;
    }

    function getEntityImageDecals(o) {
      if (game.fxLevel === "classic" || !o?.model) return null;
      if (TEST_BITMAP_SKINS_ALL_MESHES) {
        const role = bitmapSkinRole(o);
        const key = `bitmap-skin:${o.type || "mesh"}:${o.model}:${role}:${o.police ? 1 : 0}`;
        const generatedTop = getGeneratedBitmapSkin(o.model, "top", key);
        const generatedBottom = getGeneratedBitmapSkin(o.model, "bottom", key);
        const generatedBack = getGeneratedBitmapSkin(o.model, "back", key);
        if (generatedTop || generatedBottom || generatedBack) {
          return {
            top: generatedTop,
            bottom: generatedBottom,
            back: generatedBack,
            mirrorX: {
              top: generatedBitmapSkinMirrorX(o.model, "top"),
              bottom: generatedBitmapSkinMirrorX(o.model, "bottom"),
              back: generatedBitmapSkinMirrorX(o.model, "back")
            },
            alpha: role === "rock" ? .88 : .96,
            replaceBaseTexture: true
          };
        }
        let entry = imageDecalCache.get(key);
        if (!entry) {
          entry = {
            top: buildBitmapSkinTexture(o, "top"),
            bottom: buildBitmapSkinTexture(o, "bottom"),
            back: buildBitmapSkinTexture(o, "back"),
            alpha: role === "rock" ? .86 : .94,
            replaceBaseTexture: true
          };
          imageDecalCache.set(key, entry);
          if (imageDecalCache.size > 96) imageDecalCache.delete(imageDecalCache.keys().next().value);
        }
        return entry;
      }
      if (o.type !== "ship") return null;
      const meta = HACK_PROJECT_X_SKIN_ALL_SHIPS ? {
        imageDecalTest: true,
        imageDecalDataUrl: PROJECT_X_TOP_DECAL_DATA_URL,
        imageDecalBottomDataUrl: PROJECT_X_BOTTOM_DECAL_DATA_URL,
        imageDecalAlpha: 1,
        imageDecalReplaceBaseTexture: true
      } : modelGameMeta(o.model);
      if (!meta.imageDecalTest) return null;
      if (meta.imageDecalDataUrl || meta.imageDecalBottomDataUrl) {
        const top = getProjectedImageDecalSource(`${o.model}:top`, meta.imageDecalDataUrl);
        const bottom = getProjectedImageDecalSource(`${o.model}:bottom`, meta.imageDecalBottomDataUrl);
        return top || bottom ? {
          top,
          bottom,
          back: bottom || top,
          alpha: meta.imageDecalAlpha ?? .82,
          mirrorX: meta.imageDecalMirrorX || null,
          angle: meta.imageDecalAngle || null,
          replaceBaseTexture: !!meta.imageDecalReplaceBaseTexture
        } : null;
      }
      const key = `${o.model}:projected-test`;
      let entry = imageDecalCache.get(key);
      if (!entry) {
        entry = {
          top: buildProjectedImageDecalTexture(o.model, "top"),
          bottom: buildProjectedImageDecalTexture(o.model, "bottom"),
          back: buildProjectedImageDecalTexture(o.model, "back")
        };
        imageDecalCache.set(key, entry);
        if (imageDecalCache.size > 16) imageDecalCache.delete(imageDecalCache.keys().next().value);
      }
      return entry;
    }

    function getShipImageDecals(o) {
      return getEntityImageDecals(o);
    }

    function drawTexturedTriangle(targetCtx, img, x0, y0, x1, y1, x2, y2, u0, v0, u1, v1, u2, v2) {
      targetCtx.save();
      targetCtx.beginPath();
      targetCtx.moveTo(x0, y0);
      targetCtx.lineTo(x1, y1);
      targetCtx.lineTo(x2, y2);
      targetCtx.closePath();
      targetCtx.clip();

      u1 -= u0; v1 -= v0;
      u2 -= u0; v2 -= v0;
      x1 -= x0; y1 -= y0;
      x2 -= x0; y2 -= y0;

      const det = u1 * v2 - u2 * v1;
      if (Math.abs(det) < 1e-6) {
        targetCtx.restore();
        return;
      }
      const idet = 1 / det;
      const a = (v2 * x1 - v1 * x2) * idet;
      const b = (v2 * y1 - v1 * y2) * idet;
      const c = (u1 * x2 - u2 * x1) * idet;
      const d = (u1 * y2 - u2 * y1) * idet;
      const e = x0 - a * u0 - c * v0;
      const f = y0 - b * u0 - d * v0;

      targetCtx.transform(a, b, c, d, e, f);
      targetCtx.drawImage(img, 0, 0);
      targetCtx.restore();
    }

    function drawUVLayer(targetCtx, item, img, alpha, uv = item.uv, centered = true, composite = "multiply") {
      const pts = item.projected;
      if (!uv) return;
      const offset = centered ? img.width / 2 : 0;
      targetCtx.save();
      targetCtx.globalCompositeOperation = composite;
      targetCtx.globalAlpha = alpha;
      for (let i = 1; i + 1 < pts.length; i++) {
        drawTexturedTriangle(
          targetCtx, img,
          pts[0].x, pts[0].y, pts[i].x, pts[i].y, pts[i + 1].x, pts[i + 1].y,
          uv[0][0] + offset, uv[0][1] + offset, uv[i][0] + offset, uv[i][1] + offset, uv[i + 1][0] + offset, uv[i + 1][1] + offset
        );
      }
      targetCtx.restore();
    }

    // Canvas can only affine-map (linear) a texture across a triangle, which can't
    // represent perspective foreshortening — on a large near face (esp. the station)
    // the linear stretch visibly shifts as the face rotates, reading as the texture
    // "swimming" / staying locked to the viewer's turn. Fix: subdivide each fan
    // triangle in camera space until every sub-triangle is small on screen, so its
    // affine error is negligible. UV is affine in object space and object->camera is
    // rigid, so UV interpolates linearly right alongside the camera-space midpoints.
    const TEX_SUBDIV_PX = 48;
    function texEdgeLen(a, b) { return Math.hypot(a.x - b.x, a.y - b.y); }
    function texMid(a, b, projectFn) {
      const cam = scale(add(a.cam, b.cam), .5);
      const p = projectFn(cam);
      return p ? { cam, u: (a.u + b.u) / 2, v: (a.v + b.v) / 2, x: p.x, y: p.y } : null;
    }
    function subdivideTexTri(targetCtx, img, A, B, C, projectFn, depth, maxPx = TEX_SUBDIV_PX, maxDepth = 5) {
      const ab = texEdgeLen(A, B), bc = texEdgeLen(B, C), ca = texEdgeLen(C, A);
      const longest = Math.max(ab, bc, ca);
      if (depth >= maxDepth || longest < maxPx) {
        drawTexturedTriangle(targetCtx, img, A.x, A.y, B.x, B.y, C.x, C.y, A.u, A.v, B.u, B.v, C.u, C.v);
        return;
      }
      let m;
      if (ab >= bc && ab >= ca) {
        m = texMid(A, B, projectFn);
        if (!m) return drawTexturedTriangle(targetCtx, img, A.x, A.y, B.x, B.y, C.x, C.y, A.u, A.v, B.u, B.v, C.u, C.v);
        subdivideTexTri(targetCtx, img, A, m, C, projectFn, depth + 1, maxPx, maxDepth);
        subdivideTexTri(targetCtx, img, m, B, C, projectFn, depth + 1, maxPx, maxDepth);
      } else if (bc >= ab && bc >= ca) {
        m = texMid(B, C, projectFn);
        if (!m) return drawTexturedTriangle(targetCtx, img, A.x, A.y, B.x, B.y, C.x, C.y, A.u, A.v, B.u, B.v, C.u, C.v);
        subdivideTexTri(targetCtx, img, A, B, m, projectFn, depth + 1, maxPx, maxDepth);
        subdivideTexTri(targetCtx, img, A, m, C, projectFn, depth + 1, maxPx, maxDepth);
      } else {
        m = texMid(C, A, projectFn);
        if (!m) return drawTexturedTriangle(targetCtx, img, A.x, A.y, B.x, B.y, C.x, C.y, A.u, A.v, B.u, B.v, C.u, C.v);
        subdivideTexTri(targetCtx, img, A, B, m, projectFn, depth + 1, maxPx, maxDepth);
        subdivideTexTri(targetCtx, img, B, C, m, projectFn, depth + 1, maxPx, maxDepth);
      }
    }
    function drawUVLayerPersp(targetCtx, item, img, alpha, uv = item.uv, centered = true, maxPx = TEX_SUBDIV_PX, maxDepth = 5, composite = "multiply") {
      const projectFn = item.project, camV = item.camVerts;
      if (!projectFn || !camV || !uv) return;
      const off = centered ? img.width / 2 : 0;
      targetCtx.save();
      targetCtx.globalCompositeOperation = composite;
      targetCtx.globalAlpha = alpha;
      const mk = (i) => {
        const p = projectFn(camV[i]);
        return p ? { cam: camV[i], u: uv[i][0] + off, v: uv[i][1] + off, x: p.x, y: p.y } : null;
      };
      for (let i = 1; i + 1 < camV.length; i++) {
        const A = mk(0), B = mk(i), C = mk(i + 1);
        if (A && B && C) subdivideTexTri(targetCtx, img, A, B, C, projectFn, 0, maxPx, maxDepth);
      }
      targetCtx.restore();
    }

    function ratioClose(a, b, tolerance = .36) {
      return Number.isFinite(a) && Number.isFinite(b) && a > 0 && b > 0 && Math.abs(Math.log(a / b)) <= tolerance;
    }

    function imageDecalMirrorX(imageDecals, side, img, imageProjection = null) {
      const flags = imageDecals?.mirrorX;
      if (flags === true) return true;
      if (flags && typeof flags === "object" && flags[side]) return true;
      const w = img?.width || img?.naturalWidth || 0;
      const h = img?.height || img?.naturalHeight || 0;
      if (imageProjection?.baseW && imageProjection?.baseH) {
        const imageRatio = w / Math.max(1, h);
        const halfRatio = (imageProjection.baseW / 2) / Math.max(1, imageProjection.baseH);
        if (ratioClose(imageRatio, halfRatio, .28)) return true;
      }
      return w > 0 && h > 0 && w <= DECAL_TEXTURE_SIZE * .75 && w <= h * .75;
    }

    function imageDecalAngle(imageDecals, side) {
      const angle = imageDecals?.angle;
      if (Number.isFinite(angle)) return angle;
      if (angle && typeof angle === "object" && Number.isFinite(angle[side])) return angle[side];
      return 0;
    }

    function rotateImageDecalUv(u, v, width, height, angleDeg) {
      if (!angleDeg) return [u, v];
      const a = angleDeg * Math.PI / 180;
      const c = Math.cos(a), s = Math.sin(a);
      const cx = width / 2, cy = height / 2;
      const dx = u - cx, dy = v - cy;
      return [cx + dx * c - dy * s, cy + dx * s + dy * c];
    }

    function imageDecalDrawUv(imageProjection, imageDecals, img) {
      const side = imageProjection.side;
      const mirrorX = imageDecalMirrorX(imageDecals, side, img, imageProjection);
      const imgW = img.width || img.naturalWidth || DECAL_TEXTURE_SIZE;
      const imgH = img.height || img.naturalHeight || DECAL_TEXTURE_SIZE;
      const footprintRatio = (imageProjection.baseW || DECAL_TEXTURE_SIZE) / Math.max(1, imageProjection.baseH || DECAL_TEXTURE_SIZE);
      const effectiveImageRatio = (mirrorX ? imgW * 2 : imgW) / Math.max(1, imgH);
      const useFootprint = !imageProjection.squareUv || ratioClose(effectiveImageRatio, footprintRatio, .3);
      const sourceUv = useFootprint ? imageProjection.uv : imageProjection.squareUv;
      const projectionBaseW = useFootprint ? (imageProjection.baseW || DECAL_TEXTURE_SIZE) : DECAL_TEXTURE_SIZE;
      const projectionBaseH = useFootprint ? (imageProjection.baseH || DECAL_TEXTURE_SIZE) : DECAL_TEXTURE_SIZE;
      const baseW = mirrorX ? projectionBaseW / 2 : projectionBaseW;
      const sx = imgW / baseW;
      const sy = imgH / projectionBaseH;
      const mid = projectionBaseW / 2;
      const angle = imageDecalAngle(imageDecals, side);
      return sourceUv.map(([u, v]) => {
        const rotated = rotateImageDecalUv(u, v, projectionBaseW, projectionBaseH, angle);
        const foldedU = mirrorX ? clamp(mid - Math.abs(mid - rotated[0]), 0, mid) : rotated[0];
        return [foldedU * sx, rotated[1] * sy];
      });
    }

    function drawFaceTexture(targetCtx, item) {
      if (game.fxLevel === "classic") return;
      const b = polygonBounds(item.projected);
      if ((b.maxX - b.minX) * (b.maxY - b.minY) < 500) return;
      const img = item.texture || getHullTexture();
      const imageProjection = item.imageProjection && item.imageDecals?.[item.imageProjection.side];
      // Perspective-correct subdivided path when the projector + camera-space verts are
      // available (main flight view); otherwise the plain affine fan (ship diagram etc).
      if (!(imageProjection && item.imageDecals?.replaceBaseTexture)) {
        if (item.project && item.camVerts && item.uv) {
          drawUVLayerPersp(targetCtx, item, img, item.metalAlpha ?? .3);
        } else {
          drawUVLayer(targetCtx, item, img, item.metalAlpha ?? .3);
        }
      }
      // Decal stripes use continuous object-space UVs, while metal keeps local face UVs.
      if (item.decal) {
        if (item.project && item.camVerts && item.decalUV) {
          drawUVLayerPersp(targetCtx, item, item.decal, .86, item.decalUV, false);
        } else {
          drawUVLayer(targetCtx, item, item.decal, .86, item.decalUV, false);
        }
      }
      if (imageProjection) {
        const img = item.imageDecals[item.imageProjection.side];
        const uv = imageDecalDrawUv(item.imageProjection, item.imageDecals, img);
        if (item.project && item.camVerts) {
          drawUVLayerPersp(targetCtx, item, img, item.imageDecals.alpha ?? .82, uv, false, 42, 5, "source-over");
        } else {
          drawUVLayer(targetCtx, item, img, item.imageDecals.alpha ?? .82, uv, false, "source-over");
        }
      }
    }

    const glowSpriteCache = new Map();
    function glowSprite(key, stops, size = 128) {
      let sprite = glowSpriteCache.get(key);
      if (sprite) return sprite;
      const c = document.createElement("canvas");
      c.width = c.height = size;
      const tc = c.getContext("2d");
      const mid = size / 2;
      const g = tc.createRadialGradient(mid, mid, 0, mid, mid, mid);
      stops.forEach(([offset, color]) => g.addColorStop(offset, color));
      tc.fillStyle = g;
      tc.fillRect(0, 0, size, size);
      sprite = c;
      glowSpriteCache.set(key, sprite);
      return sprite;
    }

    function drawGlowSprite(targetCtx, x, y, radius, key, stops, alpha = 1, composite = "lighter") {
      if (!Number.isFinite(x) || !Number.isFinite(y) || !Number.isFinite(radius) || radius <= .5 || alpha <= .01) return;
      const img = glowSprite(key, stops);
      targetCtx.save();
      targetCtx.globalCompositeOperation = composite;
      targetCtx.globalAlpha = clamp(alpha, 0, 1.85);
      targetCtx.drawImage(img, x - radius, y - radius, radius * 2, radius * 2);
      targetCtx.restore();
    }

    const GLOW_SPRITES = {
      engineHaze: [
        [0, "hsla(198,95%,72%,.18)"],
        [.32, "hsla(192,92%,56%,.105)"],
        [.72, "hsla(210,92%,46%,.045)"],
        [1, "hsla(216,92%,38%,0)"]
      ],
      engineCore: [
        [0, "hsla(202,96%,88%,.76)"],
        [.26, "hsla(196,94%,68%,.38)"],
        [.62, "hsla(190,90%,52%,.16)"],
        [1, "hsla(206,90%,42%,0)"]
      ],
      policeBlue: [
        [0, "rgba(170,230,255,1)"],
        [.3, "rgba(42,168,255,.55)"],
        [1, "rgba(42,168,255,0)"]
      ],
      amberBeacon: [
        [0, "rgba(255,246,190,1)"],
        [.2, "rgba(255,168,42,.62)"],
        [.62, "rgba(255,112,32,.24)"],
        [1, "rgba(255,96,0,0)"]
      ],
      distantBlue: [
        [0, "rgba(82,170,255,.46)"],
        [.46, "rgba(56,142,255,.22)"],
        [1, "rgba(56,142,255,0)"]
      ],
      distantWhite: [
        [0, "rgba(255,255,255,.92)"],
        [.35, "rgba(255,255,255,.3)"],
        [1, "rgba(255,255,255,0)"]
      ]
    };

    function drawEngineGlow(targetCtx, points, alpha = 1) {
      if (!ultraFxEnabled()) return;
      if (performanceLod() >= 3 && targetCtx === ctx) alpha *= .65;
      alpha = clamp(alpha, 0, 1.85);
      if (alpha <= .01) return;
      const b = polygonBounds(points);
      const cx = (b.minX + b.maxX) / 2;
      const cy = (b.minY + b.maxY) / 2;
      const span = Math.max(b.maxX - b.minX, b.maxY - b.minY);
      const r = clamp(span * 3.2, 7, 54);
      const hazeR = clamp(span * 7.4, 22, 118);
      drawGlowSprite(targetCtx, cx, cy, hazeR, "engineHaze", GLOW_SPRITES.engineHaze, alpha);
      drawGlowSprite(targetCtx, cx, cy, r, "engineCore", GLOW_SPRITES.engineCore, alpha);
    }

    function drawPoliceStrobes(targetCtx, points) {
      const visible = points.filter(Boolean);
      if (visible.length < 2) return;
      const sorted = visible.slice().sort((a, b) => a.x - b.x);
      const candidates = [sorted[0], sorted[sorted.length - 1]];
      const t = performance.now() / 105;
      targetCtx.save();
      targetCtx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
      for (let i = 0; i < candidates.length; i++) {
        const p = candidates[i];
        const pulse = Math.max(0, Math.sin(t + i * Math.PI));
        const alpha = .18 + pulse * .62;
        const radius = 10 + pulse * 20;
        drawGlowSprite(targetCtx, p.x, p.y, radius, "policeBlue", GLOW_SPRITES.policeBlue, alpha);
      }
      targetCtx.restore();
    }

    // Glass is grey tinted toward the current system sun's hue, so cockpits catch the
    // local starlight (warm suns give warm glass). Falls back to a neutral warm grey in
    // witch-space or anywhere without a sun object.
    function glassGradient(targetCtx, projected) {
      if (game.fxLevel === "classic") return "#101915";
      const hue = primarySun()?.hue ?? 46;
      const b = polygonBounds(projected);
      const g = targetCtx.createLinearGradient(b.minX, b.minY, b.maxX, b.maxY);
      g.addColorStop(0, `hsl(${hue}, 26%, 84%)`);
      g.addColorStop(.35, `hsl(${hue}, 16%, 47%)`);
      g.addColorStop(.6, `hsl(${hue}, 22%, 64%)`);
      g.addColorStop(1, `hsl(${hue}, 14%, 19%)`);
      return g;
    }

    function drawSolidItems(targetCtx, items) {
      items.sort((a, b) => b.avgZ - a.avgZ);
      const tracePoly = (projected) => {
        targetCtx.beginPath();
        targetCtx.moveTo(projected[0].x, projected[0].y);
        for (let i = 1; i < projected.length; i++) targetCtx.lineTo(projected[i].x, projected[i].y);
      };
      for (const item of items) {
        if (item.kind === "beacon") {
          const p = item.projected[0];
          if (!p) continue;
          const phaseOffset = ((item.seed || 0) & 1023) / 1023 * TAU;
          const pulse = Math.pow(.5 + Math.sin(performance.now() / 1000 * TAU * .86 + phaseOffset) * .5, 3.2);
          const rgb = hexToRgb(item.color || "#ffb642");
          const core = clamp((p.s || 1) * 8, 2.2, 8.5);
          const halo = core * (5.5 + pulse * 2.4);
          targetCtx.save();
          targetCtx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
          const g = targetCtx.createRadialGradient(p.x, p.y, 0, p.x, p.y, halo);
          g.addColorStop(0, `rgba(255,250,210,${.82 + pulse * .18})`);
          g.addColorStop(.2, `rgba(${rgb.r},${rgb.g},${rgb.b},${.54 + pulse * .28})`);
          g.addColorStop(1, `rgba(${rgb.r},${rgb.g},${rgb.b},0)`);
          targetCtx.fillStyle = g;
          targetCtx.beginPath();
          targetCtx.arc(p.x, p.y, halo, 0, TAU);
          targetCtx.fill();
          targetCtx.globalCompositeOperation = "source-over";
          targetCtx.fillStyle = `rgba(255,248,188,${.8 + pulse * .2})`;
          targetCtx.beginPath();
          targetCtx.arc(p.x, p.y, core * .55, 0, TAU);
          targetCtx.fill();
          targetCtx.restore();
          continue;
        }
        if (item.glow) drawEngineGlow(targetCtx, item.projected, item.glowAlpha ?? 1);
        tracePoly(item.projected);
        if (item.kind === "line") {
          targetCtx.strokeStyle = item.strokeStyle;
          targetCtx.lineWidth = item.lineWidth || 1;
          targetCtx.lineCap = "round";
          targetCtx.lineJoin = "round";
          targetCtx.stroke();
          continue;
        }
        targetCtx.closePath();
        if (item.fillStyle) {
          targetCtx.fillStyle = item.glass ? glassGradient(targetCtx, item.projected) : item.fillStyle;
          if (item.fillInset) {
            const inset = insetProjectedPolygon(item.projected, item.fillInset);
            if (inset.length >= 3) {
              tracePoly(inset);
              targetCtx.closePath();
            }
          }
          targetCtx.fill();
          if (item.metal && item.uv) drawFaceTexture(targetCtx, item);
        }
        if (item.strokeStyle) {
          tracePoly(item.projected);
          targetCtx.closePath();
          targetCtx.strokeStyle = item.strokeStyle;
          targetCtx.lineWidth = item.lineWidth || 1;
          targetCtx.stroke();
        }
      }
    }

    function drawProjectedModelHull(targetCtx, model, camVerts, points, opts = {}) {
      const mode = opts.mode || game.graphicsMode;
      const color = opts.color || "#e9f2e4";
      const projectFn = opts.project || null;
      let wireMasks = null;
      let wireSheetFills = null;
      if (mode === "wire") {
        wireMasks = collectSolidFaces(model, camVerts, points, "#000", 1, true, null, { project: projectFn, wireMask: true });
        wireSheetFills = collectSolidFaces(model, camVerts, points, "#000", 1, true, null, { project: projectFn, wireSheetFill: true });
        const maskInset = Math.max(1.25, (opts.edgeWidth || 1) * 1.4);
        const sheetInset = Math.max(.8, (opts.edgeWidth || 1) * .9);
        wireMasks.forEach((item) => { item.fillInset = maskInset; });
        wireSheetFills.forEach((item) => { item.fillInset = sheetInset; });
      } else {
        drawSolidItems(targetCtx, collectSolidFaces(model, camVerts, points, color, 1, false, opts.decal || null, {
          project: projectFn,
          texture: opts.texture || null,
          textures: opts.textures,
          imageDecals: opts.imageDecals || null,
          metalAlphaMul: opts.metalAlphaMul
        }));
      }
      if (mode === "solid") return;
      targetCtx.strokeStyle = mode === "both" ? ULTRA_WIRE_STROKE : (opts.edgeColor || color);
      targetCtx.lineWidth = opts.edgeWidth || 1;
      const faceVisible = collectWireFaceVisibility(model, camVerts);
      targetCtx.beginPath();
      for (let edgeIndex = 0; edgeIndex < model.edges.length; edgeIndex++) {
        if (opts.detailEdges === false && opts.edgeCullNormalsCam?.[edgeIndex]) continue;
        if (!wireEdgeVisible(model, edgeIndex, faceVisible, camVerts, opts.edgeCullNormalsCam || null, points)) continue;
        const [a, b] = model.edges[edgeIndex];
        const pa = points[a], pb = points[b];
        if (!pa || !pb) continue;
        targetCtx.moveTo(pa.x, pa.y);
        targetCtx.lineTo(pb.x, pb.y);
      }
      targetCtx.stroke();
      const wireOccluders = mode === "wire" ? {
        sheetFills: wireSheetFills || [],
        hullMasks: wireMasks || []
      } : { sheetFills: [], hullMasks: [] };
      if (opts.deferWireOccluders) return wireOccluders;
      if (wireOccluders.sheetFills.length) drawSolidItems(targetCtx, wireOccluders.sheetFills);
      if (wireOccluders.hullMasks.length) drawSolidItems(targetCtx, wireOccluders.hullMasks);
      return wireOccluders;
    }

    function shipStatus(o) {
      if (o.aiMode === "flee") return { text: "FLEEING", color: "#91a78d" };
      if (o.hostile) return o.police ? { text: "PURSUING", color: "#46dfff" } : { text: "HOSTILE", color: "#ff6a55" };
      if (o.police) return { text: "PATROL", color: "#46dfff" };
      return { text: "CRUISING", color: "#65ff47" };
    }

    function drawShipLabels(w, h) {
      ctx.font = `13px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
      ctx.textAlign = "center";
      const lod = performanceLod();
      const maxLabels = lod >= 2 ? 2 : lod > 0 ? 4 : performanceSceneLoad() > .18 ? 5 : 7;
      const candidates = [];
      for (const o of game.objects) {
        if (o.type !== "ship") continue;
        if (!finiteVec3(o.pos)) continue;
        const rel = cameraTransform(o.pos, game.camera);
        if (rel.z < 40) continue;
        const pr = project(rel, w, h);
        if (!pr) continue;
        const apparentR = Math.abs(o.r * pr.s);
        if (apparentR < (lod >= 2 ? 24 : 16) || pr.x < -60 || pr.x > w + 60 || pr.y < -30 || pr.y > h + 30) continue;
        const d = len(sub(o.pos, game.camera.pos));
        const priority = (o === game.targetObject ? -10000 : 0) + (o.hostile ? -2200 : 0) + (o.police ? -900 : 0) + d;
        candidates.push({ o, pr, apparentR, d, priority });
      }

      candidates.sort((a, b) => a.priority - b.priority);
      for (const item of candidates.slice(0, maxLabels)) {
        const { o, pr, apparentR, d } = item;

        const status = shipStatus(o);
        const distText = `${Math.round(d)}m`;
        const labelY = pr.y - apparentR - 12;
        const barW = 55;
        ctx.font = `13px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
        const nameW = ctx.measureText(o.name).width;
        ctx.font = `11px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
        const statusW = ctx.measureText(status.text).width;
        const distW = ctx.measureText(distText).width;
        const boxW = Math.max(nameW, statusW, distW, barW) + 12;

        ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(3,8,3,.55)";
        ctx.fillRect(pr.x - boxW / 2, labelY - 48, boxW, 54);
        ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(101,255,71,.25)";
        ctx.lineWidth = 1;
        ctx.strokeRect(pr.x - boxW / 2, labelY - 48, boxW, 54);

        ctx.fillStyle = "#cfe9c8";
        ctx.font = `13px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
        ctx.fillText(o.name, pr.x, labelY - 34);
        ctx.fillStyle = status.color;
        ctx.font = `11px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
        ctx.fillText(status.text, pr.x, labelY - 21);
        ctx.fillStyle = "#91a78d";
        ctx.fillText(distText, pr.x, labelY - 8);

        const hpFrac = clamp((o.hp ?? 1) / (o.maxHp || o.hp || 1), 0, 1);
        const hpColor = hpFrac > .5 ? "#65ff47" : hpFrac > .22 ? "#ffd33d" : "#ff6a55";
        const barX = pr.x - barW / 2, barY = labelY + 1;
        ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(255,255,255,.12)";
        ctx.fillRect(barX, barY, barW, 5);
        ctx.fillStyle = hpColor;
        ctx.fillRect(barX, barY, barW * hpFrac, 5);
        ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(255,255,255,.3)";
        ctx.lineWidth = .75;
        ctx.strokeRect(barX, barY, barW, 5);
      }
      ctx.textAlign = "left";
    }

    function drawLaserBeam2D(from, to, opts = {}) {
      const color = opts.color || "#ffd33d";
      const beam = hexToRgb(color);
      const core = hexToRgb(opts.core || "#fff5be");
      const width = opts.width || 2;
      const alpha = clamp(opts.alpha ?? 1, 0, 1.25);
      if (alpha <= .01) return;
      const dx = to.x - from.x, dy = to.y - from.y;
      const len2d = Math.hypot(dx, dy) || 1;
      const nx = -dy / len2d, ny = dx / len2d;
      const ultraLaser = opts.ultra ?? ultraFxEnabled();

      ctx.save();
      ctx.lineCap = "round";
      if (!ultraLaser) {
        ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(${beam.r},${beam.g},${beam.b},${alpha})`;
        ctx.lineWidth = opts.classicWidth || 1.2;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(from.x, from.y);
        ctx.lineTo(to.x, to.y);
        ctx.stroke();
        ctx.restore();
        return;
      }

      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
      if (opts.wedge !== false) {
        const near = { x: from.x + dx * .09, y: from.y + dy * .09 };
        const far = { x: from.x + dx * .88, y: from.y + dy * .88 };
        const wedgeBase = Math.max(42, width * 18);
        const wedgeTip = Math.max(3, width * 2.8);
        const wedgeGrad = ctx.createLinearGradient(from.x, from.y, to.x, to.y);
        wedgeGrad.addColorStop(0, `rgba(${beam.r},${beam.g},${beam.b},${alpha * .2})`);
        wedgeGrad.addColorStop(.72, `rgba(${beam.r},${beam.g},${beam.b},${alpha * .15})`);
        wedgeGrad.addColorStop(1, `rgba(${beam.r},${beam.g},${beam.b},0)`);
        ctx.fillStyle = wedgeGrad;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(near.x + nx * wedgeBase, near.y + ny * wedgeBase);
        ctx.lineTo(near.x - nx * wedgeBase, near.y - ny * wedgeBase);
        ctx.lineTo(far.x - nx * wedgeTip, far.y - ny * wedgeTip);
        ctx.lineTo(far.x + nx * wedgeTip, far.y + ny * wedgeTip);
        ctx.closePath();
        ctx.fill();
      }

      const glowMul = opts.glowMul ?? (opts.kind === "pulse" ? 4.2 : opts.kind === "mining" ? 3.6 : 3);
      const grad = ctx.createLinearGradient(from.x, from.y, to.x, to.y);
      grad.addColorStop(0, `rgba(${core.r},${core.g},${core.b},${alpha * .84})`);
      grad.addColorStop(.18, `rgba(${beam.r},${beam.g},${beam.b},${alpha * .64})`);
      grad.addColorStop(.72, `rgba(${beam.r},${beam.g},${beam.b},${alpha * .34})`);
      grad.addColorStop(1, `rgba(${beam.r},${beam.g},${beam.b},0)`);
      ctx.strokeStyle = grad;
      ctx.shadowColor = `rgba(${beam.r},${beam.g},${beam.b},${alpha})`;
      ctx.shadowBlur = (opts.shadowBlur ?? 12) * alpha;
      ctx.lineWidth = width * glowMul;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(from.x, from.y);
      ctx.lineTo(to.x, to.y);
      ctx.stroke();

      ctx.shadowBlur = 0;
      ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(${core.r},${core.g},${core.b},${alpha * (opts.kind === "pulse" ? 1 : .92)})`;
      ctx.lineWidth = width;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(from.x, from.y);
      ctx.lineTo(to.x, to.y);
      ctx.stroke();

      if (opts.secondary) {
        ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(${beam.r},${beam.g},${beam.b},${alpha * .2})`;
        ctx.lineWidth = width * 2.4;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(from.x, from.y);
        ctx.lineTo(to.x, to.y);
        ctx.stroke();
      }

      if (opts.bloom !== false) {
        const bloomCenter = { x: from.x + dx * .06, y: from.y + dy * .06 };
        const bloomRadius = Math.max(70, width * 34);
        const bloom = ctx.createRadialGradient(bloomCenter.x, bloomCenter.y, 0, bloomCenter.x, bloomCenter.y, bloomRadius);
        bloom.addColorStop(0, `rgba(${beam.r},${beam.g},${beam.b},${alpha * .62})`);
        bloom.addColorStop(.1, `rgba(${beam.r},${beam.g},${beam.b},${alpha * .62})`);
        bloom.addColorStop(.34, `rgba(${beam.r},${beam.g},${beam.b},${alpha * .32})`);
        bloom.addColorStop(1, `rgba(${beam.r},${beam.g},${beam.b},0)`);
        ctx.fillStyle = bloom;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(bloomCenter.x, bloomCenter.y, bloomRadius, 0, TAU);
        ctx.fill();
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawExternalPlayerShot(w, h, flightCam) {
      const shot = game.playerShot;
      if (!shot || game.viewMode !== "ext") return;
      const elapsed = performance.now() - (shot.t || game.lastShot);
      const dur = shot.duration || 85;
      if (elapsed >= dur) return;
      const age = clamp(elapsed / dur, 0, 1);
      const alpha = Math.pow(1 - age, shot.kind === "pulse" ? .52 : .68);
      const playerShip = playerWorldShip(flightCam);
      const forward = shipForwardWorld(playerShip);
      const color = shot.color || "#ffd33d";
      const hardpoints = playerLaserHardpoints(playerShip);
      const muzzleCenter = hardpoints.length
        ? scale(hardpoints.reduce((sum, p) => add(sum, p), vec()), 1 / hardpoints.length)
        : flightCam.pos;
      const endWorld = shot.to || add(muzzleCenter, scale(forward, shot.range || 1800));
      const end = projectWorldPoint(endWorld, w, h, game.camera);
      if (!end) return;
      for (const hp of hardpoints) {
        const from = projectWorldPoint(hp, w, h, game.camera);
        if (!from) continue;
        drawLaserBeam2D(from, end, {
          color,
          width: Math.max(1.2, (shot.width || 2) * 1.6),
          alpha,
          kind: shot.kind,
          wedge: false,
          bloom: false,
          glowMul: shot.kind === "pulse" ? 2.8 : 2.2,
          shadowBlur: shot.kind === "pulse" ? 16 : 10
        });
      }
    }

    function effectWorldPos(effect) {
      return add(effect.pos, scale(effect.drift, effect.t));
    }

    function addWorldEffectItems(items, effects, camera) {
      if (!ultraFxEnabled() || !effects?.length) return;
      for (const effect of effects) {
        if (effect.t >= effect.dur) continue;
        const pos = effectWorldPos(effect);
        const p = cameraTransform(pos, camera);
        if (p.z <= 1) continue;
        items.push({ effect, p, d: len(sub(pos, camera.pos)) });
      }
    }

    function renderObjectRadius(o) {
      if (!o) return 0;
      if (Number.isFinite(o.r)) return Math.max(0, o.r);
      const model = MODELS[o.model];
      if (!model) return 24;
      return modelBoundingRadius(model) * (o.scaleFactor ?? o.scale ?? 1);
    }

    function makeRenderItem(o, camera, w, h) {
      if (!o || !finiteVec3(o.pos)) return null;
      const p = cameraTransform(o.pos, camera);
      const d = len(sub(o.pos, camera.pos));
      const radius = renderObjectRadius(o);
      const screenRadius = p.z > 8 ? Math.max(0, radius * (Math.min(w, h) * .82 / p.z)) : 0;
      return {
        o,
        p,
        d,
        radius,
        screenRadius,
        renderKind: objectSimulationKind(o) || "other"
      };
    }

    function buildRenderItems(camera, w, h) {
      const items = [];
      for (const o of worldSnapshot().objects) {
        const item = makeRenderItem(o, camera, w, h);
        if (item) items.push(item);
      }
      return items;
    }

    function drawWorldItems(items, w, h, camera, drawEntity) {
      items.sort((a, b) => b.d - a.d);
      for (const item of items) {
        if (item.effect) drawSmokePuff(item.effect, w, h, camera);
        else drawEntity(item);
      }
    }

    function recordRenderError(scope, err) {
      const message = `${scope}: ${err?.message || err || "unknown render error"}`;
      if (game._lastRenderError !== message) {
        game._lastRenderError = message;
        setMessage(`Render fallback: ${message}`, true);
      }
      console.error(message, err);
    }

    function drawDockedBackdropSafe(w, h) {
      try {
        drawDockedBackdrop(w, h);
      } catch (err) {
        recordRenderError("docked backdrop", err);
        const scene = game.dockScene || makeDockScene(game.dockedAt || `${currentSystem().name} STATION`, false, "", []);
        drawClassicDockedBackdrop(w, h, scene);
      }
    }

    function drawSpace() {
      const w = space.width, h = space.height;
      ensureCameraState(game.camera);
      const flightCam = game.camera;
      ctx.fillStyle = "#000";
      ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);
      ctx.save();
      try {
      game.camera = jumpTransitionRenderCamera(viewCamera(), flightCam, game.transition);
      if (game.screenShake > .05 && ultraFxEnabled()) {
        const shake = clamp(game.screenShake, 0, 12) * (window.devicePixelRatio || 1);
        ctx.translate((Math.random() - .5) * shake, (Math.random() - .5) * shake);
      }
      ctx.lineCap = "round";
      drawGalaxyBackdrop(w, h);
      drawStars(w, h, flightCam);
      if (game.transition) drawTransitionBackgroundEffect(w, h, game.transition);
      const visible = buildRenderItems(game.camera, w, h);
      updateScenePerformanceLoad(visible);
      addWorldEffectItems(visible, game.smokePuffs, game.camera);
      const deathExploded = game.transition?.kind === "death" && game.transition._exploded;
      if (game.viewMode === "ext" && !game.docked && !deathExploded) {
        // The player's own ship only exists on screen in the external view; it rides the
        // flight camera exactly (same position, orientation via quat instead of Euler).
        const shipObj = playerWorldShip(flightCam, {
          model: game.transition?.deathModel || playerShipModel(),
          color: "#e9f2e4",
          name: game.commander,
          role: "private",
          hp: Math.max(1, game.energy),
          maxHp: 100,
          playerDamageMarks: game.playerDamageMarks
        });
        const playerItem = makeRenderItem(shipObj, game.camera, w, h);
        if (playerItem) visible.push(playerItem);
      }
      drawWorldItems(visible, w, h, game.camera, (item) => drawObject(item.o, item.p, w, h));
      if (!DEV_DISABLE_LASER_EFFECTS) drawExternalPlayerShot(w, h, flightCam);
      drawExplosions(w, h);
      if (!DEV_DISABLE_LASER_EFFECTS) drawEnemyShots(w, h);
      drawSolarHeatOverlay(w, h);
      if (game.showShipLabels && performanceLod() < 3) drawShipLabels(w, h);
      if (!game.docked && game.viewMode !== "fwd" && VIEW_LABELS[game.viewMode]) {
        ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(233,242,228,.75)";
        ctx.font = `13px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
        ctx.textAlign = "center";
        ctx.fillText(VIEW_LABELS[game.viewMode], w / 2, 20);
        ctx.textAlign = "left";
      }
      if (!DEV_DISABLE_LASER_EFFECTS && !game.docked && game.viewMode === "fwd" && game.playerShot && performance.now() - (game.playerShot.t || game.lastShot) < (game.playerShot.duration || 85)) {
        const age = clamp((performance.now() - (game.playerShot.t || game.lastShot)) / (game.playerShot.duration || 85), 0, 1);
        let endX = w / 2, endY = h / 2;
        if (game.playerShot.to) {
          const p = project(cameraTransform(game.playerShot.to, game.camera), w, h);
          if (p) { endX = p.x; endY = p.y; }
        }
        const wobble = game.playerShot.kind === "beam" ? Math.sin(performance.now() / 18) * 1.6 : 0;
        const muzzleY = h * 1.08;
        const spread = w * .62;
        const muzzles = [
          { x: w / 2 - spread + wobble, y: muzzleY },
          { x: w / 2 + spread + wobble, y: muzzleY }
        ];
        const width = (game.playerShot.width || 2) * (game.playerShot.kind === "mining" ? (1.15 - age * .25) : 1);
        const fadeRate = game.playerShot.kind === "beam" ? .45 : game.playerShot.kind === "pulse" ? .52 : .68;
        const alpha = clamp(1 - age * fadeRate, .08, 1);
        const glowMul = game.playerShot.kind === "pulse" ? 4.2 : game.playerShot.kind === "mining" ? 3.6 : 3;
        const ultraLaser = ultraFxEnabled();
        const drawBeam = (from) => {
          const color = game.playerShot.color || "#ffd33d";
          drawLaserBeam2D(from, { x: endX, y: endY }, {
            color,
            width: ultraLaser ? width : 1.2,
            alpha,
            kind: game.playerShot.kind,
            glowMul,
            ultra: ultraLaser,
            secondary: game.playerShot.kind === "mining" || game.playerShot.kind === "military"
          });
        };
        muzzles.forEach(drawBeam);
      }
      if (game.transition) drawTransitionEffect(w, h, game.transition);
      if (game.jumpCountdown) drawJumpCountdown(w, h, game.jumpCountdown);
      if (!game.autoDock && !game.docked) drawManualDockingCue(w, h);
      if (game.autoDock && !game.docked) drawAutoDockHud(w, h);
      if (game.docked && !["dockHangar", "launchHangar"].includes(game.transition?.kind)) drawDockedBackdropSafe(w, h);
      } catch (err) {
        recordRenderError("space render", err);
      } finally {
        ctx.restore();
        game.camera = flightCam;
      }
    }

    function solarHeatVisualLevel() {
      if (!ultraFxEnabled() || game.docked || game.playerDestroyed) return 0;
      const heat = clamp((game.cabinTemp || 0) / 112, 0, 1.35);
      return clamp(smoothstep(.18, .88, heat), 0, 1);
    }

    function drawSolarHeatOverlay(w, h) {
      const level = solarHeatVisualLevel();
      if (level <= .01) return;
      const now = performance.now() * .001;
      const dpr = Math.max(1, Math.min(2, window.devicePixelRatio || 1));
      ctx.save();
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "screen";
      const grad = ctx.createRadialGradient(w * .5, h * .56, Math.min(w, h) * .08, w * .5, h * .56, Math.max(w, h) * .72);
      grad.addColorStop(0, `rgba(255,214,122,${level * .025})`);
      grad.addColorStop(.52, `rgba(255,126,54,${level * .06})`);
      grad.addColorStop(1, `rgba(255,54,22,${level * .012})`);
      ctx.fillStyle = grad;
      ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);

      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
      ctx.lineCap = "round";
      ctx.lineWidth = .8 * dpr;
      const lineCount = Math.max(5, Math.round(8 * dpr));
      for (let i = 0; i < lineCount; i++) {
        const y = h * (.18 + i / Math.max(1, lineCount - 1) * .66) + Math.sin(now * 1.7 + i * 1.9) * h * .012 * level;
        const wobble = Math.sin(now * 2.3 + i) * 16 * dpr * level;
        const alpha = level * (.026 + i / lineCount * .016);
        ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(255,198,92,${alpha})`;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(w * .08, y);
        ctx.bezierCurveTo(w * .32, y + wobble, w * .68, y - wobble * .7, w * .92, y + Math.sin(now + i) * 7 * dpr * level);
        ctx.stroke();
      }

      if (level > .65) {
        ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "source-over";
        ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(255,64,20,${(level - .65) * .08})`;
        ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawManualDockingCue(w, h) {
      if (game.viewMode !== "fwd" || game.transition || game.jumpCountdown) return;
      const st = dockableTarget();
      if (!st || st.type !== "station") return;
      const status = manualDockingStatus(st, false);
      const slotPhase = Math.abs(Math.sin(st.rot || 0));
      const closeEnough = status.depth > -190 && status.depth < 560 && status.lateral < 230 && game.speed < 120 && slotPhase < .68 && status.alignment > .48;
      if (!closeEnough) return;

      const dpr = Math.max(1, Math.min(2, window.devicePixelRatio || 1));
      const cx = w / 2;
      const cy = h / 2;
      const r = 43 * dpr;
      const tickLen = 13 * dpr;
      const alignScore = clamp((status.alignment - .55) / .3, 0, 1);
      const lateralScore = clamp(1 - status.lateral / 128, 0, 1);
      const speedScore = clamp(1 - Math.max(0, game.speed - 58) / 28, 0, 1);
      const slotScore = clamp((.58 - slotPhase) / .23, 0, 1);
      const ready = status.ok;
      const checks = [
        { a: -Math.PI / 2, score: speedScore },
        { a: 0, score: alignScore },
        { a: Math.PI / 2, score: slotScore },
        { a: Math.PI, score: lateralScore }
      ];

      ctx.save();
      ctx.lineCap = "round";
      ctx.shadowColor = ready ? "rgba(101,255,71,.62)" : "rgba(255,211,61,.36)";
      ctx.shadowBlur = (ready ? 9 : 5) * dpr;
      checks.forEach((check) => {
        const ok = check.score > .78;
        const a = check.a;
        const inner = r;
        const outer = r + tickLen * (.45 + check.score * .55);
        ctx.globalAlpha = .28 + check.score * .62;
        ctx.strokeStyle = ok ? "rgba(101,255,71,.96)" : "rgba(255,211,61,.86)";
        ctx.lineWidth = (ok ? 1.9 : 1.25) * dpr;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(cx + Math.cos(a) * inner, cy + Math.sin(a) * inner);
        ctx.lineTo(cx + Math.cos(a) * outer, cy + Math.sin(a) * outer);
        ctx.stroke();
      });
      if (ready) {
        ctx.globalAlpha = .58;
        ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(101,255,71,.92)";
        ctx.lineWidth = 1 * dpr;
        ctx.shadowBlur = 7 * dpr;
        const s = 18 * dpr;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(cx - s, cy - r - 8 * dpr);
        ctx.lineTo(cx + s, cy - r - 8 * dpr);
        ctx.moveTo(cx - s, cy + r + 8 * dpr);
        ctx.lineTo(cx + s, cy + r + 8 * dpr);
        ctx.stroke();
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function canvasHudScale(w) {
      const rect = space.getBoundingClientRect();
      const scale = rect.width ? w / rect.width : Math.min(window.devicePixelRatio || 1, game.performance?.dprCap || 2);
      return Number.isFinite(scale) && scale > 0 ? scale : 1;
    }

    function canvasHudPanelMetrics(w, h, opts = {}) {
      const dpr = canvasHudScale(w);
      const cssW = w / dpr;
      const cssH = h / dpr;
      const boxWcss = Math.min(cssW * (opts.widthRatio || .34), opts.maxWidth || 360);
      const boxHcss = opts.height || 86;
      const bottomClearance = opts.bottomClearance || 224;
      return {
        dpr,
        boxW: boxWcss * dpr,
        boxH: boxHcss * dpr,
        x: (cssW / 2 - boxWcss / 2) * dpr,
        y: Math.max((opts.minTop || 76) * dpr, (cssH - bottomClearance - boxHcss) * dpr),
        pad: (opts.pad || 10) * dpr
      };
    }

    function drawAutoDockHud(w, h) {
      const state = typeof game.autoDock === "object" ? game.autoDock : null;
      if (!state?.hud) return;
      const { dpr, boxW, boxH, x, y, pad } = canvasHudPanelMetrics(w, h);
      const stage = state.hud.stage || "AUTO";
      const stageText = {
        marshal: "ACQUIRING APPROACH LANE",
        goAround: "GO-AROUND VECTOR",
        approach: "LINING UP WITH SLOT AXIS",
        align: "MATCHING SLOT ROTATION",
        final: "FINAL APPROACH"
      }[stage] || "AUTO DOCK ACTIVE";
      const alignPct = clamp((state.hud.alignment || 0) * 100, 0, 100);
      const latPct = clamp(1 - (state.hud.lateral || 0) / 380, 0, 1);
      ctx.save();
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(0,0,0,.18)";
      ctx.fillRect(x, y, boxW, boxH);
      ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(101,255,71,.42)";
      ctx.lineWidth = Math.max(1, dpr);
      ctx.strokeRect(x, y, boxW, boxH);
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(101,255,71,.08)";
      ctx.fillRect(x + dpr, y + dpr, boxW - dpr * 2, 22 * dpr);
      ctx.textAlign = "left";
      ctx.font = `${11 * dpr}px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(101,255,71,.9)";
      ctx.shadowColor = "rgba(101,255,71,.32)";
      ctx.shadowBlur = 7 * dpr;
      ctx.fillText(`DOCKING COMPUTER - ${stageText}`, x + pad, y + 16 * dpr);
      ctx.shadowBlur = 0;
      ctx.font = `${8.5 * dpr}px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(145,167,141,.82)";
      const lineY = y + 38 * dpr;
      ctx.fillText(`RANGE ${Math.round(state.hud.range || 0)}M   SLOT ${Math.round(state.hud.slotRange || 0)}M`, x + pad, lineY);
      ctx.fillText(`LATERAL ${Math.round(state.hud.lateral || 0)}M   ALIGN ${Math.round(alignPct)}%   SPEED ${Math.round(game.speed)}`, x + pad, lineY + 15 * dpr);
      const barX = x + pad;
      const barY = y + boxH - 17 * dpr;
      const barW = boxW - pad * 2;
      const barH = 4 * dpr;
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(101,255,71,.12)";
      ctx.fillRect(barX, barY, barW, barH);
      ctx.fillStyle = stage === "final" ? "rgba(255,211,61,.78)" : "rgba(101,255,71,.72)";
      ctx.fillRect(barX, barY, barW * latPct * clamp(alignPct / 100, .08, 1), barH);
      ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(101,255,71,.32)";
      ctx.strokeRect(barX, barY, barW, barH);
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawLaunchSequenceHud(w, h, tr) {
      const p = clamp(tr.t / tr.dur, 0, 1);
      const { dpr, boxW, boxH, x, y, pad } = canvasHudPanelMetrics(w, h);
      const stage = p < .2
        ? "CLEAR FOR TAKE OFF"
        : p < .42
          ? "DRIVE CORES RISING"
          : p < .72
            ? "MAG CLAMPS CLEAR"
            : "DEPARTURE VECTOR LOCKED";
      const thrust = Math.round(clamp(smoothstep(.12, .34, p) * 100, 0, 100));
      const lift = Math.round(clamp(smoothstep(.34, .64, p) * 100, 0, 100));
      const exit = Math.round(clamp(smoothstep(.58, 1, p) * 100, 0, 100));
      ctx.save();
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(0,0,0,.18)";
      ctx.fillRect(x, y, boxW, boxH);
      ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(101,255,71,.42)";
      ctx.lineWidth = Math.max(1, dpr);
      ctx.strokeRect(x, y, boxW, boxH);
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(101,255,71,.08)";
      ctx.fillRect(x + dpr, y + dpr, boxW - dpr * 2, 22 * dpr);
      ctx.textAlign = "left";
      ctx.font = `${11 * dpr}px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(101,255,71,.9)";
      ctx.shadowColor = "rgba(101,255,71,.32)";
      ctx.shadowBlur = 7 * dpr;
      ctx.fillText(`LAUNCH CONTROL - ${stage}`, x + pad, y + 16 * dpr);
      ctx.shadowBlur = 0;
      ctx.font = `${8.5 * dpr}px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(145,167,141,.82)";
      const lineY = y + 38 * dpr;
      ctx.fillText(`THRUST ${thrust}%   LIFT ${lift}%   EXIT ${exit}%`, x + pad, lineY);
      ctx.fillText(`VECTOR ${Math.round(p * 100).toString().padStart(3, "0")}%   FORCEFIELD CLEARANCE ACTIVE`, x + pad, lineY + 15 * dpr);
      const barX = x + pad;
      const barY = y + boxH - 17 * dpr;
      const barW = boxW - pad * 2;
      const barH = 4 * dpr;
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(101,255,71,.12)";
      ctx.fillRect(barX, barY, barW, barH);
      ctx.fillStyle = p > .72 ? "rgba(255,211,61,.78)" : "rgba(101,255,71,.72)";
      ctx.fillRect(barX, barY, barW * p, barH);
      ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(101,255,71,.32)";
      ctx.strokeRect(barX, barY, barW, barH);
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawDockingSequenceHud(w, h, tr) {
      const p = clamp(tr.t / tr.dur, 0, 1);
      const { dpr, boxW, boxH, x, y, pad } = canvasHudPanelMetrics(w, h);
      const stage = p < .22
        ? "FORCEFIELD ENTRY"
        : p < .5
          ? "DESCENT VECTOR"
          : p < .66
            ? "LANDING CLAMPS"
            : "STATION SERVICES ONLINE";
      const entry = Math.round(clamp(smoothstep(0, .42, p) * 100, 0, 100));
      const descent = Math.round(clamp(smoothstep(.32, .76, p) * 100, 0, 100));
      const clamps = Math.round(clamp(smoothstep(.72, .9, p) * 100, 0, 100));
      ctx.save();
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(0,0,0,.18)";
      ctx.fillRect(x, y, boxW, boxH);
      ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(101,255,71,.42)";
      ctx.lineWidth = Math.max(1, dpr);
      ctx.strokeRect(x, y, boxW, boxH);
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(101,255,71,.08)";
      ctx.fillRect(x + dpr, y + dpr, boxW - dpr * 2, 22 * dpr);
      ctx.textAlign = "left";
      ctx.font = `${11 * dpr}px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(101,255,71,.9)";
      ctx.shadowColor = "rgba(101,255,71,.32)";
      ctx.shadowBlur = 7 * dpr;
      ctx.fillText(`DOCKING CONTROL - ${stage}`, x + pad, y + 16 * dpr);
      ctx.shadowBlur = 0;
      ctx.font = `${8.5 * dpr}px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(145,167,141,.82)";
      const lineY = y + 38 * dpr;
      ctx.fillText(`ENTRY ${entry}%   DESCENT ${descent}%   CLAMPS ${clamps}%`, x + pad, lineY);
      ctx.fillText(`HANGAR VECTOR ${Math.round(p * 100).toString().padStart(3, "0")}%   TOUCHDOWN SEQUENCE ACTIVE`, x + pad, lineY + 15 * dpr);
      const barX = x + pad;
      const barY = y + boxH - 17 * dpr;
      const barW = boxW - pad * 2;
      const barH = 4 * dpr;
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(101,255,71,.12)";
      ctx.fillRect(barX, barY, barW, barH);
      ctx.fillStyle = p > .66 ? "rgba(255,211,61,.78)" : "rgba(101,255,71,.72)";
      ctx.fillRect(barX, barY, barW * p, barH);
      ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(101,255,71,.32)";
      ctx.strokeRect(barX, barY, barW, barH);
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawTransitionEffect(w, h, tr) {
      if (tr.kind === "death") {
        drawDeathSequence(w, h, tr);
      } else if (tr.kind === "eject") {
        drawEjectSequence(w, h, tr);
      } else if (tr.kind === "launch" || tr.kind === "dock") {
        drawDockingTunnel(w, h, tr);
      } else if (tr.kind === "launchHangar") {
        drawLaunchHangarSequence(w, h, tr);
      } else if (tr.kind === "dockHangar") {
        drawDockHangarSequence(w, h, tr);
      } else if (tr.kind === "galactic") {
        drawGalacticTunnel(w, h, tr);
      } else {
        drawHyperspaceTunnel(w, h, tr);
      }
    }

    function drawTransitionBackgroundEffect(w, h, tr) {
      if (!tr || !ultraFxEnabled()) return;
      // Departure star stretch now lives in drawStars(), where the normal local
      // speed-reference dust is drawn. Keeping this hook quiet prevents a separate
      // cinematic layer from sitting over foreground ships and stations.
    }

    const JUMP_STATUS_LINES = {
      hyperspace: [
        "CALCULATING WITCHSPACE VECTOR LATTICE",
        "CHARGING TOROIDAL JUMP-DRIVE CAPACITORS",
        "PHASE-LOCKING QUIRIUM INJECTOR MANIFOLD",
        "ALIGNING NAV COMPUTER TO TARGET STAR",
        "MASS-LOCK EXCLUSION CONE SCAN ACTIVE",
        "THIS IS NOT DUSTING CROPS",
        "AVOIDING SUPERNOVA BOUNCE VECTOR",
        "STABILISING HYPERSPACE FIELD COILS",
        "VERIFYING FUEL PLASMA FLOW RATE",
        "ARMING FRAME-SHIFT CONTAINMENT GRID"
      ],
      galactic: [
        "INDEXING GALACTIC SEED HARMONICS",
        "PRECESSING LONG-RANGE TOROIDAL DRIVE",
        "CHARGING ONE-SHOT QUIRIUM CASCADE",
        "ALIGNING MEAN GALACTIC PLANE VECTOR",
        "VERIFYING INTERGALACTIC NAV SOLUTION",
        "THIS IS NOT DUSTING CROPS",
        "SUPERLUMINAL MASS-SHADOW CHECK",
        "LOCKING DEEP-WITCHSPACE EXIT ANCHOR",
        "SPINNING HYPERCOIL FIELD GYROS",
        "FINALISING GALAXY TRANSFER ENVELOPE"
      ]
    };

    function drawJumpCountdown(w, h, tr) {
      const remaining = Math.max(0, Math.ceil(tr.dur - tr.t));
      const p = clamp(tr.t / tr.dur, 0, 1);
      const { dpr, boxW, boxH, x: boxX, y: boxY, pad } = canvasHudPanelMetrics(w, h, {
        widthRatio: .44,
        maxWidth: 430,
        height: 104,
        bottomClearance: 224,
        minTop: 92,
        pad: 11
      });
      const lineH = 13 * dpr;
      const warning = remaining <= 3;
      const lines = JUMP_STATUS_LINES[tr.kind] || JUMP_STATUS_LINES.hyperspace;
      const scroll = tr.t * 4.2;
      const baseIndex = Math.floor(scroll);
      const frac = scroll - baseIndex;
      const hexFor = (n) => (Math.imul((n + 1) | 0, 2654435761) >>> 0).toString(16).toUpperCase().padStart(8, "0");
      const byteFor = (n) => hexFor(n).slice(0, 2);
      const asciiFor = (text, tick, width = 14) => {
        const clean = String(text).replace(/[^A-Z0-9 ]/g, " ").replace(/\s+/g, " ").trim();
        const spin = clean ? (tick % clean.length) : 0;
        return (clean.slice(spin) + " " + clean).slice(0, width).padEnd(width, ".");
      };
      ctx.save();
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(0,0,0,.18)";
      ctx.fillRect(boxX, boxY, boxW, boxH);
      ctx.strokeStyle = warning ? "rgba(255,72,72,.46)" : "rgba(101,255,71,.42)";
      ctx.lineWidth = Math.max(1, dpr);
      ctx.strokeRect(boxX, boxY, boxW, boxH);
      ctx.fillStyle = warning ? "rgba(255,72,72,.18)" : "rgba(101,255,71,.08)";
      ctx.fillRect(boxX + 1 * dpr, boxY + 1 * dpr, boxW - 2 * dpr, 24 * dpr);
      ctx.shadowColor = warning ? "rgba(255,72,72,.45)" : "rgba(101,255,71,.42)";
      ctx.shadowBlur = warning ? 12 * dpr : 8 * dpr;
      ctx.textAlign = "left";
      ctx.fillStyle = warning ? "rgba(255,72,72,.82)" : "rgba(101,255,71,.9)";
      ctx.font = `${13 * dpr}px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
      ctx.fillText(`${tr.countdownLabel || "JUMP"} T-${String(remaining).padStart(2, "0")}`, boxX + pad, boxY + 18 * dpr);
      ctx.textAlign = "right";
      ctx.fillText(`${Math.round(p * 100)}%`, boxX + boxW - pad, boxY + 18 * dpr);
      ctx.shadowBlur = 0;
      const barX = boxX + pad;
      const barY = boxY + 28 * dpr;
      const barW = boxW - pad * 2;
      const barH = 4 * dpr;
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(101,255,71,.12)";
      ctx.fillRect(barX, barY, barW, barH);
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(101,255,71,.74)";
      ctx.fillRect(barX, barY, barW * p, barH);
      ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(101,255,71,.32)";
      ctx.strokeRect(barX, barY, barW, barH);
      ctx.textAlign = "left";
      ctx.font = `${8.5 * dpr}px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(101,255,71,.78)";
      for (let i = -1; i < 5; i++) {
        const lineIndex = baseIndex + i;
        const line = lines[((lineIndex % lines.length) + lines.length) % lines.length];
        const y = boxY + 50 * dpr + i * lineH - frac * lineH;
        if (y < boxY + 38 * dpr || y > boxY + boxH - 8 * dpr) continue;
        const tick = Math.floor(tr.t * 18);
        const addr = (0x7C00 + ((lineIndex * 16 + tick * 3) & 0x03ff)).toString(16).toUpperCase().padStart(4, "0");
        const bytes = Array.from({ length: 8 }, (_, b) => byteFor(tick * 11 + lineIndex * 37 + b * 19)).join(" ");
        ctx.fillText(`&${addr}  ${bytes}  |${asciiFor(line, tick + lineIndex)}|`, boxX + pad, y);
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function easeInOut(t) {
      t = clamp(t, 0, 1);
      return t * t * (3 - 2 * t);
    }

    function smoothstep(edge0, edge1, x) {
      const t = clamp((x - edge0) / (edge1 - edge0), 0, 1);
      return t * t * (3 - 2 * t);
    }

    function smootherstep(edge0, edge1, x) {
      const t = clamp((x - edge0) / (edge1 - edge0), 0, 1);
      return t * t * t * (t * (t * 6 - 15) + 10);
    }

    function drawDeathSequence(w, h, tr) {
      const p = clamp(tr.t / tr.dur, 0, 1);
      const cx = w / 2, cy = h / 2;
      ctx.save();
      if (tr.hadCapsule) {
        const podFlash = clamp(1 - Math.abs(tr.t - .95) / .2, 0, 1);
        if (podFlash > 0) {
          ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(220,255,235,${podFlash * .22})`;
          ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);
          ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(101,255,71,${podFlash * .68})`;
          ctx.lineWidth = 1.6;
          ctx.beginPath();
          for (let i = 0; i < 18; i++) {
            const a = i / 18 * TAU + podFlash * .4;
            ctx.moveTo(cx + Math.cos(a) * 24, cy + Math.sin(a) * 16);
            ctx.lineTo(cx + Math.cos(a) * (110 + podFlash * 120), cy + Math.sin(a) * (70 + podFlash * 80));
          }
          ctx.stroke();
        }
      }
      const boomFlash = clamp(1 - Math.abs(tr.t - (tr.hadCapsule ? 1.55 : 1.08)) / .28, 0, 1);
      if (boomFlash > 0) {
        ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(255,238,190,${boomFlash * .38})`;
        ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);
      }
      const fade = smoothstep(.68, 1, p);
      if (fade > 0) {
        ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(0,0,0,${fade})`;
        ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);
      }
      ctx.font = `${Math.max(11, w * .009)}px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
      ctx.textAlign = "center";
      ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(101,255,71,${clamp(1 - fade * 1.3, 0, .9)})`;
      const status = tr.t < .9
        ? "EXTERNAL CAM - HULL FAILURE"
        : tr.hadCapsule && tr.t < 1.55
          ? "ESCAPE CAPSULE ARMED"
          : tr._exploded
            ? "PRIMARY HULL DETONATION"
            : "REACTOR CASCADE";
      ctx.fillText(status, cx, h * .18);
      if (fade > .72) {
        const finalAlpha = (fade - .72) / .28;
        ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(101,255,71,${finalAlpha * .9})`;
        ctx.font = `${Math.max(28, w * .038)}px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
        ctx.fillText("GAME OVER", cx, h * .47);
        ctx.font = `${Math.max(12, w * .012)}px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
        ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(101,255,71,${finalAlpha * .72})`;
        const promptAlpha = tr.waitingForRestart ? .42 + Math.sin(performance.now() / 240) * .28 : .42;
        ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(101,255,71,${finalAlpha * promptAlpha})`;
        ctx.fillText("PRESS ANY KEY TO RESTART", cx, h * .55);
        ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(101,255,71,${finalAlpha * .48})`;
        ctx.fillText(tr.hadCapsule ? "RECOVERY BEACON ACQUIRED" : "COMMANDER RECORD REBUILT", cx, h * .61);
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    // Player escape-capsule ejection: hard white canopy-blow flash, then the view
    // tumbles (rotating radial streaks) while a vignette closes in — the capsule
    // spinning away from the wreck — before the respawn state change lands.
    function drawEjectSequence(w, h, tr) {
      const p = clamp(tr.t / tr.dur, 0, 1);
      const cx = w / 2, cy = h / 2;
      ctx.save();
      const spin = p * 5.2;
      const streaks = 26;
      ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(200,235,240,${clamp(.75 - p * .5, 0, 1)})`;
      ctx.lineWidth = 1.6;
      ctx.beginPath();
      for (let i = 0; i < streaks; i++) {
        const a = i / streaks * TAU + spin + Math.sin(i * 7.3) * .2;
        const r0 = 40 + (i % 5) * 26;
        const r1 = r0 + 90 + easeInOut(p) * 260;
        ctx.moveTo(cx + Math.cos(a) * r0, cy + Math.sin(a) * r0 * .8);
        ctx.lineTo(cx + Math.cos(a) * r1, cy + Math.sin(a) * r1 * .8);
      }
      ctx.stroke();
      const flashA = clamp(1 - p * 2.6, 0, 1);
      if (flashA > 0) {
        ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(240,252,252,${flashA})`;
        ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);
      }
      const vig = ctx.createRadialGradient(cx, cy, Math.max(20, (1 - p) * w * .5), cx, cy, w * .75);
      vig.addColorStop(0, "rgba(0,0,0,0)");
      vig.addColorStop(1, `rgba(0,0,0,${.45 + p * .55})`);
      ctx.fillStyle = vig;
      ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawSlotRing(cx, cy, halfW, halfH, skew, color, alpha, lineWidth) {
      ctx.save();
      ctx.globalAlpha = alpha;
      ctx.strokeStyle = color;
      ctx.lineWidth = lineWidth;
      ctx.lineJoin = "miter";
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(cx - halfW + skew, cy - halfH);
      ctx.lineTo(cx + halfW + skew, cy - halfH);
      ctx.lineTo(cx + halfW - skew, cy + halfH);
      ctx.lineTo(cx - halfW - skew, cy + halfH);
      ctx.closePath();
      ctx.stroke();
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawDockingTunnel(w, h, tr) {
      const p = clamp(tr.t / tr.dur, 0, 1);
      const cx = w / 2, cy = h / 2;
      const phase = tr.kind === "launch" ? 1 - p : p;
      const travel = easeInOut(p);
      const maxHalfW = w * .66;
      const color = tr.kind === "dock" ? "#64ff47" : "#ffd33d";
      ctx.save();
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(0,0,0,.76)";
      ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(0,0,0,.92)";
      ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h * .17);
      ctx.fillRect(0, h * .83, w, h * .17);
      ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(120,150,118,.45)";
      ctx.lineWidth = 1.2;
      ctx.strokeRect(w * .035, h * .17, w * .93, h * .66);

      const wall = ctx.createLinearGradient(cx, h * .18, cx, h * .82);
      wall.addColorStop(0, "rgba(160,160,145,.28)");
      wall.addColorStop(.5, "rgba(70,78,68,.04)");
      wall.addColorStop(1, "rgba(160,160,145,.22)");
      ctx.fillStyle = wall;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(0, h * .17);
      ctx.lineTo(w, h * .17);
      ctx.lineTo(cx + w * .16, cy - h * .035);
      ctx.lineTo(cx - w * .16, cy - h * .035);
      ctx.closePath();
      ctx.fill();
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(0, h * .83);
      ctx.lineTo(w, h * .83);
      ctx.lineTo(cx + w * .16, cy + h * .035);
      ctx.lineTo(cx - w * .16, cy + h * .035);
      ctx.closePath();
      ctx.fill();

      for (let i = 0; i < 12; i++) {
        const z = ((i / 12 + phase * 1.65) % 1);
        const shaped = z * z;
        const halfW = lerp(w * .055, maxHalfW, shaped);
        const halfH = halfW * lerp(.17, .24, z);
        const skew = Math.sin((z + travel) * TAU) * halfW * .035;
        const alpha = clamp(1.1 - z * .9, .16, .86);
        drawSlotRing(cx, cy, halfW, halfH, skew, color, alpha, 1 + z * 3.4);
      }

      const doorW = lerp(w * .34, w * .16, tr.kind === "dock" ? travel : 1 - travel);
      const doorH = doorW * .17;
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(0,0,0,.9)";
      ctx.strokeStyle = color;
      ctx.lineWidth = 2;
      ctx.strokeRect(cx - doorW / 2, cy - doorH / 2, doorW, doorH);
      ctx.fillRect(cx - doorW / 2 + 3, cy - doorH / 2 + 3, doorW - 6, doorH - 6);

      ctx.globalAlpha = .55;
      ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(255,255,255,.34)";
      ctx.lineWidth = 1;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(cx - w * .48, cy);
      ctx.lineTo(cx - doorW / 2, cy);
      ctx.moveTo(cx + doorW / 2, cy);
      ctx.lineTo(cx + w * .48, cy);
      ctx.stroke();
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawDockFadeOut(w, h, tr) {
      const p = clamp(tr.t / tr.dur, 0, 1);
      const fade = smoothstep(.08, .92, p);
      ctx.save();
      ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(0,0,0,${.34 + fade * .66})`;
      ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);
      ctx.textAlign = "center";
      ctx.font = `${Math.max(10, w * .009)}px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
      ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(101,255,71,${clamp(1 - fade * 1.15, 0, .72)})`;
      ctx.fillText("DOCKING CLAMPS ENGAGED", w / 2, h * .52);
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function makeHangarCamera(pos, target) {
      return { pos, q: quatLookRotation(norm(sub(target, pos)), vec(0, 1, 0)) };
    }

    function hangarProject(p, view, w, h) {
      return project(cameraTransform(p, view), w, h);
    }

    // The hangar camera flies INSIDE the room during the launch/dock sweeps, so wall and
    // floor corners routinely fall behind it. project() nulls those corners, and dropping
    // a whole surface because one corner failed made entire walls/floors pop in and out.
    // Proper fix: Sutherland-Hodgman clip each polygon against the camera near plane in
    // 3D camera space, then project the clipped shape (every remaining vert is in front).
    const HANGAR_NEAR = 9;
    function clipPolyNear(camPts, near = HANGAR_NEAR) {
      const out = [];
      for (let i = 0; i < camPts.length; i++) {
        const a = camPts[i], b = camPts[(i + 1) % camPts.length];
        const aIn = a.z > near, bIn = b.z > near;
        if (aIn) out.push(a);
        if (aIn !== bIn) {
          const t = (near - a.z) / (b.z - a.z);
          const m = vec(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t, near);
          // Carry texture coordinates through the clip: UV is affine in camera space
          // (rigid transform), so lerping by the same t is exact.
          if (a.u !== undefined) {
            m.u = a.u + (b.u - a.u) * t;
            m.v = a.v + (b.v - a.v) * t;
          }
          out.push(m);
        }
      }
      return out;
    }

    // Clip a camera-space polygon (u/v carried) against the halfspace dot(n,p) <= 0.
    function clipPolyHalfspace(pts, nx, ny, nz) {
      const out = [];
      for (let i = 0; i < pts.length; i++) {
        const a = pts[i], b = pts[(i + 1) % pts.length];
        const da = a.x * nx + a.y * ny + a.z * nz;
        const db = b.x * nx + b.y * ny + b.z * nz;
        const aIn = da <= 0, bIn = db <= 0;
        if (aIn) out.push(a);
        if (aIn !== bIn) {
          const t = da / (da - db);
          const m = vec(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t, a.z + (b.z - a.z) * t);
          if (a.u !== undefined) {
            m.u = a.u + (b.u - a.u) * t;
            m.v = a.v + (b.v - a.v) * t;
          }
          out.push(m);
        }
      }
      return out;
    }

    // Clip to the view frustum's side planes (15% margin). Without this, a wall/floor
    // grazing the camera projects to triangles tens of thousands of px across — the
    // subdivision depth cap leaves them visibly warped, and clipping+drawing megapixel
    // textured triangles dozens of times per frame can hang or crash the tab.
    function clipPolyFrustum(pts, w, h) {
      const f = Math.min(w, h) * .82; // must match project()
      const kx = (w / 2) / f * 1.15, ky = (h / 2) / f * 1.15;
      let poly = clipPolyHalfspace(pts, 1, 0, -kx);
      if (poly.length > 2) poly = clipPolyHalfspace(poly, -1, 0, -kx);
      if (poly.length > 2) poly = clipPolyHalfspace(poly, 0, 1, -ky);
      if (poly.length > 2) poly = clipPolyHalfspace(poly, 0, -1, -ky);
      return poly;
    }

    function hangarProjectPoly(points, view, w, h) {
      let clipped = clipPolyNear(points.map((p) => cameraTransform(p, view)));
      if (clipped.length > 2) clipped = clipPolyFrustum(clipped, w, h);
      if (clipped.length < 3) return null;
      const pr = clipped.map((p) => project(p, w, h));
      return pr.some((p) => !p) ? null : pr;
    }

    // A line segment gets the same treatment: clip to the near plane instead of vanishing
    // whole whenever one endpoint dips behind the camera.
    function hangarLine(a3, b3, view, w, h) {
      let a = cameraTransform(a3, view), b = cameraTransform(b3, view);
      if (a.z <= HANGAR_NEAR && b.z <= HANGAR_NEAR) return null;
      if (a.z <= HANGAR_NEAR || b.z <= HANGAR_NEAR) {
        const t = (HANGAR_NEAR - a.z) / (b.z - a.z);
        const m = vec(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t, HANGAR_NEAR);
        if (a.z <= HANGAR_NEAR) a = m; else b = m;
      }
      const pa = project(a, w, h), pb = project(b, w, h);
      return pa && pb ? [pa, pb] : null;
    }

    function hangarTexturedQuad(points, view, w, h, texture, alpha = .58, shade = "rgba(0,0,0,.18)") {
      // Planar UVs from the quad's own edges (u along 0->1, v along 0->3), attached to
      // the camera-space verts so clipPolyNear can interpolate them at the near plane.
      const e1 = sub(points[1], points[0]), e2 = sub(points[3], points[0]);
      const uExt = len(e1) || 1, vExt = len(e2) || 1;
      const uAxis = scale(e1, 1 / uExt), vAxis = scale(e2, 1 / vExt);
      const camPts = points.map((pt) => {
        const c = cameraTransform(pt, view);
        const rel = sub(pt, points[0]);
        c.u = dot(rel, uAxis);
        c.v = dot(rel, vAxis);
        return c;
      });
      let clipped = clipPolyNear(camPts);
      if (clipped.length > 2) clipped = clipPolyFrustum(clipped, w, h);
      if (clipped.length < 3) return null;
      const pr = clipped.map((p) => project(p, w, h));
      if (pr.some((p) => !p)) return null;
      ctx.save();
      ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(54,64,57,${alpha})`;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(pr[0].x, pr[0].y);
      for (let i = 1; i < pr.length; i++) ctx.lineTo(pr[i].x, pr[i].y);
      ctx.closePath();
      ctx.fill();
      if (texture && game.fxLevel !== "classic") {
        // Real texture mapping over the flat fill, perspective-correct via the same
        // camera-space subdivision the station hull uses (coarser 130px threshold: the
        // walls are huge on screen and brushed metal hides residual affine error).
        const su = (texture.width - 2) / uExt, sv = (texture.height - 2) / vExt;
        drawUVLayerPersp(ctx, {
          camVerts: clipped,
          uv: clipped.map((c) => [c.u * su - texture.width / 2 + 1, c.v * sv - texture.height / 2 + 1]),
          project: (p) => project(p, w, h)
        }, texture, clamp(alpha + .04, .4, .72), undefined, true, 160, 4);
      }
      ctx.fillStyle = shade;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(pr[0].x, pr[0].y);
      for (let i = 1; i < pr.length; i++) ctx.lineTo(pr[i].x, pr[i].y);
      ctx.closePath();
      ctx.fill();
      ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(150,170,145,.2)";
      ctx.lineWidth = Math.max(.7, w / 1800);
      ctx.stroke();

      // Projection-stable panel seams: true 3D lines across the quad (lerped in world
      // space, clipped like everything else), so they neither crawl over the walls as
      // the camera orbits nor vanish when the quad is partially behind the camera.
      ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(185,205,175,.09)";
      ctx.lineWidth = Math.max(.5, w / 2600);
      const l3 = (a, b, t) => vec(lerp(a.x, b.x, t), lerp(a.y, b.y, t), lerp(a.z, b.z, t));
      for (let i = 1; i < 5; i++) {
        const t = i / 5;
        const seg = hangarLine(l3(points[0], points[1], t), l3(points[3], points[2], t), view, w, h);
        if (!seg) continue;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(seg[0].x, seg[0].y);
        ctx.lineTo(seg[1].x, seg[1].y);
        ctx.stroke();
      }
      for (let i = 1; i < 4; i++) {
        const t = i / 4;
        const seg = hangarLine(l3(points[0], points[3], t), l3(points[1], points[2], t), view, w, h);
        if (!seg) continue;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(seg[0].x, seg[0].y);
        ctx.lineTo(seg[1].x, seg[1].y);
        ctx.stroke();
      }
      ctx.restore();
      return pr;
    }

    function hangarPoly(points, view, w, h, fill, stroke = null) {
      const pr = hangarProjectPoly(points, view, w, h);
      if (!pr) return null;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(pr[0].x, pr[0].y);
      for (let i = 1; i < pr.length; i++) ctx.lineTo(pr[i].x, pr[i].y);
      ctx.closePath();
      if (fill) { ctx.fillStyle = fill; ctx.fill(); }
      if (stroke) { ctx.strokeStyle = stroke; ctx.stroke(); }
      return pr;
    }

    function drawHangarFloorEllipse(w, h, view, center, rx, rz, fill, segments = 34) {
      const pts = [];
      for (let i = 0; i < segments; i++) {
        const a = i / segments * TAU;
        pts.push(vec(center.x + Math.cos(a) * rx, center.y, center.z + Math.sin(a) * rz));
      }
      const pr = hangarProjectPoly(pts, view, w, h);
      if (!pr) return null;
      const bounds = polygonBounds(pr);
      if (![bounds.minX, bounds.maxX, bounds.minY, bounds.maxY].every(Number.isFinite)) return null;
      ctx.save();
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(pr[0].x, pr[0].y);
      for (let i = 1; i < pr.length; i++) ctx.lineTo(pr[i].x, pr[i].y);
      ctx.closePath();
      ctx.clip();
      const cx = (bounds.minX + bounds.maxX) / 2;
      const cy = (bounds.minY + bounds.maxY) / 2;
      const r = Math.max(bounds.maxX - bounds.minX, bounds.maxY - bounds.minY) * .62;
      const grad = ctx.createRadialGradient(cx, cy, 0, cx, cy, Math.max(1, r));
      for (const stop of fill) grad.addColorStop(stop[0], stop[1]);
      ctx.fillStyle = grad;
      ctx.fillRect(bounds.minX, bounds.minY, bounds.maxX - bounds.minX, bounds.maxY - bounds.minY);
      ctx.restore();
      return pr;
    }

    function drawHangarLightGlow(w, h, view, pos, radius, alpha = .35, warm = true) {
      const pr = hangarProject(pos, view, w, h);
      if (!pr) return;
      const r = clamp((pr.s || 1) * radius, 18, Math.max(w, h) * .34);
      ctx.save();
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
      const glow = ctx.createRadialGradient(pr.x, pr.y, 0, pr.x, pr.y, r);
      const core = warm ? "255,236,184" : "175,220,255";
      const edge = warm ? "255,170,82" : "80,150,255";
      glow.addColorStop(0, `rgba(${core},${alpha})`);
      glow.addColorStop(.22, `rgba(${core},${alpha * .34})`);
      glow.addColorStop(1, `rgba(${edge},0)`);
      ctx.fillStyle = glow;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, r, 0, TAU);
      ctx.fill();
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawHangarLightPools(w, h, view, floor, ceil) {
      if (!ultraFxEnabled()) return;
      ctx.save();
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
      const lightXs = [-250, 0, 250];
      const lightZs = [285, 505, 725];
      for (const z of lightZs) {
        for (const x of lightXs) {
          drawHangarLightGlow(w, h, view, vec(x, ceil - 8, z), 86, .32, true);
          drawHangarFloorEllipse(w, h, view, vec(x, floor + 1.5, z + 12), 112, 82, [
            [0, "rgba(255,232,176,.18)"],
            [.42, "rgba(255,205,118,.07)"],
            [1, "rgba(255,180,80,0)"]
          ], 30);
        }
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawHangarShipShadow(w, h, view, modelName, pos, scaleFactor, alpha = 1) {
      if (!ultraFxEnabled()) return;
      const floor = -175;
      const height = Math.max(0, pos.y - floor);
      const fade = clamp(1 - height / 260, 0, 1);
      if (fade <= .02) return;
      const r = Math.max(52, modelBoundingRadius(MODELS[modelName] || MODELS.cobra) * scaleFactor);
      drawHangarFloorEllipse(w, h, view, vec(pos.x, floor + 2, pos.z), r * .82, r * 1.18, [
        [0, `rgba(0,0,0,${.36 * fade * alpha})`],
        [.48, `rgba(0,0,0,${.16 * fade * alpha})`],
        [1, "rgba(0,0,0,0)"]
      ], 38);
    }

    function hangarShipScale(modelName, base = 1) {
      const r = Math.max(48, modelBoundingRadius(MODELS[modelName] || MODELS.cobra) || 95);
      // Fit all commander ships in the hangar while preserving enough size difference
      // that freighters still feel heavier than fighters.
      return base * clamp(1.08 * Math.pow(95 / r, .55), .42, 1.36);
    }

    function hangarSceneShip(scene, opts = {}) {
      const modelName = scene?.shipModel || playerShipModel();
      return {
        type: "ship",
        model: modelName,
        pos: opts.pos || vec(0, -105, 430),
        scaleFactor: opts.scaleFactor || 1.16,
        rot: opts.yaw ?? opts.rot ?? .68,
        pitch: opts.pitch ?? .28,
        roll: opts.roll ?? -.08,
        speed: Math.max(0, opts.speed ?? (opts.trail || 0) * 105),
        engineBoost: opts.engineBoost ?? Math.max(0, (opts.engineGlow ?? 1) - .65),
        engineGlow: opts.engineGlow ?? 1,
        playerDamageMarks: (opts.damageMarks || []).map((m) => ({ ...m, radius: m.radius || 12 }))
      };
    }

    function drawHangarModel(modelName, pos, view, w, h, opts = {}) {
      const model = MODELS[modelName];
      if (!model) return;
      const scale = opts.scale ?? 1;
      drawModelEntity(ctx, { camera: view, w, h, mode: game.graphicsMode }, {
        type: "prop",
        model: modelName,
        pos,
        scaleFactor: scale,
        rot: opts.yaw ?? 0,
        pitch: opts.pitch ?? 0,
        roll: opts.roll ?? 0,
        color: opts.color || "#b6c5aa",
        alpha: opts.alpha ?? 1,
        engineGlow: 0
      }, {
        edgeWidth: Math.max(.6, scale * .55)
      });
    }

    function drawHangarCargoStacks(w, h, scene, view, floor) {
      const rng = mulberry((scene?.seed || 1) ^ 0xc0a9e);
      const colors = [
        "#839277",
        "#8f8a68",
        "#6e8b91",
        "#9a873d"
      ];
      for (const side of [-1, 1]) {
        for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
          const stack = 1 + (rng() > .48 ? 1 : 0) + (rng() > .86 ? 1 : 0);
          const x = side * (330 + rng() * 72);
          const z = 245 + i * 108 + rng() * 34;
          for (let j = 0; j < stack; j++) {
            drawHangarModel("canister", vec(x + side * rng() * 16, floor + 19 + j * 33, z + rng() * 14), view, w, h, {
              scale: 1.08 + rng() * .18,
              yaw: side * Math.PI / 2 + (rng() - .5) * .18,
              pitch: (rng() - .5) * .06,
              roll: (rng() - .5) * .08,
              color: colors[(i + j + (side > 0 ? 1 : 0)) % colors.length],
              alpha: .96
            });
          }
        }
      }
    }

    function drawHangarOutsideThroughGate(view, w, h, gatePr, seed) {
      if (!gatePr) return;
      const bounds = polygonBounds(gatePr);
      if (![bounds.minX, bounds.maxX, bounds.minY, bounds.maxY].every(Number.isFinite)) return;
      const rng = mulberry(seed || 1);
      ctx.save();
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(gatePr[0].x, gatePr[0].y);
      gatePr.slice(1).forEach((p) => ctx.lineTo(p.x, p.y));
      ctx.closePath();
      ctx.clip();
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(0,0,6,.9)";
      ctx.fillRect(bounds.minX, bounds.minY, bounds.maxX - bounds.minX, bounds.maxY - bounds.minY);
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(220,245,255,.62)";
      for (let i = 0; i < 36; i++) {
        const x = lerp(bounds.minX, bounds.maxX, rng());
        const y = lerp(bounds.minY, bounds.maxY, rng());
        const s = .5 + rng() * 1.2;
        ctx.fillRect(x, y, s, s);
      }
      ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(101,255,71,.38)";
      ctx.lineWidth = 1;
      for (let i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
        const x = lerp(bounds.minX, bounds.maxX, .32 + i * .26);
        const y = lerp(bounds.minY, bounds.maxY, .36 + rng() * .3);
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(x - 7, y);
        ctx.lineTo(x + 7, y + 2);
        ctx.lineTo(x + 1, y - 5);
        ctx.closePath();
        ctx.stroke();
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    const HANGAR_FAR_Z = 900;
    const HANGAR_GATE_Z = HANGAR_FAR_Z - 5;
    const HANGAR_GATE_W = 270;
    const HANGAR_GATE_H = 150;
    const HANGAR_FLIGHT_Y = -24;

    function hangarGatePoints() {
      return [
        vec(-HANGAR_GATE_W, -HANGAR_GATE_H, HANGAR_GATE_Z),
        vec(HANGAR_GATE_W, -HANGAR_GATE_H, HANGAR_GATE_Z),
        vec(HANGAR_GATE_W, HANGAR_GATE_H, HANGAR_GATE_Z),
        vec(-HANGAR_GATE_W, HANGAR_GATE_H, HANGAR_GATE_Z)
      ];
    }

    function hangarGateProjection(view, w, h) {
      return hangarProjectPoly(hangarGatePoints(), view, w, h);
    }

    function withHangarGateClip(view, w, h, drawFn) {
      const gatePr = hangarGateProjection(view, w, h);
      if (!gatePr || gatePr.length < 3) return drawFn();
      ctx.save();
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(gatePr[0].x, gatePr[0].y);
      gatePr.slice(1).forEach((pt) => ctx.lineTo(pt.x, pt.y));
      ctx.closePath();
      ctx.clip();
      drawFn();
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawHangarForcefieldSheet(w, h, scene, view, intensity = 1) {
      const gatePr = hangarGateProjection(view, w, h);
      if (!gatePr || gatePr.length < 4 || intensity <= .01) return;
      const bounds = polygonBounds(gatePr);
      if (![bounds.minX, bounds.maxX, bounds.minY, bounds.maxY].every(Number.isFinite)) return;
      const pulse = .55 + Math.sin(performance.now() / 220 + (scene?.seed || 1)) * .16;
      ctx.save();
      const grad = ctx.createLinearGradient(bounds.minX, bounds.minY, bounds.maxX, bounds.maxY);
      grad.addColorStop(0, `rgba(112,205,255,${(.22 + pulse * .1) * intensity})`);
      grad.addColorStop(.5, `rgba(45,124,255,${(.2 + pulse * .11) * intensity})`);
      grad.addColorStop(1, `rgba(6,22,72,${(.2 + pulse * .08) * intensity})`);
      ctx.fillStyle = grad;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(gatePr[0].x, gatePr[0].y);
      gatePr.slice(1).forEach((pt) => ctx.lineTo(pt.x, pt.y));
      ctx.closePath();
      ctx.fill();
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
      ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(148,214,255,${(.24 + pulse * .34) * intensity})`;
      ctx.lineWidth = Math.max(1.2, w / 850) * (1 + intensity * .55);
      for (let i = 1; i < 5; i++) {
        const t = i / 5;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(lerp(gatePr[0].x, gatePr[3].x, t), lerp(gatePr[0].y, gatePr[3].y, t));
        ctx.lineTo(lerp(gatePr[1].x, gatePr[2].x, t), lerp(gatePr[1].y, gatePr[2].y, t));
        ctx.stroke();
      }
      ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(210,240,255,${.32 * intensity})`;
      ctx.lineWidth = Math.max(1, w / 1200);
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(gatePr[0].x, gatePr[0].y);
      gatePr.slice(1).forEach((pt) => ctx.lineTo(pt.x, pt.y));
      ctx.closePath();
      ctx.stroke();
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function hangarGateCrossingIntensity(z) {
      return Math.pow(clamp(1 - Math.abs(z - HANGAR_GATE_Z) / 170, 0, 1), .65);
    }

    function drawHangarRoom(w, h, scene, view) {
      const texture = getStationTexture(stationStyleForSystem(currentSystem()));
      const p = (x, y, z) => vec(x, y, z);
      const near = 120, far = 900, hw = 460, floor = -175, ceil = 210;
      ctx.save();
      const bg = ctx.createRadialGradient(w / 2, h / 2, 0, w / 2, h / 2, Math.max(w, h) * .72);
      bg.addColorStop(0, "#090c0a");
      bg.addColorStop(1, "#010201");
      ctx.fillStyle = bg;
      ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);

      // Back wall closing the near end of the room, so looking sideways/backwards during
      // the launch sweep shows hull panelling instead of black void. Skipped when the
      // camera sits outside the near end (the dock arrival's stage-style establishing
      // shot films through that opening).
      if (view.pos.z > near + 2) {
        hangarTexturedQuad([p(hw, floor, near), p(-hw, floor, near), p(-hw, ceil, near), p(hw, ceil, near)], view, w, h, texture, .58, "rgba(0,0,0,.22)");
      }
      hangarTexturedQuad([p(-hw, floor, far), p(hw, floor, far), p(hw, floor, near), p(-hw, floor, near)], view, w, h, texture, .66, "rgba(0,0,0,.04)");
      hangarTexturedQuad([p(-hw, ceil, near), p(hw, ceil, near), p(hw, ceil, far), p(-hw, ceil, far)], view, w, h, texture, .52, "rgba(0,0,0,.3)");
      hangarTexturedQuad([p(-hw, floor, near), p(-hw, floor, far), p(-hw, ceil, far), p(-hw, ceil, near)], view, w, h, texture, .56, "rgba(0,0,0,.28)");
      hangarTexturedQuad([p(hw, floor, far), p(hw, floor, near), p(hw, ceil, near), p(hw, ceil, far)], view, w, h, texture, .56, "rgba(0,0,0,.24)");
      hangarTexturedQuad([p(-hw, floor, far), p(-hw, ceil, far), p(hw, ceil, far), p(hw, floor, far)], view, w, h, texture, .52, "rgba(0,0,0,.36)");

      ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(200,220,190,.18)";
      ctx.lineWidth = Math.max(.7, w / 1800);
      for (let i = 0; i <= 8; i++) {
        const z = lerp(near, far, i / 8);
        const fl = hangarLine(p(-hw, floor, z), p(hw, floor, z), view, w, h);
        const cl = hangarLine(p(-hw, ceil, z), p(hw, ceil, z), view, w, h);
        ctx.beginPath();
        if (fl) { ctx.moveTo(fl[0].x, fl[0].y); ctx.lineTo(fl[1].x, fl[1].y); }
        if (cl) { ctx.moveTo(cl[0].x, cl[0].y); ctx.lineTo(cl[1].x, cl[1].y); }
        if (fl || cl) ctx.stroke();
      }
      for (let i = -3; i <= 3; i++) {
        const x = i * hw / 4;
        const seg = hangarLine(p(x, floor, near), p(x, floor, far), view, w, h);
        if (!seg) continue;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(seg[0].x, seg[0].y); ctx.lineTo(seg[1].x, seg[1].y);
        ctx.stroke();
      }
      drawHangarLightPools(w, h, view, floor, ceil);
      drawHangarCargoStacks(w, h, scene, view, floor);

      const gateW = HANGAR_GATE_W, gateH = HANGAR_GATE_H;
      const gate = hangarGatePoints();
      const gatePr = hangarPoly(gate, view, w, h, "rgba(0,0,0,.92)", "rgba(120,185,255,.36)");
      drawHangarOutsideThroughGate(view, w, h, gatePr, (scene?.seed || 1) ^ 0xa5a5);
      const pulse = .44 + Math.sin(performance.now() / 260) * .18;
      if (gatePr) {
        const bounds = polygonBounds(gatePr);
        if (![bounds.minX, bounds.maxX, bounds.minY, bounds.maxY].every(Number.isFinite)) {
          ctx.restore();
          return;
        }
        const grad = ctx.createLinearGradient(bounds.minX, bounds.minY, bounds.maxX, bounds.maxY);
        grad.addColorStop(0, `rgba(86,184,255,${.22 + pulse * .12})`);
        grad.addColorStop(.5, `rgba(42,126,255,${.18 + pulse * .16})`);
        grad.addColorStop(1, `rgba(8,36,100,${.18 + pulse * .08})`);
        ctx.fillStyle = grad;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(gatePr[0].x, gatePr[0].y);
        gatePr.slice(1).forEach((pt) => ctx.lineTo(pt.x, pt.y));
        ctx.closePath();
        ctx.fill();
        ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
        ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(120,196,255,${.3 + pulse * .32})`;
        ctx.lineWidth = Math.max(1.2, w / 900);
        for (let i = 1; i < 5 && gatePr.length >= 4; i++) {
          const t = i / 5;
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.moveTo(lerp(gatePr[0].x, gatePr[3].x, t), lerp(gatePr[0].y, gatePr[3].y, t));
          ctx.lineTo(lerp(gatePr[1].x, gatePr[2].x, t), lerp(gatePr[1].y, gatePr[2].y, t));
          ctx.stroke();
        }
        ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "source-over";
      }

      for (let i = -2; i <= 2; i++) {
        const strip = [p(i * 125 - 24, ceil - 4, 260), p(i * 125 + 24, ceil - 4, 260), p(i * 125 + 24, ceil - 4, 730), p(i * 125 - 24, ceil - 4, 730)];
        hangarPoly(strip, view, w, h, "rgba(255,244,204,.68)");
      }
      for (const b of [p(-gateW - 34, gateH + 28, far - 8), p(gateW + 34, gateH + 28, far - 8), p(-gateW - 34, -gateH - 28, far - 8), p(gateW + 34, -gateH - 28, far - 8)]) {
        const pr = hangarProject(b, view, w, h);
        if (!pr) continue;
        const blink = .4 + Math.max(0, Math.sin(performance.now() / 1000 * TAU + b.x * .01)) * .6;
        ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
        const r = Math.max(2, pr.s * 9);
        const beacon = ctx.createRadialGradient(pr.x, pr.y, 0, pr.x, pr.y, r * 5);
        beacon.addColorStop(0, `rgba(255,222,120,${.72 * blink})`);
        beacon.addColorStop(1, "rgba(255,120,20,0)");
        ctx.fillStyle = beacon;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, r * 5, 0, TAU);
        ctx.fill();
        ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "source-over";
      }

      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawHangarShip(w, h, scene, view, opts = {}) {
      const modelName = scene?.shipModel || playerShipModel();
      const model = MODELS[modelName];
      if (!model) return;
      const shipObj = hangarSceneShip(scene, opts);
      drawHangarShipShadow(w, h, view, modelName, shipObj.pos, shipObj.scaleFactor, opts.alpha ?? 1);
      drawModelEntity(ctx, { camera: view, w, h, mode: game.graphicsMode }, shipObj, {
        alpha: opts.alpha ?? 1,
        decal: getPreviewShipDecal(modelName),
        edgeWidth: Math.max(.8, shipObj.scaleFactor * 1.15)
      });
    }

    function updateHangarShipEffects(scene, shipObj, trailMul = 1, opts = {}) {
      if (!ultraFxEnabled()) return [];
      const drawTrails = opts.drawTrails !== false;
      const puffStore = scene._hangarEnginePuffs || (scene._hangarEnginePuffs = []);
      const now = performance.now() / 1000;
      const lastNow = scene._hangarEnginePuffClock || now;
      const dt = clamp(now - lastNow, 0, .08);
      scene._hangarEnginePuffClock = now;
      updatePuffStore(puffStore, dt, 180);
      if (drawTrails && trailMul > .03) {
        scene._hangarEngineSpawnClock = (scene._hangarEngineSpawnClock || 0) - dt;
        if (scene._hangarEngineSpawnClock <= 0) {
          scene._hangarEngineSpawnClock = .035 + Math.random() * .025;
          emitEnginePlasmaForShip(puffStore, shipObj, clamp(trailMul * 1.25, .55, 2.2), { limit: 180 });
        }
      }
      return drawTrails ? puffStore : [];
    }

    function drawHangarShipWithWorldEffects(w, h, scene, view, opts = {}) {
      const shipObj = hangarSceneShip(scene, opts);
      const puffs = updateHangarShipEffects(scene, shipObj, opts.trail ?? 1, opts);
      const items = [{ kind: "ship", d: len(sub(shipObj.pos, view.pos)) }];
      addWorldEffectItems(items, puffs, view);
      drawWorldItems(items, w, h, view, () => drawHangarShip(w, h, scene, view, opts));
    }

    function drawHangarSparkles(w, h, seed, strength = 1) {
      const rng = mulberry(seed || 1);
      ctx.save();
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
      for (let i = 0; i < 38; i++) {
        const x = w * (.32 + rng() * .38);
        const y = h * (.34 + rng() * .36);
        const tw = .5 + .5 * Math.sin(performance.now() / (170 + rng() * 160) + rng() * TAU);
        const a = strength * tw * (.18 + rng() * .42);
        const r = 2 + rng() * 9;
        ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(230,255,220,${a})`;
        ctx.lineWidth = .8 + rng() * .7;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(x - r, y);
        ctx.lineTo(x + r, y);
        ctx.moveTo(x, y - r);
        ctx.lineTo(x, y + r);
        ctx.stroke();
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawHangarCaption(w, h, scene, alpha = 1, repaired = false) {
      const station = scene?.stationName || game.dockedAt || `${currentSystem().name} STATION`;
      ctx.save();
      ctx.textAlign = "center";
      ctx.shadowColor = "rgba(101,255,71,.35)";
      ctx.shadowBlur = 8;
      ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(101,255,71,${alpha * .88})`;
      ctx.font = `${Math.max(14, w * .014)}px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
      ctx.fillText(`WELCOME TO ${station.toUpperCase()}`, w / 2, h * .2);
      ctx.shadowBlur = 0;
      ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(145,167,141,${alpha * .8})`;
      ctx.font = `${Math.max(9, w * .0085)}px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
      const line = repaired && scene?.hullRepaired
        ? (scene.repairLine || "Hull repair complete.")
        : "Docking clamps secured. Station services online.";
      ctx.fillText(line.toUpperCase(), w / 2, h * .235);
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function hangarShipParkPos() {
      return vec(0, -116, 430);
    }

    function drawLaunchHangarSequence(w, h, tr) {
      const scene = tr.scene || game.dockScene || {};
      const p = clamp(tr.t / tr.dur, 0, 1);
      const t = tr.t;
      const modelName = scene?.shipModel || playerShipModel();
      const spool = smoothstep(2, 3, t);
      const lift = smootherstep(0, 1, smootherstep(2.45, 4.85, t));
      const exitRun = Math.max(0, t - 4.85);
      const exitTravel = exitRun > 0 ? Math.pow(exitRun / 1.55, 2.45) : 0;
      const exit = clamp(exitTravel, 0, 1);
      const climbOut = smootherstep(6.08, 7.48, t);
      const climbArc = Math.pow(climbOut, 1.55);
      const shipBase = hangarShipParkPos();
      const shipPos = vec(
        -Math.pow(climbOut, 1.28) * 420,
        lerp(shipBase.y, HANGAR_FLIGHT_Y, lift) + climbArc * 420,
        shipBase.z + exitTravel * 1550
      );
      const cameraPos = vec(-235 + Math.sin(p * TAU * .5) * 14, -132, 170 + exit * 92);
      const target = vec(shipPos.x * .04, lerp(-104, HANGAR_FLIGHT_Y + 6, lift) + climbArc * 22, lerp(450, 1160, exit));
      const view = makeHangarCamera(cameraPos, target);
      drawHangarRoom(w, h, scene, view);
      const shipOpts = {
        pos: shipPos,
        scaleFactor: hangarShipScale(modelName, lerp(1.16, .36, smoothstep(.55, 3.7, exitTravel))),
        yaw: -climbOut * .24,
        pitch: lerp(.04, -.08, exit) + climbOut * .68,
        roll: Math.sin(p * TAU) * .012 * (1 - exit) + climbOut * .78,
        engineGlow: clamp(spool + smoothstep(4.85, 5.45, t) * 1.05, 0, 1.85),
        damageMarks: []
      };
      const drawShipPass = () => {
        const exitTrail = spool * smoothstep(4.95, 5.45, t) * (1 + exit * 2.25);
        drawHangarShipWithWorldEffects(w, h, scene, view, { ...shipOpts, trail: exitTrail });
      };
      const forcefieldInFront = shipPos.z > HANGAR_GATE_Z - 12;
      if (!forcefieldInFront) drawHangarForcefieldSheet(w, h, scene, view, hangarGateCrossingIntensity(shipPos.z));
      if (forcefieldInFront) withHangarGateClip(view, w, h, drawShipPass);
      else drawShipPass();
      if (forcefieldInFront) drawHangarForcefieldSheet(w, h, scene, view, hangarGateCrossingIntensity(shipPos.z));

      drawLaunchSequenceHud(w, h, tr);
      const fadeInBlack = 1 - smoothstep(0, 1, t);
      const fadeOut = smoothstep(7.2, 8.2, t);
      ctx.save();
      if (fadeInBlack > .01) {
        ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(0,0,0,${fadeInBlack})`;
        ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);
      }
      if (fadeOut > .01) {
        ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(0,0,0,${fadeOut})`;
        ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawDockHangarSequence(w, h, tr) {
      const scene = tr.scene || game.dockScene || {};
      const p = clamp(tr.t / tr.dur, 0, 1);
      const t = tr.t;
      const modelName = scene?.shipModel || playerShipModel();
      const dockFade = smoothstep(9.2, 10.2, t);
      if (dockFade > 0) {
        drawDockedBackdrop(w, h);
        ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(0,0,0,${1 - dockFade})`;
        ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);
        return;
      }
      const cutAt = 7.35;
      const cut = t >= cutAt;
      const gateAt = 2.65;
      const stopAt = 3.55;
      const rotateAt = 3.75;
      const approach = Math.pow(clamp(t / gateAt, 0, 1), 1.65);
      const insideEntry = 1 - Math.pow(1 - clamp((t - gateAt) / (stopAt - gateAt), 0, 1), 3);
      const landAt = 7.35;
      const parkSettle = smootherstep(0, 1, smootherstep(rotateAt, landAt, t));
      const fadeIn = smoothstep(0, 1, t);
      const fadeOut = smoothstep(8.2, 9.2, t);
      const repaired = t > 7.2;
      const settle = cut ? 1 : parkSettle;
      const descent = cut ? 1 : parkSettle;
      const bounce = 0;
      const engineGlow = cut ? 0 : clamp((1 - smoothstep(6.05, 7.2, t)) + (1 - smoothstep(2.65, 3.55, t)) * .85, 0, 1.75);
      const approachCam = vec(235 - Math.sin(p * TAU * .5) * 14, -132, 170);
      const view = makeHangarCamera(approachCam, vec(0, -108, 492));
      drawHangarRoom(w, h, scene, view);
      const parked = hangarShipParkPos();
      const gateInsideZ = HANGAR_GATE_Z - 20;
      const stagingZ = 640;
      const shipZ = cut
        ? parked.z
        : t < gateAt
          ? lerp(4200, gateInsideZ, approach)
          : t < rotateAt
            ? lerp(gateInsideZ, stagingZ, insideEntry)
            : lerp(stagingZ, parked.z, parkSettle);
      const shipOpts = {
        pos: vec(0, lerp(HANGAR_FLIGHT_Y, parked.y, descent) + bounce, shipZ),
        scaleFactor: hangarShipScale(modelName, t < gateAt ? lerp(.24, .86, approach) : lerp(.86, 1.12, Math.max(insideEntry, parkSettle))),
        yaw: lerp(Math.PI + .24, 0, settle),
        pitch: lerp(.16, .04, settle),
        roll: (1 - settle) * -.12,
        alpha: clamp(fadeIn, .08, 1),
        engineGlow,
        damageMarks: []
      };
      const drawShipPass = () => {
        const entryTrail = engineGlow * (1 - smoothstep(3.35, 6.4, t)) * .95;
        drawHangarShipWithWorldEffects(w, h, scene, view, { ...shipOpts, trail: entryTrail });
      };
      const forcefieldInFront = shipZ > HANGAR_GATE_Z - 12;
      if (!forcefieldInFront) drawHangarForcefieldSheet(w, h, scene, view, hangarGateCrossingIntensity(shipZ));
      if (forcefieldInFront) withHangarGateClip(view, w, h, drawShipPass);
      else drawShipPass();
      if (forcefieldInFront) drawHangarForcefieldSheet(w, h, scene, view, hangarGateCrossingIntensity(shipZ));
      if (t > 7.05) drawHangarSparkles(w, h, (scene.seed || 1) ^ 0x9e3779b9, smoothstep(7.05, 8.2, t));
      drawDockingSequenceHud(w, h, tr);
      const black = Math.max(1 - fadeIn, fadeOut);
      if (black > .01) {
        ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(0,0,0,${black})`;
        ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);
      }
    }

    function drawWarpStars(w, h, color, progress, lengthMul = 1) {
      const cx = w / 2, cy = h / 2;
      ctx.save();
      ctx.lineCap = "round";
      for (const star of game.stars) {
        const rel = cameraTransform(star, game.camera);
        const pr = project(rel, w, h);
        if (!pr) continue;
        const dx = pr.x - cx, dy = pr.y - cy;
        const dist = Math.hypot(dx, dy) || 1;
        const dirX = dx / dist, dirY = dy / dist;
        const streak = progress * progress * 260 * lengthMul;
        ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(${color},${clamp(.18 + progress * .58, 0, .88)})`;
        ctx.lineWidth = .7 + progress * 1.5;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(pr.x - dirX * streak * .18, pr.y - dirY * streak * .18);
        ctx.lineTo(pr.x + dirX * streak, pr.y + dirY * streak);
        ctx.stroke();
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawUltraWarpField(w, h, p, palette, opts = {}) {
      const cx = w / 2, cy = h / 2;
      const rng = mulberry(opts.seed || 0x51a7);
      const spin = (opts.spin || 0) + p * TAU * (opts.spinRate || 1.4);
      const depthSpeed = opts.depthSpeed || 2.4;
      const flare = easeInOut(clamp((p - .08) / .82, 0, 1));
      const maxR = Math.hypot(w, h) * (opts.radius || .78);
      const laneCount = opts.lanes || 150;
      ctx.save();
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
      ctx.lineCap = "round";
      for (let i = 0; i < laneCount; i++) {
        const base = rng();
        const a0 = rng() * TAU;
        const phase = (base + p * depthSpeed) % 1;
        const curve = Math.pow(phase, .62);
        const twist = spin * (1.15 - phase * .46) + Math.sin(phase * TAU * 2 + i) * (opts.wobble || .18);
        const a = a0 + twist;
        const r = lerp(6, maxR, curve);
        const tail = (38 + flare * 420 * (opts.streak || 1)) * (1 - phase * .28);
        const hue = palette[i % palette.length];
        const alpha = clamp((.12 + flare * .62) * (1 - phase * .42), .04, .86);
        const x = cx + Math.cos(a) * r;
        const y = cy + Math.sin(a) * r * (opts.flatten || .72);
        const tx = Math.cos(a + spin * .08) * tail;
        const ty = Math.sin(a + spin * .08) * tail * (opts.flatten || .72);
        const grad = ctx.createLinearGradient(x - tx, y - ty, x + tx * .16, y + ty * .16);
        grad.addColorStop(0, `hsla(${hue},100%,72%,0)`);
        grad.addColorStop(.34, `hsla(${hue},100%,68%,${alpha * .34})`);
        grad.addColorStop(1, `hsla(${hue},100%,86%,${alpha})`);
        ctx.strokeStyle = grad;
        ctx.lineWidth = (opts.line || 1.1) + phase * (opts.lineGrow || 2.6);
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(x - tx, y - ty);
        ctx.lineTo(x + tx * .16, y + ty * .16);
        ctx.stroke();
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawUltraLightRibbons(w, h, p, palette, opts = {}) {
      const cx = w / 2, cy = h / 2;
      const maxR = Math.hypot(w, h) * (opts.radius || .82);
      const twist = p * TAU * (opts.twist || 1.8) + (opts.offset || 0);
      const ribbons = opts.count || 5;
      ctx.save();
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
      ctx.lineCap = "round";
      for (let rIndex = 0; rIndex < ribbons; rIndex++) {
        const hue = palette[rIndex % palette.length];
        const offset = rIndex / ribbons * TAU;
        ctx.strokeStyle = `hsla(${hue},100%,72%,${opts.alpha || .34})`;
        ctx.lineWidth = (opts.width || 2.4) + Math.sin(p * TAU + rIndex) * .8;
        ctx.beginPath();
        for (let i = 0; i <= 96; i++) {
          const t = i / 96;
          const z = Math.pow(t, .78);
          const radius = lerp(8, maxR, z);
          const a = offset + twist * (1.25 - t * .7) + Math.sin(t * TAU * 4 + offset) * .38;
          const x = cx + Math.cos(a) * radius;
          const y = cy + Math.sin(a) * radius * (opts.flatten || .66);
          if (i === 0) ctx.moveTo(x, y);
          else ctx.lineTo(x, y);
        }
        ctx.stroke();
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawUltraAperture(w, h, p, palette, opts = {}) {
      const cx = w / 2, cy = h / 2;
      const pulse = .5 + .5 * Math.sin(p * TAU * (opts.pulses || 3));
      const open = easeInOut(clamp((p - .06) / .78, 0, 1));
      const collapse = easeInOut(clamp((p - .82) / .18, 0, 1));
      const r = Math.min(w, h) * (.05 + open * .18 + pulse * .018);
      ctx.save();
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
      const core = ctx.createRadialGradient(cx, cy, 0, cx, cy, r * (4.2 + open * 2.5));
      core.addColorStop(0, `rgba(255,255,255,${.1 + open * .42})`);
      core.addColorStop(.2, `hsla(${palette[0]},100%,80%,${.13 + open * .26})`);
      core.addColorStop(.58, `hsla(${palette[1] || palette[0]},100%,58%,${.05 + open * .14})`);
      core.addColorStop(1, "rgba(0,0,0,0)");
      ctx.fillStyle = core;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(cx, cy, r * (4.2 + open * 2.5), 0, TAU);
      ctx.fill();
      if (collapse > .01) {
        ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(255,255,255,${collapse * .42})`;
        ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function applyUltraWormholeShake(w, h, p, power = 1) {
      const dpr = window.devicePixelRatio || 1;
      const launchKick = Math.sin(clamp(p / .24, 0, 1) * Math.PI);
      const arrivalKick = Math.sin(clamp((p - .72) / .28, 0, 1) * Math.PI);
      const tunnelFlex = clamp((p - .2) / .52, 0, 1) * (1 - clamp((p - .72) / .28, 0, 1));
      const bend = Math.sin(p * TAU * 2.2) * tunnelFlex;
      const strength = (launchKick * 7 + arrivalKick * 10 + Math.abs(bend) * 3.5) * dpr * power;
      if (strength <= .05) return;
      ctx.translate(
        Math.sin(p * TAU * 17.3) * strength,
        Math.cos(p * TAU * 13.7) * strength * .68
      );
      ctx.rotate(Math.sin(p * TAU * 7.1) * strength * .0009);
    }

    function drawUltraStarAcceleration(w, h, p, palette, opts = {}) {
      const cx = w / 2, cy = h / 2;
      const rng = mulberry(opts.seed || 0x5eed);
      const maxR = Math.hypot(w, h) * .72;
      const power = easeInOut(p);
      const lanes = opts.lanes || 230;
      ctx.save();
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
      ctx.lineCap = "round";
      for (let i = 0; i < lanes; i++) {
        const a = rng() * TAU;
        const base = rng();
        const z = (base + p * (opts.speed || 2.8)) % 1;
        const r = Math.pow(z, 1.95) * maxR;
        const dx = Math.cos(a), dy = Math.sin(a) * .74;
        const x = cx + dx * r;
        const y = cy + dy * r;
        const tail = (20 + power * (opts.tail || 760)) * (.35 + z * .95);
        const hue = palette[Math.floor(rng() * palette.length)];
        const alpha = clamp((.08 + power * .74) * (1 - z * .22) * (opts.alpha || 1), 0, .92);
        const grad = ctx.createLinearGradient(x - dx * tail, y - dy * tail, x + dx * tail * .08, y + dy * tail * .08);
        grad.addColorStop(0, `hsla(${hue},100%,82%,0)`);
        grad.addColorStop(.72, `hsla(${hue},100%,78%,${alpha * .48})`);
        grad.addColorStop(1, `rgba(255,255,255,${alpha})`);
        ctx.strokeStyle = grad;
        ctx.lineWidth = (.7 + z * 2.2 + power * 1.2) * (opts.width || 1);
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(x - dx * tail, y - dy * tail);
        ctx.lineTo(x + dx * tail * .08, y + dy * tail * .08);
        ctx.stroke();
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawUltraCapturedStarStreaks(w, h, tr, p, palette, opts = {}) {
      const stars = tr.departureStars || [];
      if (!stars.length || p <= 0) return 0;
      const cx = w / 2, cy = h / 2;
      const power = easeInOut(p);
      const layerFade = 1 - smoothstep(.52, 1, p);
      if (layerFade <= .01) return 0;
      const travel = (opts.travel || 5200) * (.08 + power * power * 1.05);
      const tailBase = (opts.tail || 1450) * (.12 + power * .72);
      let drawn = 0;
      ctx.save();
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
      ctx.lineCap = "round";
      ctx.lineJoin = "round";
      for (let i = 0; i < stars.length; i++) {
        const s = stars[i];
        const start = project(vec(s.x, s.y, s.z), w, h);
        if (!start) continue;
        const dx0 = start.x - cx;
        const dy0 = start.y - cy;
        const radial = Math.hypot(dx0, dy0);
        if (radial < 3) continue;
        const stagger = s.depth * .2;
        const phase = clamp((p - stagger) / .62, 0, 1);
        if (phase <= 0 || phase >= 1) continue;
        const burst = Math.sin(phase * Math.PI);
        const ux = dx0 / radial;
        const uy = dy0 / radial;
        const depthMul = .58 + s.depth * .9;
        const headShift = travel * phase * phase * depthMul;
        const tailLen = tailBase * burst * (.38 + s.depth * .92);
        const head = {
          x: start.x + ux * headShift,
          y: start.y + uy * headShift * .82
        };
        const tail = {
          x: start.x + ux * Math.max(0, headShift - tailLen),
          y: start.y + uy * Math.max(0, headShift - tailLen) * .82
        };
        const loose = Math.max(180, tailBase * .35);
        if ((head.x < -loose || head.x > w + loose || head.y < -loose || head.y > h + loose)
          && (tail.x < -loose || tail.x > w + loose || tail.y < -loose || tail.y > h + loose)) continue;
        const dx = head.x - tail.x;
        const dy = head.y - tail.y;
        const len2d = Math.hypot(dx, dy);
        if (len2d < 2.5) continue;
        const bend = Math.sin((s.tw || 0) + p * TAU * 1.4) * len2d * .025 * burst;
        const midX = (head.x + tail.x) / 2;
        const midY = (head.y + tail.y) / 2;
        const nx = -dy / len2d;
        const ny = dx / len2d;
        const hue = s.sat ? s.hue : palette[i % palette.length];
        const screenFade = clamp(1 - radial / (Math.hypot(w, h) * .74), .18, 1);
        const alpha = clamp((.08 + power * .82) * burst * layerFade * screenFade * (opts.alpha || 1), .02, .86);
        const grad = ctx.createLinearGradient(tail.x, tail.y, head.x, head.y);
        grad.addColorStop(0, `hsla(${hue},100%,78%,0)`);
        grad.addColorStop(.62, `hsla(${hue},100%,76%,${alpha * .32})`);
        grad.addColorStop(1, `rgba(255,255,255,${alpha})`);
        ctx.strokeStyle = grad;
        ctx.lineWidth = Math.max(.65, (s.size || 1) * (.58 + burst * 1.35) * (opts.width || 1));
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(tail.x, tail.y);
        ctx.quadraticCurveTo(midX + nx * bend, midY + ny * bend, head.x, head.y);
        ctx.stroke();
        drawn++;
      }
      ctx.restore();
      return drawn;
    }

    function drawUltraJumpDepartureStreaks(w, h, tr, opts) {
      const p = clamp(tr.t / tr.dur, 0, 1);
      if (p >= opts.departureEnd) return 0;
      const streak = clamp((p - opts.streakStart) / Math.max(.04, opts.departureEnd - opts.streakStart), 0, 1);
      if (streak <= 0) return 0;
      const drawn = drawUltraCapturedStarStreaks(w, h, tr, streak, opts.palette, opts.captured);
      if (drawn < opts.fallbackMin) {
        const fallbackFade = 1 - smoothstep(.46, 1, streak);
        if (fallbackFade > .02) drawUltraStarAcceleration(w, h, streak, opts.palette, { ...opts.fallback, alpha: (opts.fallback?.alpha || 1) * fallbackFade });
      }
      return drawn;
    }

    function drawUltraCloudTunnel(w, h, p, palette, opts = {}) {
      const cx = w / 2, cy = h / 2;
      const rng = mulberry(opts.seed || 0xc10d);
      const maxR = Math.hypot(w, h) * (opts.radius || .68);
      const spin = p * TAU * (opts.spin || .62);
      const intensity = opts.intensity ?? 1;
      ctx.save();
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
      ctx.lineCap = "round";
      for (let i = 0; i < (opts.arcs ?? 48); i++) {
        const z = (rng() + p * (opts.depth || 1.35)) % 1;
        const r = lerp(18, maxR, Math.pow(z, .72));
        const a = rng() * TAU + spin * (1.2 - z * .55);
        const sweep = (.38 + rng() * .9) * (opts.sweep || 1);
        const hue = palette[Math.floor(rng() * palette.length)];
        const alpha = clamp((.05 + intensity * .22) * (1 - z * .35), .015, .34);
        ctx.strokeStyle = `hsla(${hue},100%,70%,${alpha})`;
        ctx.lineWidth = (10 + z * 28) * (opts.width || 1);
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.ellipse(cx, cy, r, r * (opts.flatten || .58), a * .04, a, a + sweep);
        ctx.stroke();
      }
      for (let i = 0; i < (opts.puffs ?? 90); i++) {
        const z = (rng() + p * (opts.depth || 1.35)) % 1;
        const a = rng() * TAU + spin * (1.4 - z * .4);
        const r = lerp(10, maxR * .92, Math.pow(z, .78));
        const x = cx + Math.cos(a) * r;
        const y = cy + Math.sin(a) * r * (opts.flatten || .58);
        const size = (12 + z * 42) * (opts.width || 1);
        const hue = palette[Math.floor(rng() * palette.length)];
        const g = ctx.createRadialGradient(x, y, 0, x, y, size);
        g.addColorStop(0, `hsla(${hue},100%,76%,${.03 + intensity * .08})`);
        g.addColorStop(1, `hsla(${hue},100%,48%,0)`);
        ctx.fillStyle = g;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.ellipse(x, y, size * 1.55, size, a + spin, 0, TAU);
        ctx.fill();
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawUltraArrivalCrackle(w, h, p, palette, opts = {}) {
      if (p <= 0) return;
      const cx = w / 2, cy = h / 2;
      const rng = mulberry(opts.seed || 0xa771);
      const snap = easeInOut(p);
      ctx.save();
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
      ctx.lineCap = "round";
      for (let i = 0; i < (opts.bolts || 20); i++) {
        const a = rng() * TAU;
        const hue = palette[Math.floor(rng() * palette.length)];
        const len0 = Math.min(w, h) * (.04 + rng() * .06);
        const len1 = Math.hypot(w, h) * (.18 + rng() * .52) * snap;
        ctx.strokeStyle = `hsla(${hue},100%,82%,${(.08 + rng() * .18) * snap})`;
        ctx.lineWidth = (1 + rng() * 2.2) * (opts.width || 1);
        ctx.beginPath();
        let x = cx + Math.cos(a) * len0;
        let y = cy + Math.sin(a) * len0 * .75;
        ctx.moveTo(x, y);
        const segs = 3 + Math.floor(rng() * 4);
        for (let s = 1; s <= segs; s++) {
          const t = s / segs;
          const wob = (rng() - .5) * 42 * snap;
          x = cx + Math.cos(a) * lerp(len0, len1, t) + Math.cos(a + Math.PI / 2) * wob;
          y = cy + Math.sin(a) * lerp(len0, len1, t) * .75 + Math.sin(a + Math.PI / 2) * wob;
          ctx.lineTo(x, y);
        }
        ctx.stroke();
      }
      const flash = clamp((p - .72) / .28, 0, 1);
      if (flash > 0) {
        ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(220,245,255,${flash * .36})`;
        ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawUltraHyperspaceTunnel(w, h, tr) {
      const p = clamp(tr.t / tr.dur, 0, 1);
      const cx = w / 2, cy = h / 2;
      const palette = [196, 210, 178, 146];
      const tunnel = clamp((p - .22) / .54, 0, 1);
      const arrival = clamp((p - .72) / .28, 0, 1);
      ctx.save();
      applyUltraWormholeShake(w, h, p, 1);
      if (p < (tr.departureEnd ?? .26)) {
        ctx.restore();
        return;
      }
      if (tr._arrived && p >= (tr.arrivalAt ?? .74)) {
        const ap = clamp((p - (tr.arrivalAt ?? .74)) / Math.max(.08, 1 - (tr.arrivalAt ?? .74)), 0, 1);
        drawUltraArrivalCrackle(w, h, clamp(ap * 1.35, 0, 1), [196, 210, 178], { seed: 0xdec1, bolts: 14, width: .75 });
        ctx.restore();
        return;
      }
      const bg = ctx.createRadialGradient(cx, cy, 0, cx, cy, Math.hypot(w, h) * .7);
      bg.addColorStop(0, `rgba(12,32,42,${.2 + tunnel * .28})`);
      bg.addColorStop(.5, `rgba(0,12,28,${.54 + tunnel * .24})`);
      bg.addColorStop(1, `rgba(0,0,0,${.84 + arrival * .1})`);
      ctx.fillStyle = bg;
      ctx.fillRect(-w * .08, -h * .08, w * 1.16, h * 1.16);
      if (tunnel > 0) drawUltraCloudTunnel(w, h, tunnel, palette, { seed: 0x4511e7, intensity: clamp(tunnel * 1.5, 0, 1) * (1 - arrival * .38), spin: .52, arcs: 0, puffs: 96, width: .82, flatten: .6 });
      drawUltraAperture(w, h, clamp((p - .12) / .74, 0, 1), palette, { pulses: 2 });
      drawUltraArrivalCrackle(w, h, arrival, [196, 210, 178], { seed: 0xdec1, bolts: 18, width: .9 });
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawUltraGalacticTunnel(w, h, tr) {
      const p = clamp(tr.t / tr.dur, 0, 1);
      const cx = w / 2, cy = h / 2;
      const palette = [204, 224, 270, 188, 318];
      const tunnel = clamp((p - .18) / .62, 0, 1);
      const arrival = clamp((p - .76) / .24, 0, 1);
      ctx.save();
      applyUltraWormholeShake(w, h, p, 1.22);
      if (p < (tr.departureEnd ?? .22)) {
        ctx.restore();
        return;
      }
      if (tr._arrived && p >= (tr.arrivalAt ?? .76)) {
        const ap = clamp((p - (tr.arrivalAt ?? .76)) / Math.max(.08, 1 - (tr.arrivalAt ?? .76)), 0, 1);
        drawUltraArrivalCrackle(w, h, clamp(ap * 1.4, 0, 1), [196, 230, 286, 52], { seed: 0x6a1ac7, bolts: 24, width: 1 });
        ctx.restore();
        return;
      }
      ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(0,0,0,${.72 + arrival * .16})`;
      ctx.fillRect(-w * .08, -h * .08, w * 1.16, h * 1.16);
      if (tunnel > 0) drawUltraCloudTunnel(w, h, tunnel, palette, { seed: 0x6a0a7, intensity: clamp(tunnel * 1.4, 0, 1) * (1 - arrival * .32), spin: .74, arcs: 0, puffs: 132, width: 1.08, flatten: .56, radius: .78, depth: 1.18, sweep: 1.25 });
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
      for (let i = 0; i < 12; i++) {
        const z = (i / 12 + tunnel * 1.18) % 1;
        const rr = lerp(28, Math.hypot(w, h) * .62, z * z);
        ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(180,225,255,${clamp(.18 + tunnel * .34 - z * .26, .04, .42)})`;
        ctx.lineWidth = 1.1 + z * 3;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.ellipse(cx, cy, rr, rr * .52, p * .28, 0, TAU);
        ctx.stroke();
      }
      drawUltraAperture(w, h, clamp((p - .1) / .78, 0, 1), palette, { pulses: 4 });
      drawUltraArrivalCrackle(w, h, arrival, [196, 230, 286, 52], { seed: 0x6a1ac7, bolts: 30, width: 1.15 });
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawHyperspaceTunnel(w, h, tr) {
      if (ultraFxEnabled()) return drawUltraHyperspaceTunnel(w, h, tr);
      const p = clamp(tr.t / tr.dur, 0, 1);
      const cx = w / 2, cy = h / 2;
      const progress = easeInOut(p);
      ctx.save();
      ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(0,0,0,${.22 + progress * .26})`;
      ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);
      drawWarpStars(w, h, "101,255,71", progress, .9);
      ctx.lineCap = "round";
      const maxR = Math.max(w, h) * .72;
      for (let i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
        const z = ((i / 10 + progress * 1.55) % 1);
        const r = lerp(12, maxR, z * z);
        const alpha = clamp(.95 - z * .8, .1, .78);
        ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(101,255,71,${alpha})`;
        ctx.lineWidth = 1 + z * 2.4;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.ellipse(cx, cy, r, r * .72, 0, 0, TAU);
        ctx.stroke();
      }
      const vignette = ctx.createRadialGradient(cx, cy, 0, cx, cy, Math.max(w, h) * .6);
      vignette.addColorStop(0, "rgba(101,255,71,0)");
      vignette.addColorStop(1, `rgba(101,255,71,${clamp(progress * .28, 0, .28)})`);
      ctx.fillStyle = vignette;
      ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawGalacticTunnel(w, h, tr) {
      if (ultraFxEnabled()) return drawUltraGalacticTunnel(w, h, tr);
      const p = clamp(tr.t / tr.dur, 0, 1);
      const cx = w / 2, cy = h / 2;
      const progress = easeInOut(p);
      const pulse = .5 + .5 * Math.sin(p * TAU * 5);
      ctx.save();
      ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(0,0,0,${.34 + progress * .4})`;
      ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);
      drawWarpStars(w, h, "180,120,255", progress, 1.55);
      drawWarpStars(w, h, "110,235,255", clamp(progress * 1.15, 0, 1), 1.05);

      const maxR = Math.max(w, h) * .86;
      for (let i = 0; i < 16; i++) {
        const z = ((i / 16 + p * 1.95) % 1);
        const r = lerp(10, maxR, z * z);
        const twist = p * TAU * 1.2 + i * .23;
        const alpha = clamp(.92 - z * .72 + pulse * .08, .12, .88);
        ctx.strokeStyle = i % 2 ? `rgba(111,242,255,${alpha})` : `rgba(164,92,255,${alpha})`;
        ctx.lineWidth = 1.1 + z * 3.2;
        ctx.beginPath();
        const segments = 40;
        for (let s = 0; s <= segments; s++) {
          const a = s / segments * TAU;
          const wobble = 1 + Math.sin(a * 6 + twist) * .025;
          const x = cx + Math.cos(a + twist * .08) * r * wobble;
          const y = cy + Math.sin(a) * r * .68 * wobble;
          if (s === 0) ctx.moveTo(x, y);
          else ctx.lineTo(x, y);
        }
        ctx.stroke();
      }

      const core = ctx.createRadialGradient(cx, cy, 0, cx, cy, Math.min(w, h) * .45);
      core.addColorStop(0, `rgba(255,255,255,${.06 + pulse * .06})`);
      core.addColorStop(.45, `rgba(141,92,255,${.08 + progress * .12})`);
      core.addColorStop(1, "rgba(0,0,0,0)");
      ctx.fillStyle = core;
      ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function randomSphereDir(rng) {
      const y = rng() * 2 - 1;
      const a = rng() * TAU;
      const r = Math.sqrt(Math.max(0, 1 - y * y));
      return vec(Math.cos(a) * r, y, Math.sin(a) * r);
    }

    function tangentFrameForDir(dir) {
      let a = cross(Math.abs(dir.y) > .82 ? vec(1, 0, 0) : vec(0, 1, 0), dir);
      if (len(a) < .001) a = cross(vec(0, 0, 1), dir);
      a = norm(a);
      return { a, b: norm(cross(dir, a)) };
    }

    function buildGalaxyBackdrop(seed) {
      const rng = mulberry(seed);
      const planeA = randomSphereDir(rng);
      let planeB = cross(planeA, randomSphereDir(rng));
      if (len(planeB) < .01) planeB = cross(planeA, vec(0, 1, 0));
      planeB = norm(planeB);
      const planeN = norm(cross(planeA, planeB));
      const palette = [
        [210 + rng() * 35, 80, 56],
        [142 + rng() * 42, 74, 48],
        [330 + rng() * 40, 78, 52],
        [24 + rng() * 30, 88, 52]
      ];
      const clouds = [];
      for (let i = 0; i < 96; i++) {
        const [hue, sat, light] = palette[Math.floor(rng() * palette.length)];
        const a = rng() * TAU;
        const lat = (rng() - .5) * (rng() < .72 ? .62 : 1.65);
        const dir = norm(add(
          add(scale(planeA, Math.cos(a) * Math.cos(lat)), scale(planeB, Math.sin(a) * Math.cos(lat))),
          scale(planeN, Math.sin(lat))
        ));
        const angular = rng() < .18 ? .19 + rng() * .18 : .055 + rng() * .14;
        const alpha = rng() < .18 ? .11 + rng() * .08 : .045 + rng() * .075;
        const frame = tangentFrameForDir(dir);
        const puffCount = 3 + Math.floor(rng() * (angular > .18 ? 7 : 4));
        for (let p = 0; p < puffCount; p++) {
          const pa = rng() * TAU;
          const pr = Math.pow(rng(), .55) * angular * .88;
          const local = add(scale(frame.a, Math.cos(pa) * pr), scale(frame.b, Math.sin(pa) * pr));
          clouds.push({
            dir: norm(add(dir, local)),
            hue: hue + (rng() - .5) * 18,
            sat,
            light,
            angular: angular * (.42 + rng() * .42),
            alpha: alpha / Math.sqrt(puffCount) * (.72 + rng() * .62)
          });
        }
      }
      const stars = [];
      for (let i = 0; i < 360; i++) {
        const nearPlane = rng() < .46;
        const a = rng() * TAU;
        const lat = nearPlane ? (rng() - .5) * 1.05 : Math.asin(rng() * 2 - 1);
        const dir = nearPlane
          ? norm(add(
            add(scale(planeA, Math.cos(a) * Math.cos(lat)), scale(planeB, Math.sin(a) * Math.cos(lat))),
            scale(planeN, Math.sin(lat) * (.28 + rng() * .72))
          ))
          : randomSphereDir(rng);
        const bright = rng() > .82;
        stars.push({
          dir,
          size: bright ? .9 + rng() * 1.3 : .45 + rng() * .7,
          alpha: bright ? .42 + rng() * .36 : .16 + rng() * .34,
          glow: bright && rng() > .25
        });
      }
      return { clouds, stars };
    }

    function galaxyBackdrop() {
      const sys = currentSystem();
      const key = `${game.galaxy}:${sys.index}:${sys.name}`;
      let backdrop = galaxyBackdropCache.get(key);
      if (!backdrop) {
        backdrop = buildGalaxyBackdrop(hash32(`galaxy-backdrop:${key}`));
        galaxyBackdropCache.set(key, backdrop);
        if (galaxyBackdropCache.size > 12) galaxyBackdropCache.delete(galaxyBackdropCache.keys().next().value);
      }
      return backdrop;
    }

    function drawGalaxyBackdrop(w, h) {
      if (game.fxLevel === "classic") return;
      const backdrop = galaxyBackdrop();
      const lod = performanceLod();
      const camInv = quatConj(ensureCameraQuat(game.camera));
      const f = Math.min(w, h) * .82;
      if (!Number.isFinite(f) || f <= 0) return;
      const trajectoryTakeover = !!game.jumpCountdown?.trajectoryControl;
      const toScreen = (dir) => {
        if (!finiteVec3(dir)) return null;
        const p = quatRotate(camInv, dir);
        if (!finiteVec3(p) || p.z <= .035) return null;
        const pr = { x: w / 2 + (p.x / p.z) * f, y: h / 2 - (p.y / p.z) * f, z: p.z, p };
        return Number.isFinite(pr.x) && Number.isFinite(pr.y) ? pr : null;
      };
      ctx.save();
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "screen";
      const cloudStep = Math.max(1, trajectoryTakeover ? 3 : lod >= 3 ? 4 : lod >= 2 ? 3 : lod >= 1 ? 2 : 1);
      for (let ci = 0; ci < backdrop.clouds.length; ci += cloudStep) {
        const cloud = backdrop.clouds[ci];
        const pr = toScreen(cloud.dir);
        if (!pr) continue;
        const edgeFade = smoothstep(.07, .34, pr.z);
        const r = clamp((f * cloud.angular) / Math.max(.18, pr.z), 12, Math.max(w, h) * .32);
        const alpha = clamp(cloud.alpha * edgeFade * (game.witchspace ? .42 : trajectoryTakeover ? .82 : 1.2), 0, 1);
        if (![pr.x, pr.y, r, alpha].every(Number.isFinite)) continue;
        if (alpha <= .008) continue;
        const g = ctx.createRadialGradient(pr.x, pr.y, 0, pr.x, pr.y, r);
        g.addColorStop(0, `hsla(${cloud.hue},${cloud.sat}%,${Math.min(86, cloud.light + 24)}%,${alpha})`);
        g.addColorStop(.42, `hsla(${cloud.hue},${cloud.sat}%,${cloud.light}%,${alpha * .42})`);
        g.addColorStop(1, `hsla(${cloud.hue},${cloud.sat}%,${Math.max(20, cloud.light - 20)}%,0)`);
        ctx.fillStyle = g;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, r, 0, TAU);
        ctx.fill();
      }
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
      const starStep = lod >= 3 ? 4 : lod >= 2 ? 3 : lod >= 1 ? 2 : 1;
      const stars = backdrop.stars || [];
      for (let si = 0; si < stars.length; si += starStep) {
        const star = stars[si];
        const pr = toScreen(star.dir);
        if (!pr) continue;
        const edgeFade = clamp((pr.z - .035) / .18, 0, 1);
        const alpha = clamp(star.alpha * edgeFade * (game.witchspace ? .55 : 1), 0, 1);
        if (alpha <= .025) continue;
        const s = clamp((star.size * f * .0028) / Math.max(.18, pr.z), .45, 2.8);
        if (![pr.x, pr.y, s, alpha].every(Number.isFinite)) continue;
        if (star.glow && lod < 2) {
          const gr = clamp(s * 4.6, 2.4, 11);
          if (!Number.isFinite(gr)) continue;
          const g = ctx.createRadialGradient(pr.x, pr.y, 0, pr.x, pr.y, gr);
          g.addColorStop(0, `rgba(255,255,255,${alpha * .22})`);
          g.addColorStop(.45, `rgba(210,228,255,${alpha * .1})`);
          g.addColorStop(1, "rgba(255,255,255,0)");
          ctx.fillStyle = g;
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, gr, 0, TAU);
          ctx.fill();
        }
        ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(245,250,255,${alpha})`;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, s, 0, TAU);
        ctx.fill();
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawStars(w, h, camera = game.camera) {
      ctx.save();
      const cx = w / 2, cy = h / 2;
      const speedFrac = clamp((game.speed || 0) / (game.maxSpeed || 220), 0, 1);
      const jumpBoost = jumpDepartureStarBoost();
      const jumpTravel = jumpDepartureDustTravel();
      const lod = performanceLod();
      const starStep = jumpBoost > .05 ? 1 : lod >= 3 ? 4 : lod >= 2 ? 3 : lod >= 1 ? 2 : 1;
      for (let si = 0; si < game.stars.length; si += starStep) {
        const star = game.stars[si];
        let p = cameraTransform(star, camera);
        if (jumpTravel > 0) {
          const near = 26, far = 3600, span = far - near;
          const phase = (((star.tw || 0) / TAU) % 1 + 1) % 1;
          const speedMul = .72 + phase * .62;
          const z = near + ((((p.z - jumpTravel * speedMul) - near) % span + span) % span);
          p = vec(p.x, p.y, z);
        }
        const pr = project(p, w, h);
        if (!pr || pr.x < 0 || pr.y < 0 || pr.x > w || pr.y > h) continue;
        if (game.fxLevel === "classic") {
          // Old-school preset: uniform flat dots, no hue/twinkle/glow/streaks.
          ctx.fillStyle = game.witchspace ? "rgba(141,92,255,.9)" : "rgba(233,242,228,.9)";
          ctx.fillRect(pr.x, pr.y, 1.6, 1.6);
          continue;
        }
        const r = clamp((star.size || 1.3) - p.z / 3200, .4, 1.9);
        const twinkle = .82 + Math.sin(performance.now() / 260 + (star.tw || 0)) * .18;
        const colorAt = game.witchspace
          ? (a) => `rgba(141,92,255,${a})`
          : star.sat
            ? (a) => `hsla(${star.hue}, ${star.sat}%, 92%, ${a})`
            : (a) => `rgba(233,242,228,${a})`;
        const alpha = clamp(clamp(1.68 - p.z / 3000, .3, 1) * twinkle * (1 + jumpBoost * 1.35), 0, 1);
        const closeness = clamp(1 - p.z / 2600, .15, 1);
        // Streaks radiate from the screen's vanishing point (where the camera is heading), so
        // near/central dust appears to rush past fastest - the classic "sensation of movement"
        // cue - while distant/off-axis stars barely stretch, matching real forward-motion parallax.
        const normalStreak = speedFrac * closeness * 30;
        const jumpStreak = jumpBoost * (h * .5) * (.5 + closeness * .65);
        const streak = normalStreak + jumpStreak;
        const dx = pr.x - cx, dy = pr.y - cy;
        const dist = Math.hypot(dx, dy) || 1;
        // Apparent motion depends on the view: radial out of the vanishing point ahead
        // (fwd/ext), radially inward behind (rear), and a horizontal sweep in the side
        // views, where the direction of travel sits off the edge of the screen.
        const vm = game.viewMode || "fwd";
        const dirX = vm === "left" ? -1 : vm === "right" ? 1 : (vm === "rear" ? -dx : dx) / dist;
        const dirY = (vm === "left" || vm === "right") ? 0 : (vm === "rear" ? -dy : dy) / dist;
        const tailX = pr.x - dirX * streak, tailY = pr.y - dirY * streak;
        // The tail fades to fully transparent rather than stroking a flat-alpha line, so a
        // streaking dust mote reads as trailing off behind it instead of a hard-edged rod.
        const grad = ctx.createLinearGradient(tailX, tailY, pr.x, pr.y);
        grad.addColorStop(0, colorAt(0));
        const inJump = jumpBoost > .02;
        grad.addColorStop(.7, inJump ? `rgba(255,255,255,${clamp(alpha * .2 * jumpBoost, 0, .55)})` : colorAt(alpha * .35));
        grad.addColorStop(1, inJump ? `rgba(255,255,255,${alpha})` : colorAt(alpha));
        ctx.lineCap = inJump ? "butt" : "round";
        ctx.strokeStyle = grad;
        ctx.shadowColor = inJump ? `rgba(255,255,255,${alpha * .72})` : colorAt(alpha);
        ctx.shadowBlur = r * (inJump ? 4.6 + jumpBoost * 3.2 : 2.2);
        ctx.lineWidth = inJump ? clamp(r * (.72 + jumpBoost * .1), .7, 1.45) : r;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(tailX, tailY);
        ctx.lineTo(pr.x, pr.y);
        ctx.stroke();
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawLensFlare(pr, r, hue, sat, light, strength, w, h) {
      if (!ultraFxEnabled() || strength <= 0) return;
      if (pr.x + r < 0 || pr.x - r > w || pr.y + r < 0 || pr.y - r > h) return;
      const cx = w / 2, cy = h / 2;
      const dx = cx - pr.x, dy = cy - pr.y;
      const dist = Math.hypot(dx, dy);
      const screenDiag = Math.hypot(w, h);
      const visible = clamp(1 - dist / (screenDiag * .8), 0, 1);
      const brightness = clamp((light - 50) / 46, .5, 1.25) * clamp(.68 + strength * 1.55, .45, 1.65);
      const a = clamp((.2 + strength * 1.08) * (.48 + visible * .62) * brightness, .045, .86);
      if (a <= .015) return;
      const axisLen = Math.hypot(dx, dy) || 1;
      const ax = dx / axisLen, ay = dy / axisLen;
      const px = -ay, py = ax;
      const axisAngle = Math.atan2(dy, dx);
      const drawOrb = (x, y, radius, alpha, hueShift = 0, stretch = 1) => {
        const g = ctx.createRadialGradient(x, y, 0, x, y, radius);
        g.addColorStop(0, `hsla(${hue + hueShift}, ${sat}%, ${light}%, ${alpha * .72})`);
        g.addColorStop(.28, `hsla(${hue + hueShift}, ${sat}%, ${Math.max(42, light - 10)}%, ${alpha * .28})`);
        g.addColorStop(.66, `hsla(${hue + hueShift}, ${Math.round(sat * .75)}%, ${Math.max(34, light - 22)}%, ${alpha * .1})`);
        g.addColorStop(1, `hsla(${hue + hueShift}, ${sat}%, ${Math.max(28, light - 28)}%, 0)`);
        ctx.save();
        ctx.translate(x, y);
        ctx.scale(stretch, 1);
        ctx.fillStyle = g;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(0, 0, radius, 0, TAU);
        ctx.fill();
        ctx.restore();
      };
      const drawAperture = (x, y, radius, alpha, hueShift = 0, sides = 6) => {
        ctx.save();
        ctx.translate(x, y);
        ctx.rotate(Math.atan2(dy, dx) + .26);
        ctx.strokeStyle = `hsla(${hue + hueShift}, ${Math.round(sat * .85)}%, ${light}%, ${alpha})`;
        ctx.lineWidth = clamp(radius * .034, .45, 1.5);
        ctx.beginPath();
        for (let i = 0; i <= sides; i++) {
          const a0 = i / sides * TAU;
          const px = Math.cos(a0) * radius;
          const py = Math.sin(a0) * radius;
          if (i === 0) ctx.moveTo(px, py);
          else ctx.lineTo(px, py);
        }
        ctx.stroke();
        ctx.restore();
      };
      const drawRingArtifact = (x, y, radius, alpha, hueShift = 0, stretch = 1) => {
        ctx.save();
        ctx.translate(x, y);
        ctx.scale(stretch, 1);
        ctx.strokeStyle = `hsla(${hue + hueShift}, ${Math.round(sat * .82)}%, ${light}%, ${alpha})`;
        ctx.lineWidth = clamp(radius * .026, .45, 1.45);
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(0, 0, radius, 0, TAU);
        ctx.stroke();
        ctx.strokeStyle = `hsla(${hue + hueShift + 80}, ${Math.round(sat * .65)}%, ${Math.max(42, light - 10)}%, ${alpha * .24})`;
        ctx.lineWidth = clamp(radius * .012, .35, .8);
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(0, 0, radius * .68, 0, TAU);
        ctx.stroke();
        ctx.restore();
      };
      const drawRay = (angle, length, width, alpha, hueShift = 0, core = false) => {
        const ux = Math.cos(angle), uy = Math.sin(angle);
        const x0 = pr.x - ux * length, y0 = pr.y - uy * length;
        const x1 = pr.x + ux * length, y1 = pr.y + uy * length;
        const g = ctx.createLinearGradient(x0, y0, x1, y1);
        g.addColorStop(0, `hsla(${hue + hueShift}, ${sat}%, ${light}%, 0)`);
        g.addColorStop(.46, `hsla(${hue + hueShift}, ${Math.min(100, sat + 8)}%, ${Math.min(98, light + 8)}%, ${alpha * .36})`);
        g.addColorStop(.5, `hsla(${hue + hueShift}, ${Math.min(100, sat + 10)}%, 96%, ${alpha})`);
        g.addColorStop(.54, `hsla(${hue + hueShift}, ${Math.min(100, sat + 8)}%, ${Math.min(98, light + 8)}%, ${alpha * .36})`);
        g.addColorStop(1, `hsla(${hue + hueShift}, ${sat}%, ${light}%, 0)`);
        ctx.save();
        ctx.strokeStyle = g;
        ctx.lineWidth = width;
        ctx.lineCap = "round";
        ctx.shadowColor = `hsla(${hue + hueShift}, ${sat}%, ${light}%, ${alpha * .8})`;
        ctx.shadowBlur = core ? width * 2.8 : width * 1.4;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(x0, y0);
        ctx.lineTo(x1, y1);
        ctx.stroke();
        ctx.restore();
      };

      ctx.save();
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
      const haloR = clamp(r * (3.6 + strength * 5.4), 42, screenDiag * .58);
      drawOrb(pr.x, pr.y, haloR, a * .26, 0, 1.18);

      const flareLen = clamp(screenDiag * (.16 + strength * .36), 130, screenDiag * .62);
      const diagonal = axisAngle + .72;
      drawRay(diagonal, flareLen, clamp(r * .06 + strength * 8, 4, 26), a * .3, 185);
      drawRay(diagonal + Math.PI, flareLen * .72, clamp(r * .04 + strength * 6, 2.8, 18), a * .22, 205);
      const spikeLen = clamp(r * (3.2 + strength * 6.5), 32, screenDiag * .3);
      drawRay(0, spikeLen, clamp(r * .02, .8, 4), a * .74, 4, true);
      drawRay(Math.PI / 2, spikeLen * .72, clamp(r * .014, .6, 3), a * .45, 18, true);
      drawRay(Math.PI / 4, spikeLen * .5, clamp(r * .011, .5, 2), a * .3, -12);
      drawRay(-Math.PI / 4, spikeLen * .5, clamp(r * .011, .5, 2), a * .28, -12);

      const ghosts = [
        { t: -.72, s: .095, a: .24, h: -70, stretch: 1.05, aperture: true, ring: true, off: -.018 },
        { t: -.32, s: .15, a: .3, h: -28, stretch: 1.28, ring: true, off: .014 },
        { t: .26, s: .26, a: .42, h: 28, stretch: 1.55, ring: true, off: -.02 },
        { t: .58, s: .12, a: .34, h: -8, stretch: 1, aperture: true, ring: true, off: .018 },
        { t: .92, s: .2, a: .25, h: 72, stretch: 1.22, ring: true, off: -.012 },
        { t: 1.22, s: .09, a: .2, h: -55, stretch: 1, aperture: true, off: .02 },
        { t: 1.58, s: .16, a: .16, h: 112, stretch: 1.36, ring: true, off: -.016 },
        { t: 2.02, s: .07, a: .12, h: 170, stretch: 1.1, ring: true, off: .012 }
      ];
      for (const g of ghosts) {
        const gx = pr.x + dx * g.t + px * screenDiag * g.off;
        const gy = pr.y + dy * g.t + py * screenDiag * g.off;
        const edgeFade = clamp(1 - Math.max(Math.abs(gx - cx) / (w * .64), Math.abs(gy - cy) / (h * .72)), .08, 1);
        const gr = clamp(screenDiag * g.s * (.34 + strength * .42), 13, 118);
        const ga = a * g.a * edgeFade;
        drawOrb(gx, gy, gr, ga * .62, g.h, g.stretch);
        if (g.ring) drawRingArtifact(gx, gy, gr * .92, ga * .58, g.h, g.stretch);
        if (g.aperture) drawAperture(gx, gy, gr * 1.08, ga * .46, g.h);
        ctx.fillStyle = `hsla(${hue + g.h}, ${sat}%, ${light}%, ${ga * .38})`;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(gx, gy, clamp(gr * .12, 1.4, 5.5), 0, TAU);
        ctx.fill();
      }

      // A faint veiling glare near the sun reduces local contrast, matching the broad
      // wash caused by scatter in real optics without covering the whole cockpit.
      const veil = ctx.createRadialGradient(pr.x, pr.y, r * .7, pr.x, pr.y, clamp(screenDiag * .42, 180, 620));
      veil.addColorStop(0, `hsla(${hue}, ${sat}%, ${light}%, ${a * .035})`);
      veil.addColorStop(1, `hsla(${hue}, ${sat}%, ${light}%, 0)`);
      ctx.fillStyle = veil;
      ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawEnemyShots(w, h) {
      for (const s of game.enemyShots) {
        const fromP = project(cameraTransform(s.from, game.camera), w, h);
        if (!fromP) continue;
        // to === null means the target is the player, who has no visible ship in this
        // first-person view. Aim around the cockpit instead of stapling every hostile
        // beam to the crosshair; damage is handled in the combat routine, so this is
        // allowed to show near-misses and glancing fire.
        let toP = {
          x: w * (.5 + (s.screenAim?.x || 0)) + (s.screenOffset?.x || 0),
          y: h * (.5 + (s.screenAim?.y || 0)) + (s.screenOffset?.y || 0)
        };
        if (s.to) {
          const p = project(cameraTransform(s.to, game.camera), w, h);
          if (!p) continue;
          toP = p;
        }
        const alpha = clamp(1 - s.t / (s.beamDur || s.dur), 0, 1);
        const sparkAlpha = clamp(1 - s.t / s.dur, 0, 1);
        const dx = toP.x - fromP.x, dy = toP.y - fromP.y;
        const dist = Math.max(1, Math.hypot(dx, dy));
        const nx = -dy / dist, ny = dx / dist;
        const color = s.color || (s.missile ? "#ff8240" : "#ff463c");
        const core = s.core || "#fff0d0";
        const beam = hexToRgb(color);
        const coreRgb = hexToRgb(core);
        const simple = !ultraFxEnabled();

        ctx.save();
        ctx.lineCap = "round";
        if (simple) {
          drawLaserBeam2D(fromP, toP, {
            color,
            width: s.width || 2,
            alpha,
            ultra: false,
            classicWidth: s.missile ? 2.6 : 1.8
          });
          ctx.restore();
          continue;
        }

        const muzzle = Math.min(60, 12 + dist * .035);
        const tail = {
          x: fromP.x + dx * .16,
          y: fromP.y + dy * .16
        };
        drawLaserBeam2D(fromP, toP, {
          color,
          core,
          width: Math.max(1, s.width || 2),
          alpha,
          wedge: false,
          bloom: false,
          glowMul: 5.2,
          shadowBlur: s.glow || 12
        });

        ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
        const forks = s.forks || 0;
        for (let i = 0; i < forks; i++) {
          const sign = i % 2 ? -1 : 1;
          const startT = .18 + i * .09;
          const endT = .82 - i * .04;
          const bend = sign * (10 + i * 7) * alpha;
          ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(${beam.r},${beam.g},${beam.b},${alpha * (.32 - i * .05)})`;
          ctx.lineWidth = Math.max(.8, (s.width || 2) * .72);
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.moveTo(fromP.x + dx * startT, fromP.y + dy * startT);
          ctx.quadraticCurveTo(
            fromP.x + dx * .5 + nx * bend,
            fromP.y + dy * .5 + ny * bend,
            fromP.x + dx * endT + nx * bend * .45,
            fromP.y + dy * endT + ny * bend * .45
          );
          ctx.stroke();
        }

        const muzzleGlow = ctx.createRadialGradient(fromP.x, fromP.y, 0, fromP.x, fromP.y, muzzle);
        muzzleGlow.addColorStop(0, `rgba(${coreRgb.r},${coreRgb.g},${coreRgb.b},${alpha * .56})`);
        muzzleGlow.addColorStop(.35, `rgba(${beam.r},${beam.g},${beam.b},${alpha * .32})`);
        muzzleGlow.addColorStop(1, `rgba(${beam.r},${beam.g},${beam.b},0)`);
        ctx.fillStyle = muzzleGlow;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(fromP.x, fromP.y, muzzle, 0, TAU);
        ctx.fill();

        if (s.flare) {
          const impactRadius = 22 + (s.width || 2) * 5;
          const impact = ctx.createRadialGradient(toP.x, toP.y, 0, toP.x, toP.y, impactRadius);
          impact.addColorStop(0, `rgba(${coreRgb.r},${coreRgb.g},${coreRgb.b},${sparkAlpha * .82})`);
          impact.addColorStop(.22, `rgba(255,225,130,${sparkAlpha * .48})`);
          impact.addColorStop(.52, `rgba(${beam.r},${beam.g},${beam.b},${sparkAlpha * .2})`);
          impact.addColorStop(1, `rgba(${beam.r},${beam.g},${beam.b},0)`);
          ctx.fillStyle = impact;
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.arc(toP.x, toP.y, impactRadius, 0, TAU);
          ctx.fill();

          ctx.save();
          ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
          ctx.shadowColor = `rgba(255,205,80,${sparkAlpha})`;
          ctx.shadowBlur = 14 * sparkAlpha;
          ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(255,245,190,${sparkAlpha * .88})`;
          ctx.lineWidth = 1.4 + (s.width || 2) * .35;
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.moveTo(toP.x - 18, toP.y);
          ctx.lineTo(toP.x + 18, toP.y);
          ctx.moveTo(toP.x, toP.y - 13);
          ctx.lineTo(toP.x, toP.y + 13);
          ctx.moveTo(toP.x - 10, toP.y - 10);
          ctx.lineTo(toP.x + 10, toP.y + 10);
          ctx.moveTo(toP.x + 10, toP.y - 10);
          ctx.lineTo(toP.x - 10, toP.y + 10);
          ctx.stroke();

          ctx.shadowBlur = 6 * sparkAlpha;
          ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(255,210,82,${sparkAlpha * .72})`;
          ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(255,238,150,${sparkAlpha * .78})`;
          ctx.lineWidth = 1.6;
          ctx.beginPath();
          for (const sp of s.sparks || []) {
            const sparkT = clamp(s.t / (s.dur * sp.life), 0, 1);
            if (sparkT >= 1) continue;
            const spread = sp.drift * sparkT;
            const x0 = toP.x + sp.x * spread;
            const y0 = toP.y + sp.y * spread;
            const x1 = toP.x + sp.x * (spread + sp.len * (1 - sparkT * .25));
            const y1 = toP.y + sp.y * (spread + sp.len * (1 - sparkT * .25));
            ctx.moveTo(x0, y0);
            ctx.lineTo(x1, y1);
          }
          ctx.stroke();
          for (const sp of s.sparks || []) {
            const sparkT = clamp(s.t / (s.dur * sp.life), 0, 1);
            if (sparkT >= 1) continue;
            const sa = (1 - sparkT) * sparkAlpha;
            if (sa <= .05) continue;
            const spread = sp.drift * sparkT;
            const x = toP.x + sp.x * (spread + sp.len * (1 - sparkT * .25));
            const y = toP.y + sp.y * (spread + sp.len * (1 - sparkT * .25));
            ctx.globalAlpha = sa * .7;
            ctx.beginPath();
            ctx.arc(x, y, clamp(sp.size * .55, .75, 2.1), 0, TAU);
            ctx.fill();
          }
          ctx.globalAlpha = 1;
          ctx.restore();
        }
        ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "source-over";
        ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(${beam.r},${beam.g},${beam.b},${alpha * .22})`;
        ctx.lineWidth = Math.max(1, (s.width || 2) * 1.1);
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(fromP.x, fromP.y);
        ctx.lineTo(tail.x + nx * 4, tail.y + ny * 4);
        ctx.moveTo(fromP.x, fromP.y);
        ctx.lineTo(tail.x - nx * 4, tail.y - ny * 4);
        ctx.stroke();
        ctx.restore();
      }
    }

    function drawEnginePlasmaVisual(pr, tailPr, p, age) {
      const hue = p.hue || 204;
      const solid = clamp(1 - age / .18, 0, 1);
      const fade = Math.pow(1 - age, .85);
      const alpha = p.alpha * fade;
      const r = clamp(p.radius * pr.s * (1 + age * 4.8), 1.4, 32);
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "screen";
      if (tailPr) {
        const grad = ctx.createLinearGradient(tailPr.x, tailPr.y, pr.x, pr.y);
        grad.addColorStop(0, `hsla(${hue},92%,56%,0)`);
        grad.addColorStop(.38, `hsla(${hue},92%,58%,${alpha * (.22 + solid * .12)})`);
        grad.addColorStop(1, `hsla(${hue + 12},95%,72%,${alpha * (.42 + solid * .28)})`);
        ctx.strokeStyle = grad;
        ctx.lineWidth = clamp(r * (.72 + solid * .35), 1.2, 10);
        ctx.lineCap = "round";
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(tailPr.x, tailPr.y);
        ctx.lineTo(pr.x, pr.y);
        ctx.stroke();
      }
      const g = ctx.createRadialGradient(pr.x, pr.y, 0, pr.x, pr.y, r * 3.4);
      g.addColorStop(0, `hsla(${hue + 10},95%,70%,${alpha * (.22 + solid * .24)})`);
      g.addColorStop(.45, `hsla(${hue},95%,54%,${alpha * .14})`);
      g.addColorStop(1, `hsla(${hue},95%,42%,0)`);
      ctx.fillStyle = g;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, r * 3.4, 0, TAU);
      ctx.fill();
    }

    function updatePuffStore(store, dt, limit = 260) {
      for (const p of store) p.t += dt;
      trimParticleStore(store, limit);
      for (let i = store.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        if (store[i].t >= store[i].dur) store.splice(i, 1);
      }
    }

    function drawSmokePuff(p, w, h, camera = game.camera) {
      if (!ultraFxEnabled()) return;
      const age = clamp(p.t / p.dur, 0, 1);
      const worldPos = add(p.pos, scale(p.drift, p.t));
      const rel = cameraTransform(worldPos, camera);
      const pr = project(rel, w, h);
      if (!pr) return;
      ctx.save();
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "screen";
      if (p.kind === "fireSmoke") {
        const r = clamp(p.radius * (1 + age * 2.6) * pr.s, 3, 130);
        const heat = Math.max(0, 1 - age * 1.55) * (p.heat || 1);
        const smokeA = p.alpha * Math.sin(age * Math.PI) * (1 - age * .12);
        if (heat > .02) {
          ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
          const fire = ctx.createRadialGradient(pr.x, pr.y, 0, pr.x, pr.y, r * .9);
          fire.addColorStop(0, `rgba(255,238,175,${heat * .55})`);
          fire.addColorStop(.28, `rgba(255,126,46,${heat * .34})`);
          fire.addColorStop(.75, `rgba(180,50,18,${heat * .12})`);
          fire.addColorStop(1, "rgba(120,30,10,0)");
          ctx.fillStyle = fire;
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, r * .9, 0, TAU);
          ctx.fill();
        }
        ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "source-over";
        const shade = Math.round(p.shade || 72);
        const smoke = ctx.createRadialGradient(pr.x, pr.y, 0, pr.x, pr.y, r);
        smoke.addColorStop(0, `rgba(${shade + 36},${shade + 28},${shade + 18},${smokeA * .34})`);
        smoke.addColorStop(.42, `rgba(${shade},${shade - 4},${shade - 10},${smokeA * .28})`);
        smoke.addColorStop(1, `rgba(${shade - 12},${shade - 12},${shade - 14},0)`);
        ctx.fillStyle = smoke;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, r, 0, TAU);
        ctx.fill();
        ctx.restore();
        return;
      }
      if (p.kind === "plasma" || p.kind === "enginePlasma" || p.kind === "missileTrail") {
        const isEngine = p.kind === "enginePlasma";
        const isMissile = p.kind === "missileTrail";
        const tailHold = isMissile ? (p.tailTime || .55) : isEngine ? (p.tailTime || .45) : .18;
        const tailWorld = sub(worldPos, scale(p.drift, Math.min(p.t, tailHold) + (isMissile ? .26 : isEngine ? .2 : .08)));
        const tailRel = cameraTransform(tailWorld, camera);
        const tailPr = project(tailRel, w, h);
        const hue = p.hue || 204;
        if (isMissile) {
          const fade = Math.pow(1 - age, .7);
          const alpha = p.alpha * fade;
          const r = clamp(p.radius * pr.s * (1 + age * 2.7), 1.2, 24);
          ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
          if (tailPr) {
            const grad = ctx.createLinearGradient(tailPr.x, tailPr.y, pr.x, pr.y);
            grad.addColorStop(0, `hsla(${hue},100%,38%,0)`);
            grad.addColorStop(.28, `hsla(${hue},100%,44%,${alpha * .28})`);
            grad.addColorStop(.72, `hsla(${hue + 8},100%,56%,${alpha * .62})`);
            grad.addColorStop(1, `hsla(${hue + 22},100%,78%,${alpha})`);
            ctx.strokeStyle = grad;
            ctx.lineWidth = clamp(r * .7, 1.1, 8);
            ctx.lineCap = "round";
            ctx.beginPath();
            ctx.moveTo(tailPr.x, tailPr.y);
            ctx.lineTo(pr.x, pr.y);
            ctx.stroke();
          }
          const g = ctx.createRadialGradient(pr.x, pr.y, 0, pr.x, pr.y, r * 2.8);
          g.addColorStop(0, `hsla(${hue + 28},100%,86%,${alpha * .78})`);
          g.addColorStop(.32, `hsla(${hue + 6},100%,52%,${alpha * .34})`);
          g.addColorStop(1, `hsla(${hue},100%,36%,0)`);
          ctx.fillStyle = g;
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, r * 2.8, 0, TAU);
          ctx.fill();
          ctx.restore();
          return;
        }
        if (isEngine) {
          drawEnginePlasmaVisual(pr, tailPr, p, age);
          ctx.restore();
          return;
        }
        const alpha = p.alpha * (1 - age) * (1 - age * .25);
        const r = clamp(p.radius * pr.s * (1 + age * 1.1), 1, 12);
        ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
        if (tailPr) {
          const grad = ctx.createLinearGradient(tailPr.x, tailPr.y, pr.x, pr.y);
          grad.addColorStop(0, `hsla(${hue},100%,58%,0)`);
          grad.addColorStop(.45, `hsla(${hue},100%,62%,${alpha * .45})`);
          grad.addColorStop(1, `hsla(${hue + 16},100%,84%,${alpha})`);
          ctx.strokeStyle = grad;
          ctx.lineWidth = clamp(r * .45, .8, 3.2);
          ctx.lineCap = "round";
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.moveTo(tailPr.x, tailPr.y);
          ctx.lineTo(pr.x, pr.y);
          ctx.stroke();
        }
        const g = ctx.createRadialGradient(pr.x, pr.y, 0, pr.x, pr.y, r * 2.8);
        g.addColorStop(0, `hsla(${hue + 18},100%,90%,${alpha * .75})`);
        g.addColorStop(.35, `hsla(${hue},100%,60%,${alpha * .35})`);
        g.addColorStop(1, `hsla(${hue},100%,46%,0)`);
        ctx.fillStyle = g;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, r * 2.8, 0, TAU);
        ctx.fill();
        ctx.restore();
        return;
      }
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "screen";
      const burst = p.burst || 0;
      const r = clamp(p.radius * (1 + age * (2.2 + burst * 1.35)) * pr.s, 1.5, 70 + burst * 85);
      const alpha = p.alpha * Math.sin(age * Math.PI) * (1 - age * (.2 - burst * .08));
      const shade = Math.round(p.shade);
      const tint = p.smokeTint;
      const c0 = tint ? tint.map((c) => Math.round(c * .72 + shade * .28)) : [shade + 32, shade + 32, shade + 28];
      const c1 = tint ? tint.map((c) => Math.round(c * .5 + shade * .5)) : [shade, shade, shade - 6];
      const c2 = tint ? tint.map((c) => Math.round(c * .25 + (shade - 18) * .75)) : [shade - 18, shade - 18, shade - 20];
      const g = ctx.createRadialGradient(pr.x, pr.y, 0, pr.x, pr.y, r);
      g.addColorStop(0, `rgba(${c0[0]},${c0[1]},${c0[2]},${alpha * (1 + burst * .18)})`);
      g.addColorStop(.3, `rgba(${c1[0]},${c1[1]},${c1[2]},${alpha * (.62 + burst * .18)})`);
      g.addColorStop(.68, `rgba(${c2[0]},${c2[1]},${c2[2]},${alpha * (.2 + burst * .18)})`);
      g.addColorStop(1, `rgba(${c1[0]},${c1[1]},${c1[2]},0)`);
      ctx.fillStyle = g;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, r, 0, TAU);
      ctx.fill();
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawExplosions(w, h) {
      for (const e of game.explosions) {
        const rel = cameraTransform(e.pos, game.camera);
        const pr = project(rel, w, h);
        if (!pr) continue;
        const t = clamp(e.t / e.dur, 0, 1);
        if (e.kind === "eject") {
          // Expanding cyan-white ring + brief glints, no fire.
          const ringR = (6 + t * 90) * pr.s;
          ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(140,230,240,${clamp(1 - t, 0, 1) * .85})`;
          ctx.lineWidth = clamp(2.4 * (1 - t) * pr.s + .6, .6, 3.4);
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, ringR, 0, TAU);
          ctx.stroke();
          ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(235,250,250,${clamp(1 - t * 1.4, 0, 1)})`;
          ctx.lineWidth = 1;
          ctx.beginPath();
          for (const s of e.shards) {
            const end = add(rel, scale(s.dir, s.len + s.speed * e.t));
            const pe = project(end, w, h);
            if (!pe) continue;
            ctx.moveTo(pr.x, pr.y);
            ctx.lineTo(pe.x, pe.y);
          }
          ctx.stroke();
          continue;
        }
        if (game.fxLevel === "classic") {
          ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(255,${170 - Math.floor(t * 90)},60,${clamp(1 - t, 0, 1) * .9})`;
          ctx.lineWidth = clamp(2.2 * pr.s, .6, 3);
          ctx.beginPath();
          for (const s of e.shards) {
            const end = add(rel, scale(s.dir, s.len + s.speed * e.t));
            const pe = project(end, w, h);
            if (!pe) continue;
            ctx.moveTo(pr.x, pr.y);
            ctx.lineTo(pe.x, pe.y);
          }
          ctx.stroke();
          continue;
        }

        const mag = e.magnitude || 1;
        const flashA = clamp(1 - t * 4.2, 0, 1);
        const heatA = clamp(1 - t * .95, 0, 1);
        const ringA = clamp(Math.sin(t * Math.PI) * (1 - t * .35), 0, 1);
        ctx.save();
        ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
        if (flashA > 0) {
          const r = (48 + mag * 56) * pr.s * (1 + t * 2.7) + 5;
          const g = ctx.createRadialGradient(pr.x, pr.y, 0, pr.x, pr.y, r);
          g.addColorStop(0, `rgba(255,255,245,${.92 * flashA})`);
          g.addColorStop(.25, `rgba(255,218,120,${.68 * flashA})`);
          g.addColorStop(.72, `rgba(255,102,42,${.34 * flashA})`);
          g.addColorStop(1, "rgba(255,72,30,0)");
          ctx.fillStyle = g;
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, r, 0, TAU);
          ctx.fill();
        }

        const coreR = (16 + mag * 28) * pr.s * (1 + t * 4.1);
        const core = ctx.createRadialGradient(pr.x, pr.y, 0, pr.x, pr.y, coreR);
        core.addColorStop(0, `rgba(255,238,170,${.7 * heatA})`);
        core.addColorStop(.45, `rgba(255,112,46,${.46 * heatA})`);
        core.addColorStop(1, "rgba(255,72,20,0)");
        ctx.fillStyle = core;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, coreR, 0, TAU);
        ctx.fill();

        const ringR = (12 + t * (105 + mag * 38)) * pr.s;
        ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(255,210,110,${.52 * ringA})`;
        ctx.lineWidth = clamp((2.2 + mag * 1.2) * pr.s * (1 - t * .35), .7, 5);
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, ringR, 0, TAU);
        ctx.stroke();

        ctx.lineCap = "round";
        for (const s of e.shards) {
          const travel = s.len + s.speed * e.t;
          const tail = add(rel, scale(s.dir, travel * .32));
          const head = add(rel, scale(s.dir, travel));
          const p0 = project(tail, w, h);
          const p1 = project(head, w, h);
          if (!p0 || !p1) continue;
          const a = clamp(1 - t * 1.15, 0, 1) * (.52 + s.warm * .38);
          const grad = ctx.createLinearGradient(p0.x, p0.y, p1.x, p1.y);
          grad.addColorStop(0, `rgba(255,70,24,0)`);
          grad.addColorStop(.55, `rgba(255,${150 + Math.floor(s.warm * 80)},64,${a * .75})`);
          grad.addColorStop(1, `rgba(255,245,190,${a})`);
          ctx.strokeStyle = grad;
          ctx.lineWidth = clamp((s.width || 1.4) * pr.s * (1.1 - t * .45), .45, 4);
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.moveTo(p0.x, p0.y);
          ctx.lineTo(p1.x, p1.y);
          ctx.stroke();
        }

        for (const s of e.sparks || []) {
          const sparkT = clamp(e.t / (e.dur * s.life), 0, 1);
          if (sparkT >= 1) continue;
          const p = project(add(rel, scale(s.dir, s.speed * e.t)), w, h);
          if (!p) continue;
          const a = (1 - sparkT) * .85;
          ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(255,230,125,${a})`;
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.arc(p.x, p.y, clamp(s.size * pr.s * (1 - sparkT * .4), .7, 3.2), 0, TAU);
          ctx.fill();
        }

        ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "source-over";
        for (const f of e.fragments || []) {
          const p = project(add(rel, scale(f.dir, f.speed * e.t)), w, h);
          if (!p) continue;
          const fade = clamp(1 - t * 1.2, 0, 1);
          const size = clamp(f.size * pr.s * (1 - t * .35), 1.2, 12);
          ctx.save();
          ctx.translate(p.x, p.y);
          ctx.rotate(f.angle + f.spin * e.t);
          ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(${f.shade},${f.shade + 8},${f.shade + 2},${fade * .82})`;
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.moveTo(size, 0);
          ctx.lineTo(-size * .55, size * .42);
          ctx.lineTo(-size * .25, -size * .5);
          ctx.closePath();
          ctx.fill();
          ctx.restore();
        }
        ctx.restore();
      }
    }

    function drawSunBody(o, cam, w, h) {
      const pr = project(cam, w, h);
      if (!pr) return;
      const baseR = Math.abs(o.r * pr.s);
      const glowR = baseR * (o.glowMul || 1.55);
      if (baseR < 2 || pr.x + glowR < 0 || pr.x - glowR > w || pr.y + glowR < 0 || pr.y - glowR > h) return;
      const r = baseR;
      const hue = o.hue ?? 46;
      const sat = o.sat ?? 100;
      const coreLight = o.coreLight ?? 93;
      const midLight = o.midLight ?? 74;
      const rimLight = o.rimLight ?? 48;
      const flareStrength = (o.flare || .1) * clamp(r / 36, .35, 1.45);

      if (game.graphicsMode === "wire") {
        ctx.strokeStyle = `hsl(${hue}, ${sat}%, ${Math.max(76, midLight)}%)`;
        ctx.lineWidth = 1.6;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, r, 0, TAU);
        ctx.stroke();
        ctx.globalAlpha = .28 + (o.corona || .4) * .22;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, r * (1.24 + (o.corona || .4) * .25), 0, TAU);
        ctx.stroke();
        ctx.globalAlpha = 1;
        drawLensFlare(pr, r, hue, sat, coreLight, flareStrength * .38, w, h);
        return;
      }

      const coronaStrength = o.corona || .4;
      const giantStar = o.stellarClass === "redGiant" || o.stellarClass === "redSupergiant";
      const coronaR = glowR * (1.14 + coronaStrength * .42);
      const corona = ctx.createRadialGradient(pr.x, pr.y, r * .35, pr.x, pr.y, coronaR);
      corona.addColorStop(0, `rgba(255,255,250,${.1 + coronaStrength * .12})`);
      corona.addColorStop(.2, `hsla(${hue}, ${Math.round(sat * .72)}%, ${Math.max(76, midLight + 8)}%, ${.18 + coronaStrength * .16})`);
      corona.addColorStop(.58, `hsla(${hue - 8}, ${Math.round(sat * .9)}%, ${Math.max(46, rimLight + 10)}%, ${.09 + coronaStrength * .13})`);
      corona.addColorStop(1, `hsla(${hue - 14}, ${sat}%, ${Math.max(18, rimLight - 18)}%, 0)`);
      ctx.fillStyle = corona;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, coronaR, 0, TAU);
      ctx.fill();

      const outerCoronaR = coronaR * (1.45 + coronaStrength * .45);
      const outerCorona = ctx.createRadialGradient(pr.x, pr.y, r * 1.1, pr.x, pr.y, outerCoronaR);
      outerCorona.addColorStop(0, `hsla(${hue + 8}, ${Math.round(sat * .78)}%, ${Math.max(64, midLight)}%, ${.07 + coronaStrength * .08})`);
      outerCorona.addColorStop(.42, `hsla(${hue - 10}, ${sat}%, ${Math.max(38, rimLight)}%, ${.045 + coronaStrength * .055})`);
      outerCorona.addColorStop(1, `hsla(${hue - 18}, ${sat}%, ${Math.max(18, rimLight - 18)}%, 0)`);
      ctx.fillStyle = outerCorona;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, outerCoronaR, 0, TAU);
      ctx.fill();

      const g = ctx.createRadialGradient(pr.x, pr.y, 0, pr.x, pr.y, glowR);
      g.addColorStop(0, "rgba(255,255,255,.98)");
      g.addColorStop(.16, "rgba(255,255,248,.9)");
      g.addColorStop(.36, `hsla(${hue}, ${Math.round(sat * .38)}%, ${Math.max(86, midLight + 14)}%, ${giantStar ? .42 : .36})`);
      g.addColorStop(.62, `hsla(${hue - 8}, ${Math.round(sat * .62)}%, ${Math.max(58, rimLight + 16)}%, ${giantStar ? .24 : .18})`);
      g.addColorStop(1, `hsla(${hue - 15}, ${sat}%, ${Math.max(20, rimLight - 10)}%, 0)`);
      ctx.fillStyle = g;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, glowR, 0, TAU);
      ctx.fill();

      const disk = ctx.createRadialGradient(pr.x, pr.y, 0, pr.x, pr.y, r);
      const warmSat = Math.round(sat * (giantStar ? .64 : .42));
      const edgeSat = Math.round(sat * (giantStar ? .82 : .58));
      disk.addColorStop(0, "rgba(255,255,255,1)");
      disk.addColorStop(.2, "rgba(255,255,250,1)");
      disk.addColorStop(.46, `hsla(${hue + 3}, ${Math.round(sat * .18)}%, 96%, .99)`);
      disk.addColorStop(.74, `hsla(${hue + 2}, ${warmSat}%, ${Math.max(78, midLight + 18)}%, .98)`);
      disk.addColorStop(.96, `hsla(${hue}, ${edgeSat}%, ${Math.max(64, rimLight + 32)}%, .95)`);
      disk.addColorStop(1, `hsla(${hue}, ${edgeSat}%, ${Math.max(58, rimLight + 28)}%, .88)`);
      ctx.fillStyle = disk;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, r, 0, TAU);
      ctx.fill();

      const limb = ctx.createRadialGradient(pr.x, pr.y, r * .88, pr.x, pr.y, r * (giantStar ? 1.18 : 1.13));
      limb.addColorStop(0, `hsla(${hue}, ${Math.round(sat * .35)}%, ${Math.max(84, midLight + 20)}%, .08)`);
      limb.addColorStop(.45, `hsla(${hue}, ${edgeSat}%, ${Math.max(66, rimLight + 34)}%, ${giantStar ? .22 : .16})`);
      limb.addColorStop(1, `hsla(${hue}, ${sat}%, ${Math.max(44, rimLight + 20)}%, 0)`);
      ctx.save();
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
      ctx.fillStyle = limb;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, r * (giantStar ? 1.18 : 1.13), 0, TAU);
      ctx.fill();
      ctx.restore();

      drawLensFlare(pr, r, hue, sat, coreLight, flareStrength, w, h);
    }

    // A ring is a real 3D circle lying in a plane fixed to the planet (via rotAxis +
    // ringTilt), not a 2D canvas ellipse rotation — ctx.ellipse's rotation angle is a
    // flat screen-space twist that ignores the camera's own orientation entirely, so a
    // fixed ringTilt used that way visibly rotates along with the *camera* (e.g. when
    // the player rolls) instead of staying anchored to the planet. Projecting real
    // per-point 3D positions through the normal cameraTransform/project pipeline (like
    // every other object) fixes that, and lets front/back occlusion be a genuine depth
    // test instead of a guessed screen-space angle range.
    // Ring brightness against the sun (1 = fully lit .. ~0.1 = black). Two parts:
    // a hard near-black core where the planet's true umbra cylinder crosses the ring
    // (anti-sun side, perpendicular distance from the sun axis under the planet radius),
    // plus a smooth falloff across the whole night half of the ring. The pure umbra
    // alone is physically right but reads as just two thin eclipsed stubs poking out
    // beside the planet disc (the rest of the band hides behind the planet) — the
    // night-half falloff gives the ring a proper dark side matching the terminator.
    function ringShade(offset, sunDir, planetR) {
      if (!sunDir) return 1;
      const d = len(offset) || 1;
      const along = dot(offset, sunDir);
      if (along >= 0) return 1;
      const perp = len(sub(offset, scale(sunDir, along)));
      if (perp < planetR) return .14;
      const t = -along / d; // 0 at the terminator plane -> 1 fully anti-sun
      return lerp(.98, .38, Math.pow(t, .75));
    }

    function ringHalfVisible(offset, viewDir, front) {
      if (front === null) return true;
      const side = dot(offset, viewDir);
      return front ? side >= 0 : side <= 0;
    }

    function ringSplitOffset(a, b, viewDir) {
      const sa = dot(a, viewDir);
      const sb = dot(b, viewDir);
      const denom = sa - sb;
      if (Math.abs(denom) < 1e-9) return null;
      const t = clamp(sa / denom, 0, 1);
      return vec(lerp(a.x, b.x, t), lerp(a.y, b.y, t), lerp(a.z, b.z, t));
    }

    function drawPlanetRing(o, r, hue, w, h, front) {
      if (game.fxLevel === "classic") return;
      if (!o._ringBasis) {
        const axis = o.rotAxis || vec(0, 1, 0);
        const tiltAxis = len(cross(axis, vec(0, 0, 1))) > .0001 ? norm(cross(axis, vec(0, 0, 1))) : vec(1, 0, 0);
        const normal = norm(quatRotate(quatFromAxisAngle(tiltAxis, o.ringTilt || 0), axis));
        let u = cross(normal, Math.abs(normal.y) < .9 ? vec(0, 1, 0) : vec(1, 0, 0));
        if (len(u) < .0001) u = cross(normal, vec(0, 0, 1));
        u = norm(u);
        o._ringBasis = { u, v: norm(cross(normal, u)) };
      }
      const { u, v } = o._ringBasis;
      const viewDir = norm(sub(game.camera.pos, o.pos));
      const sun = game.objects.find((s) => s.type === "sun");
      const sunDir = sun ? norm(sub(sun.pos, o.pos)) : null;
      const solid = game.graphicsMode !== "wire";
      const rng = mulberry((o.textureSeed || 1) ^ 0x51f15e);
      const debris = !!o.debrisRing;
      const bands = debris ? (solid ? 34 : 12) : (solid ? 26 : 10), segs = debris ? 208 : 176;
      const gapC = rng() * TAU;
      let drawnSegments = 0;
      ctx.save();
      ctx.lineCap = "butt";
      ctx.lineJoin = "round";
      for (let b = 0; b < bands; b++) {
        const t = bands === 1 ? 0 : b / (bands - 1);
        const rr = lerp(o.r * o.ringInner, o.r * o.ringOuter, t);
        const laneNoise = rng();
        const dusty = .52 + rng() * .38;
        const light = 74 - t * 22 + Math.sin(t * TAU * 5.1) * 8 + (laneNoise - .5) * 9;
        const bandHue = debris ? 34 + rng() * 18 : hue - 18 + rng() * 14;
        const bandSat = debris ? 8 + rng() * 14 : (solid ? 26 + rng() * 18 : 38);
        const bandLight = debris ? 22 + rng() * 22 : light;
        const baseAlpha = (solid ? (debris ? .34 : .3) : .36) * dusty * (laneNoise < .18 ? 1.8 : 1);
        // Shade-graded band colour: full colour lit, desaturating and darkening toward
        // near-black in the umbra core.
        const styleFor = (shade) => shade >= .99
          ? `hsla(${bandHue}, ${bandSat}%, ${bandLight}%, ${baseAlpha})`
          : `hsla(${bandHue}, ${Math.round(bandSat * (.35 + .65 * shade))}%, ${Math.max(3, Math.round(bandLight * shade))}%, ${baseAlpha})`;
        ctx.lineWidth = clamp(r * (solid ? (debris ? (.0042 + rng() * .007) : (.0038 + rng() * .006)) : .014), 1.05, solid ? 4.4 : 3.8);
        // strokeStyle can't vary within one stroke, so the shade is quantised into a few
        // levels and the current run is flushed whenever the level changes (as well as at
        // gaps and the front/back split).
        let drawing = false, curLevel = -1, prevOffset = null, prevVisible = false;
        const beginRun = (p, level) => {
          curLevel = level;
          ctx.strokeStyle = styleFor(level / 15);
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.moveTo(p.x, p.y);
          drawing = true;
        };
        for (let i = 0; i <= segs; i++) {
          const a = (i / segs) * TAU;
          const gap = debris && Math.abs(Math.atan2(Math.sin(a - gapC), Math.cos(a - gapC))) < .018 + rng() * .01;
          const ragged = debris ? 1 + Math.sin(a * (7 + b) + t * 11) * .018 + Math.sin(a * 19 + b) * .012 : 1;
          const offset = add(scale(u, Math.cos(a) * rr * ragged), scale(v, Math.sin(a) * rr * ragged));
          if (gap) {
            if (drawing) { ctx.stroke(); drawing = false; }
            prevOffset = null;
            prevVisible = false;
            continue;
          }
          const visible = ringHalfVisible(offset, viewDir, front);
          const level = Math.round((solid ? ringShade(offset, sunDir, o.r) : 1) * 15);
          if (prevOffset && visible !== prevVisible) {
            const split = ringSplitOffset(prevOffset, offset, viewDir);
            const sp = split ? project(cameraTransform(add(o.pos, split), game.camera), w, h) : null;
            if (sp) {
              if (prevVisible && drawing) {
                ctx.lineTo(sp.x, sp.y);
                ctx.stroke();
                drawing = false;
              } else if (!prevVisible && visible) {
                beginRun(sp, level);
              }
            } else if (prevVisible && drawing) {
              ctx.stroke();
              drawing = false;
            }
          }
          const p = visible ? project(cameraTransform(add(o.pos, offset), game.camera), w, h) : null;
          if (!p) {
            if (drawing && visible) { ctx.stroke(); drawing = false; }
            prevOffset = offset;
            prevVisible = visible;
            continue;
          }
          drawnSegments++;
          if (drawing && level !== curLevel) {
            ctx.lineTo(p.x, p.y);
            ctx.stroke();
            drawing = false;
          }
          if (!drawing) {
            beginRun(p, level);
          } else {
            ctx.lineTo(p.x, p.y);
          }
          prevOffset = offset;
          prevVisible = visible;
        }
        if (drawing) ctx.stroke();
      }
      ctx.restore();
      if (front === true && drawnSegments < bands * 8) {
        drawPlanetRingFallback(o, r, hue, w, h, u, v, solid, debris);
      }
      if (debris && solid) drawPlanetDebris(o, r, w, h, front, u, v);
      if (solid && front === false) {
        ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(0,0,0,.12)";
        ctx.lineWidth = clamp(r * .01, .8, 2.8);
        ctx.beginPath();
        let drawing = false;
        for (let i = 0; i <= segs; i++) {
          const a = (i / segs) * TAU;
          const offset = add(
            scale(u, Math.cos(a) * o.r * o.ringInner * 1.04),
            scale(v, Math.sin(a) * o.r * o.ringInner * 1.04)
          );
          if (!ringHalfVisible(offset, viewDir, false)) { drawing = false; continue; }
          const p = project(cameraTransform(add(o.pos, offset), game.camera), w, h);
          if (!p) { drawing = false; continue; }
          if (drawing) ctx.lineTo(p.x, p.y);
          else { ctx.moveTo(p.x, p.y); drawing = true; }
        }
        ctx.stroke();
      }
    }

    function drawPlanetRingFallback(o, r, hue, w, h, u, v, solid, debris) {
      const rng = mulberry((o.textureSeed || 1) ^ 0x515afe);
      const bands = debris ? 12 : 8;
      const segs = 160;
      ctx.save();
      ctx.lineCap = "butt";
      for (let b = 0; b < bands; b++) {
        const t = bands === 1 ? 0 : b / (bands - 1);
        const rr = lerp(o.r * o.ringInner, o.r * o.ringOuter, t);
        ctx.strokeStyle = `hsla(${debris ? 38 : hue - 12 + rng() * 10}, ${debris ? 16 : 34}%, ${debris ? 42 : 68 - t * 18}%, ${solid ? .11 : .18})`;
        ctx.lineWidth = clamp(r * (debris ? .004 : .0032), .8, 2.4);
        ctx.beginPath();
        let drawing = false;
        for (let i = 0; i <= segs; i++) {
          const a = i / segs * TAU;
          const offset = add(scale(u, Math.cos(a) * rr), scale(v, Math.sin(a) * rr));
          const p = project(cameraTransform(add(o.pos, offset), game.camera), w, h);
          if (!p) {
            if (drawing) { ctx.stroke(); drawing = false; }
            continue;
          }
          if (!drawing) {
            ctx.moveTo(p.x, p.y);
            drawing = true;
          } else {
            ctx.lineTo(p.x, p.y);
          }
        }
        if (drawing) ctx.stroke();
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawPlanetDebris(o, r, w, h, front, u, v) {
      if (!o.debrisField) return;
      const rng = mulberry((o.textureSeed || 1) ^ 0xdebb15);
      const viewDir = norm(sub(game.camera.pos, o.pos));
      const sun = game.objects.find((s) => s.type === "sun");
      const sunDir = sun ? norm(sub(sun.pos, o.pos)) : null;
      const count = 46;
      for (let i = 0; i < count; i++) {
        const a = rng() * TAU + (o.rot || 0) * (.08 + (i % 5) * .006);
        const lane = rng();
        const rr = lerp(o.r * o.ringInner * .92, o.r * o.ringOuter * 1.18, lane);
        const height = (rng() - .5) * o.r * .16;
        const normal = norm(cross(u, v));
        const offset = add(add(scale(u, Math.cos(a) * rr), scale(v, Math.sin(a) * rr)), scale(normal, height));
        const isFront = dot(offset, viewDir) >= 0;
        if (!ringHalfVisible(offset, viewDir, front)) continue;
        const p = project(cameraTransform(add(o.pos, offset), game.camera), w, h);
        if (!p) continue;
        const shadeMul = ringShade(offset, sunDir, o.r);
        const size = clamp(r * (.006 + rng() * .014), .7, Math.max(1.4, r * .035));
        const alpha = clamp(.16 + rng() * .45, .12, .58) * (isFront ? 1 : .72);
        const gold = rng() < .18;
        const cr = Math.round((gold ? 180 : 125) * shadeMul);
        const cg = Math.round((gold ? 155 : 130) * shadeMul);
        const cb = Math.round((gold ? 105 : 124) * shadeMul);
        ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(${cr},${cg},${cb},${alpha})`;
        ctx.beginPath();
        if (rng() < .55) {
          ctx.rect(p.x - size * .7, p.y - size * .35, size * 1.4, size * .7);
        } else {
          ctx.moveTo(p.x, p.y - size);
          ctx.lineTo(p.x + size * .9, p.y + size * .45);
          ctx.lineTo(p.x - size * .8, p.y + size * .65);
          ctx.closePath();
        }
        ctx.fill();
      }
    }

    function tangentBasisFor(dir) {
      let u = cross(Math.abs(dir.y) > .9 ? vec(1, 0, 0) : vec(0, 1, 0), dir);
      u = norm(u);
      return { u, v: norm(cross(dir, u)) };
    }

    function makeContinent(rng, center, radius, points) {
      const { u, v } = tangentBasisFor(center);
      const outline = [];
      for (let i = 0; i < points; i++) {
        const a = i / points * TAU;
        const rr = radius * (.58 + rng() * .52);
        const wobble = 1 + Math.sin(a * (2 + Math.floor(rng() * 3)) + rng() * TAU) * (.12 + rng() * .18);
        outline.push(norm(add(center, add(scale(u, Math.cos(a) * rr * wobble), scale(v, Math.sin(a) * rr * wobble)))));
      }
      return outline;
    }

    function planetGeography(o) {
      if (o._geography) return o._geography;
      const rng = mulberry(o.textureSeed || 1);
      const biome = o.biome || "ocean";
      const continentCount = biome === "desert" ? 4 : biome === "industrial" ? 5 : biome === "ice" ? 5 : biome === "venus" ? 4 : 6;
      const continents = [];
      for (let i = 0; i < continentCount; i++) {
        const theta = rng() * TAU;
        const lat = (rng() - .5) * (biome === "ocean" ? 1.75 : biome === "ice" ? 2.15 : biome === "venus" ? 1.25 : 1.35);
        const center = norm(vec(Math.cos(lat) * Math.cos(theta), Math.sin(lat), Math.cos(lat) * Math.sin(theta)));
        const radius = (biome === "ocean" ? .22 : biome === "ice" ? .18 : biome === "venus" ? .24 : .28) + rng() * (biome === "ocean" ? .22 : biome === "ice" ? .24 : biome === "venus" ? .24 : .3);
        const terrain = [];
        const { u, v } = tangentBasisFor(center);
        const terrainCount = biome === "industrial" ? 8 : biome === "desert" ? 14 : biome === "ice" ? 22 : biome === "venus" ? 10 : 16;
        for (let j = 0; j < terrainCount; j++) {
          const a = rng() * TAU;
          const d = Math.pow(rng(), .58) * radius * .68;
          terrain.push({
            center: norm(add(center, add(scale(u, Math.cos(a) * d), scale(v, Math.sin(a) * d)))),
            rx: radius * (biome === "ice" ? (.04 + rng() * .08) : (.028 + rng() * .055)),
            ry: radius * (biome === "ice" ? (.006 + rng() * .018) : (.008 + rng() * .025)),
            angle: rng() * TAU,
            s: .45 + rng() * .75
          });
        }
        continents.push({
          center,
          radius,
          outline: makeContinent(rng, center, radius, 16 + Math.floor(rng() * 10)),
          hueShift: rng() * 22 - 11,
          lightShift: rng() * 12 - 6,
          terrain
        });
      }
      const islands = [];
      const islandCount = biome === "ocean" ? 16 : biome === "ice" ? 12 : biome === "venus" ? 6 : 8;
      for (let i = 0; i < islandCount; i++) {
        const theta = rng() * TAU;
        const lat = (rng() - .5) * 2.25;
        const center = norm(vec(Math.cos(lat) * Math.cos(theta), Math.sin(lat), Math.cos(lat) * Math.sin(theta)));
        islands.push(makeContinent(rng, center, .035 + rng() * .055, 7 + Math.floor(rng() * 5)));
      }
      const clouds = [];
      const cloudCount = biome === "gas" ? 0 : biome === "venus" ? 15 : biome === "desert" ? 12 : biome === "rocky" ? 7 : biome === "ice" ? 11 : biome === "industrial" ? 13 : 18;
      for (let i = 0; i < cloudCount; i++) {
        const theta = rng() * TAU;
        const lat = (rng() - .5) * (biome === "ocean" ? 1.9 : 1.55);
        clouds.push({
          center: norm(vec(Math.cos(lat) * Math.cos(theta), Math.sin(lat), Math.cos(lat) * Math.sin(theta))),
          width: (biome === "ocean" ? .2 : biome === "venus" ? .28 : .14) + rng() * (biome === "ocean" ? .36 : biome === "venus" ? .34 : .26),
          height: (biome === "venus" ? .012 : .018) + rng() * (biome === "venus" ? .024 : .038),
          angle: rng() * TAU,
          alpha: (biome === "desert" ? .12 : biome === "ice" ? .13 : biome === "venus" ? .2 : .16) + rng() * .18,
          arms: 2 + Math.floor(rng() * 3),
          twist: (rng() > .5 ? 1 : -1) * (1.7 + rng() * 1.7),
          streaks: 3 + Math.floor(rng() * 5),
          seed: Math.floor(rng() * 0xfffffff)
        });
      }
      const craters = [];
      const craterCount = biome === "rocky" ? 44 : biome === "desert" ? 16 : biome === "ice" ? 10 : 0;
      for (let i = 0; i < craterCount; i++) {
        const theta = rng() * TAU;
        const lat = (rng() - .5) * 2.4;
        const radius = .025 + rng() * (biome === "rocky" ? .095 : biome === "ice" ? .045 : .055);
        craters.push({
          center: norm(vec(Math.cos(lat) * Math.cos(theta), Math.sin(lat), Math.cos(lat) * Math.sin(theta))),
          radius,
          angle: rng() * TAU,
          squash: .62 + rng() * .3,
          rimLight: (biome === "rocky" ? .18 : .1) + rng() * .16,
          floorShade: (biome === "rocky" ? .22 : .12) + rng() * .22,
          ejecta: rng() < (biome === "rocky" ? .78 : .32),
          centralPeak: rng() < (biome === "rocky" ? .42 : .18),
          alpha: (biome === "rocky" ? .34 : .22) + rng() * .32
        });
      }
      const industry = [];
      if (biome === "industrial") {
        for (let i = 0; i < 18; i++) {
          const theta = rng() * TAU;
          const lat = (rng() - .5) * 1.8;
          industry.push({
            center: norm(vec(Math.cos(lat) * Math.cos(theta), Math.sin(lat), Math.cos(lat) * Math.sin(theta))),
            width: .045 + rng() * .1,
            height: .018 + rng() * .05,
            angle: rng() * TAU
          });
        }
      }
      // Night-side population centres, density by biome (gas giants get none).
      const cities = [];
      const cityCount = biome === "industrial" ? 64 : biome === "ocean" ? 30 : biome === "desert" ? 16 : biome === "rocky" ? 7 : 0;
      for (let i = 0; i < cityCount; i++) {
        const theta = rng() * TAU;
        const lat = (rng() - .5) * 1.9;
        const dir = norm(vec(Math.cos(lat) * Math.cos(theta), Math.sin(lat), Math.cos(lat) * Math.sin(theta)));
        const { u, v } = tangentBasisFor(dir);
        const dotCount = biome === "industrial" ? 9 + Math.floor(rng() * 18) : biome === "ocean" ? 5 + Math.floor(rng() * 11) : 3 + Math.floor(rng() * 7);
        const spread = biome === "industrial" ? .018 + rng() * .038 : .012 + rng() * .026;
        const dots = [];
        for (let d = 0; d < dotCount; d++) {
          const a = rng() * TAU;
          const rr = Math.pow(rng(), .65) * spread;
          dots.push({
            dir: norm(add(dir, add(scale(u, Math.cos(a) * rr), scale(v, Math.sin(a) * rr)))),
            s: .45 + rng() * .85
          });
        }
        cities.push({ dir, s: .45 + rng() * .55, dots });
      }
      o._geography = { continents, islands, clouds, craters, industry, cities, stormPhase: rng() * TAU };
      return o._geography;
    }

    function projectSurfacePoint(o, q, dir, viewDir, w, h) {
      const worldDir = quatRotate(q, dir);
      const facing = dot(worldDir, viewDir);
      if (facing <= .015) return null;
      const p = project(cameraTransform(add(o.pos, scale(worldDir, o.r)), game.camera), w, h);
      return p ? { ...p, facing, worldDir } : null;
    }

    function planetSurfaceClearance(o, cam = null) {
      return (finiteVec3(cam) ? len(cam) : len(sub(game.camera.pos, o.pos))) - o.r;
    }

    function planetSurfaceDetailAlpha(o, cam = null) {
      const clearance = planetSurfaceClearance(o, cam);
      return clamp((clearance - o.r * .08) / Math.max(1, o.r * .22), 0, 1);
    }

    function drawProjectedPatch(points, fillStyle) {
      if (points.length < 3) return;
      ctx.fillStyle = fillStyle;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(points[0].x, points[0].y);
      for (let i = 1; i < points.length; i++) ctx.lineTo(points[i].x, points[i].y);
      ctx.closePath();
      ctx.fill();
    }

    // Planet surface rule: every cloud, crater, band, cap, city, or painted detail must
    // be stored as local sphere directions and then projected. Do not draw surface
    // features with screen-space ctx.ellipse/linear bands; those rotate with ship roll
    // and drift away from the planet's real 3D orientation.
    function surfaceEllipseDirs(center, rx, ry, angle = 0, segments = 18) {
      const { u, v } = tangentBasisFor(center);
      const ca = Math.cos(angle), sa = Math.sin(angle);
      const dirs = [];
      for (let i = 0; i < segments; i++) {
        const a = i / segments * TAU;
        const ex = Math.cos(a) * rx;
        const ey = Math.sin(a) * ry;
        dirs.push(norm(add(center, add(
          scale(u, ex * ca - ey * sa),
          scale(v, ex * sa + ey * ca)
        ))));
      }
      return dirs;
    }

    function projectedSurfacePatch(o, q, dirs, viewDir, w, h, minVisible = .55) {
      const pts = dirs.map((d) => projectSurfacePoint(o, q, d, viewDir, w, h)).filter(Boolean);
      return pts.length >= dirs.length * minVisible ? pts : null;
    }

    function strokeProjectedPatch(points, strokeStyle, lineWidth) {
      if (!points || points.length < 3) return;
      ctx.strokeStyle = strokeStyle;
      ctx.lineWidth = lineWidth;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(points[0].x, points[0].y);
      for (let i = 1; i < points.length; i++) ctx.lineTo(points[i].x, points[i].y);
      ctx.closePath();
      ctx.stroke();
    }

    function planetLandStyle(o, dir, lightShift = 0, hueShift = 0, sunFacing = 0, alpha = .86) {
      const biome = o.biome || "ocean";
      const lat = Math.abs(dir.y);
      const sunLift = sunFacing * 10 + lightShift;
      if (biome === "industrial") {
        const l = clamp(17 + lat * 9 + sunLift * .55, 8, 36);
        return `hsla(${48 + hueShift * .25}, 18%, ${l}%, ${alpha})`;
      }
      if (biome === "desert") {
        const polar = smoothstep(.68, .92, lat);
        const l = clamp(52 + polar * 18 + sunLift * .6, 24, 76);
        const h = lerp(35, 208, polar) + hueShift * .16;
        const s = lerp(58, 10, polar);
        const iceL = lerp(l, 86, polar);
        return `hsla(${h}, ${s}%, ${iceL}%, ${alpha})`;
      }
      if (biome === "rocky") {
        const polar = smoothstep(.74, .95, lat);
        const l = clamp(33 + polar * 22 + sunLift * .65, 16, 68);
        return `hsla(${34 + hueShift * .18}, ${lerp(24, 12, polar)}%, ${l}%, ${alpha})`;
      }
      if (biome === "ice") {
        const rock = smoothstep(.18, .62, 1 - lat);
        const l = clamp(76 - rock * 24 + sunLift * .55, 34, 88);
        return `hsla(${lerp(204, 32, rock) + hueShift * .12}, ${lerp(18, 20, rock)}%, ${l}%, ${alpha})`;
      }
      if (biome === "venus") {
        const upland = smoothstep(.32, .75, lat);
        const h = lerp(38, 28, upland) + hueShift * .12;
        const s = lerp(42, 24, upland);
        const l = clamp(43 - upland * 13 + sunLift * .45, 18, 58);
        return `hsla(${h}, ${s}%, ${l}%, ${alpha * .72})`;
      }
      const polar = smoothstep(.74, .94, lat);
      const equatorDesert = 1 - smoothstep(.16, .34, lat);
      const boreal = smoothstep(.42, .7, lat) * (1 - polar);
      const h = equatorDesert > .45 ? lerp(92, 38, equatorDesert) : lerp(112, 96, boreal);
      const s = equatorDesert > .45 ? lerp(44, 55, equatorDesert) : lerp(46, 34, boreal);
      const baseL = equatorDesert > .45 ? lerp(40, 56, equatorDesert) : lerp(38, 24, boreal);
      const iceL = lerp(baseL, 84, polar);
      return `hsla(${h + hueShift * .22}, ${lerp(s, 12, polar)}%, ${clamp(iceL + sunLift, 12, 88)}%, ${alpha})`;
    }

    function planetTerrainStyle(o, dir, strength, sunFacing) {
      const biome = o.biome || "ocean";
      const lat = Math.abs(dir.y);
      const shade = clamp(.45 + sunFacing * .45, .12, 1);
      if (biome === "industrial") return `rgba(5,7,6,${.16 * strength * shade})`;
      if (biome === "desert") return lat > .66
        ? `rgba(235,232,210,${.14 * strength * shade})`
        : `rgba(118,83,43,${.13 * strength * shade})`;
      if (biome === "rocky") return `rgba(58,50,43,${.16 * strength * shade})`;
      if (biome === "ice") return lat > .58
        ? `rgba(250,255,255,${.16 * strength * shade})`
        : `rgba(70,78,82,${.2 * strength * shade})`;
      if (biome === "venus") return `rgba(82,59,35,${.11 * strength * shade})`;
      if (lat > .74) return `rgba(245,250,246,${.22 * strength * shade})`;
      if (lat > .42) return `rgba(18,42,24,${.19 * strength * shade})`;
      if (lat < .28) return `rgba(164,116,58,${.13 * strength * shade})`;
      return `rgba(20,72,34,${.12 * strength * shade})`;
    }

    function drawProjectedCloud(o, q, cloud, cp, viewDir, sunDir, w, h, r) {
      const rng = mulberry((cloud.seed || 1) ^ 0xc10dd);
      const { u, v } = tangentBasisFor(cloud.center);
      const sunFacing = dot(cp.worldDir, sunDir);
      const baseAlpha = cloud.alpha * clamp(.45 + sunFacing * .45, .15, 1) * cp.facing;
      if (baseAlpha <= .01 || r * cloud.width * cp.facing < 2) return;
      const arms = cloud.arms || 2;
      const steps = performanceLod() > 1 ? 7 : 11;

      for (let arm = 0; arm < arms; arm++) {
        for (let i = 0; i < steps; i++) {
          const t = i / (steps - 1);
          const curl = cloud.angle + arm / arms * TAU + t * cloud.twist * TAU;
          const radial = cloud.width * (.06 + t * .58) * (.82 + rng() * .28);
          const lateral = cloud.height * (1.1 + t * 2.25);
          const puffCenter = norm(add(cloud.center, add(
            scale(u, Math.cos(curl) * radial),
            scale(v, Math.sin(curl) * lateral)
          )));
          const puff = projectedSurfacePatch(o, q, surfaceEllipseDirs(
            puffCenter,
            cloud.width * (.045 + (1 - t) * .06) * (1 + rng() * .35),
            cloud.height * (.58 + (1 - t) * .62) * (1 + rng() * .35),
            curl + Math.PI / 2,
            12
          ), viewDir, w, h, .38);
          if (!puff) continue;
          drawProjectedPatch(puff, `rgba(255,255,255,${baseAlpha * (.14 + (1 - t) * .16)})`);
        }
      }

      const streaks = performanceLod() > 1 ? Math.min(3, cloud.streaks || 3) : (cloud.streaks || 4);
      for (let i = 0; i < streaks; i++) {
        const t = (i + .5) / streaks;
        const curl = cloud.angle + t * cloud.twist * TAU * .72 + (rng() - .5) * .45;
        const streakCenter = norm(add(cloud.center, add(
          scale(u, Math.cos(curl) * cloud.width * (.15 + t * .38)),
          scale(v, Math.sin(curl) * cloud.height * (1.8 + t * 2.4))
        )));
        const streak = projectedSurfacePatch(o, q, surfaceEllipseDirs(
          streakCenter,
          cloud.width * (.18 + rng() * .18),
          cloud.height * (.06 + rng() * .05),
          curl,
          14
        ), viewDir, w, h, .32);
        if (streak) drawProjectedPatch(streak, `rgba(255,255,255,${baseAlpha * (.08 + rng() * .08)})`);
      }

      for (let i = 0; i < 6; i++) {
        const a = rng() * TAU;
        const d = Math.pow(rng(), .7) * cloud.width * .18;
        const coreCenter = norm(add(cloud.center, add(scale(u, Math.cos(a) * d), scale(v, Math.sin(a) * d * .65))));
        const core = projectedSurfacePatch(o, q, surfaceEllipseDirs(
          coreCenter,
          cloud.width * (.07 + rng() * .05),
          cloud.height * (.8 + rng() * .8),
          cloud.angle + rng() * .7,
          12
        ), viewDir, w, h, .4);
        if (core) drawProjectedPatch(core, `rgba(255,255,255,${baseAlpha * (.28 + rng() * .18)})`);
      }
    }

    function drawProjectedCrater(o, q, crater, cp, viewDir, sunDir, w, h, r) {
      const cr = r * crater.radius * cp.facing;
      if (cr < .7) return;
      const angle = crater.angle || 0;
      const squash = crater.squash || .72;
      const sunFacing = clamp(dot(cp.worldDir, sunDir) * .5 + .5, 0, 1);
      const alpha = crater.alpha * cp.facing;
      const { u, v } = tangentBasisFor(crater.center);

      if (crater.ejecta && cr > 2.2) {
        for (let i = 0; i < 7; i++) {
          const a = angle + i / 7 * TAU;
          const streakCenter = norm(add(crater.center, add(
            scale(u, Math.cos(a) * crater.radius * .72),
            scale(v, Math.sin(a) * crater.radius * .48)
          )));
          const streak = projectedSurfacePatch(o, q, surfaceEllipseDirs(
            streakCenter,
            crater.radius * (.8 + (i % 3) * .18),
            crater.radius * .055,
            a,
            10
          ), viewDir, w, h, .32);
          if (streak) drawProjectedPatch(streak, `rgba(214,204,186,${alpha * .055})`);
        }
      }

      const outer = projectedSurfacePatch(o, q, surfaceEllipseDirs(
        crater.center,
        crater.radius * 1.34,
        crater.radius * squash * 1.02,
        angle,
        24
      ), viewDir, w, h, .42);
      if (outer) drawProjectedPatch(outer, `rgba(235,224,202,${alpha * crater.rimLight * (.45 + sunFacing * .65)})`);

      const floor = projectedSurfacePatch(o, q, surfaceEllipseDirs(
        crater.center,
        crater.radius * .98,
        crater.radius * squash * .72,
        angle,
        24
      ), viewDir, w, h, .42);
      if (floor) drawProjectedPatch(floor, `rgba(18,17,16,${alpha * crater.floorShade * (1.05 - sunFacing * .35)})`);

      const gullyCount = performanceLod() > 1 ? 5 : 10;
      for (let i = 0; i < gullyCount; i++) {
        const a = angle + i / gullyCount * TAU + (i % 2 ? .08 : -.05);
        const mid = norm(add(crater.center, add(
          scale(u, Math.cos(a) * crater.radius * (.46 + (i % 3) * .08)),
          scale(v, Math.sin(a) * crater.radius * squash * (.42 + (i % 4) * .06))
        )));
        const gully = projectedSurfacePatch(o, q, surfaceEllipseDirs(
          mid,
          crater.radius * (.32 + (i % 3) * .08),
          crater.radius * .018,
          a,
          8
        ), viewDir, w, h, .3);
        if (gully) drawProjectedPatch(gully, `rgba(7,8,9,${alpha * .11 * (1.12 - sunFacing * .45)})`);
      }

      const shadowCenter = norm(add(crater.center, add(
        scale(u, Math.cos(angle + .18) * crater.radius * .2),
        scale(v, Math.sin(angle + .18) * crater.radius * .12)
      )));
      const shadow = projectedSurfacePatch(o, q, surfaceEllipseDirs(
        shadowCenter,
        crater.radius * .74,
        crater.radius * squash * .36,
        angle + .12,
        18
      ), viewDir, w, h, .38);
      if (shadow) drawProjectedPatch(shadow, `rgba(4,4,5,${alpha * .22 * (1.08 - sunFacing * .45)})`);

      const rim = projectedSurfacePatch(o, q, surfaceEllipseDirs(
        crater.center,
        crater.radius * 1.16,
        crater.radius * squash * .88,
        angle,
        26
      ), viewDir, w, h, .42);
      strokeProjectedPatch(rim, `rgba(35,31,27,${alpha * .86})`, Math.max(.55, cr * .13));
      strokeProjectedPatch(rim, `rgba(236,226,205,${alpha * .28 * sunFacing})`, Math.max(.35, cr * .045));

      if (crater.centralPeak && cr > 4) {
        const peak = projectedSurfacePatch(o, q, surfaceEllipseDirs(
          crater.center,
          crater.radius * .18,
          crater.radius * .08,
          angle + .4,
          9
        ), viewDir, w, h, .34);
        if (peak) drawProjectedPatch(peak, `rgba(210,200,178,${alpha * .18 * (.4 + sunFacing)})`);
      }
    }

    function drawPlanetSurface(o, pr, r, w, h) {
      const rng = mulberry(o.textureSeed || 1);
      const axis = o.rotAxis || vec(0, 1, 0);
      const q = quatFromAxisAngle(axis, o.rot || 0);
      const viewDir = norm(sub(game.camera.pos, o.pos));
      const sun = game.objects.find((s) => s.type === "sun");
      const sunDir = sun ? norm(sub(sun.pos, o.pos)) : viewDir;
      const biome = o.biome || "ocean";
      const geo = planetGeography(o);
      if (biome === "gas") {
        drawGasGiantSurface(o, pr, r, geo, q, viewDir, w, h);
        return;
      }
      for (const c of geo.continents) {
        const pts = c.outline.map((d) => projectSurfacePoint(o, q, d, viewDir, w, h)).filter(Boolean);
        if (pts.length < c.outline.length * .72) continue;
        const avgDir = norm(c.outline.reduce((sum, d) => add(sum, quatRotate(q, d)), vec()));
        const sunFacing = dot(avgDir, sunDir);
        drawProjectedPatch(pts, planetLandStyle(o, avgDir, c.lightShift, c.hueShift, sunFacing, .86));
        if (planetSurfaceDetailAlpha(o) > .32 && (performanceLod() < 2 || r > 145)) {
          for (const spot of c.terrain || []) {
            const sp = projectSurfacePoint(o, q, spot.center, viewDir, w, h);
            if (!sp) continue;
            const patch = projectedSurfacePatch(o, q, surfaceEllipseDirs(spot.center, spot.rx, spot.ry, spot.angle, 9), viewDir, w, h, .34);
            if (!patch) continue;
            drawProjectedPatch(patch, planetTerrainStyle(o, sp.worldDir, spot.s, dot(sp.worldDir, sunDir)));
          }
        }
      }
      for (const island of geo.islands) {
        const pts = island.map((d) => projectSurfacePoint(o, q, d, viewDir, w, h)).filter(Boolean);
        if (pts.length < island.length * .7) continue;
        const avgDir = norm(island.reduce((sum, d) => add(sum, quatRotate(q, d)), vec()));
        drawProjectedPatch(pts, planetLandStyle(o, avgDir, rng() * 8 - 4, rng() * 8 - 4, dot(avgDir, sunDir), .78));
      }
      for (const crater of geo.craters) {
        const cp = projectSurfacePoint(o, q, crater.center, viewDir, w, h);
        if (!cp) continue;
        drawProjectedCrater(o, q, crater, cp, viewDir, sunDir, w, h, r);
      }
      for (const zone of geo.industry) {
        const zp = projectSurfacePoint(o, q, zone.center, viewDir, w, h);
        if (!zp) continue;
        const patch = projectedSurfacePatch(o, q, surfaceEllipseDirs(zone.center, zone.width, zone.height, zone.angle, 14), viewDir, w, h, .5);
        if (patch) drawProjectedPatch(patch, `rgba(8,10,9,${.54 * zp.facing})`);
        // Night-side city glow is handled separately (drawPlanetNightLights), drawn on
        // top of the terminator shadow so it reads against the dark side.
      }
      for (const pole of [vec(0, 1, 0), vec(0, -1, 0)]) {
        const pp = projectSurfacePoint(o, q, pole, viewDir, w, h);
        if (!pp) continue;
        const polarScale = biome === "ice" ? .38 : biome === "desert" ? .3 : .22;
        const capR = r * (polarScale + Math.abs(pp.worldDir.y) * .08) * pp.facing;
        if (capR < 1) continue;
        const cap = projectedSurfacePatch(o, q, surfaceEllipseDirs(pole, polarScale, biome === "ice" ? .11 : .08, 0, 24), viewDir, w, h, .38);
        if (cap) drawProjectedPatch(cap, `rgba(242,250,248,${(biome === "ice" ? .72 : .62) * pp.facing})`);
      }
      if (biome === "venus") drawVenusWeatherSurface(o, pr, r, geo, q, viewDir, w, h);
      for (const cloud of geo.clouds) {
        const cp = projectSurfacePoint(o, q, cloud.center, viewDir, w, h);
        if (!cp) continue;
        drawProjectedCloud(o, q, cloud, cp, viewDir, sunDir, w, h, r);
      }
    }

    function gasBandDirs(lat0, lat1, phase, segments = 72) {
      const upper = [], lower = [];
      for (let i = 0; i <= segments; i++) {
        const lon = i / segments * TAU;
        const wobble = Math.sin(lon * 2.4 + phase) * .018 + Math.sin(lon * 5.1 + phase * .7) * .006;
        const make = (lat) => vec(Math.cos(lat) * Math.cos(lon), Math.sin(lat), Math.cos(lat) * Math.sin(lon));
        upper.push(norm(make(lat0 + wobble)));
        lower.unshift(norm(make(lat1 + wobble * .8)));
      }
      return upper.concat(lower);
    }

    function gasBandPoint(lat, lon, phase, wobbleMul = 1) {
      const wobble = (Math.sin(lon * 2.4 + phase) * .018 + Math.sin(lon * 5.1 + phase * .7) * .006) * wobbleMul;
      return norm(vec(Math.cos(lat + wobble) * Math.cos(lon), Math.sin(lat + wobble), Math.cos(lat + wobble) * Math.sin(lon)));
    }

    function drawGasBandSegments(o, q, lat0, lat1, phase, segments, fillStyle, viewDir, w, h) {
      for (let i = 0; i < segments; i++) {
        const lon0 = i / segments * TAU;
        const lon1 = (i + 1) / segments * TAU;
        const dirs = [
          gasBandPoint(lat0, lon0, phase),
          gasBandPoint(lat0, lon1, phase),
          gasBandPoint(lat1, lon1, phase, .8),
          gasBandPoint(lat1, lon0, phase, .8)
        ];
        const pts = dirs.map((d) => projectSurfacePoint(o, q, d, viewDir, w, h));
        if (pts.some((p) => !p)) continue;
        drawProjectedPatch(pts, fillStyle);
      }
    }

    function drawVenusWeatherSurface(o, pr, r, geo, q, viewDir, w, h) {
      const rng = mulberry((o.textureSeed || 1) ^ 0x7e005);
      const hue = o.hue ?? 42;
      const bands = performanceLod() > 1 ? 7 : 10;
      for (let i = 0; i < bands; i++) {
        const lat0 = Math.asin(1 - i * 2 / bands);
        const lat1 = Math.asin(1 - (i + 1) * 2 / bands);
        const phase = geo.stormPhase + i * 1.3 + (o.rot || 0) * .18;
        const light = clamp((o.light || 50) + (i % 2 ? 12 : -5) + rng() * 7, 28, 76);
        drawGasBandSegments(o, q, lat0, lat1, phase, 46, `hsla(${hue + (i % 2 ? 8 : -5)}, ${46 + rng() * 18}%, ${light}%, .34)`, viewDir, w, h);
      }
      for (let i = 0; i < 7; i++) {
        const lat = lerp(.72, -.72, i / 6);
        drawGasBandSegments(o, q, lat + .006, lat - .006, geo.stormPhase + i * .7, 58, `rgba(255,224,154,${.08 + rng() * .08})`, viewDir, w, h);
      }
    }

    function drawGasGiantSurface(o, pr, r, geo, q, viewDir, w, h) {
      const rng = mulberry((o.textureSeed || 1) ^ 0x9e3779b9);
      const hue = o.hue ?? 32;
      const bands = 10;
      for (let i = 0; i < bands; i++) {
        const lat0 = Math.asin(1 - i * 2 / bands);
        const lat1 = Math.asin(1 - (i + 1) * 2 / bands);
        const sat = clamp((o.sat || 50) + (i % 2 ? 10 : -8), 18, 80);
        const light = clamp((o.light || 54) + (i % 3 - 1) * 9 + rng() * 8, 18, 82);
        drawGasBandSegments(o, q, lat0, lat1, geo.stormPhase + i * 1.7 + (o.rot || 0) * .22, 58, `hsla(${hue + (i % 2 ? 10 : -8)}, ${sat}%, ${light}%, .92)`, viewDir, w, h);
      }
      for (let i = 0; i < 6; i++) {
        const lat = lerp(.72, -.68, i / 5);
        drawGasBandSegments(o, q, lat + .008, lat - .008, geo.stormPhase + i, 64, `rgba(255,255,255,${.12 + rng() * .12})`, viewDir, w, h);
      }
      const stormCenter = norm(vec(Math.cos(.18) * Math.cos(geo.stormPhase + .9), Math.sin(.18), Math.cos(.18) * Math.sin(geo.stormPhase + .9)));
      const storm = projectedSurfacePatch(o, q, surfaceEllipseDirs(stormCenter, .2, .095, -.18, 22), viewDir, w, h, .35);
      if (storm) drawProjectedPatch(storm, "rgba(160,65,42,.58)");
      const stormRim = projectedSurfacePatch(o, q, surfaceEllipseDirs(stormCenter, .24, .12, -.18, 26), viewDir, w, h, .35);
      strokeProjectedPatch(stormRim, "rgba(255,218,180,.42)", Math.max(1, r * .015));
    }

    function planetBaseStops(o) {
      const hue = o.hue ?? 110, sat = o.sat ?? 45, light = o.light ?? 45;
      switch (o.biome || "ocean") {
        case "ocean":
          return [
            `hsl(${hue - 2}, ${sat + 8}%, ${clamp(light + 22, 32, 72)}%)`,
            `hsl(${hue}, ${sat}%, ${clamp(light, 18, 48)}%)`,
            `hsl(${hue + 10}, ${sat + 4}%, ${clamp(light - 20, 6, 30)}%)`
          ];
        case "industrial":
          return [
            `hsl(${hue + 10}, ${sat}%, ${clamp(light + 12, 16, 36)}%)`,
            `hsl(${hue + 16}, ${sat * .85}%, ${clamp(light - 1, 8, 24)}%)`,
            `hsl(${hue + 22}, ${sat * .65}%, ${clamp(light - 12, 3, 16)}%)`
          ];
        case "rocky":
          return [
            `hsl(${hue}, ${sat}%, ${clamp(light + 18, 32, 66)}%)`,
            `hsl(${hue + 8}, ${sat * .85}%, ${clamp(light, 18, 48)}%)`,
            `hsl(${hue - 8}, ${sat * .65}%, ${clamp(light - 16, 8, 30)}%)`
          ];
        case "ice":
          return [
            `hsl(${hue - 6}, ${sat + 8}%, ${clamp(light + 20, 68, 92)}%)`,
            `hsl(${hue}, ${sat}%, ${clamp(light, 46, 78)}%)`,
            `hsl(${hue + 18}, ${sat * .55}%, ${clamp(light - 22, 20, 48)}%)`
          ];
        case "venus":
          return [
            `hsl(${hue + 8}, ${sat + 8}%, ${clamp(light + 22, 54, 82)}%)`,
            `hsl(${hue}, ${sat}%, ${clamp(light, 32, 62)}%)`,
            `hsl(${hue - 10}, ${sat * .72}%, ${clamp(light - 22, 10, 34)}%)`
          ];
        case "gas":
          return [
            `hsl(${hue}, ${sat}%, ${clamp(light + 20, 44, 82)}%)`,
            `hsl(${hue + 8}, ${sat}%, ${clamp(light, 30, 68)}%)`,
            `hsl(${hue - 10}, ${sat * .82}%, ${clamp(light - 20, 16, 46)}%)`
          ];
        case "desert":
        default:
          return [
            `hsl(${hue + 2}, ${sat}%, ${clamp(light + 18, 46, 76)}%)`,
            `hsl(${hue}, ${sat}%, ${clamp(light, 30, 60)}%)`,
            `hsl(${hue - 10}, ${sat * .82}%, ${clamp(light - 18, 14, 38)}%)`
          ];
      }
    }

    // Population centres glowing on the night hemisphere, drawn over the terminator
    // shadow. Density/colour come from the biome (industrial = dense amber sprawl,
    // ocean = scattered coastal white-blue, rocky = a few sparse outposts).
    function drawPlanetNightLights(o, r, w, h, sunDir) {
      if (!sunDir || !ultraFxEnabled()) return;
      const biome = o.biome || "ocean";
      if (biome === "gas") return;
      const geo = planetGeography(o);
      if (!geo.cities.length) return;
      const q = quatFromAxisAngle(o.rotAxis || vec(0, 1, 0), o.rot || 0);
      const viewDir = norm(sub(game.camera.pos, o.pos));
      const warm = biome === "industrial" ? "255,196,92" : biome === "ocean" ? "186,214,255" : biome === "rocky" ? "255,222,150" : biome === "ice" ? "205,230,255" : "255,206,120";
      ctx.save();
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
      for (const city of geo.cities) {
        const wd = quatRotate(q, city.dir);
        const camFacing = dot(wd, viewDir);
        if (camFacing <= .04) continue;
        const night = -dot(wd, sunDir);      // >0 on the night side
        if (night <= .05) continue;
        const p = project(cameraTransform(add(o.pos, scale(wd, o.r)), game.camera), w, h);
        if (!p) continue;
        const intensity = clamp(night * 1.5, 0, 1) * clamp(camFacing * 1.6, 0, 1) * city.s;
        if (intensity < .03) continue;
        const haloR = Math.max(1.8, r * (biome === "industrial" ? .018 : .012)) * (.55 + intensity);
        const g = ctx.createRadialGradient(p.x, p.y, 0, p.x, p.y, haloR);
        g.addColorStop(0, `rgba(${warm},${.09 * intensity})`);
        g.addColorStop(.55, `rgba(${warm},${.035 * intensity})`);
        g.addColorStop(1, `rgba(${warm},0)`);
        ctx.fillStyle = g;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(p.x, p.y, haloR, 0, TAU);
        ctx.fill();
        for (const dotInfo of city.dots || [{ dir: city.dir, s: 1 }]) {
          const dw = quatRotate(q, dotInfo.dir);
          const dotFacing = dot(dw, viewDir);
          if (dotFacing <= .04) continue;
          const dotNight = -dot(dw, sunDir);
          if (dotNight <= .05) continue;
          const dp = project(cameraTransform(add(o.pos, scale(dw, o.r)), game.camera), w, h);
          if (!dp) continue;
          const dotI = clamp(dotNight * 1.55, 0, 1) * clamp(dotFacing * 1.9, 0, 1) * dotInfo.s * city.s;
          if (dotI < .04) continue;
          const dotR = clamp(r * (biome === "industrial" ? .0024 : .0019) * (.8 + dotInfo.s), .45, 2.2);
          ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(${warm},${clamp(.38 + dotI * .5, .25, .88)})`;
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.arc(dp.x, dp.y, dotR, 0, TAU);
          ctx.fill();
        }
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    // Atmospheric limb glow, coloured by planet type (industrial = yellow smog, ocean =
    // blue/white, desert = pale gold, gas = its own hue, rocky = thin dusty haze).
    function drawPlanetAtmosphere(o, pr, r) {
      if (!ultraFxEnabled()) return;
      const atm = {
        industrial: { h: 46, s: 72, l: 54, str: .28 },
        ocean: { h: 208, s: 64, l: 64, str: .32 },
        desert: { h: 44, s: 48, l: 68, str: .22 },
        rocky: { h: 30, s: 22, l: 58, str: .12 },
        ice: { h: 205, s: 52, l: 72, str: .22 },
        venus: { h: 43, s: 72, l: 66, str: .34 },
        gas: { h: o.hue ?? 32, s: 54, l: 60, str: .28 }
      }[o.biome || "ocean"] || { h: 208, s: 55, l: 64, str: .32 };
      ctx.save();
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
      const glow = ctx.createRadialGradient(pr.x, pr.y, r * .97, pr.x, pr.y, r * 1.085);
      glow.addColorStop(0, `hsla(${atm.h}, ${atm.s}%, ${atm.l}%, 0)`);
      glow.addColorStop(.58, `hsla(${atm.h}, ${atm.s}%, ${atm.l}%, ${.04 * atm.str})`);
      glow.addColorStop(.82, `hsla(${atm.h}, ${atm.s}%, ${atm.l}%, ${.32 * atm.str})`);
      glow.addColorStop(1, `hsla(${atm.h}, ${atm.s}%, ${atm.l}%, 0)`);
      ctx.fillStyle = glow;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, r * 1.085, 0, TAU);
      ctx.fill();
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawPlanetHaze(o, pr, r, lx, ly) {
      if (!ultraFxEnabled()) return;
      const haze = {
        industrial: { h: 48, s: 46, l: 48, a: .145 },
        ocean: { h: 204, s: 58, l: 74, a: .17 },
        desert: { h: 42, s: 54, l: 70, a: .18 },
        rocky: { h: 34, s: 24, l: 62, a: .105 },
        ice: { h: 204, s: 42, l: 82, a: .145 },
        venus: { h: 42, s: 68, l: 72, a: .235 },
        gas: { h: o.hue ?? 34, s: 48, l: 70, a: .105 }
      }[o.biome || "ocean"] || { h: 204, s: 55, l: 68, a: .09 };
      const g = ctx.createRadialGradient(
        pr.x + lx * r * .18, pr.y + ly * r * .18, r * .08,
        pr.x - lx * r * .18, pr.y - ly * r * .18, r * 1.02
      );
      g.addColorStop(0, `hsla(${haze.h}, ${haze.s}%, ${haze.l + 8}%, ${haze.a * .42})`);
      g.addColorStop(.42, `hsla(${haze.h}, ${haze.s}%, ${haze.l + 3}%, ${haze.a * .34})`);
      g.addColorStop(.72, `hsla(${haze.h}, ${haze.s}%, ${haze.l}%, ${haze.a * .62})`);
      g.addColorStop(.92, `hsla(${haze.h}, ${haze.s}%, ${haze.l}%, ${haze.a * 1.08})`);
      g.addColorStop(1, `hsla(${haze.h}, ${haze.s}%, ${haze.l}%, ${haze.a * .28})`);
      ctx.save();
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "screen";
      ctx.fillStyle = g;
      ctx.fillRect(pr.x - r, pr.y - r, r * 2, r * 2);
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "source-over";
      ctx.fillStyle = `hsla(${haze.h}, ${Math.max(10, haze.s - 18)}%, ${Math.min(86, haze.l + 8)}%, ${haze.a * .12})`;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, r, 0, TAU);
      ctx.fill();
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawPlanetTerminatorShadow(o, cam, pr, r, sunDir, w, h) {
      if (!sunDir) return;
      const f = Math.min(w, h) * .82;
      const camQ = ensureCameraQuat(game.camera);
      const step = clamp(Math.ceil(r / 92), 2, 8);
      const halfStep = step * .5;
      const sphereRadius = o.r;
      const centerD2 = dot(cam, cam);
      const minX = Math.max(0, Math.floor(pr.x - r));
      const maxX = Math.min(w, Math.ceil(pr.x + r));
      const minY = Math.max(0, Math.floor(pr.y - r));
      const maxY = Math.min(h, Math.ceil(pr.y + r));

      ctx.save();
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, r, 0, TAU);
      ctx.clip();

      for (let sy = minY + halfStep; sy < maxY; sy += step) {
        const rayY = -(sy - h / 2) / f;
        for (let sx = minX + halfStep; sx < maxX; sx += step) {
          const ray = norm(vec((sx - w / 2) / f, rayY, 1));
          const b = dot(ray, cam);
          const disc = b * b - (centerD2 - sphereRadius * sphereRadius);
          if (disc <= 0) continue;
          const t = b - Math.sqrt(disc);
          if (t <= 0) continue;

          const surfaceCamDir = norm(sub(scale(ray, t), cam));
          const surfaceWorldDir = norm(quatRotate(camQ, surfaceCamDir));
          const night = clamp((-dot(surfaceWorldDir, sunDir) + .012) / .055, 0, 1);
          if (night <= .015) continue;

          const alpha = Math.pow(night, .5) * .98;
          const level = Math.ceil(alpha * 18) / 18;
          ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(0,1,4,${level})`;
          ctx.fillRect(sx - halfStep - .5, sy - halfStep - .5, step + 1, step + 1);
        }
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawPlanetBody(o, cam, w, h) {
      ctx.save();
      ctx.globalAlpha = 1;
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "source-over";
      const pr = project(cam, w, h);
      if (!pr) {
        ctx.restore();
        return;
      }
      const r = Math.abs(o.r * pr.s);
      const cullR = o.hasRing ? r * (o.ringOuter || 1) * 1.08 : r;
      if (r < 2 || pr.x + cullR < 0 || pr.x - cullR > w || pr.y + cullR < 0 || pr.y - cullR > h) {
        ctx.restore();
        return;
      }

      const hue = o.hue ?? 110, sat = o.sat ?? 45, light = o.light ?? 45;
      const meridianAngle = (o.rot || 0) * .2;

      if (game.graphicsMode === "wire") {
        ctx.strokeStyle = `hsl(${hue}, 60%, 75%)`;
        ctx.lineWidth = 1.4;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, r, 0, TAU);
        ctx.stroke();
        ctx.globalAlpha = .8;
        ctx.lineWidth = 1;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.ellipse(pr.x, pr.y, r * .72, r * .16, .25 + meridianAngle, 0, TAU);
        ctx.stroke();
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.ellipse(pr.x, pr.y, r * .2, r, -.2 + meridianAngle, 0, TAU);
        ctx.stroke();
        ctx.globalAlpha = 1;
        ctx.restore();
        return;
      }

      const sun = game.objects.find((s) => s.type === "sun");
      const sunDir = sun ? norm(sub(sun.pos, o.pos)) : null;
      // Gentle day-side tint only. The hard terminator is drawn below by sampling the
      // visible sphere against the real world-space star direction; keeping it out of a
      // flat canvas gradient stops the dark side behaving like a screen-space sticker.
      let lx = Math.cos(-.6), ly = Math.sin(-.6);
      if (sunDir) {
        const sc = worldDirToCam(sunDir);
        const sl = Math.hypot(sc.x, sc.y);
        if (sl > .0001) { lx = sc.x / sl; ly = -sc.y / sl; } // project() flips y
      }

      const detailAlpha = planetSurfaceDetailAlpha(o, cam);
      const planetDetail = detailAlpha > .04 && (performanceLod() < 2 || r > 120);
      const planetFineDetail = detailAlpha > .18 && (performanceLod() < 1 || r > 170);
      const ringDetail = performanceLod() < 3 || r > 110;

      if (o.hasRing && ringDetail) drawPlanetRing(o, r, hue, w, h, false);
      const g = ctx.createRadialGradient(pr.x + lx * r * .35, pr.y + ly * r * .35, r * .05, pr.x, pr.y, r * 1.05);
      const base = planetBaseStops(o);
      g.addColorStop(0, base[0]);
      g.addColorStop(.55, base[1]);
      g.addColorStop(1, base[2]);

      ctx.save();
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, r, 0, TAU);
      ctx.clip();
      ctx.fillStyle = g;
      ctx.fillRect(pr.x - r, pr.y - r, r * 2, r * 2);

      // Day-side surface features first, so the terminator shadow below darkens them.
      if (planetDetail) {
        ctx.save();
        ctx.globalAlpha *= detailAlpha;
        drawPlanetSurface(o, pr, r, w, h);
        ctx.restore();
      }

      if (planetDetail || r > 90) drawPlanetHaze(o, pr, r, lx, ly);

      drawPlanetTerminatorShadow(o, cam, pr, r, sunDir, w, h);

      // Population centres glowing on the now-dark night side.
      if (planetFineDetail) {
        ctx.save();
        ctx.globalAlpha *= detailAlpha;
        drawPlanetNightLights(o, r, w, h, sunDir);
        ctx.restore();
      }
      ctx.restore();

      // Atmospheric limb glow (coloured by type), outside the disc clip so it haloes.
      if (performanceLod() < 3 || r > 150) drawPlanetAtmosphere(o, pr, r);

      if (o.hasRing && ringDetail) drawPlanetRing(o, r, hue, w, h, true);
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawObject(o, cam, w, h) {
      if (o.type === "sun") {
        drawSunBody(o, cam, w, h);
        return;
      }
      if (o.type === "planet") {
        drawPlanetBody(o, cam, w, h);
        return;
      }
      if (o.type === "station") {
        drawStation(o, cam, w, h);
        return;
      }
      const model = MODELS[o.model || "cobra"];
      if (!model) return;
      drawSceneModel(o, cam, w, h);
    }

    function drawPlayerHullDamageMarks(o, cam, w, h, camera = game.camera, projectFn = null) {
      if (!ultraFxEnabled() || !o.playerDamageMarks?.length) return;
      const roll = o.roll ?? (o.rot || 0) * .7;
      const orient = (v) => o.quat ? quatRotate(o.quat, v) : rotateShipPoint(v, o.rot || 0, o.pitch || 0, roll);
      ctx.save();
      for (const mark of o.playerDamageMarks) {
        const local = vec(mark.x, mark.y, mark.z);
        const normalLocal = norm(local);
        const camPos = add(worldDirToCam(orient(local), camera), cam);
        const camNormal = worldDirToCam(norm(orient(normalLocal)), camera);
        const facing = -dot(camNormal, norm(camPos));
        if (facing <= .02) continue;
        const pr = projectFn ? projectFn(camPos) : project(camPos, w, h);
        if (!pr) continue;

        const radius = clamp((mark.radius || 12) * pr.s * (.82 + facing * .55), 3.5, 36);
        const alpha = clamp((.38 + (mark.severity || .35) * .42) * (.36 + facing * .7), .18, .82);
        const scorch = ctx.createRadialGradient(pr.x, pr.y, 0, pr.x, pr.y, radius);
        scorch.addColorStop(0, `rgba(12,8,5,${alpha})`);
        scorch.addColorStop(.38, `rgba(68,28,12,${alpha * .46})`);
        scorch.addColorStop(.72, `rgba(18,14,10,${alpha * .2})`);
        scorch.addColorStop(1, "rgba(0,0,0,0)");
        ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "multiply";
        ctx.fillStyle = scorch;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(pr.x, pr.y, radius, 0, TAU);
        ctx.fill();

        ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "source-over";
        ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(255,152,60,${alpha * .28})`;
        ctx.lineWidth = Math.max(.7, radius * .055);
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(pr.x - radius * .35, pr.y - radius * .08);
        ctx.lineTo(pr.x + radius * .28, pr.y + radius * .04);
        ctx.moveTo(pr.x - radius * .1, pr.y + radius * .31);
        ctx.lineTo(pr.x + radius * .16, pr.y - radius * .26);
        ctx.stroke();
      }
      ctx.restore();
    }

    // Canonical mesh render path: ships, stations, previews, hangar ships and
    // cut-scene mesh props should enter through modelMeshForRender/drawModelEntity.
    // Keep bespoke renderers for true non-mesh systems only: planets/rings/stars,
    // particles, lasers, HUD/chart UI and hangar architecture panels.
    function modelMeshForRender(model, camera, w, h, opts = {}) {
      const scaleFactor = opts.scaleFactor ?? 1;
      const centerCam = opts.centerCam || cameraTransform(opts.pos || vec(), camera);
      const orient = opts.orient || ((v) => v);
      const projectFn = opts.project || ((p) => project(p, w, h));
      const camVerts = model.verts.map(([x, y, z]) =>
        add(worldDirToCam(orient(vec(x * scaleFactor, y * scaleFactor, z * scaleFactor)), camera), centerCam)
      );
      return {
        camVerts,
        points: camVerts.map(projectFn),
        centerCam,
        project: projectFn
      };
    }

    function modelRenderQuality(renderCtx, entity, model, centerCam, scaleFactor) {
      if (DEV_FORCE_FULL_RENDER) {
        return { pxRadius: Infinity, textures: true, decals: true, details: true, detailEdges: true, damage: true, effects: true };
      }
      if (renderCtx.quality === false) {
        return { pxRadius: Infinity, textures: true, decals: true, details: true, damage: true, effects: true };
      }
      const f = Math.min(renderCtx.w, renderCtx.h) * .82;
      const radius = Math.max(1, modelBoundingRadius(model) * scaleFactor);
      const pxRadius = Math.abs(radius * f / Math.max(1, centerCam.z));
      const thresholdMul = performanceThresholdMul();
      const load = performanceSceneLoad();
      const texturePx = Math.max(MODEL_RENDER_QUALITY.texturePx * thresholdMul, lerp(0, 72, load));
      const decalPx = Math.max(MODEL_RENDER_QUALITY.decalPx * thresholdMul, lerp(0, 110, load));
      const detailPx = Math.max(MODEL_RENDER_QUALITY.detailPx * thresholdMul, lerp(0, 54, load));
      const damagePx = Math.max(MODEL_RENDER_QUALITY.damagePx * thresholdMul, lerp(0, 86, load));
      const camera = renderCtx.camera || game.camera;
      const damageDistance = entity.pos && camera.pos ? len(sub(entity.pos, camera.pos)) : 0;
      const damageRange = 1000 * sceneModelDistanceLodScale(model, entity);
      const detailDistance = entity.pos && camera.pos ? len(sub(entity.pos, camera.pos)) : 0;
      const detailRange = MODEL_RENDER_QUALITY.detailDistance * sceneModelDistanceLodScale(model, entity);
      const detailEdgeRange = MODEL_RENDER_QUALITY.detailEdgeDistance * sceneModelDistanceLodScale(model, entity);
      const effectPx = Math.max(MODEL_RENDER_QUALITY.effectPx * thresholdMul, lerp(0, 48, load));
      return {
        pxRadius,
        textures: pxRadius > texturePx,
        decals: pxRadius > decalPx,
        details: pxRadius > detailPx && (!detailDistance || detailDistance <= detailRange),
        detailEdges: !detailDistance || detailDistance <= detailEdgeRange,
        damage: pxRadius > damagePx && (!damageDistance || damageDistance <= damageRange),
        effects: pxRadius > effectPx && performanceLod() < 3 && load < .92
      };
    }

    function drawModelEntity(targetCtx, renderCtx, entity, opts = {}) {
      const modelName = entity.model || "cobra";
      const model = MODELS[modelName];
      if (!model) return null;
      const camera = renderCtx.camera || game.camera;
      const w = renderCtx.w, h = renderCtx.h;
      const scaleFactor = entity.scaleFactor ?? entity.scale ?? 1;
      const yaw = entity.rot ?? entity.yaw ?? 0;
      const pitch = entity.pitch ?? 0;
      const roll = entity.roll ?? yaw * .7;
      const pos = entity.pos || vec();
      const centerCam = renderCtx.centerCam || cameraTransform(pos, camera);
      const orient = opts.orient || ((v) => entity.quat ? quatRotate(entity.quat, v) : rotateShipPoint(v, yaw, pitch, roll));
      const projectFn = renderCtx.project || ((p) => project(p, w, h));
      const mesh = modelMeshForRender(model, camera, w, h, { scaleFactor, centerCam, orient, project: projectFn });
      const { camVerts, points } = mesh;
      const quality = opts.quality || modelRenderQuality(renderCtx, entity, model, centerCam, scaleFactor);
      const mode = renderCtx.mode || game.graphicsMode;
      const alpha = entity.alpha ?? opts.alpha ?? 1;
      const hullColor = entity.color || opts.color || shipColor(modelName, entity.police);
      const decal = quality.decals && opts.decal === undefined
        ? (entity.type === "ship" ? getShipDecal(entity) : null)
        : (quality.decals ? opts.decal : null);
      const imageDecals = quality.decals && opts.imageDecals === undefined
        ? getEntityImageDecals(entity)
        : (quality.decals ? opts.imageDecals : null);
      const renderShip = {
        ...entity,
        type: entity.type || "ship",
        model: modelName,
        rot: yaw,
        pitch,
        roll,
        cam: centerCam,
        engineGlow: resolvedEngineGlowLevel(entity, opts),
        project: projectFn,
        playerDamageMarks: (entity.playerDamageMarks || opts.damageMarks || []).map((m) => ({
          ...m,
          x: m.x * scaleFactor,
          y: m.y * scaleFactor,
          z: m.z * scaleFactor,
          radius: (m.radius || 12) * scaleFactor
        }))
      };

      targetCtx.save();
      targetCtx.globalAlpha *= alpha;
      if (mode !== "wire" && quality.detailEdges !== false) {
        const protrudingEdges = collectProtrudingModelEdges(
          model,
          camVerts,
          points,
          opts.edgeColor || hullColor,
          opts.edgeWidth ?? clamp(680 / Math.max(80, centerCam.z), .7, 2)
        );
        if (protrudingEdges.length) drawSolidItems(targetCtx, protrudingEdges);
      }
      const wireOccluders = drawProjectedModelHull(targetCtx, model, camVerts, points, {
        mode,
        color: hullColor,
        decal,
        imageDecals,
        project: projectFn,
        texture: opts.texture || null,
        textures: opts.textures ?? quality.textures,
        metalAlphaMul: opts.metalAlphaMul ?? (quality.textures ? 1 : 0),
        edgeColor: opts.edgeColor || hullColor,
        edgeWidth: opts.edgeWidth ?? clamp(680 / Math.max(80, centerCam.z), .7, 2),
        detailEdges: quality.detailEdges !== false,
        deferWireOccluders: mode === "wire",
        edgeCullNormalsCam: model.edgeCullNormals
          ? Object.fromEntries(Object.entries(model.edgeCullNormals).map(([edgeIndex, normal]) => [
            edgeIndex,
            worldDirToCam(norm(orient(vec(normal[0], normal[1], normal[2]))), camera)
          ]))
          : null
      });
      if (mode === "wire") {
        if (wireOccluders?.hullMasks?.length) drawSolidItems(targetCtx, wireOccluders.hullMasks);
        if (quality.details) {
          const wireDetails = collectSolidDetails(model, renderShip, camVerts, points, w, h, scaleFactor, camera, {
            mode,
            wireDetails: true,
            wireColor: opts.edgeColor || hullColor
          });
          if (wireDetails.length) drawSolidItems(targetCtx, wireDetails);
        }
        if (wireOccluders?.sheetFills?.length) {
          const visibleSheetFills = wireOccluders.sheetFills.filter((item) =>
            !itemOccludedByCloserPolys(item, wireOccluders.hullMasks || [])
          );
          if (visibleSheetFills.length) drawSolidItems(targetCtx, visibleSheetFills);
        }
      } else {
        if (quality.details) {
          drawSolidItems(targetCtx, collectSolidDetails(model, renderShip, camVerts, points, w, h, scaleFactor, camera, {
            mode,
            skipProtrudingEdges: true
          }));
        } else if ((renderShip.engineGlow ?? 0) > .02) {
          drawSolidItems(targetCtx, collectSolidDetails(model, renderShip, camVerts, points, w, h, scaleFactor, camera, { enginesOnly: true, mode }));
        }
        if (quality.damage && targetCtx === ctx) drawPlayerHullDamageMarks(renderShip, centerCam, w, h, camera, projectFn);
        if (quality.effects && renderShip.police && ultraFxEnabled()) drawPoliceStrobes(targetCtx, points);
      }
      targetCtx.restore();
      return { model, points, camVerts, centerCam };
    }

    function drawDockPortal(points, station) {
      if (points.some((p) => !p)) return;
      const [a, b, c, d] = points;
      const bounds = polygonBounds(points);
      const span = Math.max(bounds.maxX - bounds.minX, bounds.maxY - bounds.minY);
      const centroid = { x: (a.x + b.x + c.x + d.x) / 4, y: (a.y + b.y + c.y + d.y) / 4 };
      const quadPoint = (u, v) => ({
        x: lerp(lerp(a.x, b.x, u), lerp(d.x, c.x, u), v),
        y: lerp(lerp(a.y, b.y, u), lerp(d.y, c.y, u), v)
      });
      const quadPath = () => {
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(a.x, a.y);
        ctx.lineTo(b.x, b.y);
        ctx.lineTo(c.x, c.y);
        ctx.lineTo(d.x, d.y);
        ctx.closePath();
      };

      // The opening itself: solid black slot with a faint blue force-field "seal".
      ctx.save();
      quadPath();
      ctx.clip();
      ctx.fillStyle = "#000";
      ctx.fillRect(bounds.minX - 6, bounds.minY - 6, bounds.maxX - bounds.minX + 12, bounds.maxY - bounds.minY + 12);
      if (ultraFxEnabled()) {
        // Slot-local hangar glimpse: textured wall/floor/ceiling panels sit behind the
        // blue field, so from outside the entrance reads as a real station interior.
        const tex = getStationTexture(station?.stationStyle || stationStyleForSystem(currentSystem()));
        const texQuad = (p0, p1, p2, p3, alpha = .55, shade = "rgba(0,0,0,.15)") => {
          ctx.save();
          ctx.globalAlpha = alpha;
          drawTexturedTriangle(ctx, tex, p0.x, p0.y, p1.x, p1.y, p2.x, p2.y, 0, 0, tex.width, 0, tex.width, tex.height);
          drawTexturedTriangle(ctx, tex, p0.x, p0.y, p2.x, p2.y, p3.x, p3.y, 0, 0, tex.width, tex.height, 0, tex.height);
          ctx.restore();
          ctx.fillStyle = shade;
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.moveTo(p0.x, p0.y);
          ctx.lineTo(p1.x, p1.y);
          ctx.lineTo(p2.x, p2.y);
          ctx.lineTo(p3.x, p3.y);
          ctx.closePath();
          ctx.fill();
        };
        const back = [.26, .22, .74, .78];
        const b0 = quadPoint(back[0], back[1]);
        const b1 = quadPoint(back[2], back[1]);
        const b2 = quadPoint(back[2], back[3]);
        const b3 = quadPoint(back[0], back[3]);
        texQuad(quadPoint(.05, .05), quadPoint(.95, .05), b1, b0, .42, "rgba(0,0,0,.22)");
        texQuad(quadPoint(.05, .95), b3, b2, quadPoint(.95, .95), .46, "rgba(0,0,0,.08)");
        texQuad(quadPoint(.05, .05), b0, b3, quadPoint(.05, .95), .48, "rgba(0,0,0,.32)");
        texQuad(b1, quadPoint(.95, .05), quadPoint(.95, .95), b2, .48, "rgba(0,0,0,.28)");
        texQuad(b0, b1, b2, b3, .52, "rgba(0,0,0,.38)");

        ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(190,205,180,.16)";
        ctx.lineWidth = Math.max(.7, span * .0032);
        for (let i = 1; i < 5; i++) {
          const t = i / 5;
          const p0 = quadPoint(lerp(.07, back[0], t), lerp(.08, back[1], t));
          const p1 = quadPoint(lerp(.93, back[2], t), lerp(.08, back[1], t));
          const p2 = quadPoint(lerp(.07, back[0], t), lerp(.92, back[3], t));
          const p3 = quadPoint(lerp(.93, back[2], t), lerp(.92, back[3], t));
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.moveTo(p0.x, p0.y);
          ctx.lineTo(p1.x, p1.y);
          ctx.moveTo(p2.x, p2.y);
          ctx.lineTo(p3.x, p3.y);
          ctx.stroke();
        }
        ctx.strokeStyle = "rgba(225,245,220,.24)";
        ctx.lineWidth = Math.max(1, span * .007);
        for (const u of [.38, .62]) {
          const p0 = quadPoint(u, .12);
          const p1 = quadPoint(lerp(u, .5, .55), .33);
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.moveTo(p0.x, p0.y);
          ctx.lineTo(p1.x, p1.y);
          ctx.stroke();
        }
      }
      if (ultraFxEnabled()) {
        // Keep every seal feature in slot UV coordinates. Screen-space gradients/lines
        // look fine until the station rotates, then they visibly swim across the portal.
        const shimmer = .42 + Math.max(0, Math.sin(performance.now() / 430 + (station?.rot || 0))) * .38;
        for (let i = 0; i < 6; i++) {
          const inset = i * .07;
          const p0 = quadPoint(inset, inset);
          const p1 = quadPoint(1 - inset, inset);
          const p2 = quadPoint(1 - inset, 1 - inset);
          const p3 = quadPoint(inset, 1 - inset);
          ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(58,128,255,${(.018 + i * .008) * shimmer})`;
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.moveTo(p0.x, p0.y);
          ctx.lineTo(p1.x, p1.y);
          ctx.lineTo(p2.x, p2.y);
          ctx.lineTo(p3.x, p3.y);
          ctx.closePath();
          ctx.fill();
        }
        ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
        ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(120,180,255,${.10 * shimmer})`;
        ctx.lineWidth = Math.max(1, span * .012);
        for (let i = 1; i < 5; i++) {
          const v = clamp(i / 5 + Math.sin(performance.now() / 260 + i + (station?.rot || 0)) * .018, .04, .96);
          const p0 = quadPoint(.04, v);
          const p1 = quadPoint(.96, v);
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.moveTo(p0.x, p0.y);
          ctx.lineTo(p1.x, p1.y);
          ctx.stroke();
        }
      }
      ctx.restore();
      if (!ultraFxEnabled()) return;

      // Hazard strip around the OUTSIDE of the slot. Segments are projected edge-band
      // polygons, not diagonal screen-space strokes, so the border stays outside the hole.
      const bandW = Math.max(2, span * .04);
      ctx.save();
      [[a, b], [b, c], [c, d], [d, a]].forEach(([p, q], edgeIndex) => {
        const dx = q.x - p.x, dy = q.y - p.y, elen = Math.hypot(dx, dy) || 1;
        const ux = dx / elen, uy = dy / elen;
        let nx = -uy, ny = ux;
        const mx = (p.x + q.x) / 2, my = (p.y + q.y) / 2;
        if ((mx - centroid.x) * nx + (my - centroid.y) * ny < 0) { nx = -nx; ny = -ny; }
        const n = 9;
        for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {
          const t0 = i / n * elen;
          const t1 = (i + 1) / n * elen;
          const p0 = { x: p.x + ux * t0, y: p.y + uy * t0 };
          const p1 = { x: p.x + ux * t1, y: p.y + uy * t1 };
          const o0 = { x: p0.x + nx * bandW, y: p0.y + ny * bandW };
          const o1 = { x: p1.x + nx * bandW, y: p1.y + ny * bandW };
          ctx.fillStyle = (i + edgeIndex) % 2 ? "#0c0f0c" : "#ffd33d";
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.moveTo(p0.x, p0.y);
          ctx.lineTo(p1.x, p1.y);
          ctx.lineTo(o1.x, o1.y);
          ctx.lineTo(o0.x, o0.y);
          ctx.closePath();
          ctx.fill();
        }
      });
      ctx.restore();

      // Blue force-field edge glow around the opening.
      const pulse = .4 + Math.max(0, Math.sin(performance.now() / 240)) * .6;
      ctx.save();
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
      ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(90,160,255,${.24 * pulse})`;
      ctx.lineWidth = Math.max(1.5, span * .018);
      ctx.shadowColor = "rgba(90,160,255,.9)";
      ctx.shadowBlur = span * .1;
      quadPath();
      ctx.stroke();
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function projectedModelRadius(model, centerCam, w, h, scaleFactor = 1) {
      const f = Math.min(w, h) * .82;
      const radius = Math.max(1, modelBoundingRadius(model) * scaleFactor);
      return Math.abs(radius * f / Math.max(1, centerCam.z));
    }

    function sceneModelImpostorThreshold() {
      const load = performanceSceneLoad();
      return 4 + performanceLod() * 5 + load * 22;
    }

    function sceneModelDistance(o) {
      return o?.pos ? len(sub(o.pos, game.camera.pos)) : 0;
    }

    function sceneModelCanDistanceLod(o) {
      if (DEV_FORCE_FULL_RENDER) return false;
      return ultraFxEnabled() && (o.type === "ship" || o.type === "missile");
    }

    function sceneModelDistanceLodScale(model, o) {
      const scaleFactor = o?.scaleFactor ?? o?.scale ?? 1;
      const radius = model ? modelBoundingRadius(model) * scaleFactor : 80;
      return clamp(Math.sqrt(radius / 80), .72, 1.75);
    }

    function sceneModelPlainDistance(model, o) {
      return 2000 * sceneModelDistanceLodScale(model, o);
    }

    function sceneModelDotDistance(model, o) {
      return 3000 * sceneModelDistanceLodScale(model, o);
    }

    function shouldDrawSceneModelDot(o, model) {
      return sceneModelCanDistanceLod(o) && sceneModelDistance(o) > sceneModelDotDistance(model, o);
    }

    function shouldDrawSceneModelImpostor(o, model, cam, w, h) {
      if (!model || o === game.targetObject || game.fxLevel === "classic" || game.graphicsMode === "wire") return false;
      if (o.type === "station" || o.type === "hermit") return false;
      const load = performanceSceneLoad();
      if (load < .25 && performanceLod() < 2) return false;
      const scaleFactor = o.scaleFactor ?? o.scale ?? 1;
      return projectedModelRadius(model, cam, w, h, scaleFactor) < sceneModelImpostorThreshold();
    }

    function drawSceneModelDot(o, cam, w, h) {
      const c = project(cam, w, h);
      if (!c) return;
      const glow = clamp(resolvedEngineGlowLevel(o, {}) || .2, .15, 1.1);
      const rect = space.getBoundingClientRect();
      const dpr = rect.width ? w / rect.width : Math.max(1, window.devicePixelRatio || 1);
      const r = o.type === "missile" ? 1.6 : 2.2;
      const whiteR = 10 * dpr;
      const blueR = whiteR * (2.5 + glow * .7);
      ctx.save();
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "lighter";
      drawGlowSprite(ctx, c.x, c.y, blueR, "distantBlue", GLOW_SPRITES.distantBlue, .74 + glow * .24);
      drawGlowSprite(ctx, c.x, c.y, whiteR, "distantWhite", GLOW_SPRITES.distantWhite, .82 + glow * .18);
      ctx.globalCompositeOperation = "source-over";
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(0,0,0,.92)";
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(c.x, c.y, r * dpr, 0, TAU);
      ctx.fill();
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawSceneModelImpostor(o, model, cam, w, h) {
      const c = project(cam, w, h);
      if (!c) return;
      const scaleFactor = o.scaleFactor ?? o.scale ?? 1;
      const px = projectedModelRadius(model, cam, w, h, scaleFactor);
      const r = clamp(px, 2.2, 11);
      const yaw = o.rot ?? o.yaw ?? 0;
      const pitch = o.pitch ?? 0;
      const roll = o.roll ?? yaw * .7;
      const nose = project(add(worldDirToCam(rotateShipPoint(vec(0, 0, modelBoundingRadius(model) * scaleFactor), yaw, pitch, roll), game.camera), cam), w, h);
      const angle = nose ? Math.atan2(nose.y - c.y, nose.x - c.x) + Math.PI / 2 : -Math.PI / 2;
      const hull = o.type === "missile" ? "#ff584c" : (o.color || shipColor(o.model, o.police) || "#e9f2e4");
      ctx.save();
      ctx.translate(c.x, c.y);
      ctx.rotate(angle);
      ctx.globalAlpha = clamp(.8 - performanceSceneLoad() * .22, .48, .82);
      ctx.fillStyle = hull;
      ctx.strokeStyle = o.police ? "rgba(83,180,255,.75)" : "rgba(210,245,210,.46)";
      ctx.lineWidth = Math.max(1, r * .15);
      if (o.type === "missile") {
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(0, -r * 1.65);
        ctx.lineTo(r * .45, r * 1.2);
        ctx.lineTo(-r * .45, r * 1.2);
        ctx.closePath();
      } else {
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(0, -r * 1.35);
        ctx.lineTo(r * 1.05, r * .68);
        ctx.lineTo(0, r * .25);
        ctx.lineTo(-r * 1.05, r * .68);
        ctx.closePath();
      }
      ctx.fill();
      if (r > 3.5) ctx.stroke();
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function sceneModelDrawOptions(o, model, distanceLod) {
      const rock = isRockEntity(o);
      const rockSeed = o.textureSeed ?? o.decalSeed ?? hash32(`${game.galaxy}:${currentSystem().index}:${o.name || ""}:${o.model || o.type}:rock`);
      return {
        color: rock ? (o.color || "#9b927f") : (distanceLod ? distantModelColor(o) : (o.color || "#e9f2e4")),
        quality: distanceLod
          ? { pxRadius: Infinity, textures: false, decals: false, details: false, damage: false, effects: false }
          : undefined,
        texture: rock && !distanceLod ? getRockTexture(rockSeed) : undefined,
        edgeColor: rock ? "rgba(178,168,142,.58)" : undefined,
        metalAlphaMul: distanceLod ? 0 : (rock ? .82 : undefined)
      };
    }

    function renderObject(targetCtx, renderCtx, entity, opts = {}) {
      const model = opts.model || MODELS[entity?.model || "cobra"];
      if (!entity || !model) return { route: "missing", result: null };

      if (opts.sceneLod) {
        if (shouldDrawSceneModelDot(entity, model)) {
          drawSceneModelDot(entity, renderCtx.centerCam, renderCtx.w, renderCtx.h);
          return { route: "dot", result: null };
        }
        if (shouldDrawSceneModelImpostor(entity, model, renderCtx.centerCam, renderCtx.w, renderCtx.h)) {
          drawSceneModelImpostor(entity, model, renderCtx.centerCam, renderCtx.w, renderCtx.h);
          return { route: "impostor", result: null };
        }
      }

      const result = drawModelEntity(targetCtx, renderCtx, entity, opts.drawOptions || opts);
      return { route: "mesh", result };
    }

    function drawSceneModel(o, cam, w, h) {
      const model = MODELS[o.model || "cobra"];
      const distanceLod = sceneModelCanDistanceLod(o) && sceneModelDistance(o) > sceneModelPlainDistance(model, o);
      renderObject(ctx, { camera: game.camera, w, h, centerCam: cam, mode: distanceLod ? "solid" : game.graphicsMode }, o, {
        model,
        sceneLod: true,
        drawOptions: sceneModelDrawOptions(o, model, distanceLod)
      });
      if (o === game.targetObject) {
        const c = project(cam, w, h);
        if (c) {
          ctx.strokeStyle = "#ffd33d";
          ctx.strokeRect(c.x - 18, c.y - 18, 36, 36);
        }
      }
    }

    function renderBenchModelFrame(canvas, opts = {}) {
      const targetCtx = canvas?.getContext?.("2d");
      if (!targetCtx) return null;
      const w = canvas.width || canvas.clientWidth || 1;
      const h = canvas.height || canvas.clientHeight || 1;
      const modelName = MODELS[opts.model] ? opts.model : "cobra";
      const model = MODELS[modelName];
      const previousFx = game.fxLevel;
      const previousMode = game.graphicsMode;
      const previousPerformance = { ...(game.performance || {}) };
      const previousObjects = game.objects;

      game.fxLevel = opts.fxLevel || "ultra";
      game.graphicsMode = opts.mode || "solid";
      game.performance = {
        ...(game.performance || {}),
        lod: clamp(Math.trunc(Number(opts.lod) || 0), 0, 3),
        visibleModels: Math.max(0, Number(opts.sceneLoadModels) || 1)
      };
      game.objects = [];

      const radius = Math.max(1, modelBoundingRadius(model));
      const targetPx = Math.min(w, h) * clamp(Number(opts.targetScale) || .46, .12, .9);
      const distance = Math.max(40, radius * Math.min(w, h) * .82 / Math.max(1, targetPx));
      const camera = makeCamera(0);
      const qualityMode = opts.quality || "live";
      const quality = qualityMode === "full" ? {
        pxRadius: Infinity,
        textures: true,
        decals: true,
        details: true,
        detailEdges: true,
        damage: true,
        effects: true
      } : qualityMode === "plain" ? {
        pxRadius: Infinity,
        textures: false,
        decals: false,
        details: false,
        detailEdges: false,
        damage: false,
        effects: false
      } : undefined;

      targetCtx.save();
      targetCtx.clearRect(0, 0, w, h);
      targetCtx.fillStyle = "#000";
      targetCtx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);
      if (opts.grid) {
        targetCtx.strokeStyle = "rgba(62,255,74,.09)";
        targetCtx.lineWidth = 1;
        for (let x = 0; x <= w; x += 80) {
          targetCtx.beginPath();
          targetCtx.moveTo(x, 0);
          targetCtx.lineTo(x, h);
          targetCtx.stroke();
        }
        for (let y = 0; y <= h; y += 80) {
          targetCtx.beginPath();
          targetCtx.moveTo(0, y);
          targetCtx.lineTo(w, y);
          targetCtx.stroke();
        }
      }

      const routed = renderObject(targetCtx, {
        camera,
        centerCam: vec(0, 0, distance),
        w,
        h,
        mode: game.graphicsMode,
        quality: qualityMode === "full" ? false : undefined
      }, {
        type: "ship",
        model: modelName,
        scaleFactor: Number(opts.scaleFactor) || 1,
        rot: Number(opts.yaw) || 0,
        pitch: Number(opts.pitch) || 0,
        roll: Number(opts.roll) || 0,
        color: modelGameMeta(modelName).baseColor || shipColor(modelName, false),
        role: opts.role || previewDecalRole(modelName),
        decalSeed: hash32(`bench:${modelName}`),
        hp: 100,
        maxHp: 100,
        engineGlow: Number(opts.engineGlow ?? .65),
        police: modelName === "viper"
      }, {
        model,
        quality,
        drawOptions: {
          quality,
          edgeColor: opts.edgeColor || (game.fxLevel === "classic" ? "#e9f2e4" : undefined),
          edgeWidth: Number(opts.edgeWidth) || undefined,
          textures: qualityMode === "plain" ? false : undefined,
          metalAlphaMul: qualityMode === "plain" ? 0 : undefined
        }
      });
      const result = routed.result;
      targetCtx.restore();

      game.fxLevel = previousFx;
      game.graphicsMode = previousMode;
      game.performance = previousPerformance;
      game.objects = previousObjects;

      return {
        model: modelName,
        rendered: !!result,
        route: routed.route,
        radius,
        distance,
        points: result?.points?.filter(Boolean).length || 0,
        faces: model.faces?.length || 0,
        edges: model.edges?.length || 0,
        details: model.details?.length || 0
      };
    }

    function installRenderBenchApi() {
      window.UltraEliteRenderBench = {
        version: GAME_VERSION,
        models: ALL_MODEL_LIST.map((id) => {
          const model = MODELS[id];
          return {
            id,
            name: modelDisplayName(id),
            faces: model.faces?.length || 0,
            edges: model.edges?.length || 0,
            details: model.details?.length || 0,
            radius: Math.round(modelBoundingRadius(model) * 10) / 10,
            size: Math.round(modelOverallSize(model) * 10) / 10
          };
        }).sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name)),
        renderFrame: renderBenchModelFrame
      };
      window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent("ultraelite:renderbench-ready"));
    }

    function drawStation(o, cam, w, h) {
      const rendered = drawModelEntity(ctx, { camera: game.camera, w, h, centerCam: cam, mode: game.graphicsMode }, {
        type: "station",
        model: o.model || "coriolis",
        pos: o.pos,
        rot: o.rot || 0,
        color: o.color || "#d8ded4",
        engineGlow: 0
      }, {
        orient: (v) => rotatePoint(v, 0, 0, o.rot),
        edgeColor: "#d8ded4",
        edgeWidth: clamp(800 / Math.max(110, cam.z), .7, 2),
        texture: getStationTexture(o.stationStyle || stationStyleForSystem(currentSystem())),
        metalAlphaMul: o.stationStyle?.wealth > .72 ? 1.05 : o.stationStyle?.wealth < .32 ? .82 : .95
      });
      if (!rendered) return;
      const slotVerts = stationSlotVertexIndices(rendered.model).map((i) => rendered.camVerts[i]);
      const [slotA, slotB, slotC, slotD] = slotVerts.map((p) => project(p, w, h));
      // The portal is painted on top of the hull (no depth buffer), so gate it on the
      // slot face actually pointing at the camera — otherwise it shows through the
      // station from the back and sides.
      if (slotA && slotB && slotC && slotD && faceFacing(slotVerts).facing > .02) {
        drawDockPortal([slotA, slotB, slotC, slotD], o);
        ctx.strokeStyle = "#ffd33d";
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(slotA.x, slotA.y);
        ctx.lineTo(slotB.x, slotB.y);
        ctx.lineTo(slotC.x, slotC.y);
        ctx.lineTo(slotD.x, slotD.y);
        ctx.closePath();
        ctx.stroke();
      }
    }

    function drawClassicDockedShip(w, h) {
      const modelName = playerShipModel();
      const model = MODELS[modelName];
      if (!model) return;
      const t = performance.now() / 1000;
      const centerY = h * .38;
      const focal = 900;
      const tempCam = vec(0, 0, 1400);
      const identityCamera = makeCamera(0);
      const targetPx = Math.min(w * .32, h * .34);
      const scaleFactor = targetPx / modelOverallSize(model) * (tempCam.z / focal);
      const projectClassic = (p) => {
        if (!Number.isFinite(p.z) || p.z <= 8) return null;
        const f = focal / p.z;
        return { x: w / 2 + p.x * f, y: centerY - p.y * f };
      };

      ctx.save();
      ctx.shadowColor = "rgba(233,242,228,.22)";
      ctx.shadowBlur = 8;
      drawModelEntity(ctx, {
        camera: identityCamera,
        centerCam: tempCam,
        w,
        h,
        mode: "wire",
        project: projectClassic,
        quality: false
      }, {
        type: "ship",
        model: modelName,
        scaleFactor,
        rot: t * .42,
        pitch: -.18 + Math.sin(t * .37) * .06,
        roll: .12,
        color: "#e9f2e4",
        engineGlow: 0,
        playerDamageMarks: []
      }, {
        decal: null,
        textures: false,
        metalAlphaMul: 0,
        edgeColor: "#e9f2e4",
        edgeWidth: 1.15
      });
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawClassicDockedBackdrop(w, h, scene) {
      ctx.fillStyle = "#000";
      ctx.fillRect(0, 0, w, h);
      drawHangarCaption(w, h, scene, .9, true);
      drawClassicDockedShip(w, h);
      ctx.save();
      ctx.textAlign = "center";
      ctx.font = `${Math.max(9, w * .0085)}px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
      ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(145,167,141,.74)";
      ctx.fillText("MARKET, EQUIPMENT, CHARTS AND COMMANDER STATUS AVAILABLE", w / 2, h * .58);
      ctx.restore();
    }

    function drawDockedBackdrop(w, h) {
      if (!game.dockScene) {
        game.dockScene = makeDockScene(game.dockedAt || `${currentSystem().name} STATION`, false, "", []);
      }
      const scene = game.dockScene;
      syncDockSceneShip();
      if (!ultraFxEnabled()) {
        drawClassicDockedBackdrop(w, h, scene);
        return;
      }
      const modelName = scene?.shipModel || playerShipModel();
      const t = performance.now() / 7200;
      const shipPos = hangarShipParkPos();
      const orbitAxis = norm(vec(.16, 1, .09));
      const orbitBase = vec(0, -26, -315);
      const camOffset = quatRotate(quatFromAxisAngle(orbitAxis, t), orbitBase);
      const camPos = add(shipPos, camOffset);
      camPos.y = Math.max(camPos.y, -128);
      const view = makeHangarCamera(camPos, shipPos);
      drawHangarRoom(w, h, scene, view);
      drawHangarShip(w, h, scene, view, {
        pos: shipPos,
        scaleFactor: hangarShipScale(modelName, 1.16),
        yaw: Math.sin(t * .9) * .045,
        pitch: .04 + Math.sin(t * .65) * .018,
        roll: Math.sin(performance.now() / 8400) * .025,
        engineGlow: 0,
        damageMarks: []
      });
      drawHangarSparkles(w, h, scene.seed ^ 0x51ed270b, .42);
      drawHangarCaption(w, h, scene, .9, true);
    }

    function scannerStyleFor(o) {
      if (o === game.targetObject) return { color: "#ffd33d", size: 5, shape: "target" };
      if (o.type === "planet") return { color: "#58a6ff", size: 5, shape: "circle" };
      if (o.type === "sun") return { color: "#ffd36a", size: 6, shape: "sun" };
      if (o.type === "station") return { color: "#ffd33d", size: 5, shape: "square" };
      if (o.type === "hermit") return { color: "#b7a070", size: 4, shape: "diamond" };
      if (o.type === "missile") return { color: "#ff4848", size: 4, shape: "triangle" };
      if (o.type === "asteroid" || o.type === "boulder" || o.type === "splinter") return { color: "#9aa39a", size: 3, shape: "diamond" };
      if (o.type === "canister" || o.type === "plate") return { color: "#cfe9c8", size: 3, shape: "square" };
      if (o.hostile) return { color: "#ff4848", size: 4, shape: "square" };
      if (o.police) return { color: "#46dfff", size: 4, shape: "square" };
      return { color: "#65ff47", size: 3, shape: "square" };
    }

    function drawScannerMarker(x, y, style) {
      const s = style.size || 3;
      sctx.fillStyle = style.color;
      sctx.strokeStyle = style.color;
      sctx.beginPath();
      if (style.shape === "circle" || style.shape === "sun") {
        sctx.arc(x, y, s, 0, TAU);
        sctx.fill();
        if (style.shape === "sun") {
          sctx.globalAlpha = .35;
          sctx.beginPath();
          sctx.arc(x, y, s * 1.8, 0, TAU);
          sctx.stroke();
          sctx.globalAlpha = 1;
        }
      } else if (style.shape === "diamond") {
        sctx.moveTo(x, y - s);
        sctx.lineTo(x + s, y);
        sctx.lineTo(x, y + s);
        sctx.lineTo(x - s, y);
        sctx.closePath();
        sctx.fill();
      } else if (style.shape === "triangle") {
        sctx.moveTo(x, y - s);
        sctx.lineTo(x + s, y + s);
        sctx.lineTo(x - s, y + s);
        sctx.closePath();
        sctx.fill();
      } else if (style.shape === "target") {
        sctx.strokeRect(x - s, y - s, s * 2, s * 2);
        sctx.beginPath();
        sctx.moveTo(x - s * 1.5, y);
        sctx.lineTo(x + s * 1.5, y);
        sctx.moveTo(x, y - s * 1.5);
        sctx.lineTo(x, y + s * 1.5);
        sctx.stroke();
      } else {
        sctx.fillRect(x - s, y - s, s * 2, s * 2);
      }
    }

    function drawScanner() {
      const w = scanner.width, h = scanner.height;
      sctx.clearRect(0, 0, w, h);
      const cx = w / 2, cy = h / 2 + 8, rx = w * .42, ry = h * .34;
      const rangeX = 9000, rangeZ = 12000, rangeY = 6000;
      sctx.strokeStyle = "#2bb934";
      sctx.lineWidth = 1;
      sctx.beginPath();
      sctx.ellipse(cx, cy, rx, ry, 0, 0, TAU);
      sctx.stroke();
      sctx.globalAlpha = .55;
      for (let i = -2; i <= 2; i++) {
        sctx.beginPath();
        sctx.moveTo(cx - rx, cy + i * ry / 2);
        sctx.lineTo(cx + rx, cy + i * ry / 2);
        sctx.stroke();
      }
      sctx.beginPath();
      sctx.moveTo(cx, cy - ry);
      sctx.lineTo(cx, cy + ry);
      sctx.stroke();
      sctx.globalAlpha = 1;
      sctx.fillStyle = "#65ff47";
      sctx.beginPath();
      sctx.moveTo(cx, cy - 8);
      sctx.lineTo(cx + 12, cy + 8);
      sctx.lineTo(cx - 12, cy + 8);
      sctx.closePath();
      sctx.fill();
      for (const o of game.objects) {
        const p = cameraTransform(o.pos, game.camera);
        const sx = cx + clamp(p.x / rangeX, -1, 1) * rx;
        // Camera +Z is forward; the scanner nose points upward, while canvas Y grows down.
        const baseY = cy - clamp(p.z / rangeZ, -1, 1) * ry;
        const stick = clamp(-p.y / rangeY, -1, 1) * ry * .8;
        const style = scannerStyleFor(o);
        sctx.strokeStyle = style.color;
        sctx.fillStyle = sctx.strokeStyle;
        sctx.beginPath();
        sctx.moveTo(sx, baseY);
        sctx.lineTo(sx, baseY + stick);
        sctx.stroke();
        drawScannerMarker(sx, baseY + stick, style);
      }
    }

    function drawForeAftRadarMarker(x, y, style, sizeMul = 1) {
      const s = Math.max(2, (style.size || 3) * sizeMul);
      rctx.fillStyle = style.color;
      rctx.strokeStyle = style.color;
      rctx.beginPath();
      if (style.shape === "triangle") {
        rctx.moveTo(x, y - s);
        rctx.lineTo(x + s, y + s);
        rctx.lineTo(x - s, y + s);
        rctx.closePath();
        rctx.fill();
      } else if (style.shape === "target") {
        rctx.strokeRect(x - s, y - s, s * 2, s * 2);
      } else {
        rctx.arc(x, y, s, 0, TAU);
        rctx.fill();
      }
    }

    function drawForeAftRadar() {
      const w = foreAftRadar.width, h = foreAftRadar.height;
      rctx.clearRect(0, 0, w, h);
      const cx = w / 2, cy = h / 2;
      const radius = Math.min(w, h) * .38;
      rctx.strokeStyle = "#2bb934";
      rctx.lineWidth = Math.max(1, Math.min(w, h) / 120);
      rctx.beginPath();
      rctx.arc(cx, cy, radius, 0, TAU);
      rctx.stroke();
      rctx.globalAlpha = .42;
      rctx.beginPath();
      rctx.moveTo(cx, cy - radius);
      rctx.lineTo(cx, cy + radius);
      rctx.moveTo(cx - radius, cy);
      rctx.lineTo(cx + radius, cy);
      rctx.stroke();
      rctx.globalAlpha = .28;
      rctx.beginPath();
      rctx.arc(cx, cy, radius * .5, 0, TAU);
      rctx.stroke();
      rctx.globalAlpha = 1;
      rctx.fillStyle = "#ffd33d";
      rctx.font = `${Math.max(7, Math.floor(radius * .17))}px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
      rctx.textAlign = "center";
      rctx.fillText("FWD", cx, cy - radius - 2);
      rctx.fillStyle = "#65ff47";
      rctx.fillText("AFT", cx, cy + radius + 8);
      rctx.beginPath();
      rctx.arc(cx, cy, 2.5, 0, TAU);
      rctx.fill();
      for (const o of game.objects) {
        const p = cameraTransform(o.pos, game.camera);
        const fore = p.z >= 0;
        const dirLen = Math.max(1, Math.hypot(p.x, p.y, p.z));
        const x = cx + clamp(p.x / dirLen, -1, 1) * radius * .86;
        const y = cy - clamp(p.y / dirLen, -1, 1) * radius * .86;
        const style = { ...scannerStyleFor(o), color: fore ? "#ffd33d" : "#65ff47" };
        drawForeAftRadarMarker(x, y, style, .72);
      }
    }

    function devChordActive() {
      return keys.has("KeyD") && keys.has("KeyE") && keys.has("KeyV");
    }

    function updatePanelDrawer() {
      if (lastPanelOpenRendered === game.panelOpen) return;
      lastPanelOpenRendered = game.panelOpen;
      sidePanel.classList.toggle("open", game.panelOpen);
      panelToggle.classList.toggle("active", game.panelOpen);
      panelToggle.setAttribute("aria-expanded", String(game.panelOpen));
      panelToggle.setAttribute("aria-label", game.panelOpen ? "Hide panel" : "Show panel");
      panelToggle.title = game.panelOpen ? "Hide panel" : "Show panel";
    }

    function renderPanel() {
      if (game.panel === "cheats" && !game.developerMode) game.panel = "status";
      const activeModels = previewModelList();
      if (!activeModels.includes(shipDiagramState.model)) shipDiagramState.model = activeModels[0] || "cobra";
      updatePanelDrawer();
      document.querySelectorAll(".tabs .btn").forEach((b) => b.classList.toggle("active", b.dataset.panel === game.panel));
      const title = game.panel === "cheats" ? "Dev" : game.panel[0].toUpperCase() + game.panel.slice(1);
      byId("panelTitle").textContent = title;
      byId("panelSub").textContent = game.docked ? `Docked at ${game.dockedAt || currentSystem().name + " Station"}` : "In flight";
      const map = { market: renderMarket, chart: renderChart, equip: renderEquip, status: renderStatus, ship: renderShip, library: renderLibrary, help: renderHelp, about: renderAbout, cheats: renderCheats };
      const panelChanged = lastRenderedPanel !== game.panel;
      panelBody.innerHTML = map[game.panel]();
      if (panelChanged || game.panel === "ship" || game.panel === "library") panelBody.scrollTop = 0;
      lastRenderedPanel = game.panel;
      attachPanelEvents();
      updateReadouts();
    }

    function renderMarket() {
      const marketOpen = canUseMarket();
      const disabled = marketOpen ? "" : "disabled";
      const fuelNeedTenths = Math.max(0, Math.round((7 - game.fuel) * 10));
      const fuelFullCost = fuelNeedTenths * 0.2;
      const fuelDisabled = !marketOpen || fuelNeedTenths <= 0 || game.credits < 0.2 ? "disabled" : "";
      const fuelLabel = fuelNeedTenths <= 0 ? "Fuel Tanks Full" : `Refuel to Full (${fmt(fuelFullCost)} CR)`;
      let rows = marketFor(currentSystem()).map((item) => {
        const cargo = game.cargo[item.name] || 0;
        const buyDisabled = disabled || item.qty <= 0 || usedCargo() >= game.cargoCap || game.credits < item.price ? "disabled" : "";
        return `<tr>
          <td class="${item.illegal ? "illegal" : ""}">${item.name}</td>
          <td>${fmt(item.price)}</td>
          <td>${item.qty}${item.unit}</td>
          <td>${cargo}</td>
          <td><button class="btn mini" data-buy="${item.name}" ${buyDisabled}>Buy</button></td>
          <td><button class="btn mini" data-sell="${item.name}" ${disabled || cargo <= 0 ? "disabled" : ""}>Sell</button></td>
        </tr>`;
      }).join("");
      return `<div class="notice">Credits ${fmt(game.credits)} CR &nbsp; Cargo ${usedCargo()}/${game.cargoCap}t &nbsp; Fuel ${fmt(game.fuel)} LY</div>
        <button class="btn primary" data-fuel ${fuelDisabled || disabled}>${fuelLabel}</button>
        <table><thead><tr><th>Goods</th><th>Price</th><th>Avail</th><th>Cargo</th><th></th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody>${rows}</tbody></table>`;
    }

    function renderGalaxyMap() {
      const w = 480, h = 300, pad = 16;
      const sys = galaxies[game.galaxy];
      const xs = sys.map((s) => s.x), ys = sys.map((s) => s.y);
      const minX = Math.min(...xs), maxX = Math.max(...xs);
      const minY = Math.min(...ys), maxY = Math.max(...ys);
      const sx = (x) => pad + (x - minX) / (maxX - minX || 1) * (w - pad * 2);
      const sy = (y) => pad + (y - minY) / (maxY - minY || 1) * (h - pad * 2);
      const dots = sys.map((s) => {
        const isCur = s.index === game.current;
        const isTgt = s.index === game.target;
        const r = isCur || isTgt ? 4.2 : 2.1;
        const fill = isCur ? "var(--cyan)" : isTgt ? "var(--amber)" : "var(--green-dim)";
        const x = sx(s.x).toFixed(1), y = sy(s.y).toFixed(1);
        return `<g class="map-dot" data-sys="${s.index}">
          <circle cx="${x}" cy="${y}" r="8" class="map-hit"><title>${s.name}</title></circle>
          <circle cx="${x}" cy="${y}" r="${r}" fill="${fill}" pointer-events="none"></circle>
        </g>`;
      }).join("");
      return `<svg viewBox="0 0 ${w} ${h}" class="star-map" data-map="galaxy">${dots}</svg>`;
    }

    function renderLocalMap() {
      const w = 480, h = 300, cx = w / 2, cy = h / 2;
      const cur = currentSystem();
      const zoom = 4;
      const maxLy = 24 / zoom;
      const scalePx = (Math.min(w, h) / 2 - 10) / maxLy;
      const originX = cx - (game.localMapPanX || 0) * scalePx;
      const originY = cy - (game.localMapPanY || 0) * scalePx;
      const nearby = galaxies[game.galaxy].map((s) => {
        const dxLy = (s.x - cur.x) / 4;
        const dyLy = (s.y - cur.y) / 4;
        return { s, d: distance(cur, s), x: originX + dxLy * scalePx, y: originY + dyLy * scalePx };
      }).filter((x) => x.x >= -20 && x.x <= w + 20 && x.y >= -20 && x.y <= h + 20);
      const maxRangeLy = 7;
      const currentRangeLy = clamp(game.fuel || 0, 0, maxRangeLy);
      const rings = [4, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24].map((ly) =>
        `<circle cx="${originX.toFixed(1)}" cy="${originY.toFixed(1)}" r="${(ly * scalePx).toFixed(1)}" class="range-ring"></circle>`
      ).join("")
        + (currentRangeLy > .05 ? `<circle cx="${originX.toFixed(1)}" cy="${originY.toFixed(1)}" r="${(currentRangeLy * scalePx).toFixed(1)}" class="range-ring current-range"></circle>` : "")
        + `<circle cx="${originX.toFixed(1)}" cy="${originY.toFixed(1)}" r="${(maxRangeLy * scalePx).toFixed(1)}" class="range-ring max-range"></circle>`;
      const dots = nearby.map(({ s, d, x, y }) => {
        const isCur = s.index === game.current;
        const isTgt = s.index === game.target;
        const label = isCur || d <= maxRangeLy ? `<text x="${(x + 7).toFixed(1)}" y="${(y + 4).toFixed(1)}" class="map-label">${s.name}</text>` : "";
        return `<g class="map-dot" data-sys="${s.index}">
          <circle cx="${x.toFixed(1)}" cy="${y.toFixed(1)}" r="${isCur ? 12 : 10}" class="map-hit"><title>${s.name}</title></circle>
          <circle cx="${x.toFixed(1)}" cy="${y.toFixed(1)}" r="${isCur || isTgt ? 4.4 : 3}" fill="${isCur ? "var(--cyan)" : isTgt ? "var(--amber)" : "var(--green)"}" pointer-events="none"></circle>
          ${label}
        </g>`;
      }).join("");
      return `<svg viewBox="0 0 ${w} ${h}" class="star-map" data-map="local">
        ${rings}
        ${dots}
      </svg>`;
    }

    function deterministicSystemBriefing(s) {
      const rng = mulberry(hash32(`${s.galaxy}:${s.index}:${s.name}:local-briefing`));
      const choose = (items) => items[Math.floor(rng() * items.length) % items.length];
      const biome = planetBiomeForSystem(s);
      const star = stellarProfileForSystem(s);
      const economy = ECONOMIES[s.economy] || "Unclassified";
      const government = GOVS[s.government] || "Unclassified";
      const pop = s.population / 10;
      const productivity = s.productivity || 0;
      const climate = {
        ocean: [
          "Most settlements cling to the coasts and platform cities; anything called inland transport is usually a ferry with opinions.",
          "The weather office tracks storms, tides and migrating customs inspectors with equal seriousness."
        ],
        desert: [
          "Surface traffic follows the cooler terminator routes, and sand in the docking seals is treated as a local weather report.",
          "Equatorial deserts make water rights the quiet second currency behind credits."
        ],
        venus: [
          "Dense yellow cloud decks hide the surface for days at a time, which the tourism board calls privacy.",
          "Atmospheric mining, pressure politics and permanent bad visibility shape most local decisions."
        ],
        gas: [
          "The main world is a swollen gas giant; the advertised surface is a polite fiction maintained by the tourism board.",
          "Most citizens live on moons, aerostat cities or service platforms, all insisting they are the real capital."
        ],
        ice: [
          "Ice ranges dominate the lit hemisphere, and every landing permit includes a small-print argument about avalanches.",
          "Polar ports run hot, loud and expensive because warmth is treated as infrastructure."
        ],
        rocky: [
          "Craters are used for addresses, landmarks and, in several districts, excuses.",
          "The surface is hard, dry and heavily mapped by people who were paid by the crater."
        ],
        industrial: [
          "Night-side industry glows through the haze while civic brochures call the smoke employment weather.",
          "Orbital traffic is dense, dock fees are inventive, and nobody admits the air tastes of machinery."
        ]
      };
      const politics = [
        "Authority is mostly theoretical outside the docking bay; pirates are best understood as an unofficial tax office.",
        "Local nobles collect docking favours with a seriousness normally reserved for life support.",
        "Three administrations claim to run the same streets, and all of them invoice pilots separately.",
        "The Directorate insists that queues are voluntary, then issues medals for joining them correctly.",
        "Public committees publish excellent production targets and less excellent explanations for missing them.",
        "Confederal councils argue in public, which locals consider healthier than the alternatives.",
        "Elections are frequent, audited and followed by long discussions about whether anything changed.",
        "Corporate security is efficient, polite and keen to remind visitors that politeness is billable."
      ][s.government] || `${government} officials are unusually proud of their forms.`;
      const tradeNotes = [
        `The ${economy.toLowerCase()} economy keeps the port busy with ${s.tech >= 10 ? "precision components and suspiciously clever vending machines" : "bulk cargo, spare parts and optimistic invoices"}.`,
        productivity >= 18000
          ? "Productivity is high enough that even the warning signs look recently serviced."
          : "Local productivity is modest; pilots are advised to count their change and then count it again.",
        s.economy <= 3
          ? "Industrial guilds dominate the news feeds, mostly by owning the news feeds."
          : "Agricultural blocs have real leverage here, especially over food, water and who gets to call something cheese."
      ];
      const populationNotes = pop >= 4.5
        ? [
          "Population pressure has turned politics into queue management with flags.",
          "Housing, traffic and public patience are all listed as scarce strategic resources."
        ]
        : pop <= 2
          ? [
            "The population is thinly spread, giving rumours plenty of room to accelerate.",
            "Visitors are memorable here, which is flattering until the bill arrives."
          ]
          : [
            "The population is large enough for bureaucracy and small enough for everyone to know which office lost the form.",
            "Local culture is practical, suspicious of miracles and very attached to docking schedules."
          ];
      const guidebookNotes = [
        "Guidebook compilers rate the system as mostly harmless, provided you do not ask who sponsored the guidebook.",
        "Towel hire is available on the main concourse, although the deposit is described as philosophically non-refundable.",
        "The port maintains an improbability desk for permits that should not exist but somehow do.",
        `${star.label} light gives the customs hall a dramatic tone that local officials have mistaken for charisma.`
      ];
      return [
        choose(climate[biome] || climate.rocky),
        politics,
        choose(tradeNotes),
        choose(populationNotes),
        choose(guidebookNotes)
      ].join(" ");
    }

    function renderSystemInfo(s, from = currentSystem()) {
      const star = stellarProfileForSystem(s);
      const distanceLine = s.index === from.index ? "Current system" : `${fmt(distance(from, s))} LY from ${from.name}`;
      const briefing = deterministicSystemBriefing(s);
      return `<div class="notice" style="margin-top:10px">
        <strong class="about-heading">Selected System</strong>
        <div class="grid2">
          ${stat("System", s.name)}
          ${stat("Distance", distanceLine)}
          ${stat("Economy", ECONOMIES[s.economy])}
          ${stat("Gov.", GOVS[s.government])}
          ${stat("Tech", s.tech + 1)}
          ${stat("Pop.", `${fmt(s.population / 10)} Billion`)}
          ${stat("Prod.", `${s.productivity} M CR`)}
          ${stat("Size", `${(s.radius * 2000).toLocaleString()} m`)}
          ${stat("Star", star.label)}
          ${stat("Species", s.species)}
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top:10px">${s.description}</div>
        <div class="system-briefing">
          <strong class="about-heading">Local Briefing</strong>
          <p>${escapeHtml(briefing)}</p>
        </div>
      </div>`;
    }

    function renderChart() {
      const from = currentSystem();
      const tgt = targetSystem();
      const mode = game.mapMode === "local" ? "local" : "galaxy";
      const rangeText = game.developerMode ? `max unlimited. fuel ${fmt(game.fuel)} LY` : `max 7.0 LY. fuel ${fmt(game.fuel)} LY`;
      const mapHtml = mode === "galaxy"
        ? renderGalaxyMap()
        : `<div class="chart-map-wrap">
            <button class="btn mini map-home" data-mapreset aria-label="Reset local chart view" title="Reset local chart view"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M2 8L8 3l6 5"/><path d="M4.5 7.5v5h7v-5"/><path d="M6.5 12.5v-3h3v3"/></svg></button>
            ${renderLocalMap()}
            <span class="drag-hint">Click system · drag to move</span>
          </div>`;
      return `<div class="notice" style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap">
          <span>
            <button class="btn mini ${mode === "galaxy" ? "primary" : ""}" data-mapmode="galaxy">Galaxy Map</button>
            <button class="btn mini ${mode === "local" ? "primary" : ""}" data-mapmode="local">Local Map</button>
          </span>
          <span style="font-size:11px;color:var(--muted)">Galaxy ${game.galaxy + 1}. Range ${rangeText}.</span>
        </div>
        ${mapHtml}
        ${renderSystemInfo(tgt, from)}`;
    }

    function renderEquip() {
      const sys = currentSystem();
      const rows = EQUIPMENT.map((e) => {
        const fitted = game.equipment[e.id];
        const okTech = sys.tech + 1 >= e.tech;
        const can = game.docked && !fitted && okTech && game.credits >= e.cost;
        return `<div class="row">
          <span class="label">${e.name}<br><span style="color:var(--muted);font-size:11px">${e.desc} TL ${e.tech}</span></span>
          <span class="value">${fitted ? "FITTED" : `${e.cost} CR`} <button class="btn mini" data-equip="${e.id}" ${can ? "" : "disabled"}>Buy</button></span>
        </div>`;
      }).join("");
      return `<div class="notice">Local tech level ${sys.tech + 1}. Missiles cost 30 CR each and refill one rack slot.</div>
        <button class="btn" data-missile ${game.docked && game.credits >= 30 && game.missiles < 4 ? "" : "disabled"}>Buy Missile</button>
        ${rows}`;
    }

    function renderStatus() {
      const saveDisabled = canSaveCommander() ? "" : "disabled";
      return `<div class="grid2">
        ${stat("Commander", game.commander)}
        ${stat("Rating", rankName())}
        ${stat("Cash", `${fmt(game.credits)} CR`)}
        ${stat("Kills", game.kills)}
        ${stat("Legal", legalStatus())}
        ${stat("Galaxy", game.galaxy + 1)}
        ${stat("Ship", shipName(playerShipModel()))}
        ${stat("Cargo", `${usedCargo()}/${game.cargoCap}t`)}
        ${stat("Fuel", `${fmt(game.fuel)} LY`)}
        ${stat("Laser", laserPower().name)}
        ${stat("Missiles", game.missiles)}
        ${stat("Docked", game.docked ? "Yes" : "No")}
      </div>
      <div class="notice save-actions">
        <button class="btn" data-rename-commander>Rename Commander</button>
        <button class="btn" data-save ${saveDisabled}>Save Browser Save</button>
        <button class="btn" data-load ${browserSaveExists() ? "" : "disabled"}>Load Browser Save</button>
        <button class="btn danger" data-delete-save ${browserSaveExists() ? "" : "disabled"}>Delete Browser Save</button>
        <button class="btn" data-download-save ${saveDisabled}>Download Commander</button>
        <label class="btn" for="commanderFileInput">Upload Commander</label>
        <input id="commanderFileInput" type="file" accept=".uelite,application/json,.json,.txt" data-upload-save style="display:none">
      </div>`;
    }

    function shipRoleLabel(model) {
      if (modelGameMeta(model).roleLabel) return modelGameMeta(model).roleLabel;
      if (!SHIP_NAMES[model]) return "Object";
      if (POLICE_MODELS.includes(model)) return "Police";
      if (ALIEN_MODELS.includes(model)) return "Alien";
      const roles = [];
      if (TRADER_MODELS.includes(model)) roles.push("Trader");
      if (PIRATE_MODELS.includes(model)) roles.push("Pirate");
      return roles.length ? roles.join(" / ") : "—";
    }

    const SHIP_LORE = {
      cobra: "The Cobra Mk III is the benchmark independent trader: enough cargo space to matter, enough speed to survive, and enough weapon mounts to make bad decisions feel briefly tactical.",
      cobra1: "The Cobra Mk I is older, lighter and less forgiving than its famous successor. Pilots who love them use words like character when they mean maintenance.",
      krait: "The Krait is a knife with engines: small, flat, fast and popular with pilots who prefer ambushes to conversations.",
      viper: "The Viper is a police interceptor built around acceleration, weapons power and the deeply held belief that criminals should have a short working day.",
      adder: "The Adder is cheap, compact and surprisingly useful, which is why traders, pirates and nervous beginners all pretend they chose it deliberately.",
      gecko: "The Gecko sits in that awkward region between courier and raider, with just enough speed to start trouble and just enough hold space to explain it later.",
      mamba: "The Mamba is all hard angles and bad intentions, a pirate favourite for quick strikes where the cargo transfer is expected to be involuntary.",
      sidewinder: "The Sidewinder is fast, twitchy and lightly built. In pirate hands it is a wasp; in honest hands it is usually a repayment plan.",
      worm: "The Worm is small-haul utility craftwork: modest drive, modest hold, modest dignity, and an admirable talent for being somewhere else when fighting starts.",
      moray: "The Moray was designed for wet worlds and awkward atmospheres, but in space it has become a favourite of pilots who like their ships unusual and their insurance complicated.",
      asp: "The Asp Mk II is a dangerous wedge of speed and firepower, respected by bounty hunters and disliked by almost everyone they have ever met.",
      ferdelance: "The Fer-de-Lance is expensive, sleek and faintly arrogant. Its owners call it refined; its victims rarely have time to file a counterargument.",
      python: "The Python is a working hauler with a serious hull and a serious appetite for profitable routes. It turns slowly, earns steadily and complains through its landing gear.",
      boa: "The Boa is a long-haul bulk carrier, beloved by accountants and feared by docking crews asked to guide it through a crowded slot.",
      anaconda: "The Anaconda is less a ship than a private economy with engines. When one arrives, traffic control clears its throat and hopes the pilot has read the manual. They hang in the sky in exactly the same way that bricks don't.",
      shuttle: "The Shuttle is station traffic made visible: practical, slow and full of people who did not expect to become part of a combat incident.",
      transporter: "The Transporter moves freight, tools and local politics between station and surface. It is not glamorous, but neither is most civilisation.",
      thargoid: "The Thargoid warship remains badly explained by human engineers. It is elegant, hostile and apparently built by minds that considered symmetry optional.",
      thargon: "The Thargon drone is a remote weapon with no cockpit, no cargo bay and no useful conversation. If it is close enough to admire, you have left it too late.",
      constrictor: "The Constrictor is a rare military-grade menace, fast and unpleasantly purposeful, usually mentioned in bars by pilots who were not present.",
      cougar: "The Cougar is a sleek, secretive design with a reputation for vanishing acts, special equipment and owners who do not answer ordinary questions. For some reason, pilots of these vessels tend to prefer to date much younger men.",
      diamondback: "The Diamondback is an off-books hunter craft: Sleek like a running shoe, over-engined and fully fitted out with the latest Sirius Cybernetics Corp. GPP technology.",
    };

    const SHIP_PRICES = {
      adder: 27000,
      gecko: 43000,
      worm: 33000,
      cobra1: 90000,
      cobra: 150000,
      moray: 82000,
      krait: 72000,
      sidewinder: 42000,
      mamba: 95000,
      asp: 180000,
      viper: 120000,
      ferdelance: 485000,
      python: 210000,
      boa: 300000,
      anaconda: 580000,
      shuttle: 18000,
      transporter: 65000,
      thargoid: null,
      thargon: null,
      constrictor: null,
      cougar: null,
      diamondback: 2500000
    };

    function shipPriceText(modelName) {
      const price = SHIP_PRICES[modelName] ?? modelGameMeta(modelName).valueCr;
      return Number.isFinite(price) ? `${price.toLocaleString()} CR` : "Restricted";
    }

    function playerShipValueText(modelName) {
      const base = SHIP_PRICES[modelName];
      if (!Number.isFinite(base)) return "Restricted";
      const condition = clamp(Number.isFinite(game.energy) ? game.energy : 100, 0, 100) / 100;
      const equipmentValue = EQUIPMENT.reduce((sum, item) => sum + (game.equipment[item.id] ? item.cost * .45 : 0), 0);
      const value = Math.round((base * (.38 + condition * .52) + equipmentValue) / 100) * 100;
      return `${value.toLocaleString()} CR`;
    }

    function shipLore(model, personal = false) {
      const stats = shipStats(model);
      const base = modelGameMeta(model).description || SHIP_LORE[model] || `${modelDisplayName(model)} records are sparse, but the hull profile suggests a machine best approached with curiosity and shields online.`;
      if (!personal) return base;
      return `Commander ${game.commander}'s ${shipName(model)} is rated for ${Math.round(stats.hp)} hull points, ${playerBaseCargoCap(model)}t standard cargo and ${Math.round(220 * (stats.speed || 1))}m/s under polite conditions. ${base}`;
    }

    function shipMissionLore(model) {
      const meta = modelGameMeta(model);
      const text = meta.missionLore || meta.mission || "";
      return typeof text === "string" ? text.trim() : "";
    }

    function renderMissionLore(model) {
      const text = shipMissionLore(model);
      if (!text) return "";
      return `<div class="notice ship-lore">
        <strong class="about-heading">Mission Notes</strong>
        <p>${escapeHtml(text)}</p>
      </div>`;
    }

    function playerHullConditionText() {
      const pct = clamp(Number.isFinite(game.energy) ? game.energy : 100, 0, 100);
      const marks = game.playerDamageMarks?.length || 0;
      let label = "Factory fresh";
      if (pct < 25) label = "Critical";
      else if (pct < 55) label = "Damaged";
      else if (pct < 82 || marks > 4) label = "Scuffed";
      else if (marks > 0) label = "Recently polished";
      return `${Math.round(pct)}% ${label}`;
    }

    function estimatedFlightHours() {
      const earned = Math.max(0, game.credits - 100);
      const activity = earned / 1450 + game.kills * .42 + Math.max(0, game.legal || 0) * .18 + (game.galaxy || 0) * 6;
      return Math.max(.4, activity + 1.7);
    }

    function renderShipBlueprint(modelName) {
      const model = MODELS[modelName];
      if (!model?.verts?.length) return "";
      const views = [
        ["TOP", 0, 2, "X/Z", 1],
        ["FRONT", 0, 1, "X/Y", 2],
        ["SIDE", 2, 1, "Z/Y", 0]
      ];
      const viewW = 160, viewH = 146, drawingH = 112, pad = 18;
      const size = modelOverallSize(model);
      const scaleLabel = size >= 180 ? "100m" : size >= 90 ? "50m" : "25m";
      const scaleMeters = size >= 180 ? 100 : size >= 90 ? 50 : 25;
      const totalW = viewW * 3;
      const blocks = views.map(([label, ax, ay, axes, viewAxis], vi) => {
        const xs = model.verts.map((v) => v[ax]);
        const ys = model.verts.map((v) => v[ay]);
        const minX = Math.min(...xs), maxX = Math.max(...xs);
        const minY = Math.min(...ys), maxY = Math.max(...ys);
        const sx = (viewW - pad * 2) / Math.max(1, maxX - minX);
        const sy = (drawingH - pad * 2 - 12) / Math.max(1, maxY - minY);
        const sc = Math.min(sx, sy);
        const ox = vi * viewW + viewW / 2 - (minX + maxX) * .5 * sc;
        const oy = 18 + drawingH / 2 + (minY + maxY) * .5 * sc;
        const project = (v) => ({ x: ox + v[ax] * sc, y: oy - v[ay] * sc });
        const faceVisible = model.normals
          ? model.normals.map((normal) => (normal?.[viewAxis] || 0) > -0.015)
          : null;
        const edges = (model.edges || []).map(([a, b], edgeIndex) => {
          if (!wireEdgeVisible(model, edgeIndex, faceVisible)) return "";
          const p1 = project(model.verts[a]);
          const p2 = project(model.verts[b]);
          return `<line x1="${p1.x.toFixed(1)}" y1="${p1.y.toFixed(1)}" x2="${p2.x.toFixed(1)}" y2="${p2.y.toFixed(1)}"></line>`;
        }).join("");
        return `<g class="bp-view">
          <text x="${vi * viewW + 10}" y="16" class="bp-title">${label}</text>
          <text x="${vi * viewW + viewW - 10}" y="16" text-anchor="end" class="bp-axis">${axes}</text>
          <g class="bp-lines">${edges}</g>
        </g>`;
      }).join("");
      const panelW = 112;
      const panelH = 25;
      const panelX = totalW - panelW - 8;
      const panelY = viewH - panelH - 6;
      const scaleW = Math.max(34, Math.min(72, scaleMeters * .72));
      const scaleX = panelX - scaleW - 18;
      const scaleY = panelY + panelH - 8;
      const meta = `<g class="bp-meta">
        <line class="bp-scale" x1="${scaleX}" y1="${scaleY}" x2="${scaleX + scaleW}" y2="${scaleY}"></line>
        <line class="bp-scale" x1="${scaleX}" y1="${scaleY - 4}" x2="${scaleX}" y2="${scaleY + 4}"></line>
        <line class="bp-scale" x1="${scaleX + scaleW}" y1="${scaleY - 4}" x2="${scaleX + scaleW}" y2="${scaleY + 4}"></line>
        <text x="${scaleX + scaleW * .5}" y="${scaleY - 7}" text-anchor="middle" class="bp-small">SCALE ${scaleLabel}</text>
        <rect class="bp-panel" x="${panelX}" y="${panelY}" width="${panelW}" height="${panelH}"></rect>
        <line class="bp-panel-line" x1="${panelX}" y1="${panelY + 10}" x2="${panelX + panelW}" y2="${panelY + 10}"></line>
        <line class="bp-panel-line" x1="${panelX + 34}" y1="${panelY + 10}" x2="${panelX + 34}" y2="${panelY + panelH}"></line>
        <text x="${panelX + 5}" y="${panelY + 7}" class="bp-panel-title">ULTRA ELITE SHIP BLUEPRINT</text>
        <text x="${panelX + 5}" y="${panelY + 20}" class="bp-small">HULL</text>
        <text x="${panelX + 39}" y="${panelY + 20}" class="bp-small">${modelDisplayName(modelName).toUpperCase()}</text>
        <text x="${panelX + 39}" y="${panelY + 25}" class="bp-small">SIZE ${Math.round(size)}M</text>
      </g>`;
      return `<svg class="blueprint-diagram" viewBox="0 0 ${totalW} ${viewH}" aria-label="${shipName(modelName)} blueprint">
        <style>
          .bp-lines line{stroke:rgba(235,248,255,.92);stroke-width:1.05;vector-effect:non-scaling-stroke}
          .bp-view:nth-of-type(2){opacity:.94}
          .bp-title{fill:#ffffff;font:8px monospace;letter-spacing:.45px}
          .bp-axis,.bp-small{fill:rgba(220,244,255,.72);font:5.6px monospace}
          .bp-scale,.bp-panel-line{stroke:rgba(230,248,255,.82);stroke-width:.8;vector-effect:non-scaling-stroke}
          .bp-panel{fill:rgba(0,18,42,.58);stroke:rgba(230,248,255,.7);stroke-width:.8;vector-effect:non-scaling-stroke}
          .bp-panel-title{fill:rgba(255,255,255,.86);font:5.2px monospace;letter-spacing:.3px}
        </style>
        <line class="bp-panel-line" x1="${viewW}" y1="8" x2="${viewW}" y2="${drawingH + 2}"></line>
        <line class="bp-panel-line" x1="${viewW * 2}" y1="8" x2="${viewW * 2}" y2="${drawingH + 2}"></line>
        ${blocks}
        ${meta}
      </svg>`;
    }

    function renderShipStats(modelName, personal = false) {
      const stats = shipStats(modelName);
      const model = MODELS[modelName];
      const speed = Math.round(220 * (stats.speed || 1));
      return `<div class="grid2">
        ${personal ? "" : stat("Role", shipRoleLabel(modelName))}
        ${personal ? stat("Ship Value", playerShipValueText(modelName)) : stat("Price", shipPriceText(modelName))}
        ${personal ? stat("Hull Condition", playerHullConditionText()) : ""}
        ${personal ? stat("Flight Hours", `${estimatedFlightHours().toFixed(1)} est.`) : ""}
        ${stat("Hull HP", Math.round(stats.hp))}
        ${stat("Speed", `${speed} m/s`)}
        ${stat("Size", `${Math.round(modelOverallSize(model))} m`)}
        ${stat("Target Area", `${Math.round(stats.r)} m`)}
        ${stat("Cargo", `${personal ? `${usedCargo()}/` : ""}${playerBaseCargoCap(modelName)}t${personal && game.equipment.cargoBay ? " + bay" : ""}`)}
      </div>`;
    }

    function renderShip() {
      const currentShip = playerShipModel();
      shipDiagramState.renderModel = currentShip;
      return `<div class="ship-panel">
      <div class="preview-wrap">
        <canvas class="ship-diagram library-diagram" id="shipDiagram" width="640" height="260" data-starry-preview="true"></canvas>
        <span class="drag-hint">Click + drag to move view</span>
      </div>
      ${renderShipStats(currentShip, true)}
      <div class="grid2">
        ${stat("Laser", laserPower().name)}
        ${stat("Missiles", game.missiles)}
        ${stat("Fuel Scoop", game.equipment.fuelScoop ? "Yes" : "No")}
        ${stat("Docking Computer", game.equipment.dockingComputer ? "Yes" : "No")}
        ${stat("ECM", game.equipment.ecm ? "Yes" : "No")}
        ${stat("Extra Energy", game.equipment.extraEnergy ? "Yes" : "No")}
        ${stat("Escape Capsule", game.equipment.escapeCapsule ? "Yes" : "No")}
      </div>
      <div class="notice ship-lore">
        <strong class="about-heading">Ship Notes</strong>
        <p>${escapeHtml(shipLore(currentShip, true))}</p>
      </div>
      ${renderMissionLore(currentShip)}
      ${renderShipBlueprint(currentShip)}
      </div>`;
    }

    function renderLibrary() {
      const models = previewModelList();
      if (!models.includes(shipDiagramState.model)) shipDiagramState.model = models[0] || "cobra";
      shipDiagramState.renderModel = null;
      const browsed = shipDiagramState.model;
      const options = models.map((model) => `<option value="${model}" ${model === browsed ? "selected" : ""}>${modelDisplayName(model)}</option>`).join("");
      return `<div class="ship-panel">
      <div class="preview-wrap">
        <canvas class="ship-diagram library-diagram" id="shipDiagram" width="640" height="260" data-starry-preview="true"></canvas>
        <span class="drag-hint">Click + drag to move view</span>
      </div>
      <div class="ship-selector-row">
        <span class="label">Library Hull</span>
        <select class="btn mini" data-shipselect>${options}</select>
      </div>
      ${renderShipStats(browsed)}
      <div class="notice ship-lore">
        <strong class="about-heading">Library Notes</strong>
        <p>${escapeHtml(shipLore(browsed))}</p>
      </div>
      ${renderMissionLore(browsed)}
      ${renderShipBlueprint(browsed)}
      </div>`;
    }

    function renderCheats() {
      const currentShip = playerShipModel();
      const shipOptions = playerSelectableShipList().map((model) =>
        `<option value="${model}" ${model === currentShip ? "selected" : ""}>${shipName(model)}</option>`
      ).join("");
      const equipmentRows = [...EQUIPMENT].sort((a, b) =>
        (DEV_EQUIPMENT_ORDER[a.id] ?? 100) - (DEV_EQUIPMENT_ORDER[b.id] ?? 100) || a.name.localeCompare(b.name)
      ).map((e) => {
        const fitted = !!game.equipment[e.id];
        return `<div class="row">
          <span class="label">${e.name}</span>
          <span class="value">${fitted ? "FITTED" : "NOT FITTED"}
            <button class="btn mini" data-cheat-equip="${e.id}" data-cheat-equip-state="${fitted ? "remove" : "add"}">${fitted ? "Remove" : "Add"}</button>
          </span>
        </div>`;
      }).join("");
      return `<div class="notice">Testing helpers only — free, no legal or economic side effects, work whether docked or in flight.</div>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;margin:10px 0">
        <button class="btn mini" data-cheat="credits1000">+1,000 CR</button>
        <button class="btn mini" data-cheat="credits10000">+10,000 CR</button>
        <button class="btn mini" data-cheat="refillShip">Refill Ship</button>
        <button class="btn mini" data-cheat="fillCargo">Fill Cargo Hold</button>
        <button class="btn mini" data-cheat="cleanLegal">Clear Legal Status</button>
        <button class="btn mini ${game.godMode ? "primary" : ""}" data-cheat="godMode">${game.godMode ? "God Mode On" : "God Mode Off"}</button>
        <button class="btn mini warn" data-cheat="armada">Deploy Armada</button>
      </div>
      <div class="grid2">
        ${stat("Ship", shipName(currentShip))}
        ${stat("Max Speed", Math.round(game.maxSpeed))}
        ${stat("Credits", `${fmt(game.credits)} CR`)}
        ${stat("Cargo", `${usedCargo()}/${game.cargoCap}t`)}
        ${stat("Missiles", game.missiles)}
        ${stat("Legal", legalStatus())}
        ${stat("God Mode", game.godMode ? "ON" : "OFF")}
      </div>
      <div class="notice">
        Player ship
        <select class="btn mini" data-cheat-ship>${shipOptions}</select>
      </div>
      <div class="notice">
        Visual test rig
        <div class="equipment-cheats">
          <div class="row">
            <span class="label">Star type</span>
            <span class="value"><select class="btn mini" data-dev-world="star">${optionList(DEV_STAR_TYPES, game.devStarType)}</select></span>
          </div>
          <div class="row">
            <span class="label">Planet type</span>
            <span class="value"><select class="btn mini" data-dev-world="planet">${optionList(DEV_PLANET_TYPES, game.devPlanetType)}</select></span>
          </div>
          <div class="row">
            <span class="label">Station type</span>
            <span class="value"><select class="btn mini" data-dev-world="station">${optionList(DEV_STATION_TYPES, game.devStationType)}</select></span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="notice">
        Equipment
        <div class="equipment-cheats">${equipmentRows}</div>
      </div>`;
    }

    function renderHelp() {
      const updates = UPDATE_LOG.map(([version, text]) =>
        `<li><strong>v${version}</strong> ${text}</li>`
      ).join("");
      return `<div class="help-heading">Keyboard</div>
      <div class="help-table">
        <div class="help-row"><div class="help-keys"><span class="kbd">W</span><span class="kbd">S</span></div><div class="help-desc">Pitch</div></div>
        <div class="help-row"><div class="help-keys"><span class="kbd">A</span><span class="kbd">D</span></div><div class="help-desc">Roll</div></div>
        <div class="help-row"><div class="help-keys"><span class="kbd">Q</span><span class="kbd">E</span><span class="kbd">,</span><span class="kbd">.</span></div><div class="help-desc">Yaw</div></div>
        <div class="help-row"><div class="help-keys"><span class="kbd">+</span><span class="kbd">-</span></div><div class="help-desc">Speed</div></div>
        <div class="help-row"><div class="help-keys"><span class="kbd">Space</span></div><div class="help-desc">Fire forward laser</div></div>
        <div class="help-row"><div class="help-keys"><span class="kbd">↑</span><span class="kbd">↓</span><span class="kbd">←</span><span class="kbd">→</span></div><div class="help-desc">View fwd / rear / left / right</div></div>
        <div class="help-row"><div class="help-keys"><span class="kbd">V</span></div><div class="help-desc">External view. Click and drag to move the camera; wheel to zoom.</div></div>
        <div class="help-row"><div class="help-keys"><span class="kbd">M</span></div><div class="help-desc">Fire missile</div></div>
        <div class="help-row"><div class="help-keys"><span class="kbd">B</span></div><div class="help-desc">Energy bomb</div></div>
        <div class="help-row"><div class="help-keys"><span class="kbd">T</span></div><div class="help-desc">Cycle priority targets</div></div>
        <div class="help-row"><div class="help-keys"><span class="kbd">G</span></div><div class="help-desc">Toggle Ultra / Old School</div></div>
        <div class="help-row"><div class="help-keys"><span class="kbd">L</span></div><div class="help-desc">Toggle ship labels</div></div>
        <div class="help-row"><div class="help-keys"><span class="kbd">N</span></div><div class="help-desc">Toggle sound</div></div>
        <div class="help-row"><div class="help-keys"><span class="kbd">J</span></div><div class="help-desc">Hyperspace countdown</div></div>
        <div class="help-row"><div class="help-keys"><span class="kbd">C</span></div><div class="help-desc">Docking computer</div></div>
        <div class="help-row"><div class="help-keys"><span class="kbd">1</span><span class="kbd">2</span><span class="kbd">3</span><span class="kbd">4</span></div><div class="help-desc">Open Market / Chart / Equip / Status</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="help-note">Dock manually by flying slowly through an aligned station slot. On the local chart, click a system to target it and drag to move the map. Ship previews can also be clicked and dragged.</div>
      <div class="notice">
        <strong>Update Log</strong>
        <ul class="update-log">${updates}</ul>
      </div>`;
    }

    function renderAbout() {
      const blocks = ABOUT_COPY.trim().split(/\n\s*\n/);
      const title = blocks.shift() || "About Ultra Elite";
      const copy = blocks.map((block) => {
        const text = block.trim();
        if (ABOUT_HEADINGS.has(text)) {
          return `<strong class="about-heading">${escapeHtml(text)}</strong>`;
        }
        return `<p>${linkifyAboutText(text)}</p>`;
      }).join("");
      return `<div class="notice about-section about-copy">
        <div class="about-title">${escapeHtml(title)}</div>
        ${copy}
      </div>`;
    }

    function linkifyAboutText(text) {
      return escapeHtml(text).replace(
        /https:\/\/github\.com\/dansto1974\/UltraElite/g,
        `<a href="https://github.com/dansto1974/UltraElite" target="_blank" rel="noopener">github.com/dansto1974/UltraElite</a>`
      );
    }

    function stat(label, value) {
      return `<div class="stat-line"><span class="label">${label}</span><span class="value">${value}</span></div>`;
    }

    function graphicsModeLabel(mode) {
      if (mode === "wire") return "Old School Wire";
      if (mode === "both") return "Ultra Shaded + Wire";
      return "Ultra Shaded";
    }

    // Two presentation presets: "classic" is the 1984 feel (pure wireframe, flat
    // white star dots, no textures/decals/glass/labels/effects), "ultra" is shaded
    // textured hulls with full effects and no hidden-line wire overlay cost.
    function applyPresetMode(mode) {
      game.fxLevel = mode === "classic" ? "classic" : "ultra";
      game.graphicsMode = mode === "classic" ? "wire" : "solid";
      game.showShipLabels = mode !== "classic";
      if (!ultraFxEnabled()) {
        game.smokePuffs = [];
        game.screenShake = 0;
      }
      setMessage(mode === "classic" ? "Standard old-school mode engaged. It is 1984." : "Ultra Elite mode engaged: full effects.", true);
      renderPanel();
      updateReadouts();
    }

    function attachPanelEvents() {
      panelBody.querySelectorAll("[data-buy]").forEach((b) => b.addEventListener("click", () => buyGood(b.dataset.buy)));
      panelBody.querySelectorAll("[data-sell]").forEach((b) => b.addEventListener("click", () => sellGood(b.dataset.sell)));
      panelBody.querySelectorAll(".map-dot").forEach((b) => b.addEventListener("click", () => {
        if (performance.now() < (game.localMapSuppressClickUntil || 0)) return;
        game.target = Number(b.dataset.sys);
        setMessage(game.target === game.current ? `Selected current system: ${targetSystem().name}.` : `Target system: ${targetSystem().name}.`);
        renderPanel();
      }));
      panelBody.querySelectorAll("[data-mapmode]").forEach((b) => b.addEventListener("click", () => {
        game.mapMode = b.dataset.mapmode;
        renderPanel();
      }));
      const mapReset = panelBody.querySelector("[data-mapreset]");
      if (mapReset) mapReset.addEventListener("click", () => {
        game.localMapZoom = 4;
        game.localMapPanX = 0;
        game.localMapPanY = 0;
        renderPanel();
      });
      attachLocalMapDrag();
      panelBody.querySelectorAll("[data-equip]").forEach((b) => b.addEventListener("click", () => buyEquipment(b.dataset.equip)));
      panelBody.querySelectorAll("[data-ship-nav]").forEach((b) => b.addEventListener("click", () => cycleShipDiagram(Number(b.dataset.shipNav))));
      panelBody.querySelectorAll("[data-shipselect]").forEach((select) => select.addEventListener("change", () => {
        shipDiagramState.model = select.value;
        renderPanel();
      }));
      panelBody.querySelectorAll("[data-cheat]").forEach((b) => b.addEventListener("click", () => {
        const action = b.dataset.cheat;
        if (action === "credits1000") cheatAddCredits(1000);
        else if (action === "credits10000") cheatAddCredits(10000);
        else if (action === "refillShip") cheatRefillShip();
        else if (action === "fillCargo") cheatFillCargo();
        else if (action === "cleanLegal") cheatClearLegalStatus();
        else if (action === "godMode") cheatToggleGodMode();
        else if (action === "armada") spawnArmada();
      }));
      panelBody.querySelectorAll("[data-cheat-equip]").forEach((b) => b.addEventListener("click", () => {
        cheatSetEquipment(b.dataset.cheatEquip, b.dataset.cheatEquipState === "add");
      }));
      const cheatShip = panelBody.querySelector("[data-cheat-ship]");
      if (cheatShip) cheatShip.addEventListener("change", () => cheatChangePlayerShip(cheatShip.value));
      panelBody.querySelectorAll("[data-dev-world]").forEach((select) => {
        select.addEventListener("change", () => cheatSetWorldOverride(select.dataset.devWorld, select.value));
      });
      const fuel = panelBody.querySelector("[data-fuel]");
      if (fuel) fuel.addEventListener("click", buyFuel);
      const missile = panelBody.querySelector("[data-missile]");
      if (missile) missile.addEventListener("click", () => {
        if (game.credits >= 30 && game.missiles < 4) {
          game.credits -= 30;
          game.missiles++;
          renderPanel();
        }
      });
      const load = panelBody.querySelector("[data-load]");
      if (load) load.addEventListener("click", loadGame);
      const deleteSave = panelBody.querySelector("[data-delete-save]");
      if (deleteSave) deleteSave.addEventListener("click", deleteBrowserSave);
      const save = panelBody.querySelector("[data-save]");
      if (save) save.addEventListener("click", () => {
        saveGame();
        renderPanel();
      });
      const renameCommander = panelBody.querySelector("[data-rename-commander]");
      if (renameCommander) renameCommander.addEventListener("click", () => askCommanderName(false));
      const downloadSave = panelBody.querySelector("[data-download-save]");
      if (downloadSave) downloadSave.addEventListener("click", downloadCommanderFile);
      const uploadSave = panelBody.querySelector("[data-upload-save]");
      if (uploadSave) uploadSave.addEventListener("change", () => {
        uploadCommanderFile(uploadSave.files && uploadSave.files[0]);
        uploadSave.value = "";
      });
      const diagram = byId("shipDiagram");
      if (diagram) {
        drawShipDiagram(diagram);
        attachShipDiagramDrag(diagram);
      }
    }

    function attachLocalMapDrag() {
      const svg = panelBody.querySelector('.star-map[data-map="local"]');
      if (!svg) return;
      let moved = false;
      let lastX = 0;
      let lastY = 0;
      const start = (e) => {
        if (e.button !== 0 || e.target.closest("[data-sys]")) return;
        moved = false;
        lastX = e.clientX;
        lastY = e.clientY;
        svg.classList.add("dragging");
        document.addEventListener("pointermove", move);
        document.addEventListener("pointerup", end);
        document.addEventListener("pointercancel", end);
        e.preventDefault();
      };
      const move = (e) => {
        const activeSvg = panelBody.querySelector('.star-map[data-map="local"]') || svg;
        const viewBox = activeSvg.viewBox.baseVal;
        const rect = activeSvg.getBoundingClientRect();
        const scaleX = viewBox.width / Math.max(1, rect.width);
        const scaleY = viewBox.height / Math.max(1, rect.height);
        const dx = (e.clientX - lastX) * scaleX;
        const dy = (e.clientY - lastY) * scaleY;
        if (Math.abs(dx) + Math.abs(dy) > .2) moved = true;
        const mapScale = (Math.min(viewBox.width, viewBox.height) / 2 - 10) / (24 / 4);
        game.localMapPanX -= dx / mapScale;
        game.localMapPanY -= dy / mapScale;
        lastX = e.clientX;
        lastY = e.clientY;
        renderPanel();
        const nextSvg = panelBody.querySelector('.star-map[data-map="local"]');
        if (nextSvg) nextSvg.classList.add("dragging");
        e.preventDefault();
      };
      const end = (e) => {
        const activeSvg = panelBody.querySelector('.star-map[data-map="local"]') || svg;
        activeSvg.classList.remove("dragging");
        if (moved) game.localMapSuppressClickUntil = performance.now() + 250;
        document.removeEventListener("pointermove", move);
        document.removeEventListener("pointerup", end);
        document.removeEventListener("pointercancel", end);
      };
      svg.addEventListener("pointerdown", start);
      svg.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
        if (!moved) return;
        e.preventDefault();
        e.stopPropagation();
        moved = false;
      }, true);
    }

    const shipDiagramState = { yaw: .6, pitch: .4, roll: .2, dragging: false, lastX: 0, lastY: 0, idleSpeed: .22, model: "cobra", renderModel: null };

    function cycleShipDiagram(dir) {
      const models = previewModelList();
      const i = Math.max(0, models.indexOf(shipDiagramState.model));
      shipDiagramState.model = models[(i + dir + models.length) % models.length];
      renderPanel();
    }

    function attachShipDiagramDrag(canvas) {
      const st = shipDiagramState;
      const start = (e) => {
        st.dragging = true;
        st.lastX = e.clientX;
        st.lastY = e.clientY;
        canvas.setPointerCapture(e.pointerId);
        canvas.style.cursor = "grabbing";
      };
      const move = (e) => {
        if (!st.dragging) return;
        st.yaw += (e.clientX - st.lastX) * .012;
        st.pitch = clamp(st.pitch - (e.clientY - st.lastY) * .012, -1.4, 1.4);
        st.lastX = e.clientX;
        st.lastY = e.clientY;
      };
      const end = () => {
        st.dragging = false;
        canvas.style.cursor = "grab";
      };
      canvas.style.cursor = "grab";
      canvas.style.touchAction = "none";
      canvas.addEventListener("pointerdown", start);
      canvas.addEventListener("pointermove", move);
      canvas.addEventListener("pointerup", end);
      canvas.addEventListener("pointerleave", end);
      canvas.addEventListener("pointercancel", end);
    }

    function attachExternalViewControls(canvas) {
      const st = game.externalView;
      const active = () => game.viewMode === "ext" && !game.docked && !game.transition;
      const start = (e) => {
        if (!active() || e.button !== 0) return;
        st.dragging = true;
        st.lastX = e.clientX;
        st.lastY = e.clientY;
        canvas.setPointerCapture(e.pointerId);
        canvas.style.cursor = "grabbing";
        e.preventDefault();
      };
      const move = (e) => {
        if (!st.dragging) return;
        st.yaw += (e.clientX - st.lastX) * .008;
        st.pitch = clamp(st.pitch + (e.clientY - st.lastY) * .006, -.85, 1.15);
        st.lastX = e.clientX;
        st.lastY = e.clientY;
        e.preventDefault();
      };
      const end = (e) => {
        if (!st.dragging) return;
        st.dragging = false;
        canvas.style.cursor = active() ? "grab" : "";
        if (e?.pointerId != null && canvas.hasPointerCapture(e.pointerId)) canvas.releasePointerCapture(e.pointerId);
      };
      canvas.addEventListener("pointerdown", start);
      canvas.addEventListener("pointermove", move);
      canvas.addEventListener("pointerup", end);
      canvas.addEventListener("pointerleave", end);
      canvas.addEventListener("pointercancel", end);
      canvas.addEventListener("wheel", (e) => {
        if (!active()) return;
        st.zoom = clamp(st.zoom * (e.deltaY > 0 ? 1.1 : .9), .42, 2.8);
        e.preventDefault();
      }, { passive: false });
    }

    function drawShipPreviewBackground(c, canvas, modelName, starry) {
      c.fillStyle = "#010201";
      c.fillRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);
      if (!starry) return;
      const rng = mulberry(hash32(`ship-preview-stars:${modelName}`));
      const cloudCount = 4;
      for (let i = 0; i < cloudCount; i++) {
        const x = rng() * canvas.width;
        const y = rng() * canvas.height;
        const r = canvas.width * (.16 + rng() * .28);
        const hue = [204, 186, 302, 34][i % 4] + rng() * 18 - 9;
        const g = c.createRadialGradient(x, y, 0, x, y, r);
        g.addColorStop(0, `hsla(${hue}, ${42 + rng() * 34}%, ${35 + rng() * 24}%, ${.075 + rng() * .055})`);
        g.addColorStop(.52, `hsla(${hue}, 42%, 24%, ${.025 + rng() * .025})`);
        g.addColorStop(1, `hsla(${hue}, 30%, 12%, 0)`);
        c.fillStyle = g;
        c.beginPath();
        c.arc(x, y, r, 0, TAU);
        c.fill();
      }
      const stars = 78;
      for (let i = 0; i < stars; i++) {
        const x = rng() * canvas.width;
        const y = rng() * canvas.height;
        const twinkle = rng();
        const r = twinkle > .92 ? 1.4 + rng() * 1.4 : .45 + rng() * .9;
        c.fillStyle = `rgba(210,238,255,${.2 + rng() * .58})`;
        c.beginPath();
        c.arc(x, y, r, 0, TAU);
        c.fill();
        if (twinkle > .93) {
          c.strokeStyle = `rgba(190,224,255,${.14 + rng() * .18})`;
          c.lineWidth = .7;
          c.beginPath();
          c.moveTo(x - r * 4, y);
          c.lineTo(x + r * 4, y);
          c.moveTo(x, y - r * 3);
          c.lineTo(x, y + r * 3);
          c.stroke();
        }
      }
    }

    function drawShipDiagram(canvas, dt = 0) {
      if (!shipDiagramState.dragging) shipDiagramState.yaw += dt * shipDiagramState.idleSpeed;
      const c = canvas.getContext("2d");
      const modelName = shipDiagramState.renderModel || shipDiagramState.model;
      const model = MODELS[modelName];
      const starry = canvas.dataset.starryPreview === "true";
      drawShipPreviewBackground(c, canvas, modelName, starry);
      if (!model) return;
      const tempCam = vec(0, 0, starry ? 440 : 380);
      // Preview by overall extent rather than target radius; this keeps long stations and
      // cargo objects framed more honestly while leaving a little more breathing room.
      const targetPx = Math.min(canvas.width * (starry ? .58 : .48), canvas.height * (starry ? .72 : .68));
      const scaleFactor = targetPx / modelOverallSize(model) * (tempCam.z / 320);
      const { yaw, pitch, roll } = shipDiagramState;
      const identityCamera = makeCamera(0);
      const detailProject = (p) => {
        const f = 320 / p.z;
        return { x: canvas.width / 2 + p.x * f, y: canvas.height / 2 - p.y * f };
      };
      const rockPreview = isRockModelName(modelName);
      const hullColor = rockPreview ? "#9b927f" : shipColor(modelName, POLICE_MODELS.includes(modelName));
      const mode = game.graphicsMode;
      const previewDecal = rockPreview ? null : getPreviewShipDecal(modelName);
      // Details (windows/engine glow/trim) are culled via worldDirToCam, which reads the
      // real player camera's orientation -- correct for the main flight view, but this
      // widget is a self-contained turntable with no relation to game.camera at all, so
      // without an identity override here, detail visibility would flip randomly with
      // whichever way the player actually happens to be flying.
      drawModelEntity(c, {
        camera: identityCamera,
        centerCam: tempCam,
        w: canvas.width,
        h: canvas.height,
        mode,
        project: detailProject,
        quality: false
      }, {
        type: rockPreview ? modelName : "ship",
        model: modelName,
        scaleFactor,
        rot: yaw,
        pitch,
        roll,
        police: POLICE_MODELS.includes(modelName),
        engineGlow: rockPreview ? 0 : 1,
        color: hullColor
      }, {
        decal: previewDecal,
        texture: rockPreview ? getRockTexture(hash32(`preview:${modelName}:rock`)) : undefined,
        edgeColor: rockPreview ? "rgba(178,168,142,.58)" : undefined,
        metalAlphaMul: rockPreview ? .82 : undefined,
        edgeWidth: 1.4
      });
      c.fillStyle = hullColor;
      c.font = `13px ${UI_CANVAS_FONT}`;
      c.fillText(modelDisplayName(modelName), 14, 22);
    }

    function updateReadouts() {
      ensureShipSystems();
      const sys = currentSystem();
      const target = targetSystem();
      const lockDist = game.targetObject && isWorldObjectLive(game.targetObject) && finiteVec3(game.targetObject.pos) && finiteVec3(game.camera?.pos)
        ? len(sub(game.targetObject.pos, game.camera.pos))
        : null;
      setDomText(hudEls.roCommander, game.commander);
      setDomText(hudEls.roCredits, fmt(game.credits));
      setDomText(hudEls.roLegal, legalStatus());
      setDomText(hudEls.roTarget, target.name);
      setDomText(hudEls.roSystem, sys.name);
      setDomText(hudEls.roDistance, `${fmt(distance(sys, target))} LY`);
      setDomText(hudEls.roLockDist, Number.isFinite(lockDist)
        ? `LOCK ${game.targetObject.name} ${Math.round(lockDist)}m`
        : "LOCK --");
      setLevelMeter(hudEls.barForeShield, game.foreShield, { lowWarn: 42, lowCritical: 18 });
      setLevelMeter(hudEls.barAftShield, game.aftShield, { lowWarn: 42, lowCritical: 18 });
      setLevelMeter(hudEls.barFuel, game.fuel / 7 * 100, { lowWarn: 28, lowCritical: 12 });
      setLevelMeter(hudEls.barSpeed, clamp(game.speed / game.maxSpeed, 0, 1) * 100);
      const altitude = playerAltitude();
      const altitudePct = altitude == null ? 0 : clamp(altitude / 4200 * 100, 0, 100);
      setLevelMeter(hudEls.barAltitude, altitudePct, { lowWarn: 28, lowCritical: 12 });
      setCenteredMeter(hudEls.barRoll, game.rollRate, 2.05);
      setCenteredMeter(hudEls.barPitch, game.pitchRate, 1.42);
      setCenteredMeter(hudEls.barYaw, game.yawRate, 1.24);
      updateEnergyBankMeter(1);
      updateEnergyBankMeter(2);
      updateEnergyBankMeter(3);
      updateEnergyBankMeter(4);
      const cabinTemp = clamp(game.cabinTemp, 0, 125);
      const cabinPct = clamp(cabinTemp, 0, 100);
      const cabinBar = hudEls.barCabinTemp;
      setLevelMeter(cabinBar, cabinPct, { highWarn: 58, highCritical: 84 });
      const laserHeat = clamp(game.laserHeat, 0, 100);
      const heatBar = hudEls.barLaserHeat;
      setLevelMeter(heatBar, laserHeat, { highWarn: 55, highCritical: 82 });
      setDomText(hudEls.txtForeShield, `${Math.round(game.foreShield)}%`);
      setDomText(hudEls.txtAftShield, `${Math.round(game.aftShield)}%`);
      setDomText(hudEls.txtFuel, fmt(game.fuel));
      setDomText(hudEls.txtAltitude, altitude == null ? "--" : altitude < 999 ? `${Math.round(altitude)}` : `${(altitude / 1000).toFixed(1)}K`);
      setDomText(hudEls.txtCabinTemp, cabinTemp >= 100 ? "HOT" : `${Math.round(cabinTemp)}%`);
      setDomText(hudEls.txtSpeed, Math.round(game.speed));
      setDomText(hudEls.txtRoll, signedMeterText(game.rollRate, 2.05));
      setDomText(hudEls.txtPitch, signedMeterText(game.pitchRate, 1.42));
      setDomText(hudEls.txtYaw, signedMeterText(game.yawRate, 1.24));
      setDomText(hudEls.txtLaserHeat, laserHeat >= 95 ? "HOT" : `${Math.round(laserHeat)}%`);
      hudEls.missileSlots.forEach((slot, i) => toggleClass(slot, "full", i < game.missiles));
      setDomText(hudEls.modeSwitchBtn, game.fxLevel === "classic" ? "Ultra" : "Old School");
      toggleClass(hudEls.modeSwitchBtn, "primary", game.fxLevel !== "classic");
      setDomAttr(hudEls.modeSwitchBtn, "aria-pressed", game.fxLevel !== "classic" ? "true" : "false");
      const jumpBusy = !!game.transition || !!game.jumpCountdown;
      const canLaunch = game.docked && !jumpBusy;
      const canJump = !game.docked && !jumpBusy;
      const hasAutoDock = !game.docked && !jumpBusy && game.equipment.dockingComputer;
      const canAutoDock = hasAutoDock && (game.autoDock || stationSafeZoneActive());
      const canGalJump = game.equipment.galacticHyperdrive && !jumpBusy;
      setDomDisabled(hudEls.launchBtn, !canLaunch);
      setDomDisabled(hudEls.jumpBtn, !canJump);
      setDomDisabled(hudEls.autoDockBtn, !canAutoDock);
      setDomDisabled(hudEls.galJumpBtn, !canGalJump);
      setDomText(hudEls.autoDockBtn, game.autoDock ? "Cancel Dock" : "Auto Dock");
      toggleClass(hudEls.autoDockBtn, "primary", !!game.autoDock);
      setDomHidden(hudEls.launchBtn, !canLaunch);
      setDomHidden(hudEls.jumpBtn, !canJump);
      setDomHidden(hudEls.autoDockBtn, !hasAutoDock && !game.autoDock);
      setDomHidden(hudEls.galJumpBtn, !canGalJump);
      setDomHidden(hudEls.modeSwitchBtn, jumpBusy);
      updatePauseHud();
      updateVolumeHud();
      updateBrightnessHud();
      updatePerformanceTickerHud();
      if (lastDeveloperModeRendered !== game.developerMode) {
        lastDeveloperModeRendered = game.developerMode;
        devOnlyEls.forEach((el) => {
          setDomHidden(el, !game.developerMode);
        });
      }
      updatePanelDrawer();
    }

    function setCenteredMeter(el, value, maxAbs) {
      const pct = clamp(value / maxAbs, -1, 1) * 50;
      setStyleProp(el, "left", `calc(${50 + pct}% - 1px)`);
      setStyleProp(el, "width", "2px");
    }

    function signedMeterText(value, maxAbs) {
      const pct = Math.round(clamp(value / maxAbs, -1, 1) * 99);
      return pct > 0 ? `+${pct}` : `${pct}`;
    }

    function updateEnergyBankMeter(bank) {
      const raw = clamp(game.energy - (bank - 1) * 25, 0, 25);
      const pct = raw / 25 * 100;
      setLevelMeter(hudEls[`barEnergy${bank}`], pct, { lowWarn: 45, lowCritical: 20 });
      setDomText(hudEls[`txtEnergy${bank}`], `${Math.round(pct)}`);
    }

    function setLevelMeter(el, value, thresholds = {}) {
      const pct = clamp(value, 0, 100);
      const width = `${Math.round(pct * 10) / 10}%`;
      setStyleProp(el, "width", width);
      const warn = (thresholds.lowWarn != null && pct <= thresholds.lowWarn)
        || (thresholds.highWarn != null && pct >= thresholds.highWarn);
      const critical = (thresholds.lowCritical != null && pct <= thresholds.lowCritical)
        || (thresholds.highCritical != null && pct >= thresholds.highCritical);
      toggleClass(el, "warn", warn && !critical);
      toggleClass(el, "warm", warn && !critical);
      toggleClass(el, "critical", critical);
      toggleClass(el, "hot", critical);
    }

    function toggleDeveloperMode() {
      game.developerMode = !game.developerMode;
      if (!game.developerMode && game.panel === "cheats") game.panel = "status";
      if (!game.developerMode && !SHIP_MODEL_LIST.includes(shipDiagramState.model)) shipDiagramState.model = "cobra";
      setMessage(`Developer mode: ${game.developerMode ? "enabled" : "disabled"}.`);
      renderPanel();
    }

    function setGamePaused(value) {
      const paused = !!value;
      if (game.paused === paused) return;
      if (paused) keys.clear();
      eliteAudio.setPaused(paused);
      updatePauseHud();
      setMessage(paused ? "Game paused." : "Game resumed.", true);
    }

    function loop(now) {
      const rawDt = (now - last) / 1000;
      updatePerformanceBudget(rawDt);
      const dt = Math.min(.05, rawDt);
      last = now;
      if (game.paused) renderGameFrame();
      else update(dt);
      requestAnimationFrame(loop);
    }

    if (ULTRA_ELITE_RENDER_BENCH) {
      installRenderBenchApi();
    } else {
      window.addEventListener("resize", resizeCanvases);
      window.addEventListener("pointerdown", () => eliteAudio.resume(), { capture: true });
      const splashEl = byId("splash");
      const gettingStartedEl = byId("gettingStarted");
      let shouldAskCommanderName = false;
      byId("splashVersion").textContent = GAME_VERSION;

      function dismissSplash() {
        if (!splashEl || splashEl.classList.contains("hidden")) return false;
        splashEl.classList.add("hidden");
        setTimeout(() => splashEl.remove(), 600);
        if (document.documentElement.requestFullscreen && !document.fullscreenElement) {
          document.documentElement.requestFullscreen({ navigationUI: "hide" }).catch(() => {});
        }
        if (shouldAskCommanderName) {
          shouldAskCommanderName = false;
          setTimeout(() => askCommanderName(false), 50);
        }
        return true;
      }
      splashEl.addEventListener("click", dismissSplash);

      window.addEventListener("keydown", (e) => {
        // The first keypress only dismisses the splash, it never triggers a game action.
        if (dismissSplash()) {
          e.preventDefault();
          return;
        }
        eliteAudio.resume();
        if (finishGameOver()) {
          e.preventDefault();
          return;
        }
        keys.add(e.code);
        if (devChordActive() && !devChordLatched) {
          devChordLatched = true;
          toggleDeveloperMode();
          e.preventDefault();
          return;
        }
        const gameplayKey = [
          "Space", "KeyW", "KeyA", "KeyS", "KeyD", "KeyQ", "KeyE",
          "ArrowUp", "ArrowDown", "ArrowLeft", "ArrowRight",
          "Equal", "NumpadAdd", "Minus", "NumpadSubtract",
          "KeyJ", "KeyC", "KeyM", "KeyB", "KeyT", "KeyG", "KeyL", "KeyV"
        ].includes(e.code);
        if (game.paused && gameplayKey) {
          e.preventDefault();
          return;
        }
        updateReadouts();
        if (["Space", "KeyW", "KeyA", "KeyS", "KeyD", "KeyQ", "KeyE", "ArrowUp", "ArrowDown", "ArrowLeft", "ArrowRight"].includes(e.code)) e.preventDefault();
        if (e.code === "ArrowUp") setViewMode("fwd");
        if (e.code === "ArrowDown") setViewMode("rear");
        if (e.code === "ArrowLeft") setViewMode("left");
        if (e.code === "ArrowRight") setViewMode("right");
        if (e.code === "KeyV" && !(keys.has("KeyD") && keys.has("KeyE"))) setViewMode(game.viewMode === "ext" ? "fwd" : "ext");
        if (e.code === "Space") fireLaser();
        if (e.code === "KeyJ") hyperspace();
        if (e.code === "KeyC") startAutoDock();
        if (e.code === "KeyM") fireMissile();
        if (e.code === "KeyB") useEnergyBomb();
        if (e.code === "KeyT") lockNextTarget();
        if (e.code === "KeyG") {
          applyPresetMode(game.fxLevel === "ultra" ? "classic" : "ultra");
        }
        if (e.code === "KeyL") {
          game.showShipLabels = !game.showShipLabels;
          setMessage(`Ship labels: ${game.showShipLabels ? "on" : "off"}.`);
        }
        if (e.code === "KeyN") eliteAudio.toggle();
        if (e.code === "Digit1") { game.panel = "market"; game.panelOpen = true; renderPanel(); }
        if (e.code === "Digit2") { game.panel = "chart"; game.panelOpen = true; renderPanel(); }
        if (e.code === "Digit3") { game.panel = "equip"; game.panelOpen = true; renderPanel(); }
        if (e.code === "Digit4") { game.panel = "status"; game.panelOpen = true; renderPanel(); }
      });
      window.addEventListener("keyup", (e) => {
        keys.delete(e.code);
        if (!devChordActive()) devChordLatched = false;
        updateReadouts();
      });

      document.querySelectorAll(".tabs .btn").forEach((b) => b.addEventListener("click", () => {
        if (b.dataset.panel === "cheats" && !game.developerMode) return;
        game.panel = b.dataset.panel;
        game.panelOpen = true;
        renderPanel();
      }));
      panelToggle.addEventListener("click", () => {
        game.panelOpen = !game.panelOpen;
        renderPanel();
      });
      byId("launchBtn").addEventListener("click", launch);
      byId("jumpBtn").addEventListener("click", hyperspace);
      byId("modeSwitchBtn").addEventListener("click", () => applyPresetMode(game.fxLevel === "ultra" ? "classic" : "ultra"));
      byId("autoDockBtn").addEventListener("click", startAutoDock);
      byId("galJumpBtn").addEventListener("click", galacticJump);
      if (hudEls.pauseBtn) {
        hudEls.pauseBtn.addEventListener("click", () => setGamePaused(!game.paused));
        updatePauseHud();
      }
      if (hudEls.volumeSlider) {
        hudEls.volumeSlider.addEventListener("input", () => {
          eliteAudio.setVolume(Number(hudEls.volumeSlider.value) / 100);
          updateVolumeHud();
        });
        updateVolumeHud();
      }
      if (hudEls.brightnessSlider) {
        hudEls.brightnessSlider.addEventListener("input", () => {
          game.visualBrightness = normalizeVisualBrightness(Number(hudEls.brightnessSlider.value) / 100);
          saveVisualBrightnessSetting(game.visualBrightness);
          updateBrightnessHud();
        });
        updateBrightnessHud();
      }
      attachExternalViewControls(space);

      resizeCanvases();
      (function boot() {
        const hadBrowserSave = browserSaveExists();
        setDomHidden(gettingStartedEl, hadBrowserSave);
        const loadedBrowserSave = loadBrowserSave(true);
        shouldAskCommanderName = !loadedBrowserSave;
        resetFlightScene(false);
        if (loadedBrowserSave) setMessage("Browser commander save loaded.", true);
        else if (hadBrowserSave) setMessage("Browser save could not be loaded.");
        renderPanel();
        requestAnimationFrame(loop);
      })();
    }
